ber 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Croatia===\n*[[Vinko Pintari\u0107]]: murdered five people, including his wife, between 1973 and 1990; escaped from custody three times, killed in a 1991 shootout with the police.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vjesnik.hr/Pdf/2003/01/08/21A21.PDF |title=Ako Baricu ne puste iz pritvora pobit \u0107u 30 ljudi |last=Lazarevi\u0107 |first=Branko |date=8 January 2003 |newspaper=[[Vjesnik]] |language=hr |accessdate=2010-04-04}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Czech Republic===\n*[[Oto Biederman]]: member of the \"Kol\u00ednsk\u00fd Gang\" who murdered five people from 1993 to 1995, including a former accomplice; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/dvojka/historiezlocinu/_zprava/pripad-apollo-aneb-pet-vrazd-kolinskeho-gangu--1661034 |title=P\u0159\u00edpad Apollo aneb p\u011bt vra\u017ed Kol\u00ednsk\u00e9ho gangu |trans-title=The Apollo case or the five murders of the Kol\u00ednsk\u00fd gang |last1=Taud |first1=Rostislav |last2=Vojtov\u00e1 |first2=Tereza |date=19 October 2016 |website=[[Czech Radio]] |language=cs |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jaroslava Fabi\u00e1nov\u00e1]]: murdered four men between 1981 and 2003 for financial reasons; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.securitymagazin.cz/krimi/krvava-blondyna-prostitutka-ktera-muze-uspavala-hypnotiky-a-pak-je-umlatila-kladivem-rozsekala-sekackem-na-maso-nebo-znetvorila-sidlem-1404059523.html?fb_comment_id=2346677882012613_2348173891863012 |title=Krvav\u00e1 blond\u00fdna: Prostitutka, kter\u00e1 mu\u017ee usp\u00e1vala hypnotiky a pak je uml\u00e1tila kladivem, rozsekala sek\u00e1\u010dkem na maso nebo znetvo\u0159ila \u0161\u00eddlem |trans-title=Bloody blonde: A prostitute who drugged her victims then beat, slashed or stabbed them |first=Petr |last=Duchoslav |date=25 March 2018 |website=Security Magazin |language=cs |accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Marie Fik\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1]]: female nurse in [[Su\u0161ice]] who was executed by [[hanging]] in 1961 for the murders of ten babies.\n*[[Ladislav Hojer]]: sadist who raped and strangled at least five women from 1978 to 1981 around Czechoslovakia; executed 1986.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.odsouzeni.estranky.cz/clanky/co-prinesla-media/rozhovor-s-poslednim-ceskym-katem_-pred-popravou-rvacka_-po-ni-panak-rumu___.html |title=Rozhovor s posledn\u00edm \u010desk\u00fdm katem! |trans-title=Interview with the last Czech executioner! |date=30 July 2007 |website=P\u0159\u00edb\u011bhy odsouzen\u00fdch v \u010cR |language=cs |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701230140/http://www.odsouzeni.estranky.cz/clanky/co-prinesla-media/rozhovor-s-poslednim-ceskym-katem_-pred-popravou-rvacka_-po-ni-panak-rumu___.html |archive-date=1 July 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Kate\u0159ina z Kom\u00e1rova]]: 16th-century noblewoman who tortured and maimed between 14 and 30 serfs in [[Pi\u010d\u00edn]] and [[P\u0159\u00edbram]]; exiled to [[Prague Castle]], where she died in March 1534.<ref>DA\u010cICK\u00dd Z HESLOVA, Mikul\u00e1\u0161. Pam\u011bti. Praha: Akropolis, 1996. S. 280.</ref>\n*[[V\u00e1clav Mr\u00e1zek]]: convicted of the murders of seven women around [[Chomutov]]; executed in 1957.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/cerna-kronika/vrah-mrazek-poprava-60-let-soudruzi.A171215_123038_krimi_iri/foto/IRI7003c0_DSC09263.JPG |title=Fotogalerie: \u010c\u00e1st protokolu o poprav\u011b V\u00e1clava Mr\u00e1zka |trans-title=Photogallery: Part of the protocol on the execution of V\u00e1clav Mr\u00e1zek |first=Ji\u0159\u00ed |last=P\u00e1nek |website=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|iDNES.cz]] |language=cs |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Leci\u00e1n]]: responsible for killing three policemen and a prison officer; executed in 1927.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zpravodajstvi.olomouc.cz/view2.php?cisloclanku=2005110808 |title=Martin Leci\u00e1n - postrach Moravy |trans-title=Martin Leci\u00e1n - the terror of Moravia |date=November 9, 2005 |website=Olomouc.cz |language=cs |accessdate=February 8, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203023030/http://zpravodajstvi.olomouc.cz/view2.php?cisloclanku=2005110808 |archive-date=December 3, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Hubert Pil\u010d\u00edk]]: killed at least five people whom he helped cross the border from [[Czechoslovakia]] into [[West Germany]]; committed suicide in prison in 1951.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://plzensky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/mohl-byt-vrah-pilcik-tajnym-agentem20080824.html |title=Mohl b\u00fdt vrah Pil\u010d\u00edk tajn\u00fdm agentem? |trans-title=Could the murderer Pil\u010d\u00edk be a secret agent? |first=Miroslava |last=Vejvodov\u00e1 |date=24 August 2008 |newspaper=[[Den\u00edk|Plze\u0148sk\u00fd den\u00edk]] |language=cs |accessdate=28 January 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Roh\u00e1\u010d]]: former soldier who robbed and killed 59 people between 1568 and 1571 with his accomplices; all were executed in 1571.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.detektorweb.cz/index.4me?s=show&i=3690&mm=1&vd=1&PHPSSIDW=90374151b234840f6ae124a7c9323cc2 |title=Brut\u00e1ln\u00ed vojensk\u00e1 loupe\u017en\u00e1 vra\u017eda |trans-title=A brutal military robbery |date=30 January 2006 |website=Detektorweb.cz |language=cs |accessdate=2018-05-20}}</ref>\n*[[Ivan Roubal]]: occultist who murdered five people from 1991 to 1994; sentenced to life imprisonment and died in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.securitymagazin.cz/krimi/chovatel-prasat-a-mystik-roubal-byl-odsouzen-za-pet-vrazd-ale-jich-ma-na-svedomi-kolem-patnacti-nebo-take-zadnou-spravedlnost-privital-samostrilem-1404059599.html |title=Chovatel prasat a mystik Roubal byl odsouzen za p\u011bt vra\u017ed... |trans-title=Pig-breeder and mystic Roubal was sentenced for five murders... |date=4 April 2018 |website=SecurityMagazin.cz |language=cs |access-date=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Jaroslav and Dana Stodolovi]]: couple who robbed and killed eight pensioners from 2001 to 2002; both sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/musite-vedet/22265/domy-hruzy-nikdo-je-nechce-mista-kde-zabijeli-stodolovi.html |title=Domy hr\u016fzy! Nikdo je nechce... M\u00edsta, kde zab\u00edjeli Stodolovi |trans-title=Houses of horror! No one wants them...The places where the Stodolovis killed |first=Iva |last=Kot\u0115\u0161ovcov\u00e1 |date=5 March 2008 |newspaper=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] |language=cs |accessdate=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Petr Zelenka (serial killer)|Petr Zelenka]]: male nurse convicted of murdering seven patients in [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]] by lethal injections to \"test\" doctors; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.radio.cz/en/article/85964 |title=Nurse Committed Murders To \"Test\" Doctors |last=Velinger |first=Jan |date=5 December 2006 |website=[[Radio Prague]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Denmark===\n*[[Christina Aistrup Hansen]]: nurse who killed three patients at the [[Nyk\u00f8bing Falster]] Hospital; charges changed from three murders to four attempted manslaughter charges; initially sentenced to life imprisonment, changed to 12 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://politiken.dk/indland/art5627110/Anklagers-afsluttende-bem%C3%A6rkning-Sygeplejerske-dr%C3%A6bte-i-et-bizart-skuespil |title=Anklagers afsluttende bem\u00e6rkning: Sygeplejerske dr\u00e6bte i et bizart skuespil |trans-title=Prosecutor's closing remarks: Nurse killed in a bizarre acts |first=Kristian |last=Corfixen |date=9 June 2016 |newspaper=[[Politiken]] |language=da |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Lundin]]: killed his mother in the United States in 1991, then killed his mistress and her two children in Denmark 9 years later; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://finans.tv2.dk/nyheder/article.php/lundin-morderen-der-vidste-at-ligene-sladrer/?id=8173031 |title=Lundin: Morderen der vidste at ligene sladrer |trans-title=Lundin: The killer who knew that bodies will talk |first=Niels |last=Tradsfeldt |date=9 September 2007 |website=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV 2]] |language=da |accessdate=9 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Dagmar Overbye]]: childcare provider who killed between nine and twenty-five children; sentenced to death in 1921 then [[Clemency#Related concepts|reprieved]]; died in prison on 6 May 1929.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |url=http://www.kvinfo.dk/side/170/bio/904/ |title=Dagmar Overby (1887\u20131929) |first=Hanne Rimmen |last=Nielsen |encyclopedia=[[Dansk kvindebiografisk leksikon]] |year=2003 |publisher=[[KVINFO]] |language=da |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ecuador===\n*[[Gilberto Chamba]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Machala]]\"; murdered eight people in Ecuador and one in Spain; sentenced to 45 years in prison in Spain on 5 November 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/gilberto-chamba-alias-el-monstruo-de-machala-una-historia-real-a-lo-alfred-hitchcock-250160.html |title=Gilberto Chamba alias \"El Monstruo de Machala\": Una historia real a lo Alfred Hitchcock |trans-title=Gilberto Chamba alias the \"Moster of Machala\": A true story of Alfred Hitchcock |date=8 November 2006 |newspaper=[[Hoy (Ecuadorian newspaper)|Hoy]] |location=Quito |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222001443/http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/gilberto-chamba-alias-el-monstruo-de-machala-una-historia-real-a-lo-alfred-hitchcock-250160.html |archive-date=22 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Juan Fernando Hermosa]]: also known as \"Ni\u00f1o del Terror\"; minor responsible for killing twenty-three people from 1991 to 1992 in [[Quito]], mostly taxi drivers and homosexuals; sentenced to four years imprisonment and then released, later murdered on his 20th birthday by unknown assailants.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/1/el-nino-del-terror-mataba-a-balazos-video |title=El 'Ni\u00f1o del terror' mataba a balazos |trans-title=The 'Child of Terror' shot to death |date=13 June 2014 |newspaper=[[El Tel\u00e9grafo (Ecuador)|El Tel\u00e9grafo]] |language=es |accessdate=26 March 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326210719/https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/1/el-nino-del-terror-mataba-a-balazos-video |archivedate=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Egypt===\n*[[Ramadan Abdel Rehim Mansour]]: also known as \"Al-Tourbini\"; gang leader who raped and murdered homeless children across Egypt by throwing them off trains in the 2000s, sometimes burying them alive; executed in 2010.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/insideegyptlando00brad/page/199 |title=Inside Egypt: The Land of the Pharaohs on the Brink of a Revolution |first=John R. |last=Bradley |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |year=2008 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/insideegyptlando00brad/page/199 199\u2013200] |isbn=978-1-4039-8477-7 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.mawared.org/english/files/Qatrannada11.pdf |title=Street Children: From Negligence to Confrontation |journal=Qatr An-Nada: Towards a Fair Start for Children in the Arab World |pages=2\u20133 |issue=11 |year=2007 |publisher=Arab Resource Collective |accessdate=January 20, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727072155/http://www.mawared.org/english/files/Qatrannada11.pdf |archivedate=July 27, 2011}}</ref><ref name=et>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.egypttoday.com/article.aspx?ArticleID=7119 |title=Killing Kids |first=Manal |last=el-Jesri |date=January 2007 |magazine=[[Egypt Today]] |accessdate=January 20, 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080113105035/http://www.egypttoday.com/article.aspx?ArticleID=7119 |archive-date=13 January 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Raya and Sakina]]: Egypt's most famous serial killers and the first Egyptian women to be executed by the modern state of Egypt; executed along with their husbands in 1921.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/434/chrncls.htm |title=The women killers |first=Yunan Labib |last=Rizk |date=23 June 1999 |newspaper=[[Al-Ahram Weekly]] |issue=434 |accessdate=20 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307042506/http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/434/chrncls.htm |archivedate=7 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Estonia===\n*[[Johannes-Andreas Hanni]]: murderer, rapist, and cannibal who killed three people in 1982; committed suicide in police custody on 6 November 1982<ref>{{cite web |url=http://maaja.ee/andreas-hanni-tallinna-inimsooja/ |title=Andreas Hanni \u2013 Tallinna inims\u00f6\u00f6ja |trans-title=Andreas Hanni - Tallinn cannibal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=9 April 2007 |website=Maaja |language=et |access-date=29 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Bomb man of Pae street|M\u00e4rt Ringmaa]]: also known as the \"Bomb Man of Pae Street\"; killed seven people over the course of ten years in [[Tallinn]] using [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] that exploded in public places.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.epl.ee/uudised/370737 |title=Pae t\u00e4nava pommimees l\u00e4heb kohtusse |trans-title=Pae Street bomb man goes to court |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 January 2007 |newspaper=[[Eesti P\u00e4evaleht]] |language=et |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070123154734/http://www.epl.ee/uudised/370737 |archive-date=23 January 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Aleksandr Rubel]]: Ukrainian-born killer who was convicted the murderers of six people in [[Tallinn]] as a minor in the late 1990s; released from prison on 8 June 2006.\n*[[Yuri Ustimenko and Dmitry Medvedev]]: Russian duo who committed robberies, killing five people; Medvedev was killed by police, and Ustimenko was captured in Poland, extradited to Estonia and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.delfi.ee/a/50939117 |title=Sarim\u00f5rvar Ustimenko toodi Eestisse t\u00e4iendatud |trans-title=Serial killer Ustimenko brought to Estonia |first=Tanel |last=\u00d5unapuu |date=12 November 2002 |newspaper=Eesti P\u00e4evaleht |language=et |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Finland===\n* [[Juhani Aataminpoika]]: also known as \"Kerpeikkari\"; murdered twelve people in the span of two months in 1849, including his parents; sentenced to death, commuted to life imprisonment; died in 1854.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/a1477882673704 |title=Juhani Adaminpoika tappoi kaksitoista ihmist\u00e4 ja koki lopulta mestaustakin karmeamman kohtalon \u2013 elokuvan taustavoimina kaksi eturivin n\u00e4yttelij\u00e4\u00e4 |trans-title=Juhani Adaminpoika killed twelve people and finally suffered the brutal fate of casting - two front-line actors behind the film |first=Veli-Pekka |last=Lehtonen |date=1 November 2016 |newspaper=[[Helsingin Sanomat]] |language=fi |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Matti Haapoja]]: convicted murderer of three, but admitted to the killing of 18. Evidence suggests having killed as many as 22\u201325 people between 1867 and 1894 in Finland and [[Siberia]]. Sentenced to life imprisonment, but committed suicide by hanging in a prison cell.\n* [[Ismo Junni]]: killed his wife in 1980, then killed four people in arson attacks at the Kivinokka allotment garden in [[Helsinki]] from 1986 to 1989; committed suicide while in custody.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Suomalainen murha 1991\u20131994 |trans-title=Finnish murder 1991\u20131994 |first=Hannes |last=Markkula |date=1994 |pages=13\u201317 |publisher=Eurooppalainen kustannustalo |location=Helsinki |language=fi |isbn=951-96267-2-7}}</ref>\n* [[Ensio Koivunen]]: also known as \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enska\"; abducted and murdered three female hitchhikers between July and August 1971; sentenced for 25 years to prison, but released in the 1980s; died in 2003.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000005218663.html |title=Kolme liftaritytt\u00f6\u00e4 l\u00e4hti viimeiselle matkalleen \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enskan\" amerikanraudan kyydiss\u00e4 |trans-title=Three hitchhiking girls began their last journey in \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enska\"'s American car |date=20 May 2017 |newspaper=[[Ilta-Sanomat]] |language=fi |accessdate=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jukka Lindholm]]: murdered three women from 1985 to 1993 in and around [[Oulu]] and one in Helsinki in 2018; sentenced to life imprisonment, and is currently appealing the decision. Has spent 25 years in prison between his crimes.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000005671206.html |title=Ep\u00e4ill\u00e4\u00e4n murhasta: N\u00e4in oululaisesta Jukka Lindholmista kasvoi sarjakuristajana tunnettu Michael Maria Penttil\u00e4 \u2013 ensimm\u00e4inen uhri oli oma \u00e4iti |trans-title=Suspected Murder: Jukka Lindholm from Oulu became Michael Maria Penttil\u00e4 a well-known serial killer - the first victim was his own mother |first1=Rami |last1=M\u00e4kinen |first2=Miika |last2=Viljakainen |date=2018-05-07 |newspaper=Ilta-Sanomat |accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>\n* [[Aino Nykopp-Koski]]: a female nurse convicted of five murders and five attempted murders between 2004 and 2009. Sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/finland/8220323/Finnish-nurse-gets-life-for-murdering-five-patients.html |title=Finnish nurse gets life for murdering five patients |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 December 2010 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Oulu child murders|Kaisa Vornanen-Karaduman]]: purposefully neglected her newborn children, starving them to death between 2005 and 2013; initially convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment, later reduced to 13 years imprisonment for manslaughter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/yllatyskaanne-vauvasurmajutun-tuomio-muuttui-rajusti-hovissa/730196/|title=The Surprise Turn: The verdict on the baby murder case changed dramatically|last=Kemppainen|first=Susanna|date=June 10, 2016|website=Kaleva|access-date=June 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===France===\n*[[Vincenzo Aiutino]]: also known as \"The Man with the Fifty Affairs\"; Swiss man who raped and strangled three women between 1991 and 1992 in [[Meurthe-et-Moselle]]; sentenced to life imprisonment without parole.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2013/09/10/le-tueur-de-femmes-du-pays-haut |title=Vincenzo Aiutino, le tueur de femmes du pays haut |trans-title=Vincenzo Aiutino, the country's top killer of women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 September 2013 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Patrice Al\u00e8gre]]: predator who killed five women from 1989 to 1997; suspected of more murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/justice/l-homme-qui-aimait-tuer-les-femmes_494034.html |title=L'homme qui aimait tuer les femmes |trans-title=The man who loved to kill women |first=Marie |last=Huret |date=7 February 2002 |magazine=[[L'Express]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Madame de Brinvilliers|Marie-Madeleine-Marguerite d'Aubray, Marquise de Brinvilliers]]: aristocratic French poisoner of three individuals; executed in 1676.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.intratext.com/IXT/ENG1175/_INDEX.HTM |title=The Marquise de Brinvilliers |first=Alexandre |last=Dumas |author-link=Alexandre Dumas |date=1850s |location=Paris |publisher=Marpon et Flammarion |via=IntraText CT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Brinvilliers, Marie Madeleine Marguerite d'Aubray, Marquise de |volume=4 |page=572}}</ref>\n*[[Jean-Charles-Alphonse Avinain]]: also known as \"The Terror of [[Gonesse]]\"; butcher who killed two people in March and June 1867 for robbery purposes; guillotined that same year.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan&tt=&titre=&auteur=&plan=&personne=&quand=&lieu=&publi=&annee=&parpage=&oper1=&oper2=&oper3=&oper4=&oper5=&oper6=&histo=&atri=&dtri=&offset=16801&nbmax=100 |title=Cour d'assises of Seine. The butcher of Avinain |website=Criminocorpus |language=fr |accessdate=12 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061117130149/http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan |archive-date=17 November 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Marcel Barbeault]]: also known as \"The Shadow Killer\"; killed seven women and a man between 1969 and 1976 during night time or early morning; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.francesoir.fr/actualite/faits-divers/grands-crimes-du-xxe-siecle-marcel-barbeault-41340.html |title=Les grands crimes du XXe si\u00e8cle : Marcel Barbeault |trans-title=The great crimes of the 20th century: Marcel Barbeault |date=9 August 2009 |newspaper=[[France-Soir]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ludivine Chambet]]: also known as \"The Poisoner of [[Chamb\u00e9ry]]\"; nurse's aide who poisoned ten elderly people from 2012 to 2013 using antidepressants; sentenced to 25 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lindependant.fr/2017/05/23/13-personnes-agees-empoisonnees-l-aide-soignante-condamnee-a-25-ans,3017863.php |title=13 personnes \u00e2g\u00e9es empoisonn\u00e9es : l'aide-soignante condamn\u00e9e \u00e0 25 ans |trans-title=13 Poisoned seniors: caregiver sentenced to 25 years |date=23 May 2017 |newspaper=[[L'Ind\u00e9pendant (Pyr\u00e9n\u00e9es-Orientales)|L'Ind\u00e9pendant]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Chanal]]: soldier and military instructor who killed seventeen men and boys between 1980 and 1987 in [[Marne (department)|Marne]]; committed suicide in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/reunionfrance/1378581/Sadistic-sergeant-tries-to-escape-serial-killer-trial.html |title=Sadistic sergeant tries to escape serial killer trial |last=Jacobson |first=Philip |date=17 December 2000 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=2016-05-14}}</ref>\n*[[Dominique Cottrez]]: murdered eight of her newborn infants between 1989 and 2006 in her home in [[Villers-au-Tertre]]; sentenced to 9 years imprisonment in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-10803080 |title=Details emerge in French baby killing case |date=29 July 2010 |website=BBC News |accessdate=21 April 2017}}</ref>\n*[[V\u00e9ronique Courjault]]: confessed to killing three of her babies, stuffing two of them in a freezer at their family home in South Korea; sentenced to 8 years imprisonment in 2009, released 2010.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://psmag.com/social-justice/the-babies-in-the-freezer-neonaticide-pregnancy-denial-mental-illness-95639 |title=The Babies in the Freezer |first=Nabeelah |last=Jaffer |date=8 December 2014 |magazine=[[Pacific Standard]] |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Dumollard]]: condemned to the guillotine after having been arrested and charged with the deaths of maids from 1855 to 1861.\n*[[Michel Fourniret]]: also known as \"The Ogre of [[Ardennes]]\"; confessed to nine murders of young girls; allegedly killed ten more between 1987 and 2001.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2018/02/16/le-tueur-en-serie-michel-fourniret-a-avoue-les-meurtres-de-deux-femmes_1630327 |title=Le tueur en s\u00e9rie Michel Fourniret a avou\u00e9 les meurtres de deux femmes |trans-title=Serial killer Michel Fourniret confessed to the murders of two women |date=16 February 2018 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] |language=fr |access-date=17 February 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Gilles Garnier]]: confessed to killing four children between October 1572 and January 1573.\n*[[Guy Georges]]: also known as the \"Beast of the [[Place de la Bastille|Bastille]]\"; serving a life sentence for seven murders between 1991 and 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.crimeandinvestigation.co.uk/crime-files/beast-of-bastille-guy-georges |title=Beast of Bastille: Guy Georges \u2013 Crime Files |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Crime & Investigation Network]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jacquy Haddouche]]: delinquent who attacked six women from 1992 to 2002, killed three of them; sentenced to life imprisonment; died of [[intracerebral hemorrhage]] while incarcerated.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lobservateurdebeauvais.fr/2010/10/27/beauvais-mort-de-jacquy-haddouche-en-prison/ |title=Beauvais: mort de Jacquy Haddouche en prison |trans-title=Beauvais: death of Jacquy Haddouche in prison |first=Rapha\u00ebl |last=Thiollier |date=27 October 2010 |newspaper=L'Observateur de Beauvais |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Francis Heaulme]]: also known as the \"Criminal Backpacker\"; serving a life sentence for twenty murders between 1984 and 1992.\n*[[H\u00e9l\u00e8ne J\u00e9gado]]: [[domestic servant]] who poisoned at least twenty-three people between 1833 and 1851 in [[Brittany]]; executed in 1852.\n*[[Yvan Keller]]: also known as the \"Pillow Killer\"; killed and then robbed at least twenty-three old women from 1989 to 2006; confessed to 150 murders across France, Switzerland and Germany; committed suicide before trial in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/tueur-en-serie-l-affaire-yvan-keller-est-definitivement-close-27-05-2013-2840493.php |title=Tueur en s\u00e9rie: l'affaire Yvan Keller est d\u00e9finitivement close |trans-title=Serial Killer: The Yvan Keller affair is definitely closed |date=27 May 2013 |newspaper=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr |access-date=26 November 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Fran\u00e7ois Lacenaire]]: poet and army defector who killed two men between 1834 and 1835 with his accomplices; guillotined 1836.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bonjourparis.com/history/pierre-francois-lacenaire-murder-mystery-paris/ |title=Pierre Fran\u00e7ois Lacenaire: The Murderous Poet Dandy who Inspired \"Crime and Punishment\" |last=Brouwer |first=Marilyn |date=6 September 2017 |website=BonjourParis.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Henri D\u00e9sir\u00e9 Landru]]: killed eleven people; inspired the character of ''[[Monsieur Verdoux]]'' played by [[Charlie Chaplin]]; executed by guillotine on 25 February 1922.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=srw2DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT51&dq=henri+landru#v=onepage&q=henri%20landru |title=Serial Killers & Psychopaths |last1=Cawthorne |first1=Nigel |last2=Greig |first2=Charlotte |date=21 September 2017 |publisher=Arcturus Publishing |location=London, UK |isbn=978-1-78828-657-2 |page=51}}</ref>\n*[[Claude Lastennet]]: convicted of murdering five elderly women between August 1993 and January 1994 in [[\u00cele-de-France]]; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/societe/0101225965-il-a-fait-ce-qu-il-avait-a-faire-sans-sentiment-claude-lastenet-a-etrangle-cinq-femmes-agees-aujourd-hui-l-accuse-voudrait-que-ce-proces-l-aide-a-comprendre-pourquoi-cet-autre-lui-meme-qu-il-appelle-i |title=\"Il a fait ce qu'Il avait \u00e0 faire, sans sentiment\". Claude Lastenet a \u00e9trangl\u00e9 cinq femmes \u00e2g\u00e9es. Aujourd'hui l'accus\u00e9 voudrait que ce proc\u00e8s l'aide \u00e0 comprendre pourquoi cet autre lui-m\u00eame qu'il appelle \"Il\" l'a pouss\u00e9 \u00e0 tuer |trans-title=\"He did what He had to do, without feeling.\" Claude Lastenet strangled five elderly women. Today the accused would like this trial to help him understand why this other himself whom he calls \"He\" pushed him to kill |last=Henry |first=Michel |date=23 October 1997 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Celine Lesage]]: suffocated and strangled six of her newborn infants between 2000 and 2007; sentenced to 15 years imprisonment in 2007.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/mar/19/french-woman-15-years-babies |title=French woman sentenced to 15 years for killing six babies |first=Lizzy |last=Davies |date=March 19, 2010 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[\u00c9mile Louis]]: preyed on young handicapped women (seven murders) in the 1970s in [[Yonne]]; died in prison in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4045359.stm |title=French serial killer given life |date=26 November 2004 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Christine Mal\u00e8vre]]: nurse sentenced for the murders of at least 30 [[terminally ill]] patients in [[Mantes-la-Jolie]].<ref name=\"Sage\">{{cite news|title='Mercy killer' on murder charges|last=Sage|first=Adam|date=16 June 1999|newspaper=The Times|location=London, UK|via=[[Academic OneFile]]}}<!-- |access-date=7 March 2014 --></ref>\n*[[Albert Millet]]: also known as \"The Boar of the Moors\"; killed two girlfriends in 1954 and 1979; murdered his lover's friend in 2007; committed suicide to avoid apprehension.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/albert-millet-meurtrier-jusqu-a-son-dernier-jour-21-11-2007-3291377850.php |title=Albert Millet, meurtrier jusqu'\u00e0 son dernier jour |trans-title=Albert Millet, murderer until his last day |last=Boutry |first=Timoth\u00e9e |date=November 21, 2007 |newspaper=Le Parisien |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Catherine Monvoisin]]: also known as \"La Voisin\"; 17th century poisoner-for-hire who allegedly thousands of infants; burned at the stake in 1680.<ref>{{cite book |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |date=2005 |title=The Human Predator |location=New York |publisher=[[Berkley Books]] |isbn=978-0-42526-553-6}}</ref>\n*[[Rodica Negroiu]]: also known as the \"Poisoner of Max\u00e9ville\"; Romanian woman who poisoned two husbands in [[Nancy, France|Nancy]] in 1985 and 2004; suspected of the 1982 murder of her first husband in Romania; sentenced to 20 years imprisonment, released in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2015/01/25/ils-m-ont-vole-ma-vie |title=Rodica Negroiu : \" Ils m'ont vol\u00e9 ma vie\u2026 \" |trans-title=Rodica Negroiu: \"They stole my life ...\" |first=\u00c9ric |last=Nicolas |date=25 January 2015 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=28 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Yoni Palmier]]: also known as the \"Killer of [[Essonne]]\"; shot and killed four people from 2011 to 2012 during motorcycle drive-bys; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/2015/04/02/tueur-de-l-essonne-en-larmes-l-ex-petite-amie-raconte-sa-vie-avec-l-accuse-yoni-palmier-244471.html |title=Tueur de l'Essonne : en larmes, l'ex-petite amie raconte sa vie avec l'accus\u00e9, Yoni Palmier |trans-title=Killer of Essonne: in tears, the ex-girlfriend tells her life with the accused, Yoni Palmier |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 April 2015 |website=Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Thierry Paulin]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Montmartre]]\"; preyed on the elderly in the 1980s and murdered twenty-one old women.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://moreas.blog.lemonde.fr/2009/01/27/le-complice-du-tueur-des-vieilles-dames-est-libere-mathurin-paulin/ |title=Le complice du tueur des vieilles dames est lib\u00e9r\u00e9 |trans-title=The accomplice of the killer of the old ladies is released |last=Mor\u00e9as |first=G. |date=27 January 2009 |newspaper=[[Le Monde]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michel Peiry]]: also known as the \"Sadist of [[Romont]]\"; Swiss soldier who sexually abused and killed at least five hitchhikers between 1981 and 1987 in Switzerland, France and the United States; suspected of more murders.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pipiou.over-blog.com/article-13989130.html |title=Michel Peiry \"Le sadique de Romont\" |trans-title=Michel Peiry \"The sadist of Romont\" |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 November 2007 |website=Meurtres en tout genre |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Albert Pel]]: also known as \"The Watchmaker of [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]]; watchmaker who poisoned his parents and lovers from 1872 to 1884; sentenced to penal labour in [[New Caledonia]], where he died in 1924.<ref>{{cite book |last=Brouardel |first=Paul |title=The Pel Affair |publisher=Bailli\u00e8re |date=1886 |page=48}}</ref>\n*[[Marcel Petiot]]: doctor who killed 63 would-be refugees in Paris who were fleeing from the [[Nazis]]; executed in 1946.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/history/petiot/5.html |title=Crime Library: Serial Killers: Dr. Marcel Petiot |first=Michael |last=Newton |website=TruTV.com |access-date=2013-06-11 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007230412/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/history/petiot/5.html |archive-date=2012-10-07}}</ref>\n*[[Louis Poirson]]: also known as \"Rambo\"; [[Madagascar|Malagasy]]-born stonemason who kidnapped women from 1995 to 2000, killing four of them; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/plongee-dans-le-terrible-passe-du-tueur-en-serie-30-05-2002-2003110943.php |title=Plong\u00e9e dans le terrible pass\u00e9 du tueur en s\u00e9rie |trans-title=Diving into the terrible past of the serial killer |last=Albouy |first=St\u00e9phane |date=30 May 2002 |newspaper=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Victor Pr\u00e9vost]]: also known as the \"Butcher of La Chapelle\"; former peacekeeper who murdered an acquaintance and his mistress between 1877 and 1879; suspected in two other disappearances; executed 1880.<ref>{{harvsp|La Lanterne|10/12/1880|p=1|id=LL}}</ref>\n*[[Gilles de Rais]]: 15th century satanist and child killer who is reputed to have killed 400; executed on 23 October 1440.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/rais/execution_13.html |title=Gilles de Rais: The Pious Monster |first=Mark |last=Gribben |website=The Crime Library |accessdate=17 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419115554/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/rais/execution_13.html |archive-date=April 19, 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Tommy Recco]]: killed his godfather in 1960; released in 1977, after which he killed a total of six cashiers in [[B\u00e9ziers]] and [[Carqueiranne]] from 1979 to 1980; also suspected of murdering a trio of German tourists; one of the oldest French prisoners.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lci.fr/faits-divers/corse-le-tueur-en-serie-tommy-recco-auteur-de-7-meurtres-demande-une-nouvelle-fois-sa-liberation-a-l-age-de-83-ans-2052546.html |title=Corse : Tommy Recco, auteur de 7 meurtres, demande une nouvelle fois sa lib\u00e9ration \u00e0 l'\u00e2ge de 83 ans |trans-title=Corsica: Tommy Recco, perpetrator of 7 murders, again requests release at the age of 83 |last=Mousset |first=L. |date=19 May 2017 |website=[[La Cha\u00eene Info]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Sid Ahmed Rezala]]: known as \"the Killer of the Trains\"; Algerian-born serial killer who killed three women in 1999; committed suicide in custody in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/755008.stm |title='Confession' in Peake murder |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=19 May 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[R\u00e9my Roy]]: also known as the \"[[Minitel]] Killer\"; murdered three gay men after staged sadomasochistic acts from 1990 to 1991; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/france-archive/1996/06/29/le-tueur-du-minitel-condamne-a-perpetuite-remy-roy-etait-juge-pour-le-meurtre-de-trois-homosexuels-r_173025 |title=Le tueur du Minitel condamn\u00e9 \u00e0 perp\u00e9tuit\u00e9. R\u00e9my Roy \u00e9tait jug\u00e9 pour le meurtre de trois homosexuels rencontr\u00e9s par le biais de messageries |trans-title=The killer of Minitel sentenced to life. R\u00e9my Roy was tried for the murder of three homosexuals met through couriers |last=Vital-Durand |first=Brigitte |date=29 June 1996 |newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Giuseppe Sasia]]: known as the \"Shepherds' Killer\"; Italian criminal who killed at least four men in the span of a few months in 1934 in [[Draguignan]], also suspected of a 1930 murder; executed 1936.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.retronews.fr/journal/le-temps/9-decembre-1934/123/649815/3 |title=Faits-Divers: Les assassinats de bergers dans le Haut-Var |trans-title=News in brief: The murders of shepherds in the Haut-Var |date=9 December 1934 |page=3 |newspaper=[[Le Temps (Paris)|Le Temps]] |language=fr |access-date=23 November 2019 |via=RetroNews}}</ref>\n* [[Antoinette Scieri]]: nurse who confessed to killing twelve elderly patients, convicted on 27 April 1926 and died in prison.<ref>{{cite book |last=Nash |first=Jay Robert |title=Look for the Woman: A Narrative Encyclopedia of Female Prisoners, Kidnappers, Thieves, Extortionists, Terrorists, Swindlers and Spies from Elizabethan Times to the Present |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D9zaCQAAQBAJ |date=1 November 1986 |location=Lanham, Maryland |publisher=[[M. Evans and Company]] |isbn=978-1-4617-4772-7}}</ref>\n*[[Nadir Sedrati]]: also known as the \"Cutter of the Canal\"; murdered and dismembered three people in 1999, throwing the remains into the [[Marne-Rhine Canal]]; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/faits-divers/2013/09/06/nadir-sedrati-le-depeceur-du-canal |title=Nadir Sedrati, tueur machiav\u00e9lique |trans-title=Nadir Sedrati, Machiavellian killer |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=12 September 2013 |newspaper=L'Est R\u00e9publicain |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Alfredo Stranieri]]: also known as the \"Classified Ad Killer\"; Italian-born con man who committed two double murders in 1997 and 1999; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/societe/1999/07/21/quatre-cadavres-avec-preuves-d-achat-ce-sont-les-ex-proprietaires-des-commerces-rachetes-par-stranie_279306 |title=Quatre cadavres avec preuves d'achat. Ce sont les ex-propri\u00e9taires des commerces rachet\u00e9s par Stranieri |trans-title=Four corpses with proof of purchase. These are the former owners of the shops bought by Stranieri |last=Bertrand |first=Olivier |date=21 July 1999 |newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Tissier]]: recidivistic rapist who killed three people from 1971 to 1993; sentenced to life imprisonment with a minimum of 30 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.la-croix.com/Archives/1998-02-02/Patrick-Tissier-est-condamne-a-la-reclusion-criminelle-a-perpetuite-_NP_-1998-02-02-451354 |title=Patrick Tissier est condamn\u00e9 \u00e0 la r\u00e9clusion criminelle \u00e0 perp\u00e9tuit\u00e9 |trans-title=Patrick Tissier is sentenced to life imprisonment |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 February 1998 |newspaper=[[La Croix]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Joseph Vacher]]: also known as \"The French Ripper\" and \"The South-East Ripper\"; 19th century serial killer of eleven people; executed by guillotine on 31 December 1898.<ref>{{cite book |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.V/v/vacher-joseph.htm |first1=Brian |last1=Lane |first2=Wilfred |last2=Gregg |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |date=1992 |location=London, UK |publisher=[[Headline Publishing Group|Headline]] |isbn=978-0-74723-731-0 |accessdate=7 January 2013 |quote=Yes, I committed the crimes... I committed them all in moments of frenzy. |via=Murderpedia}}</ref>\n*[[Denis Waxin]]: pedophile who raped six children from 1985 to 1992 in the [[Nord (French department)|Nord department]], killing three of them; sentenced to life imprisonment for a minimum of 29 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nordeclair.fr/Locales/Lille/2009/08/04/le-cauchemar-du-pompiste-pedophile.shtml |title=Le cauchemar du pompiste p\u00e9dophile |trans-title=The nightmare of the pedophile pump attendant |last=Renoul |first=Bruno |date=4 August 2009 |newspaper=[[Nord \u00e9clair]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001200459/http://www.nordeclair.fr/Locales/Lille/2009/08/04/le-cauchemar-du-pompiste-pedophile.shtml |archive-date=1 October 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Jeanne Weber]]: convicted of the strangulation murders of ten children; committed suicide in custody in 1918.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://28rueaffre.eklablog.com/jeanne-weber-l-ogresse-de-la-goutte-d-or-a113380782 |title=Jeanne Weber, l'Ogresse de la Goutte d'Or |trans-title=Jeanne Weber, the Ogress of the [[Goutte d'Or]] |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=27 November 2014 |website=28 rue Affre |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Eugen Weidmann]]: German who strangled and robbed American dancer [[Jean de Koven]], shot a former accomplice, and shot dead and robbed four other people around Paris in 1937.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/1938/02/05/american-in-paris |title=American in Paris |last=Flanner |first=Janet |date=29 January 1938 |magazine=[[The New Yorker]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Germany===\n{{Main|List of German serial killers}}\n\n===Ghana===\n*[[Charles Quansah]]: known as the \"Accra Strangler\"; convicted of the [[strangulation]] deaths of nine women in [[Accra]]; suspected of killing 34; sentenced to death in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.modernghana.com/GhanaHome/NewsArchive/news_details.asp?id=VFhwck1VNUVZejA9&type=&section=&gender=General_News&menu_id=1&menu_id2=0&sub_menu_id=0 |title=Serial Killer Speaks Out |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 August 2003 |website=The Ghana Resource Center |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927025650/http://www.modernghana.com/GhanaHome/NewsArchive/news_details.asp?id=VFhwck1VNUVZejA9&type=&section=&gender=General_News&menu_id=1&menu_id2=0&sub_menu_id=0 |archive-date=27 September 2007}}</ref>\n\n===Greece===\n*[[Antonis Daglis]]: also known as the \"[[Athens]] Ripper\"; convicted in 1997 of the strangulation murder and dismemberment of three women and the attempted murder of six others; committed suicide in police custody in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hri.org/news/greek/ana/1996/96-01-26.ana.html |title=Police charge 21-year-old with murder of two prostitutes |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=26 January 1996 |website=Athens News Agency Bulletin |number=797 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Hermann Duft and Hans Wilhelm Bassenauer]]: Germans who murdered six persons in Greece, within a short period in 1969, were captured, tried, sentenced to death and executed in 1969.<ref name=palm>{{cite web |url=http://www.palmografos.com/permalink/20902.html#ixzz2z8BylBnB |title=\u0397 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c6\u03c4 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039c\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03b5\u03bd\u03ac\u03bf\u03c5\u03b5\u03c1 |trans-title=The execution of Duft and Basenauer |last=Kontogiannidis |first=T\u00e1sou |date=16 December 2013 |website=Palmographos |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Aristidis Pagratidis]]: also known as the \"Ogre of Seikh Sou\"; allegedly attacked couples in the forested area of Seikh Sou in suburban [[Thessaloniki]] from 1958 to 1959, killing three people; executed 1968, and since then his guilt has been questioned.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.athensmagazine.gr/article/news/36593-oi-thewries-synwmosias-gia-ton-laquo-drako-raquo-toy-seix-soy-h-skoteinh-ypothesh-kai-ta-fonika-poy-anatrixiazoyn-akoma-kai-miso-aiwna-meta |title=\u039f\u03b9 \u03b8\u03b5\u03c9\u03c1\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c9\u03bc\u03bf\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \"\u03b4\u03c1\u03ac\u03ba\u03bf\" \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a3\u03ad\u03b9\u03c7 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c5! \u0397 \u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae \u03c5\u03c0\u03cc\u03b8\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c6\u03bf\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03c7\u03b9\u03ac\u03b6\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bc\u03b9\u03c3\u03cc \u03b1\u03b9\u03ce\u03bd\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03ac!!! |trans-title=The conspiracy theories about the \"dragon\" of the Sheikh Shu! The dark affair and the killings that shake even half a century later!!! |last=\u0391\u03b4\u03b1\u03bc\u03bf\u03c5 |first=\u039d\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b1\u03c3 |date=2013-04-11 |website=Athens Magazine |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kyriakos Papachronis]]: also known as the \"Ogre of [[Drama, Greece|Drama]]\"; murdered three women from 1981 to 1982, committing other crimes as well; sentenced to life imprisonment, released on bail in 2004.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.kathimerini.gr/202903/article/epikairothta/ellada/eley8eros-o-papaxronhs-poy-apokhry3e-ton-ewsforo |title=\u0395\u03bb\u03b5\u03cd\u03b8\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03ba\u03ae\u03c1\u03c5\u03be\u03b5 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0395\u03c9\u03c3\u03c6\u03cc\u03c1\u03bf |last=\u039a\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03c3\u03b7 |first=\u0395\u03bb\u03b5\u03bd\u03b1 |date=9 December 2004 |newspaper=[[Kathimerini]] |language=el |access-date=2018-05-19}}</ref>\n*[[Mariam Soulakiotis]]: also known as the \"Woman Rasputin\"; convent abbot who lured, tortured and killed 177 wealthy women and children from 1939 to 1951; died 1954.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.reporter.com.cy/greece/article/61972/i-monachi-serial-killer-mariam-tis-kerateas |title=\u0397 \u03bc\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03c7\u03ae serial killer \u039c\u03b1\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bc \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1\u03c4\u03ad\u03b1\u03c2 |trans-title=The serial killer nun Mariam of Keratea |first=\u0395\u03bb\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 |last=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 |date=2016-05-09 |website=\u03a1\u03b5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1 |language=el |access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref>\n*[[Dimitris Vakrinos]]: killed five people and attempted seven more murders for minor quarrels between 1987 and 1996; hanged himself in the prison showers in 1997.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tovima.gr/relatedarticles/article/?aid=87285 |title=\u03a4\u03bf\u2026 \u03b2\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03b2\u03ac\u03ba\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c7\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03cd |first=\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b3\u03b9\u03c9\u03c4\u03b1 |last=\u039c\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b9\u03ba\u03b1 |date=13 April 1997 |newspaper=[[To Vima]] |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Hong Kong===\n*[[Lam Kor-wan]]: sexual sadist who murdered and dismembered four women in the 1980s; sentenced to death (commuted to life imprisonment as per tradition at that time).<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scmp.com/magazines/post-magazine/short-reads/article/2106303/our-archives-capture-hong-kongs-jars-killer |title=From our archives: the capture of Hong Kong's Jars Killer |first=Jessica |last=Li |date=August 13, 2017 |newspaper=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lam Kwok-wai]]: murdered three women, apprehended in 1993 and sentenced to life imprisonment (capital punishment already abolished).<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/article/128162/tuen-mun-rapist-loses-plea |title=Tuen Mun rapist loses plea |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=17 August 1995 |newspaper=South China Morning Post |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Hungary===\n*[[Angel Makers of Nagyr\u00e9v]]: group of women led by Susanna Fazekas who poisoned around 300 people in the village of [[Nagyr\u00e9v]] between 1914 and 1929.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/3567679.stm |title=Unearthing Hungary husband murders |last1=Fish |first1=Jim |accessdate=10 December 2016 |website=BBC News |date=29 March 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/articles/199911/bad-girls |title=Bad Girls |first=Barry |last=Yeoman |magazine=[[Psychology Today]] |date=1 November 1999 |publisher=Sussex Publishers, LLC |accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Erzs\u00e9bet B\u00e1thory]]: [[countess]] who killed servant girls; rumored to have killed more than 600.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/bathory/7.html |title=Countess Elizabeth Bathory \u2013 The Blood Countess |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |website=The Crime Library |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815205239/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/bathory/7.html |archive-date=2011-08-15}}</ref>\n*[[Alad\u00e1r Don\u00e1szi]]: robber who killed four people from 1991 to 1992 with his accomplice L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Bene; committed suicide in prison in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kisalfold.hu/szieszta/irnoka_volt_donaszi_a_hirhedt_gyilkos/1164138/ |title=\u00cdrnoka volt Don\u00e1szi, a h\u00edrhedt gyilkos |trans-title=Clerk was Don\u00e1szi, the notorious killer |date=25 March 2006 |website=Kisalf\u00f6ld |language=hu |accessdate=23 September 2015}}</ref>\n*[[B\u00e9la Kiss]]: murdered at least twenty-four women, escaped justice in the confusion of [[World War I]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/justice-story/killer-murdered-24-pickled-corpses-barrels-article-1.1607445 |title=Hungarian man murdered 24, pickled each corpse in barrels of alcohol in early 1900s |first=Mara |last=Bovsun |date=9 February 2014 |newspaper=[[New York Daily News]] |access-date=20 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302235328/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/justice-story/killer-murdered-24-pickled-corpses-barrels-article-1.1607445 |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[P\u00e9ter Kov\u00e1cs (serial killer)|P\u00e9ter Kov\u00e1cs]]: also known as the \"[[Martf\u0171]] Monster\"; truck driver who raped and killed between four and five women from 1957 and 1967, possibly responsible for more murders; executed 1968.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nol.hu/mozaik/hatodik_tipusu_sorozatgyilkossag-333179 |title=Hatodik t\u00edpus\u00fa sorozatgyilkoss\u00e1g |trans-title=Sixth type serial killer |date=17 May 2009 |newspaper=[[N\u00e9pszabads\u00e1g]] |language=hu |accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Guszt\u00e1v Nemesk\u00e9ri]]: also known as the \"Kat\u00f3ka Street Killer\"; killed four people between 1996 and 1999 to settle his debts, including his half-brother; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://index.hu/bulvar/gyilkos1009/ |title=T\u00e9nyleges \u00e9letfogytiglant kapott a n\u00e9gyszeres gyilkos |trans-title=The four-time killer got life imprisonment |date=9 October 2003 |website=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |language=hu |accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Zolt\u00e1n Szab\u00f3 (serial killer)|Zolt\u00e1n Szab\u00f3]]: also known as the \"Bal\u00e1stya Monster\"; killed and mutilated at least four women on his farm in [[Bal\u00e1stya]] between 1998 and 2001; committed suicide while imprisoned in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ma.hu/tart/rcikk/a/0/65744/1 |title=\u00c9letfogytiglani fegyh\u00e1z a \"bal\u00e1styai r\u00e9m\" meg\u00e9rdemelt b\u00fcntet\u00e9se |trans-title=Life imprisonment is a well-deserved punishment for \"Bal\u00e1stya's Nightmare\" |date=20 November 2003 |website=Ma.hu |language=hu |accessdate=2 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Iceland===\n*[[Axlar-Bj\u00f6rn|Bj\u00f6rn P\u00e9tursson]]: also known as \"Axlar-Bj\u00f6rn\"; killed at least nine travellers in the 16th century.\n\n===India===\n*[[Thug Behram]] (ca. 1765\u20131840): alleged to have killed over 900 people; executed in 1840.<ref>{{cite book |last=Dash |first=Mike |author-link=Mike Dash |date=2005 |title=Thug: The True Story of India's Murderous Cult |location=London, UK |publisher=Granta Books |pages=283\u2013289 |isbn=1-86207-604-9}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Ash |first=Russell |date=1995 |title=The Top Ten of Everything 1996 |location=London, UK |publisher=[[Dorling Kindersley]] |page=[https://archive.org/details/toptenofeverythi00russ_0/page/65 65] |isbn=0-7894-0196-7 |url=https://archive.org/details/toptenofeverythi00russ_0/page/65 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Rubinstein |first=William D. |author-link=William Rubinstein |date=2004 |title=Genocide: A History |location=Harlow, Essex |publisher=[[Pearson Education Limited]] |page=83 |isbn=978-0-58250-601-5}}</ref>\n*[[Seema Gavit and Renuka Shinde]] (born 1975 and 1973): sisters who kidnapped and murdered five children between 1990 and 1996.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/thieves-who-kidnapped-used-and-killed-babies |title=Thieves who kidnapped, used and killed babies |first=Atikh |last=Rashid |date=18 August 2014 |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[M. Jaishankar]] (born 1977): also known as \"Psycho Shankar\", involved in about 30 rapes, murders and robbery cases around [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref name=\"IT_how_2013\">{{cite magazine |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/psycho-shankar-how-serial-rapist-killer-was-nabbed/1/308631.html |title=Psycho Shankar \u2013 How the serial rapist and killer was nabbed |first1=T. S. |last1=Sudhir |first2=Rohini |last2=Swamy |first3=Shreesha |last3=Reddy |lastauthoramp=yes |date=6 September 2013 |magazine=[[India Today]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710200427/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/psycho-shankar-how-serial-rapist-killer-was-nabbed/1/308631.html |archivedate=10 July 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Chandrakant Jha]] (born 1967): befriended and murdered seven male migrants from 1998 to 2007; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/north/story/rohini-court-death-sentence-to-serial-killer-chandrakant-jha-153306-2013-02-05 |title=Rohini Court awards death sentence to serial killer Chandrakant Jha |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=5 February 2013 |magazine=India Today |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Joshi-Abhyankar serial murders]]: series of ten murders committed by four art students in [[Pune]]; all were executed on 27 November 1983.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rahulchandawarkar.com/news/general/general03float.htm |title=The Evil and the Dead |first=Rahul |last=Chandawarkar |date=September 6, 1998 |newspaper=[[Sunday Mid-Day]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=rahulchandawarkar.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715150717/http://www.rahulchandawarkar.com/news/general/general03float.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n*[[KD Kempamma]] (born 1970): also known as \"Cyanide Mallika\"; poisoned six women from 1999 to 2007 with cyanide; India's first convicted female serial killer; sentenced to death, commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/First-woman-serial-killer-nabbed/articleshow/2665976.cms |title=First woman serial killer nabbed |date=1 January 2008 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/cyanide-mallika-serial-killers-women-crime/story/1/21649.html |title=Women who kill: The story behind India's first woman serial killer |last=Anand |first=Pinky |date=10 January 2018 |website=Daily O |accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n*[[2006 Noida serial murders|Surendra Koli]] (born 1970-71): convicted of raping and murdering four children in [[Delhi]] in 2005 and 2006 with another twelve cases pending.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rediff.com/news/report/how-indira-jaising-got-midnight-reprieve-for-convict-koli/20140908.htm |title=How Indira Jaising got midnight reprieve for convict Koli |date=September 8, 2014 |website=[[Rediff]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://scroll.in/article/679297/nine-reasons-not-to-hang-alleged-nithari-serial-killer-surendra-koli |title=Nine reasons not to hang alleged Nithari serial killer Surendra Koli |first=Shivam |last=Vij |date=17 September 2014 |website=[[Scroll.in]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mohan Kumar (serial killer)|Mohan Kumar]] (born 1963): also known as \"Cyanide Mohan\"; killed twenty female victims with cyanide, claiming they were contraceptive pills; sentenced to death in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=67282 |title=Mangalore: Neighbours, Family, Refuse to Accept Mohan as Serial Killer |date=23 October 2009 |website=[[Daijiworld Media|Daijiworld.com]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ravinder Kumar (serial killer)|Ravinder Kumar]] (born 1991): killed the children of poor families from 2008 until his arrest in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/delhi-serial-rapist-ravinder-kumar-admits-killing-30-children-2355078.html |title=Delhi serial rapist Ravinder Kumar admits to killing more than 30 children |date=21 July 2015 |website=[[Firstpost]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Motta Navas]] (born 1966): killed pavement dwellers in their sleep during a three-month period in 2012 in [[Kollam]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/man-held-on-charge-of-five-murders/article4060891.ece |title=Man held on charge of five murders |date=3 November 2012 |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Santosh Pol]] (born 1974): also known as \"Dr. Death\"; killed six people with [[succinylcholine]] in the town of Dhom.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/maharashtra-doctor-death-six-murders/1/741281.html |title=Maharashtra's 'Dr Death' confesses to 6 murders, five of them women |date=August 16, 2016 |magazine=India Today |accessdate=2016-08-17}}</ref>\n*[[Raman Raghav]] (1929\u20131995): also known as \"Psycho Raman\"; [[Mumbai]] man who killed homeless people and others in their sleep.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/life-style/the-monsoon-murders |title=The real man behind Raman Raghav 2.0: Mumbai's first big-ticket serial killer |first=Smita |last=Nair |date=2016-06-26 |newspaper=The Indian Express |access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/inside-the-mind-of-raman-raghav-mumbai-s-serial-killer-of-the-60s/story-LaA01MtT0wrAM0ZprCoLYJ.html |title=Inside the mind of Raman Raghav, Mumbai's serial killer of the 1960s |first=Poonam |last=Saxena |date=2016-06-11 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref>\n*[[Umesh Reddy]] alias BA Umesh (born 1969): confessed to eighteen rapes and murders, convicted in nine cases.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1091108/jsp/7days/story_11713568.jsp |title=Murders most foul |first=Varun |last=Verma |date=2009-11-08 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (Kolkata)|The Telegraph]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ripper Jayanandan]] (born 1968): also known as the \"Singing Serial Killer\"; killed seven people during robberies.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/Ripper-Jayanandan-gets-life-sentence/articleshow/11228173.cms |title=Ripper Jayanandan gets life sentence |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=24 December 2011 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Satish (Bahadurgarh baby killer)|Satish]] (born c. 1973): also known as the \"[[Bahadurgarh]] Baby Killer\"; confessed to and convicted for ten murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Serial-killers-life-spared/articleshow/2722792.cms |title=Serial killer's life spared |date=22 January 2008 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Auto Shankar]] (1954\u20131995): murdered nine teenage girls in [[Thiruvanmiyur]], [[Chennai]] during a six-month period in 1988; executed in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=EoZlAAAAIBAJ&sjid=mZ4NAAAAIBAJ&dq=auto%20shankar&pg=1032%2C3469058 |title=The mass murderer of Madras |first1=K. M. |last1=Thomas |date=9 September 1990 |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PIxlAAAAIBAJ&sjid=q54NAAAAIBAJ&pg=817%2C2582855 |title=Auto Shankar, two others sentenced to death |date=1 June 1991 |newspaper=The Indian Express |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Kampatimar Shankariya]] (1952\u20131979): killed at least 70 people with hammer in 1977-78; hung in Jaipur.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA239&lpg=PA239&dq=kampatimar+shankariya#v=onepage&q=kampatimar%20shankariya&f=false|title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers|last=Newton|first=Michael|publisher=Infobase Publishing|year=2006|isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3|location=|pages=239|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Darbara Singh (murderer)|Darbara Singh]] (born 1952): convicted for two murders, seventeen suspected victims.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/india-s-cruel-serial-baby-killer-darbara-singh-who-murdered-2674.html |title=India's cruel serial baby killer Darbara Singh, who murdered seventeen babies |date=2013-02-17 |website=[[India TV]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> Singh had three children; his wife expelled him from their house, because of his \"bad habits\".\n*[[Charles Sobhraj]] (born 1944): killed at least twelve Western tourists in [[Southeast Asia]] during the 1970s; imprisoned in [[India]] (released) and [[Nepal]] (in prison).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/story/international-serial-killer-charles-sobhraj-64-engaged-to-woman-20 |title=International Serial Killer Charles Sobhraj, 64, Engaged to Woman, 20 |date=5 July 2008 |website=[[Fox News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/famous/charles_sobraj/1.html |title=Charles Sobhraj |first=Mark |last=Gribben |website=[[Crime Library]] |accessdate=20 February 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224131111/http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/famous/charles_sobraj/1.html |archivedate=24 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Akku Yadav]] (died 2004): murdered at least three people and dumped their bodies on the railroad tracks; lynched by a mob of around 200 women in [[Nagpur]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-23/nagpur/34679336_1_murder-case-akku-yadav-panch-witness |title=Trial in Akku Yadav murder case begins |date=22 October 2012 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2005/sep/16/india.gender |title='Arrest us all': the 200 women who killed a rapist |first=Raekha |last=Prasad |date=16 September 2005 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/01/15/opinion/in-india-one-womans-stand-says-enough.html |title=In India, One Woman's Stand Says 'Enough' |first=Nicholas D. |last=Kristof |date=15 January 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Indonesia===\n*[[Baekuni]]: also known as \"Babe\"; pedophile who killed between four and fourteen boys from 1993 to 2010; sentenced to life imprisonment, later changed to the death sentence.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2010/01/17/07262786/Mutilasi.Baekuni.Lebih.Keji.Ryan.Henyansah.Lebih.Rumit |title=Mutilasi, Baekuni Lebih Keji, Ryan Henyansah Lebih Rumit |trans-title=Mutilation, Baekuni more vile, Ryan Henyansah more complex |date=17 January 2010 |newspaper=[[Kompas]] |language=id |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Very Idham Henyansyah]]: also known as \"Ryan\" and the \"Singing Serial Killer\"; convicted and sentenced to death in 2008 for the killing of eleven people.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/03/24/2525127.htm |title=Indonesia seeks death for singing serial killer |date=24 March 2009 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=2011-01-10}}</ref>\n*[[Ahmad Suradji]]: admitted to killing 42 women around [[Medan]]; sentenced to death and executed by firing squad on 10 July 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/indonesia/2286216/Black-Magic-Killer-executed-for-42-murders.html |title=Black Magic Killer executed for 42 murders |first=Thomas |last=Bell |date=11 July 2008 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\n*[[Asghar the Murderer|Ali Asghar Borujerdi]]: also known as \"Asghar the Murderer\"; killed 33 young adults in Iraq and Iran; executed on 26 June 1934.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://ulib.aub.edu.lb/data/hist258k-cs-47/Schayegh-Serial_murder_in_Tehran.pdf |title=Serial Murder in Tehran: Crime, Science, and the Formation of Modern State and Society in Interwar Iran |last=Schayegh |first=Cyrus |date=2005 |journal=Comparative Studies in Society and History |publisher=Cambridge University Press |volume=47 |issue=4 |pages=836\u2013862 |doi=10.1017/S001041750500037X |issn=0010-4175 |jstor=3879345 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520022651/http://ulib.aub.edu.lb/data/hist258k-cs-47/Schayegh-Serial_murder_in_Tehran.pdf |archive-date=20 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Louay Omar Mohammed al-Taei]]: medical doctor found to have killed 43 wounded policemen, soldiers and officials in [[Kirkuk]]; was a member of an [[Insurgency|insurgent cell]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/insurgent-doctor-killed-dozens-of-wounded-soldiers-6105814.html |title=Insurgent doctor killed dozens of wounded soldiers |last=Cockburn |first=Patrick |date=23 March 2006 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Iran===\n*[[Mohammed Bijeh]]: also known as the \"Tehran Desert Vampire\"; killed at least sixteen young boys near [[Tehran]]; executed in 2005.\n*[[Saeed Hanaei]]: also known as \"The Spider Killer\"; killed at least sixteen women around [[Mashhad]]; executed in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/04/18/world/iran-executes-worker-who-strangled-16-women-over-2-years.html |title=Iran Executes Worker Who Strangled 16 Women Over 2 Years |first=Nazila |last=Fathi |date=April 18, 2002 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Esmail Jafarzadeh]]: murdered a young girl in 2017, confessing to the murder of two women in 2012 and 2014 after his arrest; executed 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fararu.com/fa/news/324976/%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84-%D8%A2%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D9%88-%D8%B2%D9%86-%D8%AF%D9%8A%DA%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D9%87%D9%85-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title=\u0642\u0627\u062a\u0644 \u0622\u062a\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0648 \u0632\u0646 \u062f\u064a\u06af\u0631 \u0631\u0627 \u0647\u0645 \u06a9\u0634\u062a\u0647\u200c \u0627\u0633\u062a |trans-title=Athena's killer has also killed two other women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=6 August 2008 |website=[[Fararu]] |language=fa |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gholamreza Khosroo Kurdieh]]: also known as \"The Night Bat\"; murdered nine women in Tehran in 1997, burning the bodies afterwards; executed 1997.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://images.hamshahrionline.ir/hamnews/1376/760523/HAVAD30.HTM |title=\u0634\u062f\u061f 214 \u0627\u0639\u062f\u0627\u0645\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0686\u06af\u0648\u0646\u0647\u200c\u200f\u200e \u062f\u062e\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0646\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0648\u200f\u200e \u0632\u0646\u0627\u0646\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0642\u0627\u062a\u0644\u200c\u200f\u200e |trans-title=214 was it? Execution of killer of girls and women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=23 August 1997 |newspaper=[[Hamshahri]] |language=fa |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Majid Salek Mohammadi]]: murdered twenty-four people from 1981 to 1985, primarily women he considered unfaithful to their husbands; committed suicide in prison before he could be sentenced.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.isna.ir/news/95050119135/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84-%D8%B3%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%B2%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86 |title=White rope murders |date=2016-08-20 |website=[[Iranian Students News Agency]] |language=fa |accessdate=25 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Republic of Ireland===\n*[[Geoffrey Evans|Geoffrey Evans and John Shaw]]: Englishmen who traveled to Ireland in 1976 and vowed to murder a woman once a week, killing two; both apprehended and sentenced. Until his 2012 death, Evans was one of Ireland's longest-serving prisoners.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.wicklownews.net/Post/2012/5/1911/brittas-bay-killer-geoffrey-evans-dies |title=Brittas bay killer Geoffrey Evans dies |date=21 May 2012 |newspaper=Wicklow News |accessdate=21 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120524044621/http://www.wicklownews.net/Post/2012/5/1911/brittas-bay-killer-geoffrey-evans-dies |archivedate=24 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Darkey Kelly]]: [[brothel]]-keeper who killed six men in the 18th century; accused of witchcraft and was [[death by burning|burned at the stake]] in 1761.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/was-irish-witch-darkey-kelly-really-irelands-first-serial-killer-113340849-237364711.html |title=Was Irish witch Darkey Kelly really Ireland's first serial killer? |first=Cathy |last=Hayes |date=2011-01-12 |website=IrishCentral.com |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite podcast |url=https://www.podomatic.com/podcasts/nosmokewithouthellfire1/episodes/2011-01-19T14_46_14-08_00 |title=No Smoke Without Hellfire Part I |host=McLoughlin, Eamonn |date=2011-01-19 |website=PodOmatic |access-date=2015-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Alice Kyteler]]: also known as \"The Witch of [[Kilkenny]]\"; alleged witch who poisoned four husbands in the 14th century; fled to England, fate unknown.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Chapter II: \"Dame Alice Kyteler, the Sorceress of Kilkenny |title=Irish Witchcraft and Demonology |first=St. John D., B.D. |last=Seymour |date=1913 |pages=25\u201326 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/irishwitchcraftd00seymrich#page/24/mode/2up |location=Dublin |publisher=Hodges, Figgs}}</ref>\n\n===Israel===\n*[[Yahya Farhan]]: [[Bedouin]] serial killer, who murdered between two and four people from 1994 to 2004, including [[Murder of Dana Bennett|Dana Bennett]]; sentenced to three consecutive life sentences, and later acquitted of one murder.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mako.co.il/news-law/legal/Article-cec7b38cde5f921004.htm |title=See: Farhan reconstructs Bennett's murder |first=Yossi |last=Mizrahi |date=July 21, 2010 |website=Mako |language=he |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nicolai Bonner]]: killed four people in 2005 in [[Haifa]], three of them homeless; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/homeless-man-found-guilty-of-haifa-serial-murders-1.204551 |title=Homeless Man Found Guilty of Haifa Serial Murders |date=2006-11-07 |newspaper=[[Haaretz]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Italy===\n*[[Wolfgang Abel and Marco Furlan]]: German-Italian duo found guilty of ten of 27 counts of murder in 1987.\n*[[Beasts of Satan]]: Satanic cult members who committed three notorious ritual murders from 1998 to 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/this_world/4446342.stm |title=Investigating the 'death metal' murders |last=Bagnall |first=Sam |date=23 November 2005 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Marco Bergamo (serial killer)|Marco Bergamo]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Bolzano]]\"; murdered five women in Bolzano from 1985 to 1992; died from a lung infection in 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/17_ottobre_17/morto-margo-bergamo-mostro-bolzano-che-aveva-ucciso-5-donne-8368d79c-b35d-11e7-9cef-7c546dada489.shtml |title=Morto Marco Bergamo, il \"mostro di Bolzano\" che aveva ucciso 5 donne |trans-title=Marco Bergamo, the \"Monster of Bolzano\" who had killed 5 women, is dead |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=17 October 2017 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Donato Bilancia]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Liguria]]\" murdered seventeen people in seven months between 1997 and 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.occhirossi.it/biografie/DonatoBilancia.htm |title=Donato Bilancia |last=Del Frate |first=Daniele |date=31 October 2004 |website=Occhi Rossi |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Antonio Boggia]]: also known as the \"Monster of Milan\"; first documented Italian serial killer; murdered four people for monetary purposes between 1849 and 1859; hanged 1862.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cultura/storia-primo-serial-killer-italiano-944632.html |title=Storia del primo serial killer italiano |trans-title=History of the first Italian serial killer |first=Luca |last=Crovi |date=22 August 2013 |newspaper=[[Il Giornale]] |language=it |accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Ralph Brydges]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Rome]]\"; English pastor who is widely believed to have murdered five girls in Rome in the 1920s, and four in other countries; never convicted of his crimes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/genova/mostro-e-commissario-che-bracc-fino-genova.html |title=Il mostro e il commissario che lo bracc\u00f2 fino a Genova |trans-title=The monster and the commissioner who chased him to Genoa |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=9 May 2012 |newspaper=Il Giornale |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Sonya Caleffi]]: nurse who poisoned terminally ill patients between 2003 and 2004, killing 5 of them; sentenced to 20 years of imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ildue.it/Notizie/SVittore/Dettaglio.asp?ID=537 |title=Sonya Caleffi a 'Grazia': 'Non sono un'assassina' |trans-title=Sonya Caleffi to 'Grazia': 'I am not a murderer' |date=28 March 2006 |website=IlDue.it |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514001944/http://www.ildue.it/Notizie/SVittore/Dettaglio.asp?ID=537 |archive-date=May 14, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Luigi Chiatti]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Foligno]]\"; kidnapped and killed two children in 1992 and 1993; sentenced to two life sentences, but he was found unfit to stand trial and was reduced to 30 years in a mental hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.umbria24.it/cronaca/lavvocato-bacino-%c2%abchiatti-non-e-uscito-dal-carcere-ne-ha-mai-chiesto-la-semiliberta%c2%bb |title=Luigi Chiatti non \u00e8 uscito dal carcere n\u00e9 ha mai chiesto la semilibert\u00e0 |trans-title=Luigi Chiatti was not released from prison and has never asked for parole |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=18 November 2010 |website=Umbria24 |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Leonarda Cianciulli]]: also known as the \"Soap-Maker of [[Correggio]]\"; murderer of three women between 1939 and 1940; died in a women's criminal asylum in 1970.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.museocriminologico.it/correggio_uk.htm |title=The Correggio soap-maker |website=Museo Criminologico |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060912155116/http://www.museocriminologico.it/correggio_uk.htm |archivedate=2006-09-12}}</ref>\n*[[Ferdinand Gamper]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Merano]]\"; killed six people in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.italiacriminale.it/ferdinand-gamper-il-mostro-di-merano/ |title=Ferdinand Gamper: the monster Merano |website=Italia Criminale |language=it |access-date=17 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330223112/http://www.italiacriminale.it/ferdinand-gamper-il-mostro-di-merano/ |archive-date=2016-03-30}}</ref>\n*[[Pier Paolo Brega Massone]]: murdered at least four people in [[Milan]] and maimed other dozens of victims through unnecessary surgeries to illegally obtain a large amounts of money refunds; convicted and given a life sentence.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://milano.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/14_aprile_09/clinica-orrori-condanna-all-ergastolo-brega-massone-80c798e6-c006-11e3-a6b2-109f6a781e55.shtml |title=Clinica degli orrori: Ergastolo per Brega Massone, arresto in aula |trans-title=Clinic of horrors: life imprisonment for Brega Massone, arrest in court |date=2014-04-09 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Andrea Matteucci]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Aosta]]\"; murdered a merchant and three prostitutes in Aosta from 1980 to 1995; sentenced to 28 years imprisonment and three years in a mental institution.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.gqitalia.it/underground/2015/06/05/andrea-matteucci-il-mostro-di-aosta/ |title=L'inquietante parabola di Andrea Matteucci, il mostro di Aosta |trans-title=The disturbing parable of Andrea Matteucci, the monster of Aosta |first=Edoardo |last=Montolli |date=5 June 2015 |magazine=[[GQ|GQ Italia]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Maurizio Minghella]]: killed five women in his hometown of [[Genoa]] in 1978; imprisoned and released, after which he murdered at least four more and is suspected of other murders between 1997 and 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lastampa.it/Torino/cmsSezioni/cronaca/200810articoli/8420girata.asp |title=Il pugile schizofrenico che strangola e dimentica; Diciotto anni di prigione Liberato, torna a uccidere |trans-title=The schizophrenic boxer who strangles and forgets; freed after eighteen years in prison to kill again |first=Massimo |last=Numa |date=22 October 2008 |newspaper=[[La Stampa]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081022213240/http://www.lastampa.it/Torino/cmsSezioni/cronaca/200810articoli/8420girata.asp |archive-date=22 October 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Giorgio Orsolano]]: also known as the \"Hyena of [[San Giorgio Canavese|San Giorgio]]\"; raped, killed and dismembered three girls from 1834 to 1835 in his hometown of San Giorgio Canavese; executed 1835.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.torinoscienza.it/anatomia/le_collezioni/aprieed6eed6.html?obj_id=2375 |title=Death mask of Giorgio Orsolano |access-date=2018-11-24 |website=Torino Museo di Anatomia |language=it |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210191624/http://www.torinoscienza.it/anatomia/le_collezioni/aprieed6eed6.html?obj_id=2375 |archivedate=2015-02-10}}</ref>\n*[[Ernesto Picchioni]]: also known as \"The Monster of [[Nerola]]\"; murdered people around his home; died of cardiac arrest in 1967.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.P/p/picchioni-ernesto.htm |title=Ernesto Picchioni A.K.A.: \"The Monster of Nerola\" |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Milena Quaglini]]: murdered her husband and two men who tried to rape her from 1995 to 1999; committed suicide while imprisoned in 2001.<ref name=Milena>{{Cite web |url=http://www.misteriditalia.it/cn/?page_id=5150 |title=1995-1998: Milena Quaglini, La Donna Che Uccideva gli Uomini Violenti |trans-title=Milena Quaglini, The Woman Who Killed Violent Men |website=Misteri d'Italia |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gianfranco Stevanin]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Terrazzo]]\"; raped and murdered prostitutes after violent sex games between 1993 and 1994; violated the corpse of one victim; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1996/08/25/sono-morte-dopo-un-gioco-di.html |title=Sono Morte Dopo Un Gioco Di Sesso Estremo ... |trans-title=I Died After An Extreme Sex Game ... |date=1996-08-25 |newspaper=[[la Repubblica]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Roberto Succo]]: murdered at least five people, including his parents, committed suicide while in prison in 1988.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/c-dric-kahn-inside-the-mind-of-a-killer-178982.html |title=C\u00e9dric Kahn: Inside the mind of a killer |last=Romney |first=Jonathan |date=2 June 2002 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Giulia Tofana]]: leader of a group of female poisoners in the 17th century; died in her bed, never been arrested.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mikedashhistory.com/2015/04/06/aqua-tofana-slow-poisoning-and-husband-killing-in-17th-century-italy/ |title=Aqua Tofana: Slow-Poisoning and Husband-Killing in 17th Century Italy |first=Mike |last=Dash |date=6 April 2015 |website=A Blast From the Past |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Giorgio Vizzardelli]]: shot and killed five people around [[Sarzana]] from 1937 to 1939; sentenced to life imprisonment; committed suicide by slitting his throat with a kitchen knife in 1973.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/genova/mostro-sarzana-80-anni-906542.html |title=Il mostro di Sarzana 80 anni dopo |trans-title=The monster of Sarzana 80 years later |date=14 April 2013 |newspaper=[[Il Giornale]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Jamaica===\n*[[Lewis Hutchinson]]: Scottish immigrant convicted of shooting dozens of people in the 18th century; executed in 1773.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/history/story0036.htm |title=Pieces of the Past \u2013 Lewis Hutchinson: The Mad Master |last=Tortello |first=Rebecca |date=6 November 2002 |newspaper=[[The Gleaner (newspaper)|Jamaica Gleaner]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150127042527/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/history/story0036.htm |archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Japan===\n*[[Ryuun Daimai]]: also known as the \"Nun Slayer\"; former monk who raped and killed at least five people in several cities between 1905 and 1915; executed 1916.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www5b.biglobe.ne.jp/~madison/murder/text_japan/ryuun.html|title=Daimai Ryuun|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=December 25, 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Sachiko Eto]]: also known as the \"Drumstick Killer\"; cult leader who murdered six of her followers with [[Taiko]] sticks from 1994 to 1995; executed 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201904/20190414_13031.html|title=<Retrospective of the Heisei Era> (6) Sukagawa Prayer Murders (7 years)|last=|first=|date=April 14, 2019|work=[[Kahoku Shimp\u014d]]|access-date=2019-04-16|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416041418/https://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201904/20190414_13031.html|archive-date=16 April 2019|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Satar\u014d Fukiage]]: raped and killed at least seven girls in the early 20th century; executed 1926.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www8.ocn.ne.jp/~moonston/child.htm |title=Child Killers: \u5439\u4e0a\u4f50\u592a\u90ce |website=Monsters |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071117231639/http://www8.ocn.ne.jp/~moonston/child.htm |archivedate=2007-11-17}}</ref>\n*[[Sokichi Furuya]]: murdered eight elderly people in several western Japanese cities for more than a month in 1965; suspected of four earlier murders, for two of which an accomplice was executed; executed 1985.<ref>[[Asahi Shimbun]] (June 1, 1985) Tokyo morning newspaper, p. 23 \"Robbery murderer, execution of Furuya at Osaka Detention Center\"</ref>\n*[[Hiroaki Hidaka]]: killed four prostitutes in [[Hiroshima]] in 1996; executed 25 December 2006.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/02/09/news/lawyer-to-sue-after-prison-bars-meeting-before-inmate-is-executed/ |title=Lawyer to sue after prison bars meeting before inmate is executed |date=2007-02-09 |newspaper=[[The Japan Times]] |accessdate=2008-02-23}}</ref>\n*[[Miyuki Ishikawa]]: [[midwife]] who murdered an estimated 103 infants, but could have been up to 169, in the 1940s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://homepage3.nifty.com/koseki-t/yougo2.html |script-title=ja:\u990a\u8b77\u65bd\u8a2d\u306e\u5b50\u3069\u3082\u305f\u3061\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u5150\u7ae5\u3068\u798f\u7949\u306b\u95a2\u9023\u3059\u308b\u3067\u304d\u3054\u3068 |first=Takashi |last=Koseki |website=Koseki-t |language=ja |accessdate=2008-02-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070211225216/http://homepage3.nifty.com/koseki-t/yougo2.html |archivedate=February 11, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://homepage2.nifty.com/kousinren/nenhyo/nenpyo4/1948.htm |title=15 March 1948 |website=Kousinren |language=ja |accessdate=2008-02-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120713061748/http://homepage2.nifty.com/kousinren/nenhyo/nenpyo4/1948.htm |archive-date=2012-07-13}}</ref>\n*[[Chisako Kakehi]]: poisoned her husband and two other men to death, attempted to kill a fourth man, and is a suspect in another seven deaths; sentenced to death in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/japans-black-widow-given-death-penalty-for-murders/news-story/a2c64e7c3f304991462bed828274a8f7 |title=Japan's 'Black Widow' given death penalty for murders |last=Palin |first=Megan |date=7 November 2017 |website=[[News.com.au]] |access-date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Kiyotaka Katsuta]]: [[firefighter]] who shot and strangled at least eight people, some during robberies, between 1972 and 1982.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2000/12/01/national/serial-killer-two-other-murderers-hanged/ |title=Serial killer, two other murderers hanged |date=December 1, 2000 |newspaper=The Japan Times |accessdate=2008-03-01}}</ref>\n*[[Kanae Kijima]]: also known as \"The Konkatsu Killer\"; marriage fraudster who poisoned between three and seven men for money, from 2007 to 2009; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20170414/k10010948561000.html|title=Kanae Kijima, accused of killing three men in staged accidents, on death row|last=|first=|date=April 14, 2017|work=NHK|access-date=April 15, 2017|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415103815/http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20170414/k10010948561000.html|archive-date=15 April 2017|publisher=[[NHK]]}}</ref>\n*[[Yoshio Kodaira]]: rapist thought to have killed eleven people in Japan and China as a soldier; executed on 5 October 1949.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,853940-2,00.html |title=Peace, It's Wonderful |date=1949-10-17 |magazine=TIME |accessdate=2008-02-09}}</ref>\n*[[Genzo Kurita]]: killed six women and two children and engaged in rape and [[necrophilia]]; executed on 16 January 1959.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kokkai.ndl.go.jp/SENTAKU/sangiin/024/0640/02405100640002c.html |title=\u7b2c024\u56de\u56fd\u4f1a \u6cd5\u52d9\u59d4\u54e1\u4f1a\u516c\u8074\u4f1a \u7b2c2\u53f7 |trans-title=The 24th Diet Legal Committee Hearing No.2 |date=1956-05-10 |website=[[National Diet Library]] |language=ja |accessdate=2008-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023230218/http://kokkai.ndl.go.jp/SENTAKU/sangiin/024/0640/02405100640002c.html |archive-date=23 October 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Hiroshi Maeue]]: also known as \"Suicide Website Murderer\"; [[Osaka]] man who lured people from suicide clubs promising to kill himself with his victims.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/03/29/national/man-gets-death-for-murdering-suicidal-trio/ |title=Man gets death for murdering suicidal trio |date=2007-03-29 |newspaper=The Japan Times |accessdate=2008-02-23}}</ref>\n*[[Futoshi Matsunaga]] and [[Junko Ogata]]: also known as \"House of Horror\"; tortured and killed at least seven people between 1996 and 1998, including Ogata's family.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/weekly/news/nn2005/nn20050312a5.htm |title=Pair accused of slaying 7 face gallows |date=2005-03-03 |newspaper=The Japan Times Weekly |accessdate=2008-02-10 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121227215212/search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/nn20050303a1.html |archive-date=27 December 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Tsutomu Miyazaki]]: also known as \"The [[Otaku]] Murderer\", \"The Little Girl Murderer\" and \"Dracula\"; killed four pre-school-age girls and ate the hand of a victim; executed in 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/national/20080618TDY02306.htm |title=Miyazaki unrepentant to the last / Serial child killer goes to execution without apologizing or explaining his thinking |date=2008-06-18 |newspaper=[[Yomiuri Shimbun]] |location=Tokyo |accessdate=2008-06-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20080621044230/http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/national/20080618TDY02306.htm |archivedate=2008-06-21}}</ref>\n*[[Seisaku Nakamura]]: also known as the \"[[Hamamatsu]] Deaf Killer\", murdered at least nine people; executed in 1943.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kangaeru.s59.xrea.com/senzen.htm |first=Eruo |last=Kanga |script-title=ja:\u6226\u524d\u306e\u5c11\u5e74\u72af\u7f6a |website=Juvenile crime database |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-22}}</ref>\n*[[Akira Nishiguchi]]: killed five people and engaged in fraud; executed on 11 December 1970.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alpha-net.ne.jp/users2/knight9/nisiguti.htm |script-title=ja:\u897f\u53e3\u5f70\u9023\u7d9a\u5f37\u76d7\u6bba\u4eba\u4e8b\u4ef6 |website=\u7121\u9650\u56de\u5eca |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071201122525/http://www.alpha-net.ne.jp/users2/knight9/nisiguti.htm |archivedate=2007-12-01}}</ref>\n*[[Kiyoshi \u014ckubo]]: also known as \"Tanigawa Ivan\"; raped and murdered eight young women over a period of 41 days in 1971.\n*[[Miyuki Ueta]]: former snack hostess who murdered between two and six men she dated in [[Tottori (city)|Tottori]], from 2004 to 2009; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/170826/afr1708260002-n1.html|title=Tottori Consecutive Suspicious Deaths Case: former snack hostess, defandant Ueta on death row|last=|first=|date=August 26, 2017|work=Sankei Shimbun|access-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926113636/http://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/170826/afr1708260002-n1.html|archive-date=September 26, 2017|publisher=Sankei Shimbun}}</ref>\n*[[Yukio Yamaji]]: murdered his own mother in 2000, and then murdered a 27-year-old woman and her 19-year-old sister in 2005.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2006/12/14/national/man-to-hang-for-sisters-murders/ |title=Man to hang for sisters' murders |date=14 December 2006 |newspaper=The Japan Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Kazakhstan===\n*[[Nikolai Dzhumagaliev]]: also known as \"Metal Fang\"; raped and hacked seven women to death with an axe in [[Almaty]] in 1980, then cannibalised them using his unusual false teeth.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/blog/2012/05/17/modern-cannibalism-six-killers-with-a-taste-for-human-flesh/index.html |title=Modern cannibalism: Six killers with a taste for human flesh |first=Michael |last=Washburn |date=2012-05-17 |website=TruTV.com |accessdate=2014-01-18 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626165904/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/blog/2012/05/17/modern-cannibalism-six-killers-with-a-taste-for-human-flesh/index.html |archive-date=26 June 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Yuri Ivanov (serial killer)|Yuri Ivanov]]: also known as the \"Ust-Kamenogorsk Maniac\"; raped and killed sixteen girls and young women who spoke badly of men in [[Ust-Kamenogorsk]] from 1974 to 1987; executed 1987.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://meta.kz/novosti/kazakhstan/814276-gromkie-prestupleniya-sovetskogo-vremeni-ust-kamenogorskiy-manyak.html |title=\u0413\u0440\u043e\u043c\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438: \u0423\u0441\u0442\u044c-\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a |trans-title=High-profile crimes of the Soviet era: Ust-Kamenogorsk maniac |date=29 July 2013 |website=Novosti Kazakhstana |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Latvia===\n*[[Ansis Kaup\u0113ns]]: army deserter who committed 30 robberies and 19 murders from 1920 to 1926; executed 1927 in [[Vircava Parish]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vietas.lv/index.php?p=10&id=481 |title=Ansis Kaup\u0113ns (1895-1927) |first=Zemgales |last=Zi\u0146as |date=11 November 2005 |website=Vietas.lv |language=lv |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180823042154/http://www.vietas.lv/index.php?p=10&id=481 |archive-date=2018-08-23}}</ref> \n*[[Kaspars Petrovs]]: convicted of murdering thirteen elderly [[Riga]] women in 2005; confessed to killing 38.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://newsfromrussia.com/hotspots/2005/05/12/59725.html |title=Latvian serial killer sentenced to life in prison for 13 murders |date=2005-05-12 |website=[[Pravda.ru]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060327205411/http://newsfromrussia.com/hotspots/2005/05/12/59725.html |archivedate=March 27, 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Stanislav Rogolev]]: also known as \"Agent 000\"; robbed, raped and killed ten women from 1980 to 1982; suspected of having inside information for the investigation on him; executed 1984.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kriminal.lv/news/retrodetektiv-delo-rogaleva-manyyak-byl-lichnym-agentom-generala-kavalierisa |title=\u0420\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432. \u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0420\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430: \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a \u0431\u044b\u043b \u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043c \u0433\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u041a\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0430 |trans-title=Retrodetective. The case of Rogalev: the maniac was a personal agent of General Cavalieris |first=\u0418\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c |last=\u0418\u0449\u0443\u043a |date=13 May 2010 |website=Kriminal.lv |language=lv |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Lebanon===\n*[[George and Michel Tanielian]]: also known as the \"Taxi Driver Killers\"; [[Syria]]n brothers who killed and robbed mostly taxi drivers in the [[Matn District]] from July to November 2011; both sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lbcgroup.tv/news/d/lebanon-news/10173/beirut-serial-killer-mystery-solved/en |title=Beirut serial killer mystery solved |date=November 15, 2011 |website=Lebanon News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Lithuania===\n*[[Antanas Varnelis]]: murdered and robbed six pensioners between July and December 1992 around several municipalities; first known serial killer in Lithuania; executed 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/lithuania/ivykiai-sukrete-lietuva-a-varnelio-istorija-danu-tv-pranese-lietuvoje-psichopatai-saudomi-teismo-nuosprendziu.d?id=34684635|title=\"Events that shocked Lithuania\" The Story of A. Varnelis. Danish TV reported: Lithuanian psychopath executed|last=Knispeliu|first=Egidijumi|date=July 21, 2010|website=DELFI|access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Malta===\n*[[Silvio Mangion]]: only known serial killer in Malta; murdered three elderly pensioners during robberies between 1984 and 1998; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2012-07-04/local-news/Man-On-trial-for-third-murder:-Mangion-made-%E2%80%98serial-killer%E2%80%99-joke-about-his-tattoos-312479|title=Man On trial for third murder: Mangion made 'serial killer' joke about his tattoos|publisher=[[The Malta Independent]]|date=July 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Mexico===\n*[[Macario Alcala Canchola]]: also known as \"Jack Mexicano\" (\"Mexican Jack\"), was a [[Jack the Ripper]] copycat active in the 1960s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://enciclopediadelosasesinosenserie.blogspot.mx/2010/02/macario-alcala-canchola-jack-el.html |title=Macario Alcala Canchola. \"Jack el Mexicano\" (M\u00e9xico) |trans-title=Macario Alcala Canchola. \"Mexican Jack\" (Mexico) |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=February 10, 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los Asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=April 24, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Sara Aldrete]]: also known as \"La Madrina\"; cult follower of Adolfo Constanzo; convicted in 1994 of murdering several individuals during her association with Constanzo.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DEEDA103AF93BA35756C0A96F948260 |title=Leader in Cult Slayings Ordered Own Death, Two Companions Say |date=May 8, 1989 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |quote=The leader of a drug-smuggling cult that is believed to have killed fifteen people and buried their bodies along the United States-Mexican border ordered his own killing when the police closed in on him, two of his companions said today. |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[David Avenda\u00f1o Ballina]]: also known as \"The Hamburger\"; alleged leader of a sex servant gang who robbed and poisoned their clients from 1997 to 2007; arrested in 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n592543.htm |title=Cay\u00f3 El Hamburguesa, l\u00edder de la banda de \"Las Goteras\" |trans-title=The fall of 'El Hamburguesa', leader of the band of \"Las Goteras\" |first=Manuel |last=Olmos |date=13 February 2008 |website=[[Organizaci\u00f3n Editorial Mexicana]] |language=es |accessdate=18 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305022326/http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n592543.htm |archive-date=5 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Juana Barraza]]: also known as \"Mataviejitas\" (\"Old Lady Killer\"); operated within the metropolitan area of [[Mexico City]] until 25 January 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/7323821.stm |title=Life for Mexico's Old Lady Killer |date=2008-04-01 |website=BBC News |accessdate=2009-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/latestCrisis/idUKN3122188820080401 |title=Mexico's \"Little Old Lady Killer\" gets life term |date=2008-04-01 |website=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=2009-03-31}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Luis Calva]]: cannibal; police found the remains of multiple female victims in his house; committed suicide on 11 December 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/americas/12/11/mexico.suicide.ap/ |title='Cannibal' killer commits suicide |date=11 December 2007 |website=[[CNN]] |accessdate=2007-12-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215011523/http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/americas/12/11/mexico.suicide.ap/ |archivedate=2007-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Gregorio C\u00e1rdenas Hern\u00e1ndez]]: known as \"the Strangler of Tacuba\"; strangled four women in the [[Tacuba (Mexico)|Tacuba]] neighbourhood in 1942; died in 1999 of natural causes.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/english/2016/11/16/el-goyo-cardenas-one-mexicos-most-infamous-serial-killers |title=El Goyo C\u00e1rdenas, one of Mexico's most infamous serial killers |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=16 November 2016 |newspaper=[[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Andr\u00e9s Ulises Castillo Villarreal]]: known as the \"Chihuahua Ripper\"; drugged, raped, killed and mutilated three men in [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] in 2015; confessed to twelve more murders, but suspected of twenty overall; sentenced to 120 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.milenio.com/opinion/jose-luis-duran-king/vidas-ejemplares/el-descuartizador-de-chihuahua |title=El Descuartizador de Chihuahua |trans-title=The Chihuahua Ripper |last=Dur\u00e1n King |first=Jos\u00e9 Luis |date=9 January 2016 |newspaper=[[Milenio]] |language=es |access-date=1 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[The Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez Rebels]]: gang of serial killers who killed women in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez from 1995 to 1996; convicted of eight murders, suspected of killing from ten to 14; claimed to have worked for Abdul Latif Sharif.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2009/09/el-depredador-de-ciudad-juarez-mexico.html |title=El Depredador De Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez |trans-title=The Predator of Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez |last=Rivera |first=Horacio B. |date=29 September 2009 |website=Encyclopedia of serial killers |accessdate=4 January 2013 |quote=... the detainees were: Sergio Armendariz Diaz \"El Diablo\", Jose Luis Rosales, Fernando Germes Aguirre, Juan Jose Contreras Jurado, Gerardo Fernandez Molina, Carlos Hernandez Molina Mariscal, Carlos Barrientos Vidales, Hector Raymundo Olivares, Romel Omar Ceniceros Garcia and Ericka Fierro, the majority were released due to lack of incriminating evidence ...}}</ref>\n*[[Adolfo Constanzo]]: also known as \"The Godfather of Matamoros\"; serial killer and cult leader in Mexico; committed suicide in 1989.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE0D71F3FF930A25757C0A96F948260 |title=Drugs, Death and the Occult Meet In Grisly Inquiry at Mexico Border |first=Peter |last=Applebome |date=April 13, 1989 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=2008-07-28}}</ref>\n*[[Feminicides of the cotton field|Edgar \u00c1lvarez Cruz and Francisco Granados]]: responsible for the so-called \"Feminicides of the cotton field\"; Cruz, with the help of the drugged Granados, kidnapped, raped, tortured and killed at least 8-10 young women in satanic rituals between 1993 and 2003; suspected of committing a total of fourteen murders.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n911023.htm |title=Vinculan feminicidios con actos sat\u00e1nicos |trans-title=They link feminicides with satanic acts |first=Adri\u00e1n |last=S\u00e1nchez |website=Organizaci\u00f3n Editorial Mexicana |language=es |accessdate=23 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216214811/http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n911023.htm |archive-date=December 16, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro Padilla Flores]]: also known as \"El Asesino de Rio Bravo\"; killed three women in 1986; escaped to the US but was deported back to Mexico; suspect in the Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez murders.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2011/02/pedro-padilla-flores-el-asesino-del-rio.html |title=Pedro Padilla Flores \"El Asesino del R\u00edo Bravo\" (M\u00e9xico) |first=Horacio B. |last=Rivera |date=3 February 2011 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |access-date=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Gabriel Garza Hoth]]: also known as \"The Black Widower\"; killed three women in Mexico City between 1991 and 1998, his victims were wives and lovers.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt |url-access=registration |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt/page/346 346] |quote=gabriel garza hoth. |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |date=February 2006 |location=New York |publisher=Facts On File, Inc. |isbn=0-8160-6195-5 |accessdate=November 2, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Delfina and Mar\u00eda de Jes\u00fas Gonz\u00e1lez]]: also known as \"Las Poquianchis\"; killed a total of 91 in [[Guanajuato]]; arrested and sentenced to 40 years in prison in 1964.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/most-prolific-murder-partnership |title=Most prolific murder partnership |website=[[Guinness World Records]] |accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco Guerrero P\u00e9rez]]: also known as \"El Chalequero\" (\"The man of the vests\"); the first documented serial killer in Mexico; committed approximately twenty murders in Mexico City between 1880 and 1888 plus one more in 1908.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Sausage Rebellion: Public Health, Private Enterprise, and Meat in Mexico City, 1890\u20131917 |first=Jeffrey M. |last=Pilcher |chapter=2. The Porfirian Jungle |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GHgF0Xz2fcYC&pg=PA63&dq=francisco+guerrero+chalequero#v=onepage&q=francisco%20guerrero%20chalequero |year=2006 |edition=1st |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |location=Albuquerque, New Mexico |pages=62\u201365 |isbn=978-0-8263-3796-2 |accessdate=2012-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Libro Rojo, Vol. 1 |last=Vi\u00f1as |first=Gerardo Villadel\u00e1ngel |chapter=13. El Chalequero |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hTkS8dDnorQC&pg=PA129&dq=francisco+guerrero+el+chalequero#v=onepage&q=francisco%20guerrero%20el%20chalequero |language=es |edition=1st |year=1888 |publisher=Fondo de Cultura Econ\u00f3mica |location=Mexico City, Mexico |pages=128\u2013145 |isbn=9681686152 |accessdate=2012-07-20}}</ref>\n*[[Fernando Hern\u00e1ndez Leyva]]: convicted of 33 murders in 1986, suspected of 137 killings.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/L/LEYVA_fernando_hernandez.php |title=Fernando Hern\u00e1ndez Leyva |last=Wetsch |first=Elisabeth |website=Serial Killer Crime Index |accessdate=24 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923211212/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/L/LEYVA_fernando_hernandez.php |archive-date=23 September 2015 }}</ref>\n*[[Monsters of Ecatepec|Juan Carlos Hern\u00e1ndez and Patricia Mart\u00ednez]]: pair from [[Ecatepec]], [[State of Mexico]], known as \"The Monsters of Ecatepec\", who raped, murdered and cannibalized between ten and twenty women. Active between 2012 and 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/killers-confess-to-eating-remains/ |title=Serial killers of Ecatepec confess to eating the remains of their victims |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 October 2018 |website=Mexico News Daily |access-date=19 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Luis Oscar Jim\u00e9nez Herrera]]: also known as \"The Tinaco Killer\"; murdered sixteen women in Nuevo Le\u00f3n between 2013 and 2016, but also suspected of a 2010 murder in San Luis Potos\u00ed; sentenced to 123 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://elmanana.com.mx/noticia/162970/Dan-123-aos-por-homicidios-y-secuestros.html |title=Dan 123 a\u00f1os por homicidios y secuestros |trans-title=Given 123 years for homicides and kidnappings |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=March 10, 2018 |newspaper=[[El Ma\u00f1ana (Nuevo Laredo)|El Ma\u00f1ana]] |location=[[Nuevo Laredo]] |language=es |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[C\u00e9sar Armando Librado Legorreta]]: also known as \"El Coqueto\"; raped and killed six women in the [[Greater Mexico City]] between 2011 and 2012; sentenced to 240 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portal2.edomex.gob.mx/pgjem/seguridad_delicuencia/buscados/prioridad1/groups/public/documents/edomex_archivo/pgjem_pdf_media_librado_l.pdf |title=C\u00e9sar Armando Librado Legorreta alias \"El Coqueto\" |date=2012 |website=Procuradur\u00eda General de Justicia del Estado de M\u00e9xico |language=es |access-date=3 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022001612/http://portal2.edomex.gob.mx/pgjem/seguridad_delicuencia/buscados/prioridad1/groups/public/documents/edomex_archivo/pgjem_pdf_media_librado_l.pdf |archive-date=22 October 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Los Huipas]]: gang of four indigenous homosexual men, led by Eusebio Yocupicio Soto, who murdered seven men who made fun of them between 1949 and 1950; initially sentenced to death, later commuted to 30 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elgrafico.mx/especiales/asesinos-seriales/11-03-2016/huipas-desollaron-siete-por-burlas-homofobicas|title=Huipas: seven were skinned for homophobic ridicule|last=|first=|date=|website=www.elgrafico.mx|language=es|access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Rudolfo Infante and Anna Villeda]]: couple from [[Matamoros, Tamaulipas|Matamoros]] responsible for the murders of eight women. Apprehended in 1991.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt |url-access=registration |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt/page/447 447] |quote=the encyclopedia of serial killers villeda. |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |date=February 2006 |location=New York, USA |publisher=Facts On File, Inc. |isbn=0-8160-6195-5 |accessdate=2013-11-24}}</ref>\n*[[Abdul Latif Sharif]]: also known as \"The Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez Predator\"; Egyptian man responsible for murdering an unknown number of women in [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/ciudad_juarez/4.html |title=Ciudad Juarez:The Serial Killer's Playground |first=Michael |last=Newton |website=TruTV.com |page=4 |accessdate=2012-07-22 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505045358/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/ciudad_juarez/4.html |archive-date=2012-05-05}}</ref> possibly as many as fifteen but convicted of only one; died in prison.\n*[[Daniel Audiel L\u00f3pez Mart\u00ednez]]: killed five women in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez between 2007 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/node/700670 |title=Detienen a asesino serial de mujeres de Ciudad Juarez |trans-title=Serial killer of women captured in Ciudad Juarez |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=January 3, 2011 |website=Excelsior |language=es |accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Ra\u00fal Osiel Marroqu\u00edn]]: also known as \"El Gato Imperial\"; killed four gay men in Mexico City.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pgr.gob.mx/cmsocial/coms06/260106.htm |title=Conferencia de Prensa que ofreci\u00f3 Genaro Garc\u00eda Luna, titular de la Agencia Federal de Investigaci\u00f3n para anunciar la detenci\u00f3n del presunto asesino serial y secuestrador Ra\u00fal Marroqu\u00edn Reyes |trans-title=Press conference held by Genaro Garc\u00eda Luna, head of the Federal Investigation Agency, to announce the capture of the serial killer Ra\u00fal Marroqu\u00edn Reyes |date=January 26, 2006 |website=Procuradur\u00eda General de Justicia |language=es |accessdate=18 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226070959/http://www.pgr.gob.mx/cmsocial/coms06/260106.htm |archivedate=26 February 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Filiberto Hern\u00e1ndez Mart\u00ednez]]: killed six people between 2010 and 2013 in [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.omahasuntimes.com/2014/07/filiberto-hernandez-child-serial-killer-suspect-confesses-to-5-murders-cops/ |title=Filiberto Hernandez, Child Serial Killer Suspect, Confesses To 5 Murders: Cops |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=5 July 2014 |newspaper=Omaha Sun Times |location=[[Omaha, Nebraska]] |accessdate=17 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402191055/http://www.omahasuntimes.com/2014/07/filiberto-hernandez-child-serial-killer-suspect-confesses-to-5-murders-cops/ |archive-date=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Jorge Humberto Mart\u00ednez C\u00f3rtez]]: also known as \"El Matanovias\"; killed between two and three of his romantic partners from 2011 to 2014; currently awaiting sentencing.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.proceso.com.mx/508643/interpol-captura-en-guatemala-al-matanovias-la-pgj-cdmx-solicitara-traslado |title=Interpol captura en Guatemala al \"Matanovias\"; la PGJ-CDMX solicitar\u00e1 su traslado |trans-title=Interpol captures the \"Matanovias\" in Guatemala; the PGJ-CDMX requests his transfer |date=24 October 2017 |magazine=[[Proceso (magazine)|Proceso]] |language=es |publisher=Comunicaci\u00f3n e Informaci\u00f3n S.A. de C.V |accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/entregan-el-matanovias-pgr-en-guatemala |title=Entregan a \"El Matanovias\" a PGR en Guatemala |trans-title=They deliver \"El Matanovias\" to PGR in Guatemala |first=Jos\u00e9 |last=Mel\u00e9ndez |date=15 October 2017 |newspaper=El Universal |language=es |accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Alejandro M\u00e1ynez]]: may have killed over 50 women with accomplices.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pr5HAAAAYAAJ&q=alejandro+maynez&dq=alejandro+maynez |title=Cosechja de mujeres: safar\u00ed en el desierto mexicano |first=Diana |last=Washington V\u00e1ldez |publisher=University of Texas |year=2005 |isbn=9706519882 |pages=168\u2013170}}</ref>\n*[[House of Laments|Tadeo Fulgenc\u00edo Mej\u00eda]]: responsible for several murders during the 1890s and 1900s, motivated by delirious idea of contacting his deceased wife. Now the house in [[Guanajuato]], where he committed the crimes, is known as \"The House of Laments\" (''Casa de los lamentos''), and according to legend is haunted.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aztecaamerica.com/notas/extranormal/59060/tragedia-en-casa-de-los-lamentos |title=Tragedia en Casa de los Lamentos |last=Enciso |first=Alejandra |date=2011-06-16 |website=[[TV Azteca]] |language=es |accessdate=2013-11-18}}</ref>\n*[[Silvia Meraz]]: [[Sonora]] woman involved in an occult sect, killed three persons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/centralamericaandthecaribbean/mexico/9177633/Children-sacrificed-to-Mexicos-cult-of-Saint-Death.html |title=Children 'sacrificed' to Mexico's cult of Saint Death |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=31 March 2012 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Agust\u00edn Salas del Valle]]: also known as \"Jack the Strangler\"; killed more than twenty women in Mexico City's Central Zone.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2010/01/agustin-salas-del-valle-el.html |title=Agust\u00edn Salas del Valle, \"El Estrangulador de mujeres\" (M\u00e9xico) |first=Horacio B. |last=Rivera |date=19 January 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |access-date=10 July 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Fel\u00edcitas S\u00e1nchez Aguill\u00f3n]]: named \"The Ogress of [[Colonia Roma]]\" was a nurse, midwife and baby farmer responsible for an unknown number of murders during the 1930s, possibly 50 victims, in [[Mexico City]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://enciclopediadelosasesinosenserie.blogspot.mx/2010/12/felicitas-sanchez-aguillon-la.html |title=Fel\u00edcitas S\u00e1nchez Agill\u00f3n. \"La Descuartizadora de la Colonia Roma\". (M\u00e9xico) |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=6 December 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=25 December 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Cristina Soledad S\u00e1nchez Esquivel]]: also known as \"La Matataxistas\"; killed between five and six taxi drivers in [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]] in 2010 with her accomplice Aar\u00f3n Herrera Hern\u00e1ndez; sentenced to 130 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.info7.mx/seccion/la-matataxistas-actuo-por-venganza-contra-los-hombres/477032 |title=La matataxistas actu\u00f3 por venganza contra los hombres |trans-title=La Matataxistas acted for revenge against men |first=Badillo |last=Victor |date=2010-06-17 |website=INFO7 |language=es |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Magdalena Sol\u00eds]]: religious fanatic, proclaimed \"The High Blood's Priestess\", killed eight persons in ritual sacrifices<ref name=\"TrueTv's Crime Library\">{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/vampires/4.html |title=Crime Library: The Vampire Killers |first=Katherine |last=Ramsland |website=TruTv |access-date=July 21, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014144507/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/vampires/4.html |archive-date=2012-10-14}}</ref>\n*[[Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9]]: killed three young girls between 2007 and 2008 in [[M\u00e9rida, Yucat\u00e1n]]; later died in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2010/02/mario-alberto-sulu-canche-el.html |title=Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9. El Matachavitas. (M\u00e9xico) |trans-title=Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9. The Young-Girls-Killer |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=19 February 2010 |website=La enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Moldova===\n*[[Alexander Skrynnik]]: also known as the \"Moldavian Chikatilo\"; killed and then mutilated three women in [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]] and [[Yakutia]] from the mid\u20131970s to 1980; executed 1981.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://brw.md/moldavskii-maniac-aleksander-skrynnikov/ |title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043a \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 2. \u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0421\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043d\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 |trans-title=Handwriting of the criminal 2. The case of Skrynnik |date=October 25, 2017 |website=BRW \u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Morocco===\n*[[Hadj Mohammed Mesfewi]]: also known as the \"[[Marrakesh]] Arch-Killer\"; drugged and killed 36 women; died 1906.\n\n===Netherlands===\n*[[Klaas Annink]]: also known as \"Huttenkloas\"; robber and murderer from [[Twente]] who killed along with his wife Anna and son Jannes; both he and his wife were executed in 1775.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.molenaarshuis.nl/huttenkloas.htm |title=Huttenkloas |website=Molenaarshuis |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060620072915/http://www.molenaarshuis.nl/huttenkloas.htm |archivedate=June 20, 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Hendrikje Doelen]]: 19th century farm-wife who poisoned several people in a [[poorhouse]] from 1845 to 1846, killing three of them; died of natural causes in 1847.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.drenlias.nl/index.html?option=com_familias&task=zoeken&bron=na1811&lname1=DOELEN&fname1=HENDRIKJE&header=advanced&plaats=&van=1848&tot=1848&methode=exact&submit.x=21&submit.y=14&submit=Zoeken |title=Hendrikje Doelen |website=Drenlias.nl |access-date=24 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827044030/http://www.drenlias.nl/index.html?option=com_familias&task=zoeken&bron=na1811&lname1=DOELEN&fname1=HENDRIKJE&header=advanced&plaats=&van=1848&tot=1848&methode=exact&submit.x=21&submit.y=14&submit=Zoeken |archive-date=27 August 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Willem van Eijk]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Harkstede]]\"; convicted of the murders of five women between 1971 and 2001.\n*[[Koos Hertogs]]: convicted of the murders of three women between 1979 and 1980.\n*[[Aalt Mondria]]: escaped mental patient who murdered a family of three in 1978; after release, murdered his girlfriend's son in 1997; died 2011 from untreated [[Hepatitis C]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.destentor.nl/hardenberg/seriemoordenaar-aalt-mondria-overleden~ae72d3fa/ |title=Seriemoordenaar Aalt Mondria overleden |trans-title=Serial killer Aalt Mondria dies |date=28 September 2011 |newspaper=[[De Stentor]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gustav M\u00fcller (serial killer)|Gustav M\u00fcller]]: German watchmaker who murdered his wife and son in [[Rotterdam]] in 1897; surrendered and subsequently confessed to killing his parents and at least fourteen other wives around the world; acquitted by reason of insanity and confined to an asylum.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/2016270503/1897-11-09/ed-1/seq-6/#date1=1897&sort=date&rows=20&words=Gustav+Muller&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=12&state=&date2=1898&proxtext=Gustav+Muller&y=19&x=19&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2 |title=Slew Fourteen Wives |date=November 9, 1897 |newspaper=Waterbury Evening Democrat |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Chronicling America}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Soultana]]: strangled two women in 2010, suspected of three more murders; sentenced to 25 years plus provision in 2014.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2686/Binnenland/article/detail/3600023/2014/02/19/Patrick-S-bekent-betrokkenheid-bij-moord-op-Farida-Zargar.dhtml |title=Patrick S. bekent betrokkenheid bij moord op Farida Zargar |trans-title=Patrick S. confesses involvement in the murder of Farida Zargar |date=24 March 2017 |newspaper=de Volkskrant |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michel Stockx]]: murdered three children around [[Assen]] in 1991; sentenced to 20 years in prison in 1992; died of severe burns from an incident during his work therapy in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.misdaadjournalist.nl/rapportages/michelstockxendedodekinderen.html |title=Michel Stockx en de dode kinderen |trans-title=Michel Stockx and the dead children |first=Hendrik Jan |last=Korterink |website=Misdaad Journalist |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Maria Swanenburg]]: suspected of killing between 27 and 90 people with [[arsenic]] in [[Leiden]] in the 1880s; died in prison in 1915.\n*[[Hans van Zon]]: murdered three people from April to August 1967, including a former lover; suspected of several other murders; died 1998 from [[alcohol poisoning]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/gentleman-killer-hans-van-z-vast-voor-poging-tot-doodslag-buurman~b84f4d0a/ |title='Gentleman-killer' Hans van Z. vast voor poging tot doodslag buurman |trans-title='Gentleman-killer' Hans van Z. charged with attempted homicide of neighbor |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=12 March 1997 |newspaper=[[Trouw]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===New Zealand===\n*[[Robert Butler (criminal)|Robert Butler]]: Irish highwayman who allegedly killed a family of three in [[Dunedin]] in 1880; acquitted, but was later hanged for shooting a man in Australia.<ref>{{DNZB |title=Robert Butler |first=Brian |last=O'Brien |id=2b53 |accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Daniel Cooper (murderer)|Daniel Cooper]]: also known as \"The [[Newlands, New Zealand|Newlands]] Baby Farmer\"; killed two infants and supposedly his first wife; executed 1932.<ref>{{cite book |first=C. A. L. |last=Treadwell |title=Notable New Zealand Trials |location=New Plymouth |publisher=Thomas Avery |date=1936}}</ref>\n*[[Minnie Dean]]: Scottish immigrant [[Baby farming|baby farmer]] who killed at least three children by [[Laudanum]] poisoning and suffocation in the 1890s; executed by hanging in 1895.<ref>{{cite book |first=Graham |last=Hutchins |title=Bad: Crooks, Creeps and Killers in New Zealand |location=Auckland |publisher=Hodder Moa |date=2010 |isbn=978-1-86971-174-0}}</ref>\n\n===North Macedonia===\n*[[Viktor Karamarkov]]: known as \"The Macedonian [[Rodion Raskolnikov|Raskolnikov]]\"; drug addict who murdered four elderly women in [[Skopje]] from March to October 2009; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/109986/ |title=\u0414\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043d \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0430 \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432 |trans-title=Life imprisonment for Viktor Karamarkov |date=June 16, 2010 |website=[[Makfax]] |language=mk |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Vlado Taneski]]: crime reporter arrested in June 2008 for the murder of three elderly women on whose deaths he had written articles; committed suicide in police custody; suspected of killing another woman.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/jun/24/pressandpublishing.internationalcrime |title=The shocking story of the newspaper crime reporter who knew too much |last=Smith |first=Helena |date=2008-06-24 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |location=London, UK |accessdate=2008-06-24}}</ref>\n\n===Norway===\n*[[Arnfinn Nesset]]: manager of a [[geriatric]] nursing home who poisoned twenty-two residents at the [[Orkdal]] Alders-og Sjukeheim institution over a period of years before being convicted in 1983.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=U7QSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=cfkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=2293,1624213&dq=arnfinn-nesset |title=Slayer of 22 sentenced |date=19 March 1983 |newspaper=[[Spokane Chronicle]] |accessdate=12 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Pakistan===\n*[[Javed Iqbal (serial killer)|Javed Iqbal]]: believed to have raped and killed 100 boys, committed suicide while in prison in 1991.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/serial-killer-javed-iqbal-who-sexually-abused-and-killed-2733.html |title=Serial killer Javed Iqbal who sexually abused and killed 100 children in Pakistan |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=25 February 2013 |website=[[India TV]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6PqlVwKyg?url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/serial-killer-javed-iqbal-who-sexually-abused-and-killed-2733.html |archive-date=26 May 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Amir Qayyum]]: also known as the \"Brick Killer\"; murdered fourteen homeless men in [[Lahore]] with rocks or bricks when they were asleep and was sentenced to death in May 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.turkishweekly.net/news/31571/-death-for-lahore-brick-killer.html |title=Death for Lahore 'brick killer' |date=May 11, 2006 |website=Turkish Weekly |accessdate=February 26, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302140823/http://www.turkishweekly.net/news/31571/-death-for-lahore-brick-killer.html |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Panama===\n*[[Silvano Ward Brown]]: known as \"The Panam\u00e1 Strangler\"; first serial killer in Panamanian history; strangled three women from 1959 to 1973 in the [[Panam\u00e1 Province]]; released in 1993 after serving a 20-year sentence.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://impresa.prensa.com/mas_de_la_prensa/muertes-prostitutas_0_966653491.html |title=Las muertes de las prostitutas |trans-title=The deaths of prostitutes |date=July 13, 2003 |newspaper=[[La Prensa (Panama City)|La Prensa]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> \n*[[Gilberto Ventura Ceballos]]: [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] man who murdered five Panamanian youths of Chinese descent in [[La Chorrera, Panama|La Chorrera]] from 2010 to 2011; sentenced to 50 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Condenan-Ventura-Ceballos-asesinato-chorreranos_0_1152485117.html |title=Dictan 50 a\u00f1os de prisi\u00f3n para Ventura Ceballos y M\u00e9ndez por asesinato de 5 j\u00f3venes chorreranos |trans-title=Ventura Ceballos and M\u00e9ndez setenced to 50 years in prison for the murder of 5 young chorreranos |first=Nimay |last=Gonz\u00e1lez |date=9 July 2018 |website=[[Telemetro]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709183020/http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Condenan-Ventura-Ceballos-asesinato-chorreranos_0_1152485117.html |archive-date=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n*[[William Dathan Holbert]]: also known as \"Wild Bill\"; American expatriate who had the bodies of five other Americans buried on his property; he would kill people to get their money and properties; his wife, Laura Michelle Reese, was also arrested.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Desmienten-Wild-Bill-designado-capellan_0_731627270.html |title=Desmienten que \"Wild Bill\" haya sido designado como capell\u00e1n |trans-title=They deny that \"Wild Bill\" has been appointed as chaplain |website=Telemetro |language=es |accessdate=5 September 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908004447/http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Desmienten-Wild-Bill-designado-capellan_0_731627270.html |archive-date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/08/05/william-holbert-panama-mu_n_671658.html |title=William Holbert Panama Murders: More Bodies Found at Hostel of U.S. Man Accused of Serial Killings |first=Nicholas |last=Sabloff |date=August 5, 2010 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=28 March 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===Peru===\n\n*[[Pedro Pablo Nakada Lude\u00f1a]]: also known as \"The Apostle of Death\"; convicted of seventeen murders and claimed 25; sentenced to 35 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/13/pedro-pablo-nakada-el-mayor-asesino-en-serie-del-peru |title=Pedro Pablo Nakada, el mayor asesino en serie del Per\u00fa |trans-title=Pedro Pablo Nakada, the greatest serial killer of Peru |date=1 November 2013 |newspaper=[[El Tel\u00e9grafo (Ecuador)|El Tel\u00e9grafo]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Philippines===\n*[[Edgar Matobato]]: self-confessed hitman and serial killer who claims to have killed hundreds of people as part of the [[Davao Death Squad]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/in-depth/147414-edgar-matobato-liar-truth-teller |title=Edgar Matobato: Liar or truth-teller? |first=Chay F. |last=Hofile\u00f1a |date=27 September 2016 |website=[[Rappler]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Poland===\n*[[Bogdan Arnold]]: murdered four women in [[Katowice]] from 1966 to 1967; also attempted to poison his third wife; executed 1968.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://wiadomosci.onet.pl/na-tropie/bestia-z-katowic-horror-na-poddaszu/xr1mw |title=Bestia z Katowic. Horror na poddaszu |trans-title=The beast from Katowice. Horror in the attic |first=Joanna |last=Zaj\u0105czkowska |date=30 December 2011 |website=[[Wiadomo\u015bci]] |language=pl |accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Baczy\u0144ski]]: killed a woman and three men in Wroc\u0142aw and Bytom from 1946 to 1957; executed 1960.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://wroclaw.wyborcza.pl/wroclaw/7,142076,22437163,morderca-strzela-w-ciemnosciach-o-seryjnym-zabojcy-we-wroclawiu.html |title=Seryjny zab\u00f3jca strzela\u0142 do ludzi we Wroc\u0142awiu lat 50. Milicja Obywatelska by\u0142a bezradna |trans-title=The serial killer shot people in Wroc\u0142aw in the 1950s. Citizens' Militia was helpless |first=Karolina |last=Kijek |date=1 October 2017 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Wyborcza]] |language=pl |accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[J\u00f3zef Cyppek]]: also known as \"The Butcher of [[Niebuszewo]]\"; dismembered his neighbour in 1952; was sentenced to death and executed that same year; suspected of other murders.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://poczciarz.home.pl//wydarzenia/index.php?artikle=245 |title=Rze\u013dnik z Niebuszewa- J\u00f3zef Cyppek |trans-title=The butcher of Niebuszewo \u2013 J\u00f3zef Cyppek |first=Moniki |last=Adamowskiej |website=Poczciarz |language=pl |accessdate=28 April 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Ensztajn]]: also known as \"Vampire of \u0141owicz\"; raped and killed seven women in [[\u0141owicz]] and the surrounding areas in 1933; sentenced to 15 years in prison in 1934.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-wCXJ7aVNtcY/UEiwHUUF7VI/AAAAAAAABUQ/RNF0zgSYBDs/s1600/G%C5%82os+Poranny+22.+VII+1934.jpg |title=The story of a descendant of a rapist |website=Voice of the Morning |language=pl |access-date=19 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Krzysztof Gawlik]]: also known as \"Scorpio\"; murdered five people with a silenced machine gun in 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/pozwroc2001.htm |title=Morderstwa pi\u0119ciu os\u00f3b z Poznania i Wroc\u0142awia |trans-title=Murders of five people from Pozna\u0144 and Wroc\u0142aw |date=1 March 2003 |website=Karasmierci |language=pl |access-date=28 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080105102625/http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/pozwroc2001.htm |archive-date=5 January 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Grzesik]]: leader of the so-called \"Bureaucrats Gang\"; killed between eight and twenty people in several Polish voivodeships with his gang, mainly owners of exchange offices; suspected of more murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/krakow/krakow-kolejne-zarzuty-dla-gangu-kantorowcow/1dtbz3h |title=Hodowca truskawek ze swoim gangiem mordowa\u0142 w\u0142a\u015bcicieli kantor\u00f3w. Kolejne zarzuty |trans-title=Strawberry grower and his gang murdered the owners of money exchange offices. Further allegations |date=8 April 2017 |newspaper=[[Fakt]] |language=pl |accessdate=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Joachim Knycha\u0142a]]: also known as \"The Vampire of [[Bytom]]\" or \"Frankenstein\", who murdered five women between 1975 and 1982.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.zyciebytomskie.pl/artykul.php?id=1886&glowny=0 |title=Wampir z Bytomia |date=7 February 2011 |newspaper=\u017bycie Bytomskie |language=pl |accessdate=24 May 2012}}{{Dead link |date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wiadomosci.onet.pl/wiadomosci/slaski-frankenstein,1,3488062,wiadomosc.html |title=\u015al\u0105ski Frankenstein |trans-title=Silesian Frankenstein |first=Erika |last=Sjoblom |date=12 November 2008 |website=[[Onet.pl]] |language=pl |accessdate=24 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120716065047/http://wiadomosci.onet.pl/wiadomosci/slaski-frankenstein,1,3488062,wiadomosc.html |archive-date=16 July 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Edmund Kolanowski]]: necrophile who murdered three women from 1970 to 1982; also mutilated and desecrated corpses he excavated from chapels; executed 1986.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://poznan.wyborcza.pl/poznan/1,109268,11163581,Zanim_znow_zaatakuje____Historia_nekrofila.html |title=Zanim zn\u00f3w zaatakuje... Historia nekrofila |trans-title=Before he attacks again ... History of the necrophile |first=Piotr |last=\u017bytnicki |date=18 February 2012 |newspaper=Gazeta Wyborcza |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Karol Kot]]: killed two people from 1964 to 1966 in his native [[Krak\u00f3w]], attempted to murder many more; executed 1968.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://killer.radom.net/~sermord/zbrodnia.php?dzial=mordercy&dane=KotKarol |title=Mordercy: Kot Karol |trans-title=Killers: Kot Karol |year=1999 |website=Killer.radom.net |language=pl |accessdate=4 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040110182847/http://killer.radom.net/~sermord/zbrodnia.php?dzial=mordercy&dane=KotKarol |archive-date=January 10, 2004}}</ref>\n*[[Henryk Kuku\u0142a]]: also known as \"The Monster from [[Chorz\u00f3w]]\"; pedophile who murdered four children from 1980 to 1990; sentenced to 28 years in prison, expected to be released in 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/slask/henryk-kukula-monstrum-z-chorzowa-pedofil-ktory-mordowal-dzieci/ty7qzxe |title=Fakt24 ujawnia histori\u0119 monstrum z Chorzowa |trans-title=Fakt24 reveals the history of the monster from Chorz\u00f3w |first=Maciej |last=Molenda |date=2017-06-10 |newspaper=Fakt |language=pl |accessdate=2017-06-20}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Kwa\u015bniak]]: also known as the \"Towel Strangler\"; violent pedophile who raped and murdered five boys from 1990 and 1991; also responsible for numerous robberies; hanged himself in his prison cell before he could be sentenced.\n*[[Zdzis\u0142aw Marchwicki]]: also known as the \"[[Zag\u0142\u0119bie D\u0105browskie|Zag\u0142\u0119bie]] Vampire\"; convicted of murdering fourteen women; executed in 1976.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.murderpedia.org/male.M/m/marchwicki-zdzislaw.htm |title=Zdislaw Marchwicki |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nikifor Maruszeczko]]: criminal who killed four men for the purpose of robbery; executed 1938.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.focus.pl/artykul/kilka-smiertelnych-miesiecy |title=Kilka \u015bmiertelnych miesi\u0119cy |trans-title=A few deadly months |first=Damian |last=Szymczak |date=27 June 2013 |magazine=[[Focus (Polish magazine)|Focus]] |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz (serial killer)|W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz]]: also known as \"The Gentleman Killer\"; killed up to 30 women; executed by hanging in 1957.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://gazetakrakowska.pl/skazani-na-smierc-wladyslaw-mazurkiewicz-elegancki-morderca/ar/1049152?_d=byfUiRFGfv8ZmwkkNJ0vtk7Il0S9kEOuJ9qVGrpQfRVtAPMbhiUElfZQFTpx50jZOplusplusUioHcPEGnxKi77pUJIA |title=Skazani na \u015bmier\u0107: W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz. Elegancki morderca |trans-title=Condemned to death: W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz. An elegant killer |first=Artur |last=Dro\u017cd\u017cak |date=23 November 2013 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Krakowska]] |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160430132526/http://www.gazetakrakowska.pl/artykul/1049152,skazani-na-smierc-wladyslaw-mazurkiewicz-elegancki-morderca,id,t.html?_d=byfUiRFGfv8ZmwkkNJ0vtk7Il0S9kEOuJ9qVGrpQfRVtAPMbhiUElfZQFTpx50jZOplusplusUioHcPEGnxKi77pUJIA |archive-date=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Stanis\u0142aw Modzelewski]]: murdered seven women in [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] during the 1960s; executed in 1970.\n*[[Henryk Moru\u015b]]: killed seven people in the [[Piotrk\u00f3w Voivodeship]] from 1986 to 1992; sentenced to 25 years imprisonment; died of probable heart failure in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dzienniklodzki.pl/artykul/986609,bezwgledny-morderca-z-sulejowa-nie-zyje-henryk-morus-zmarl-w-wiezieniu,id,t.html |title=Bezwgl\u0119dny morderca z Sulejowa nie \u017cyje. Henryk Moru\u015b zmar\u0142 w wi\u0119zieniu |trans-title=The ruthless murderer from Sulej\u00f3w is dead. Henryk Moru\u015b died in prison |first=Marek |last=Okolny |date=6 September 2013 |newspaper=Dziennik Lodzki |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://piotrkowtrybunalski.naszemiasto.pl/wydarzenia/865547.html |title=Morderca z Sulejowa bez \u0142aski |trans-title=A murderer from Sulej\u00f3w without grace |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=19 June 2008 |website=Piotrk\u00f3w Trybunalski |language=pl |access-date=19 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091030054216/http://piotrkowtrybunalski.naszemiasto.pl/wydarzenia/865547.html |archive-date=30 October 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Grzegorz Musiatowicz]]: violent criminal who killed three men between 2002 and 2014; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://wyborcza.pl/7,90535,24746795,dozywotniacy-kim-sa-wiezniowie-skazani-na-najwyzszy-wymiar.html |title=Do\u017cywotniacy: \"Kim s\u0105 wi\u0119\u017aniowie skazani na najwy\u017cszy wymiar kary?\" Lizut: \"W ka\u017cdym z nich jest inna historia\" |trans-title=Do\u017cywotniacy: \"Who are the prisoners sentenced to the highest sentence?\" Lizut: \"Each of them has a different story\" |first=Marta |last=Bratkowska |date=8 May 2019 |newspaper=Gazeta Wyborcza |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Leszek P\u0119kalski]]: also known as the \"Vampire of [[Byt\u00f3w]]\"; killed up to seventeen women.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA321&dq=Leszek+Pekalski&cd=7#v=onepage&q=Leszek%20Pekalski |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |first=Eric W. |last=Hickey |date=2009-06-23 |publisher=Cengage Learning |edition=5th |page=321 |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7}}</ref>\n*[[Kazimierz Polus]]: pedophile who killed two boys and one man from 1971 to 1982; executed 1985.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.poznan.pl/mim/necropolis/plan.html?urlAnchor=OpenMap&mtype=cemeteries&cm_id=1&surname=Polus&name=Kazimierz&id=22986 |title=Kazimierz Polus - burial place in Mi\u0142ost\u00f3w in Pozna\u0144 |access-date=7 July 2017 |language=pl}}</ref>\n*[[Skin Hunters]]: Karol Bana\u015b, Andrzej Nowocie\u0144, Dr. Janusz Kuli\u0144ski and Dr. Pawe\u0142 Wasilewski; paramedics and doctors in [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] who killed patients for profit; all four were convicted and officials are investigating possible accomplices.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/3323663.stm |title=Paramedic held in funeral scam |first=Adam |last=Easton |date=2003-12-16 |website=[[BBC News Online|BBC News]] |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref>\n*[[Mariusz Sowi\u0144ski]]: also known as \"The [[Stefankowice]] Vampire\"; raped and killed four women from 1994 to 1997; sentenced to 50 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/hrub1997.html |title=Wampir ze Stefankowic (Hrubieszowskie) - 4 morderstwa i gwa\u0142ty |trans-title=Vampire from Stefankowice (Hrubieszowskie) - 4 murders and rapes |website=Krasmierci |language=pl |date=26 June 2000 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070630083700/http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/hrub1997.html |archive-date=June 30, 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Pawe\u0142 Tuchlin]]: also known as \"Scorpion\"; killed nine women and attempted to kill eleven more to feel better; executed 1987.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.wprost.pl/tygodnik/2429/lowcy.html |title=\u0141owcy |trans-title=Hunters |first=Ewa |last=Ornacka |date=3 January 1999 |magazine=[[Wprost]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mieczys\u0142aw Zub]]: also known as \"Fantomas\"; killed four women the area of [[Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]]; committed suicide in 1985.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/slask/mieczyslaw-zub-fantomas-nieuchwytny-psychopata-ktory-terroryzowal-slask/986ydes |title=Nieuchwytny psychopata terroryzowa\u0142 \u015al\u0105sk |trans-title=An elusive psychopath terrorized Silesia |first=Maciej |last=Molenda |date=2017-04-06 |newspaper=Fakt |access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref>\n\n===Portugal===\n*[[Diogo Alves]]: also known as the \"Aqueduct Murderer\"; Spanish man who robbed and threw poor people off [[Lisbon]]'s [[\u00c1guas Livres Aqueduct]] between 1836 and 1840; executed 1841.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pereulki.com/2015/06/ubijtsa-s-akveduka-istoriya-diogo-alvesha-samogo-izvestnogo-prestupnika-portugalii/ |title=\u0423\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0430 \u0441 \u0410\u043a\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0430: \u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0414\u0438\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0410\u043b\u0432\u0435\u0448\u0430, \u0421\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0418\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0443\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=Aqueduct Killer: The Story of Diogo Alves, Portugal's Most Famous Criminal |date=June 22, 2015 |website=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0443\u043b\u043a\u0438 \u041b\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043d\u0430 |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ant\u00f3nio Lu\u00eds Costa]]: ex-[[Portuguese National Republican Guard|GNR]] officer from [[Santa Comba D\u00e3o]] who murdered three women between 2005 and 2006; sentenced to 25 years in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://expresso.sapo.pt/dossies/diario/os-vizinhos-de-socrates-na-prisao=f899794 |title=Os vizinhos de S\u00f3crates na pris\u00e3o |trans-title=S\u00f3crates's prison neighbours |last1=Franco |first1=Hugo |last2=Moleiro |first2=Raquel |last3=Gustavo |first3=Rui |lastauthoramp=yes |date=25 November 2014 |newspaper=[[Expresso (newspaper)|Expresso]] |language=pt |access-date=13 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Romania===\n\n*[[Vera Renczi]]: poisoned two husbands, one son and 32 of her suitors in the 1920s and 1930s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://adevarul.ro/locale/calarasi/sfarsitul-cumplit-celei-mai-sadice-criminale-vaduva-neagra-femeia-misterioasa-ucis-35-barbati-1_57372ef05ab6550cb8eef23c/index.html |title=Sf\u00e2r\u015fitul cumplit al celei mai sadice criminale. V\u0103duva Neagr\u0103, femeia misterioas\u0103 care a ucis 35 de b\u0103rba\u0163i |trans-title=The terrible end of the most sadistic criminal. The Black Widow, the mysterious woman who killed 35 men |first=Ionela |last=St\u0103nil\u0103 |date=1 June 2016 |newspaper=[[Adev\u0103rul]] |language=ro |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.descopera.ro/cultura/3470508-vaduva-neagra-sau-castelana-din-berkerekul |title=Vaduva Neagra sau Castelana din Berkerekul |trans-title=Black Widow or Chatelaine of Berkerekul |first=Adrian |last=Nicolae |date=11 October 2008 |website=Descoper\u0103 |language=ro |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ion R\u00eemaru]]: murdered and raped young women in [[Bucharest]] from 1970 to 1971; executed in 1971.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://adevarul.ro/locale/alexandria/secretele-faimosului-criminal-ramaru-vampirul-bucuresti-sugea-sangele-victimelor-sfasia-organele-genitale-dintii-1_56602b4f7d919ed50ed9e3a3/index.html |title=Secretele faimosului criminal R\u00e2maru, \"vampirul din Bucure\u015fti\": sugea s\u00e2ngele victimelor \u015fi le sf\u00e2\u015fia organele genitale cu din\u0163ii |trans-title=Secrets of the famous criminal R\u00e2maru, \"the vampire from Bucharest\": sucked the blood of his victims and ripped their genitals with his teeth |first=Elisabeth |last=Bouleanu |date=4 December 2015 |newspaper=Adev\u0103rul |language=ro |access-date=4 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Vasile Tcaciuc]]: also known as \"The Butcher of [[Ia\u0219i]]\": murdered victims with an axe and confessed to have committed at least 26 murders; shot dead by a policeman while trying to escape from prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.procuror.ro/article/8791/Vasile-Tcaciuc-ndash-Macelarul-din-Iasi |title=Vasile Tcaciuc \u2013 Macelarul din Iasi |trans-title=Vasile Tcaciuc - Butcher from Iasi |date=2009 |website=Procuror |language=ro |accessdate=February 20, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225183013/http://www.procuror.ro/article/8791/Vasile-Tcaciuc-ndash-Macelarul-din-Iasi |archive-date=2014-02-25}}</ref>\n*[[Romulus Vere\u0219]]: convicted of five murders in the 1970s; sent to a mental institution; died in 1993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clujeanul.ro/cluj/citeste-povestea-celui-mai-temut-criminal-al-clujului-omul-cu-ciocanul-2394295 |title=Cite\u015fte povestea celui mai temut criminal al Clujului: \"Omul cu ciocanul\" |trans-title=Read the story of the most feared criminal in Cluj: \"The man with the hammer\" |date=2008-02-17 |website=Clujeanul |language=ro |accessdate=2008-03-12 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080301111548/http://www.clujeanul.ro/cluj/citeste-povestea-celui-mai-temut-criminal-al-clujului-omul-cu-ciocanul-2394295 |archive-date=2008-03-01}}</ref>\n\n===Russia===\n{{Main|List of Russian serial killers}}\n\n===Serbia===\n*[[Baba Anujka]] (also known as Anna Pistova, Ana di Pi\u0161tonja, Anuyka Dee, \"The Banat Witch\" and \"The Witch of [[Vladimirovac]]\"); professional poisoner who poisoned between 50 and 150 people until apprehended in 1928.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/reportaze/aktuelno.293.html:792782-BANATSKA-VESTICA-ZAVILA-VLADIMIROVAC-U-CRNO-Baba-Anujka-je-bila-prvi-serijski-ubica-u-Srbiji-ubila-150-ljudi |title=Baba Anujka je bila prvi serijski ubica u Srbiji, ubila 150 ljudi |trans-title=Baba Anujka was the first serial killer in Serbia, killing 150 people |date=5 May 2019 |newspaper=[[Ve\u010dernje novosti]] |language=sr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Slovakia===\n*[[Matej \u010curko]]: also known as the \"Slovak Cannibal\"; killed and cannibalized two willing victims in 2010 in [[Kysak]], suspected of another 28 such cases from 2009 to 2011; killed by police in 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.corriere.it/english/11_agosto_02/cannibal-victims_fa52f944-bcf3-11e0-b530-d2ad6f731cf9.shtml |title=Slovak Cannibal's Possible Italian Victims \u2013 Thirty Missing Women Profiled |first=Massimo |last=Sideri |translator-first=Giles |translator-last=Watson |date=August 2, 2011 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |edition=English |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Juraj Lupt\u00e1k]]: also known as the \"Strangler from [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica]]\"; shepherd who raped and strangled three women from 1978 to 1982; executed 1987 in Bratislava.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://korzar.sme.sk/c/5770728/dievca-vymodelovalo-tvar-svojho-vraha-bol-nim-krvavy-baca.html#axzz4krXbYeYQ |title=Diev\u010da vymodelovalo tv\u00e1r svojho vraha. Bol n\u00edm \"krvav\u00fd ba\u010da\" |trans-title=The girl modeled the face of her killer. He was \"bloody shepherd\" |first=Eva |last=Bombov\u00e1 |date=18 February 2011 |newspaper=[[Korz\u00e1r]] |language=sk |accessdate=2017-06-24}}</ref>\n*[[Ondrej Rigo]]: killed, raped and mutilated nine women in [[Amsterdam]], [[Munich]] and [[Bratislava]], always wearing socks on his hands; he remains the [[Slovaks|Slovak]] murderer with the highest number of victims and he is also the most prolific serial killer in modern Slovak history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://refresher.sk/33850-Ondrej-Rigo-Na-svedomi-ma-9-zivotov-a-vysluzil-si-titul-najbrutalnejsi-seriovy-vrah-Slovenska?gdpr-accept=1 |title=Ondrej Rigo: Na svedom\u00ed m\u00e1 9 \u017eivotov a vysl\u00fa\u017eil si titul najbrut\u00e1lnej\u0161\u00ed s\u00e9riov\u00fd vrah Slovenska |trans-title=Ondrej Rigo: He killed 9 and is Slovakia's most brutal serial killer |first=Franti\u0161ek |last=Kulh\u00e1nek |date=4 June 2016 |website=Refresher.sk |language=sk |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jozef Slov\u00e1k]]: after serving just 8 years for his first murder from 1978, Slov\u00e1k killed at least four other women in [[Slovakia]] and [[Czech Republic]] in the early 1990s; highly intelligent, holder of numerous patents in electronics.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pluska.sk/slovensko/vrah-genius.html |title=Vrah g\u00e9nius! |trans-title=Killer genius! |date=9 June 2008 |newspaper=[[Plus JEDEN DE\u0147]] |language=sk |accessdate=20 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Slovenia===\n*[[Silvo Plut]]: killed three women in Slovenia and Serbia from 1990 until 2006; committed suicide in prison in 2007.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.si/204085 |title=Silvo Plut obsojen na 30 let zaporne kazni |trans-title=Silvo Plut sentenced to 30 years in prison |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 October 2006 |newspaper=[[Dnevnik (Slovenia)|Dnevnik]] |language=sl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Metod Trobec]]: raped and killed at least five women between 1976 and 1978; committed suicide in prison in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.slovenskenovice.si/crni-scenarij/doma/dolenja-vas-kraj-nesrecnega-imena |title=Dolenja vas, kraj nesre\u010dnega imena |trans-title=Dolenja Vas, a place of unlucky name |first=Vojko |last=Zakraj\u0161ek |date=January 5, 2012 |newspaper=[[Slovenske novice]] |language=sl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===South Africa===\n{{as of|2014|October}}, South Africa had 160 recorded serial killers since 1950. A disproportionately large number of them were white males, although no racial group was more likely to be a victim.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/crime-courts/most-sa-serial-killers-are-white-males-1.1766044 |title=Most SA serial killers are white males |last=Geach |first=Chelsea |date=16 October 2014 |newspaper=[[Cape Argus]] |via=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n*[[Asande Baninzi]]: killed eighteen people in the span of three months in 2001 with accomplice Mthutuzeli Nombewu; was given 19 life sentences and 189 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/B/BANINZI_asande.php |title=Asande Baninzi |last=Wetsch |first=Elisabeth |date=2005 |website=Serial Killer News |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008070518/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/B/BANINZI_asande.php |archive-date=2015-10-08}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Basson]]: first documented South African serial killer; killed nine people in [[Claremont, Cape Town|Claremont]] between 1903 and 1906 and buried them in his backyard; committed suicide to avoid arrest.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.africacrime-mystery.co.za/books/fsac/chp1.htm |title=Murdering for money, Pierre Basson: 1903 |last=Marsh |first=Rob |date=2009 |website=AfricaCrime-Mystery.co.za |access-date=19 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Sibusiso Duma]]: murdered seven people in the [[Pietermaritzburg]] area of [[KwaZulu Natal]] in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Life-in-jail-for-serial-killer-20090817 |title=Life in jail for Serial Killer |date=2009-08-17 |website=[[News24]] |access-date=2010-04-10 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920180328/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Life-in-jail-for-serial-killer-20090817 |archive-date=2012-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Gamal Lineveldt]]: responsible for the \"[[Cape Flats]] Murders\"; murdered four European women from October to November 1940; executed 1942.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.L/l/lineveldt-gamal.htm |title=Gamal Salie Lineveldt |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Cedric Maake]]: also known as the \"[[Wemmer Pan]] Killer\"; serial rapist; murdered at least 27 people from 1996\u20131997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/679141.stm |title=Serial killer jailed for 1,340 years |date=16 March 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bulelani Mabhayi]]: also known as \"The Monster of Tholeni\"; killed twenty women and children from 2007 to 2012 in the village of Tholeni in the [[Eastern Cape]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Serial-killer-pleads-guilty-to-20-murders-20130828 |title=Serial killer pleads guilty to 20 murders |date=2013-08-28 |website=News24 |accessdate=5 April 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Simon Majola]]: together with accomplice Themba Nkosi, known as \"The Bruma Lake Killers\"; robbed and drowned at least eight men in Bruma Lake from 2000 to 2001; both sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.iol.co.za/saturday-star/dredging-up-the-lake-serial-killers-1136700 |title=Dredging up the lake serial killers |first=Hanlie |last=Retief |date=13 September 2011 |newspaper=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Saturday Star]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]]}}</ref>\n*[[Fanuel Makamu]]: also known as \"The [[Mpumalanga]] Serial Rapist\"; along with accomplice Henry Maile, robbed, raped and murdered six six women from February to September 2000; Maile was shot by police on September 14, while Makamu was captured and sentenced to 165 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Serial-killer-gets-165-years-20040727 |title=Serial killer gets 165 years |first1=Zenzele |last1=Kuhlase |first2=Oris |last2=Mnisi |date=27 July 2004 |website=[[News24]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jimmy Maketta]]: also known as \"The Jesus Killer\" convicted on sixteen counts of murder, nineteen counts of rape from 1996\u20131999.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-guilty-on-47-counts-351242 |title=Serial killer guilty on 47 counts |first=Caryn |last=Dolley |date=2007-05-03 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2009-08-19}}</ref>\n*[[Johannes Mashiane]]: also known as \"The Beast of [[Atteridgeville]]\" thirteen counts of murder, twelve counts of sodomy from 1982\u20131989.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |title=Serial Killers |website=A History of Madness: An Index of Serial Killers and Murderers |access-date=2010-04-09 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003172900/http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |archive-date=2011-10-03}}</ref>\n*[[Daisy de Melker]]: poisoner; killed two husbands and one son between 1923\u20131932; executed in 1932.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimemagazine.com/daisy-de-melker-south-africas-first-serial-killer-0 |title=Daisy de Melker: South Africa's First Serial Killer |first=Marilyn Z. |last=Tomlins |date=13 October 2009 |website=Crime Magazine.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Samuel Bongani Mfeka]]: strangled six women from 1993 to 1996 in KwaZulu-Natal.<ref>{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA381&lpg=PA381&dq=Samuel+Bongani+Mfeka#v=onepage&q=Samuel%20Bongani%20Mfeka |date=February 2006 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3 |page=381}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Schechter |first=Harold |title=The A to Z Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=zM7ROzJPK2MC&pg=PA341&lpg=PA341&dq=%22Samuel+Bongani+Mfeka%22#v=onepage&q=%22Samuel%20Bongani%20Mfeka%22 |date=27 November 2012 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-1-4391-3885-4 |page=341 }}</ref>\n*[[Jack Mogale]]: also known as the \"West-End serial killer\"; convicted of raping and murdering sixteen women in [[Johannesburg]] in 2008 and 2009.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316 |title=West-End killer awaits sentencing |date=2011-03-16 |website=News24 |access-date=2011-03-17 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629051305/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316 |archive-date=2011-06-29}}</ref>\n*[[Elifasi Msomi]]: also known as \"The Axe Killer\" murdered fifteen people from 1953-1955, claiming that he was under the influence of the [[Tokoloshe]].<ref name=\"LeandiLouw\">{{cite web |url=https://medium.com/@LeandiLouw/south-africas-3-most-memorable-serial-killers-560c5b7a6f1a |title=South Africa's 3 Most Memorable Serial Killers |first=Leandi |last=Louw |date=6 August 2018 |website=[[Medium.com]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mukosi Freddy Mulaudzi]]: also known as \"The [[Limpopo]] Serial Killer\"; escaped convict, originally responsible for two murders in 1990, who murdered eleven more people between 2005 and 2006; given 11 life sentences.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/limpopo-serial-killer-case-postponed-297239 |title=Limpopo serial killer case postponed |date=11 October 2006 |website=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nicholas Lungisa Ncama]]: murdered six people in the [[Eastern Cape]] in 1997; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dispatch.co.za/1997/12/09/page%201.htm |title=Serial Killer Suspect in Court |first=Stan |last=Mzimba |date=9 December 1997 |newspaper=[[Daily Dispatch]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501154307/http://www.dispatch.co.za/1997/12/09/page%201.htm |archivedate=May 1, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Velaphi Ndlangamandla]]: also known as \"The Saloon Killer\"; robber who murdered nineteen people around Mpumalanga from April to September 1998; sentenced to 137 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/saloon-killer-gets-137-years-for-19-murders-42926 |title='Saloon killer' gets 137 years for 19 murders |date=19 September 2000 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[David Randitsheni]]: also known as \"[[Modimolle]] Serial Killer\" raped and murdered ten children (kidnapped and raped more) from 2004\u20132008.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-found-hanging-by-a-sheet-456838 |title=Serial killer found hanging by a sheet |date=2009-08-31 |agency=SAPA |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2009-08-31}}</ref>\n*[[Gert van Rooyen]]: allegedly abducted and murdered at least six girls from across [[South Africa]] from 1988\u20131989.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/he-feared-god-but-loved-young-girls-1.322079 |title=Feared God but 'loved' young girls |last=Gallagher |first=Christina |date=7 April 2007 |newspaper=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Star]] |via=Independent Online |access-date=10 June 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918005419/http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/he-feared-god-but-loved-young-girls-1.322079 |archive-date=18 September 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Louis van Schoor]]: former security guard who confessed to murdering 100 people; released on parole.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-freed-after-12-years-in-prison-1.225629 |title=Serial killer freed after 12 years in prison |first=Barbara |last=Hollands |date=2004-10-31 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2015-12-09}}</ref>\n*[[Khangayi Sedumedi]]: also known as the \"Century City Killer\"; raped, robbed and murdered between four and six women in [[Century City, Cape Town|Century City]] from 2011 to 2015; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/century-city-killers-modus-operandi-revealed-2032665 |title=Century City killer's modus operandi revealed |first=Catherine |last=Rice |date=June 9, 2016 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Samuel Sidyno]]: also known as \"Capital Hill Serial Killer\"; murdered seven people in [[Pretoria]] from 1998\u20131999.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/sadistic-serial-killer-gets-seven-life-terms-45868 |title=Sadistic serial killer gets seven life terms |date=5 September 2000 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Norman Afzal Simons]]: also known as \"Station Strangler\" raped, sodomised and murdered twenty-two children on the [[Cape Flats]] from 1986\u20131994.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/revisiting-the-station-strangler-cases-1.250970 |title=Revisiting the Station Strangler cases |last1=Bailey |first1=Candice |date=16 August 2005 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Moses Sithole]]: also known as the \"ABC Killer\" and the \"South African Strangler\"; raped and killed at least 38 young women in [[Atteridgeville]], [[Boksburg]] and Cleveland from 1994\u20131995.<ref name=\"LeandiLouw\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.iafrica.com/features/827627.htm |title=Worst criminals of SA |last=Kendal |first=Rebekah |date=3 May 2007 |website=iAfrica.com |accessdate=3 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720084655/http://news.iafrica.com/features/827627.htm |archive-date=20 July 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Thozamile Taki]]: also known as the \"[[Sugarcane]] Serial Killer\"; robbed and killed ten women in [[KwaZulu Natal]] and three in [[Eastern Cape]], dumping their bodies in sugarcane and tea [[plantation]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Sugarcane-killer-Release-her-20100302 |title=Sugarcane killer : Release her |date=2010-03-02 |website=News24 |access-date=2010-04-10 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920180212/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Sugarcane-killer-Release-her-20100302 |archive-date=2012-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Sipho Thwala]]: also known as the \"[[Phoenix, Durban|Phoenix]] Strangler\"; raped and murdered nineteen women in the sugarcane fields of [[KwaZulu Natal]] from 1996 to 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discoverychannel.co.uk/crime/serialkillers/phoenixstrangler/index.shtml |title=Crimes That Shook The World: The Phoenix Strangler |date=2009 |website=Discovery Channel: Crimes and Forensics |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091208090320/http://www.discoverychannel.co.uk/crime/serialkillers/phoenixstrangler/index.shtml |archive-date=2009-12-08}}</ref>\n*[[Stewart Wilken]]: also known as \"Boetie Boer\"; raped, sodomised and murdered at least seven victims in and around [[Port Elizabeth]] from 1990\u20131997.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA344 |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |last=Hickey |first=Eric W. |date=23 June 2009 |publisher=Cengage Learning |page=344 |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s7cEAQAAIAAJ |title=Strangers on the Street: Serial Homicide in South Africa |last=Pistorius |first=Micki |authorlink=Micki Pistorius |year=2002 |publisher=Penguin |isbn=978-0-14-100356-6 |accessdate=5 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/local-news/north-harbour-news/696177 |title=Story of a Serial Killer |date=30 October 2008 |newspaper=North Harbour News |accessdate=5 April 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Elias Xitavhudzi]]: also known as \"Pangaman\" murdered sixteen people in [[Atteridgeville]] in the 1960s.<ref>{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC |date=February 2006 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |pages=207 & 246 |isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3}}</ref>\n*[[Christopher Mhlengwa Zikode]]: also known as \"Donnybrook Serial Killer\"; murdered eighteen people in [[Donnybrook, KwaZulu-Natal]] from 1994\u20131995.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA341&lpg=PA341&dq=christopher+zikode,+serial+killer#v=onepage&f=false |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |first=Eric W. |last=Hickey |date=June 23, 2009 |page=341 |publisher=Cengage Learning |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7 |via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n===South Korea===\n*[[Chijon family]]: gang of cannibals that was sentenced to death for killing five people; sentenced to death in 1994; all members were [[executed by hanging]] on November 2, 1995.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://news.joins.com/article/3684096 |title=\uc0b4\uc778\ub9c8 \uc9c0\uc874\ud30c \uc6d0\ub798 \uc870\uc9c1\uba85\uc740 \ub9c8\uc2a4\uce78 |trans-title=Murderer tribe originally named Maskan |date=2009-07-12 |newspaper=[[JoongAng Ilbo]] |language=ko |access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref>\n*[[Crown Prince Sado]]: [[Joseon]] prince who raped and killed his palace staff; sealed in a rice chest and died.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3010313 |title=The ever-changing history of Prince Sado |author=Jin Eun-Soo |date=15 October 2015 |newspaper=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jeong Du-yeong]]: killed an officer in 1986; after release, killed eight other people in robberies from 1999 to 2000; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.donga.com/fbin/output?f=eA_&n=200004160101 |title=\uc5f4\ub2ec\uc0c8 9\uba85 \uc8fd\uc600\ub2e4\u2026\ubd80\uc0b0 \u4e2d\u4f01\ud68c\uc7a5\ubd80\ubd80 \uc0b4\ud574\ubc94 \uc790\ubc31 |trans-title=Killed nine people in ten months ... confessed to murder of husband and wife |date=16 April 2000 |newspaper=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]] |language=ko |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jeong Nam-gyu]]: sexually assaulted and killed fourteen people from 2004 to 2006; died in hospital after failing to hang himself the previous day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LPOD&mid=sec&sid1=001&sid2=140&oid=001&aid=0002987292&isYeonhapFlash=Y |title=\uc5f0\uc1c4\uc0b4\uc778\ubc94 \uc815\ub0a8\uaddc \uc11c\uc6b8\uad6c\uce58\uc18c\uc11c \uc790\uc0b4 |trans-title=Serial Killer Chung Nam-gyu commits suicide at Seoul detention center |date=2009-11-22 |agency=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |website=[[Naver]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kang Ho-sun]]: sentenced to death in 2010 for killing ten women, including his wife and mother-in-law.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking_news_detail.asp?id=13851 |title=Death sentence for South Korean serial killer |date=10 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Standard (Hong Kong)|The Standard]] |accessdate=2013-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110003435/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking_news_detail.asp?id=13851 |archivedate=2013-11-10}}</ref>\n*[[Kim Hae-sun]]: violent drunkard who raped and killed three children in 2000; executed 2001.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://media.daum.net/culture/art/view.html?cateid=1021&newsid=20060323092612574&p=tvreport |title=\uc5b4\uc774\uc5c6\uace0 \ud574\uad34\ud55c \ubc94\uc8c4 '\uc0ac\uc774\ucf54\ud328\uc2dc'\uc871\ub4e4! |trans-title=A ridiculous and bizarre crime psychopath! |date=2006-03-23 |website=[[Daum.net]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kim Sun-ja (serial killer)|Kim Sun-ja]]: poisoned five people with potassium cyanide between 1986 and 1988 for monetary reasons; executed 1997.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hyunbulnews.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=296863|title=Death penalthy for the elderly Kim is unfair|last=Kim|first=Jiwon|date=November 23, 2011|work=Modern Buddhist Newspaper|access-date=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lee Choon-jae]]: responsible for the \"Hwaseong serial murders\"; murdered fifteen women, including his sister-in-law, and raped numerous others; sentenced to life imprisonment for one murder in 1994, and connected to the others decades later.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2019/09/serial-killer-who-terrorized-south-korea-identified-after-30-years/ |title=South Korean serial killer who inspired 'Memories of Murder' identified after 30 years |date=September 18, 2019 |website=[[BNO News]] |accessdate=September 19, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Yoo Young-chul]]: cannibal; killed twenty-one people from September 2003 to July 2004, mainly young women and rich men; sentenced to death in 2004.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2004/08/13/2004081361048.html |title=Serial Killer Claims to Have Eaten Victims' Organs |first=Yong-hyun |last=Ahn |date=13 August 2004 |newspaper=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Spain===\n*[[The \"Frenchman's Garden\" Murders|Andr\u00e9s Aldije Monmej\u00e1 and Jos\u00e9 Mu\u00f1oz Lopera]]: responsible for the \"Frenchman's Garden\" murders; owners of an illegal gambling house who killed six visitors from 1889 to 1904; both garroted in 1906.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://gaceta.es/noticias/huerto-frances-peligroso-casino-andalucia-profunda-26052017-1710/ |title=El huerto del franc\u00e9s, un peligroso casino en la Andaluc\u00eda profunda |trans-title=The French Orchard, a dangerous casino in deepest Andalusia |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=26 May 2017 |newspaper=[[La Gaceta (Spain)|La Gaceta]] |language=es |access-date=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Francisca Ballesteros]]: known as ''La Viuda Negra''<ref name=\"abc.es\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/espana/asesinos-serie-201012010000_noticia.html |title=La negra lista de asesinos en serie de Espa\u00f1a |trans-title=The black list of serial killers in Spain |date=December 1, 2010 |newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> (\"The [[Latrodectus|Black Widow]]\"), poisoned her husband and three children in [[Valencia, Spain|Valencia]] between 1990 and 2004 (one survived), sentenced to 84 years in prison in 2005.\n*[[Manuel Blanco Romasanta]]: travelling salesman who claimed to be a [[werewolf]], confessed to thirteen murders and was convicted of eight in 1853; his initial death sentence commuted in order to make a study in [[clinical lycanthropy]], died in prison ten years later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.typicallyspanish.com/news/publish/article_13582.shtml |title=The Wolfman of Allariz |author=m.p. |date=13 November 2007 |website=Typically Spanish |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111204040513/http://www.typicallyspanish.com/news/publish/article_13582.shtml |archive-date=2011-12-04}}</ref>\n*[[Manuel Delgado Villegas]]: also known as ''El Arropiero''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The [[Arrope]] Trader\"), wandering criminal with [[XYY syndrome]] that confessed to 48 murders in [[Spain]], [[France]] and [[Italy]], including his girlfriend; considered guilty of seven and interned in a mental institution until his death in 1998.\n*[[Joaqu\u00edn Ferr\u00e1ndiz Ventura]]: insurance salesman who murdered five women in [[Castell\u00f3n Province]] between 1995 and 1996.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/diario/1998/09/10/cvalenciana/905455100_850215.html |title=La Guardia Civil detiene al supuesto asesino de Sonia Rubio en Benic\u00e0ssim. El supuesto asesino de Sonia Rubio ya fue condenado por abuso sexual |trans-title=The Civil Guard arrests the presumed killer of Sonia Rubio in Benic\u00e0ssim. The presumed killer of Sonia Rubio had been convicted previously of sexual assault |last=Fabra |first=Mar\u00eda |date=September 10, 1998 |newspaper=El Pa\u00eds |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 5, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Alfredo Gal\u00e1n]]: also known as \"The Playing Card Killer\", Spanish Army corporal who killed six individuals in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elobservadordelmundo.com/reportaje_detalle.asp?cod=1020 |title=La Parte Oscura de la Mente: Alfredo Gal\u00e1n Sotillo - El Asesino de la Baraja |trans-title=The Dark Part of the Mind: Alfredo Gal\u00e1n Sotillo - The Killer of the Baraja |date=August 19, 2011 |website=El Observador del Mundo |language=es |accessdate=March 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110910130600/http://www.elobservadordelmundo.com/reportaje_detalle.asp?cod=1020 |archive-date=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Juan D\u00edaz de Garayo]]: also known as \"The Sacamantecas\"; killed six people from 1870 to 1879 in [[\u00c1lava]]. Executed by [[garrote]] in 1881.<ref>{{cite book |last=Becerro de Bengoa |first=Ricardo |date=1881 |title=El Sacamantecas. Su Retrato y sus Cr\u00edmenes. Narraci\u00f3n escrita con arreglo a todos los datos aut\u00e9nticos |location=Vitoria |publisher=Viuda e Hijos de Iturbe |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Bernaldo de Quir\u00f3s |first=Constancio |date=1909 |title=Vidas Delincuentes |location=Madrid |publisher=Centro Editorial G\u00f3ngora |language=es}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco Garc\u00eda Escalero]]: also known as ''El Mendigo Asesino''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The Killer Beggar\"); [[schizophrenia|schizophrenic]] beggar convicted of eleven murders, confined to a psychiatric hospital since 1995\n*[[Gila Giraldo]]: also known as \"La Serrana de la Verra\"; alleged 15th-16th century serial killer who beheaded men she slept with.\n*[[Murder of Roc\u00edo Wanninkhof#Tony Alexander King|Tony Alexander King]]: also known as the \"Costa Killer\"; British sex offender who murdered two girls in [[Malaga]] in 1999 and 2003; suspected of possibly committing more murders in his native UK; sentenced to 19 years imprisonment.<ref name=\"El Mundo\">{{cite news |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2003/09/22/sociedad/1064218068.html |title=El asesino de Sonia y Roc\u00edo estrangul\u00f3 a cinco mujeres en Reino Unido |trans-title=The murderer of Sonia and Roc\u00edo who strangled five women in the United Kingdom |date=September 23, 2003 |newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 21, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Ram\u00f3n Laso]]: killed his two wives, child and brother in law in order to pursue extra-marital relationships.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elespanol.com/reportajes/grandes-historias/20170113/185732087_0.html |title=El enterrador convertido en asesino cuyas v\u00edctimas jam\u00e1s aparecieron |trans-title=The undertaker turned murderer whose victims were never found |last=Rada |first=Juan |date=January 15, 2017 |newspaper=[[El Espa\u00f1ol]] |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 9, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Enriqueta Mart\u00ed]]: self-proclaimed [[witch]] who kidnapped, prostituted, murdered and made potions with the remains of small children in early 20th century [[Barcelona]] (12 bodies were identified in her home); murdered in prison while awaiting trial in 1913.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://hemeroteca.lavanguardia.com/preview/1912/04/19/pagina-3/33336536/pdf.html |title=Poco despu\u00e9s de las tres y media de la madrugada de ayer, falleci\u00f3 en la c\u00e1rcel de mujeres la tristemente c\u00e9lebre secuestradora Enriqueta Mart\u00ed Ripoli... |trans-title=Shortly after half past three in the morning yesterday, the sadly celebrated kidnapper Enriqueta Mart\u00ed Ripoli died in the women's prison... |date=13 May 1913 |page=3 |newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]] |language=es |access-date=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[D\u00e1maso Rodr\u00edguez Mart\u00edn]]: ''El Brujo'' (\"The Warlock\"), serial rapist and [[voyeur]] imprisoned in 1981 after attacking a couple, killing the man and raping the woman. Escaped from prison to the [[Anaga]] mountains in 1991, where he killed two German hikers (one of them was raped). Cornered in an abandoned house, he shot himself unsuccessfully, only to be shot dead in turn by law enforcement.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.laopinion.es/sucesos/2016/02/14/brujo-bestia-moquinal/655875.html |title='El Brujo', la bestia de El Moquinal |trans-title='El Brujo', the beast of El Moquinal |last=Herrero |first=Antonio |date=15 February 2016 |newspaper=[[La Opini\u00f3n]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304005951/http://www.laopinion.es/sucesos/2016/02/14/brujo-bestia-moquinal/655875.html |archive-date=4 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Rodr\u00edguez Vega]]: ''El Mataviejas''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The Old Lady Killer\"), raped and killed at least sixteen elderly women, sentenced to 440 years in prison in 1995, murdered by fellow inmates in 2002.\n*[[Abdelkader Salhi (serial killer)|Abdelkader Salhi]]: known as the \"10 Killer\"; German convicted of a robbery-murder in 1988 in Germany, later moving to Spain and allegedly murdering three prostitutes from August to September 2011; currently awaiting sentencing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.euroweeklynews.com/2011/09/29/costa-del-sol-serial-killer-arrested/#.XLCrBDAzbIV |title='Costa del Sol Serial Killer' arrested |date=29 September 2011 |website=[[EuroWeekly News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gustavo Romero Tercero]]: \"The [[Valdepe\u00f1as]] Killer\", killed three people from 1993 to 1998.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2005/04/21/sociedad/1114074425.html |title=Condenan a 103 a\u00f1os de prisi\u00f3n a Gustavo Romero por el asesinato de tres personas en Valdepe\u00f1as |trans-title=Gustavo Romero sentenced to 103 years in prison for the murder of three people in Valdepe\u00f1as |date=April 22, 2005 |newspaper=El Mundo |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 14, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Margarita S\u00e1nchez Guti\u00e9rrez]]: known as \"The Black Widow of Barcelona\"; poisoned family members and relatives, killing four of them; acquitted of the murders, but sentenced to 34 years for other crimes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/opinion/buzon/nicho/abierto/elpepiopi/19960801elpepiopi_1/Tes |title=Un buz\u00f3n como un nicho abierto |trans-title=A mailbox as an open niche |last1=Martin |first1=Andreu |date=1 August 1996 |newspaper=El Pa\u00eds |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Swaziland===\n*[[David Thabo Simelane]]: raped and killed 28 women, suspected of 45; sentenced to death in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.swazilive.com/Swaziland_News/Swaziland_News_Stories.asp?News_id=2722 |title=David Simelane gets death penalty, to be hanged |first=Linda |last=Jele |date=2 April 2011 |website=Swaziland News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Sweden===\n*[[Malm\u00f6 \u00d6stra hospital murders|Anders Hansson]]: hospital [[orderly]] in [[Malm\u00f6]] who poisoned his victims with detergents Gevisol and Ivisol between October 1978 and January 1979; his actions were called the \"[[Malm\u00f6 \u00d6stra hospital murders]]\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article12915042.ab |title=99 dagar \u2013 27 mord |trans-title=99 days - 27 murders |first=Linda |last=Hjert\u00e9n |date=2011-04-24 |newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]] |language=sv |accessdate=2014-01-17}}</ref>\n*[[Anders Lindb\u00e4ck (vicar)|Anders Lindb\u00e4ck]]: [[vicar]] who poisoned poor people with arsenic, three of them who died; committed suicide in custody in 1865.\n*[[John Ingvar L\u00f6vgren]]: confessed to four murders committed between 1958 and 1963 in the Stockholm region.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stockholm.edublogs.org/2012/12/17/vi-kartlagger-fleminggatan-nummer-for-nummer/ |title=Vi kartl\u00e4gger Fleminggatan nummer f\u00f6r nummer |trans-title=We map Fleminggatan number by number |date=2012-12-17 |website=Stockholm \u2013 en guide till kultur, sev\u00e4rdheter och |language=sv |accessdate=2014-01-17}}</ref>\n*[[Hilda Nilsson]]: known as \"The Angel Maker on Bruks Street\"; [[Helsingborg]] baby farmer who murdered eight children; committed suicide in custody in 1917.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/malmo/atskilliga-spadbarn-dog-hos-anglamakerskorna/ |title=\u00c5tskilliga sp\u00e4dbarn dog hos \u00e4nglamakerskorna |trans-title=Several infants died at the hands of angel makers |last=Andersson |first=Martin |date=2 December 2012 |newspaper=[[Sydsvenskan]] |location=[[Malm\u00f6]] |language=sv |accessdate=6 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Switzerland===\n*[[Roger Andermatt]]: also known as the \"Death-Keeper of [[Lucerne]]\"; nurse who killed twenty-two people from 1995 to 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nzz.ch/aktuell/startseite/articleDL2GQ-1.11845 |title=Es bleibt bei lebensl\u00e4nglich f\u00fcr den \"Todespfleger\" |trans-title=It remains a life sentence for the \"death-keeper\" |date=16 February 2006 |newspaper=[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]] |language=de |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Werner Ferrari]]: child killer who lured his victims from popular festivals, strangling them afterwards; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.blick.ch/news/schweiz/die-eltern-der-ermordeten-fabienne-imhof-klagen-an-warum-bloss-lernen-die-richter-nichts-id1799956.html |title=Die Eltern der ermordeten Fabienne Imhof klagen an: \"Warum bloss lernen die Richter nichts?\" |trans-title=The parents of the murdered Fabienne Imhof complain: \"Why are the judges learning nothing?\" |date=2012-03-08 |newspaper=[[Blick]] |language=de |accessdate=2014-09-25}}</ref>\n*[[Erich Hauert]]: sex offender who committed eleven rapes and three murders from 1982 to 1983; sentenced to life imprisonment; his case impacted treatment of dangerous sexual offenders in Switzerland tremendously.<ref>''Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung'', 20 September 1996, p. 53.</ref>\n\n===Taiwan===\n*[[Zhang Renbao]]: murdered three women from 1993 to 2003, also sexually violating the first victim; sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.appledaily.com.tw/appledaily/article/headline/20040617/1013505/ |title=\u7bb1\u5c4d\u6848\u8b8a\u614b\u6bba\u4eba\u72af\u5224\u6b7b |trans-title=Box corpse case murderer sentenced to death |date=17 June 2004 |newspaper=[[Apple Daily (Taiwan)|Apple Daily]] |language=zh |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Tunisia===\n*[[Naceur Damergi]]: rapist who killed thirteen minors in the [[Nabeul]] region in the 1980s; executed by hanging in 1990.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leaders.com.tn/article/11418-comment-a-ete-pendu-le-tueur-en-serie-de-nabeul |title=Comment a \u00e9t\u00e9 pendu le tueur en s\u00e9rie de Nabeul |trans-title=How was the serial killer of Nabeul hanged |date=17 May 2013 |website=Leaders |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/crime_series_show.php?series_number=13&id=857 |title=Worldwide Hangings: Naceur Damergi |date=2014 |website=True Crime Library |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222024758/http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/crime_series_show.php?series_number=13&id=857 |archive-date=February 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Turkey===\n*[[S\u00fcleyman Akta\u015f]]: also known as the \"Nailing Killer\"; killed five people and nailed them in the eyes and head; he is kept in a psychiatric hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haber7.com/guncel/haber/220403-civici-katilden-folklor-gosterisi |title='\u00c7ivici katil'den folklor g\u00f6sterisi |trans-title=Folklore show from 'The Nail Killer' |first=Aziz |last=G\u00fcl |date=2007-02-16 |website=Haber7.com |language=tr |accessdate=2014-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Adnan \u00c7olak]]: also known as \"The Beast of Artvin\"; killed seventeen elderly women in [[Artvin]], Turkey from 1992 to 1995; in 2000 he was sentenced to death six times, and 40 years in prison. However, since October 1984, Turkey has not executed any prisoners, and {{as of|2004|lc=y}}, Turkey does not have capital punishment.\n*[[Seyit Ahmet Demirci]]: also known as the \"Furniture dealers' killer\"; killed three furniture dealers selected at random and because he was sexually abused by his employer during his youth;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/mobilyaci-seri-katili-39131508 |title=Mobilyac\u0131 seri katili |trans-title=The serial killer |date=6 February 2000 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |language=tr |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref> sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/turkiye/turkiyenin-korkunc-cinayetler-isleyen-14-seri-katili |title=T\u00fcrkiye'nin korkun\u00e7 cinayetler i\u015fleyen 14 seri katili |trans-title=Turkey's 14 serial killers committed terrible murders |date=13 June 2016 |website=[[CNN T\u00fcrk]] |language=tr |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[\u00d6zg\u00fcr Dengiz]]: serial killer from [[Ankara]], who killed four people and cannibalized at least one.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/09/16/guncel/agun.html |title=Yerli Hannibal'\u0131n anatomisi |trans-title=Anatomy of the native Hannibal |first1=Mansur |last1=\u00c7eli\u0307k |first2=G\u00f6k\u00e7er |last2=Tahi\u0307nci\u0307o\u011flu |date=September 16, 2007 |newspaper=[[Milliyet]] |language=tr |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071105112638/http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/09/16/guncel/agun.html |archive-date=5 November 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Atalay Filiz]]: fugitive suspected of four murders from 2012 to 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/son-dakika-haberi-atalay-filiz-yakalandi-40116460 |title=Son dakika haberi: Atalay Filiz yakaland\u0131, \u00fcst\u00fcnden \u00e7\u0131kanlar \u015foke etti! |trans-title=Breaking news: Atalay Filiz caught, shocked by those on top! |first1=Banu |last1=\u015een |first2=Taylan |last2=Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m |date=2016-06-12 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |language=tr |accessdate=2016-06-12}}</ref>\n*[[Ali Kaya (serial killer)|Ali Kaya]]: also known as \"The Babyface Killer\"; responsible for ten murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/Yasam/2014/01/06/bebek-yuzlu-katil-firar-etti |title='Bebek y\u00fczl\u00fc katil' firar etti |trans-title='Baby-faced killer' escaped |first=Ads\u0131z |last=G\u00fcnebakan |date=6 January 2014 |newspaper=[[Sabah (newspaper)|Sabah]] |language=tr |accessdate=6 January 2014 }}</ref>\n*[[Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar]]: also known as \"Avc\u0131\" (\"Hunter\"); killed eight people from 1994 to 2018; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.haberturk.com/kayseri-haberleri/62629762-seri-katil-hamdi-kayapinar-adliyeye-sevk-edildikiz-kardesi-dahil-7-kisiyi-olduren-hamdi |title=Seri katil Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar adliyeye sevk edildi |trans-title=Serial killer Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar was sent to court |date=7 August 2018 |newspaper=[[Habert\u00fcrk]] |language=tr |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Yavuz Yap\u0131c\u0131o\u011flu]]: also known as \"The Screwdriver Killer\"; responsible for at least eighteen murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.radikal.com.tr/haber.php?haberno=60681 |title=Tornavidal\u0131 seri cinayet |trans-title=Serial murder with a screwdriver |first=Erdal |last=\u00d6zcan |date=2002-12-25 |newspaper=[[Radikal]] |language=tr |accessdate=2014-03-05 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305170036/http://www.radikal.com.tr/haber.php?haberno=60681 |archive-date=2014-03-05}}</ref>\n\n===Ukraine===\n*[[Zaven Almazyan]]: also known as the \"Voroshilovgrad Maniac\"; Russian soldier who raped and killed three women in [[Voroshilovgrad]]; executed 1973.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.allkriminal.ru/article/17492/671 |title=\u041b\u0443\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a \u0417\u0430\u0432\u0435\u043d \u0410\u043b\u043c\u0430\u0437\u044f\u043d |trans-title=Lugansk maniac Zaven Almazyan |date=3 October 2011 |website=AllKriminal.ru |language=ru |access-date=2013-10-07}}</ref>\n*[[Oleksandr Berlizov]]: also known as the \"Night Demon\"; sexual psychopath who raped numerous women from 1969 to 1972 in [[Dnipropetrovsk]], killing nine of them; executed 1972.\n*[[Sergei Dovzhenko]]: killed between seventeen and nineteen people in his native home of [[Mariupol]] for \"mocking\" him; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://ilich.in.ua/news.php?id=84 |title=\u041e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043b\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043c \u043e\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043b? |trans-title=Is he a lone serial killer and why did he kill? |first=D. |last=Sumtsov |date=1 January 2003 |newspaper=Illichivets |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716002407/http://ilich.in.ua/news.php?id=84 |archive-date=2014-07-16}}</ref>\n*[[Tamara Ivanyutina]]: also known as the \"Kiev Poisoner\"; poisoned people from personal spite 1976 to 1987, killing nine of them; executed 1987.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bulvar.com.ua/arch/2012/4/4f206e104267f/ |title=\u041e\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 |last=Poddubny |first=Nikolay |date=2012-01-24 |website=\u0411\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0432\u0430\u0440 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0430 |language=ru |access-date=2012-11-05 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DV9upYYV?url=http://www.bulvar.com.ua/arch/2012/4/4f206e104267f/ |archive-date=7 January 2013 }}</ref>\n*[[Ruslan Khamarov]]: seduced and murdered eleven women in his home from 2000 to 2003; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.segodnya.ua/oldarchive/c2256713004f33f5c2256e7f0035f846.html |title=\"\u0411\u0435\u0440\u0434\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a\" \u0422\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0443\u0435\u0442 \u041f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0414\u0435\u0432\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0443 \u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e \u041a \u041d\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0412 \u041a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0443 |date=24 April 2004 |newspaper=[[Segodnya]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Oleg Kuznetsov (serial killer)|Oleg Kuznetsov]]: also known as \"The [[Balashikha]] Ripper\"; killed a total of ten people in Russia and Ukraine; sentenced to death but commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tyurma.com/mordovskaya-edinichka-prigovorennye-k-zhizni |title=\u041c\u043e\u0440\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \"\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0430\" - \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043a \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438 |trans-title=Mordovian \"one\" - sentenced to life |website=Tyurma.com |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106104333/http://www.tyurma.com/mordovskaya-edinichka-prigovorennye-k-zhizni |archive-date=6 January 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Anatoly Onoprienko]]: also known as \"The Terminator\"; murdered 52 people from 1989 until his capture in 1996; died in prison in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/europe/9811/30/ukraine.serial.killer/index.html |title=Accused Ukrainian serial killer makes surprise request at trial |date=1998-11-30 |website=CNN |accessdate=2008-09-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080519073812/http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/europe/9811/30/ukraine.serial.killer/index.html |archivedate=2008-05-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/219734.stm |title=The lives changed by Onoprienko |first=James |last=Commarasamy |date=1998-11-23 |website=BBC News |accessdate=2008-09-10}}</ref>\n*[[Dnepropetrovsk maniacs|Viktor Sayenko and Igor Suprunyuk]]: also known as the \"Dnepropetrovsk Maniacs\"; teenagers in [[Dnipro|Dnipropetrovsk]] who bludgeoned 21 people to death in 2007 with the aid of a third teenager, often filming their murders; sentenced to life in prison in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.unian.net/eng/news/news-204617.html |title=Three 19\u2011year-old youths committed 19 murders in Dnepropetrovsk during a month|publisher=[[UNIAN]] |access-date=2008-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115153056/http://www.unian.net/eng/news/news-204617.html |archive-date=2012-01-15 |url-status=live }}</ref>   \n*[[Serhiy Tkach]]: convicted of raping and murdering 36 women between 1980-2005; claims the total is 100.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/ukraine/3933579/Man-sentenced-to-life-in-prison-for-murdering-36-women.html |title=Man sentenced to life in prison for murdering 36 women |first=Miriam |last=Elder |date=24 December 2008 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=2008-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/7798753.stm |title=BBC News: Serial killer jailed in Ukraine |date=24 December 2008 |website=BBC News |accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Nighttime Killers|Vladyslav Volkovich and Volodymyr Kondratenko]]: also known as the \"Nighttime Killers\"; charged with shooting, stabbing and bludgeoning sixteen victims to death in [[Kiev]] between 1991 and 1997; Kondratenko committed suicide in prison during the trial; Volkovich was found guilty and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.podrobnosti.com.ua/projects/vovremya/2003/06/02/62096.html |title=\u0414\u0443\u044d\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446 |trans-title=The Serial Killer Duo |date=June 2, 2003 |website=[[Podrobnosti]] |accessdate=2009-01-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123055610/http://podrobnosti.com.ua/projects/vovremya/2003/06/02/62096.html |archive-date=2009-01-23}}</ref>\n<!-- NOTE: The Dnepropetrovsk maniacs are spree killers. Please do not add them to this article. -->\n\n===United Kingdom===\n\n====England====\n*[[Stephen Akinmurele]]: also known as the \"Cul-de-sac killer\"; committed suicide in [[Manchester Prison|Strangeways]] in 1999 while awaiting trial for the murders of five elderly people in [[Blackpool]] and the [[Isle of Man]] between 1995 and 1998.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/aug/30/jamiewilson1 |title='Serial killer' found hanged |first=Jamie |last=Wilson |date=August 30, 1999 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Beverley Allitt]]: also known as \"Angel of Death\"; [[Lincolnshire]] [[paediatric]] nurse who killed four children in her care and injured at least nine others; sentenced to life imprisonment in 1991.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/child-murderer-confesses-at-last-1510845.html |title=Child murderer confesses at last |last=Foster |first=Jonathan |date=15 October 1993 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Bateman]]: also known as the \"[[Yorkshire]] Witch\"; 19th century thief hanged for the poisoning of a couple (husband survived); suspected in three more deaths; executed 1809.<ref>{{cite book |last=Strevens |first=Summer |date=2017 |title=The Yorkshire Witch: The Life and Trial of Mary Bateman |location=[[Barnsley]] |publisher=[[Pen and Sword Books]] |page=135 |isbn=978-1-47386-387-3}}</ref>\n*[[Levi Bellfield]]: also known as the \"Bus Stop Stalker\"; convicted of the 2002 [[murder of Amanda Dowler]] and two fatal hammer attacks on young women in [[South West (London sub region)|South West London]] in 2003 and 2004.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/he-murdered-two-how-many-more-did-bellfield-target-1.875373 |title=He murdered two... how many more did Bellfield target? |date=26 February 2008 |newspaper=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Herald]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[London Burkers|John Bishop, Thomas Williams, Michael Shields and James May]]: known as \"The London Burkers\"; English copycats of [[Burke and Hare murders|Burke and Hare]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.historybytheyard.co.uk/early_murder_investigations.htm |title=Early Murder Investigations |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=History by the Yard |access-date=24 January 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Geordie Bourne]]: Scottish 16th century bandit who killed seven people around the [[Scottish Marches|East English Marches]]; executed by unknown means.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/stream/memoirsrobertca00orregoog#page/n66/mode/2up |editor-last=Powell |editor-first=G. H. |date=1905 |title=Memoirs of Robert Carey, Earl of Monmouth |location=London, UK |publisher=Alexander Moring Ltd. The De La More Press |pages=42\u201345 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Brady]] and [[Myra Hindley]]: also known as the \"[[Moors murders|Moors Murderers]]\"; murdered five children, aged between 10 and 17 between 1963 and 1965. Buried four of their victims on [[Saddleworth Moor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/661139.stm |title=Hindley: I wish I'd been hanged |date=29 February 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=11 August 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Ann Britland]]: poisoned her daughter, husband, and the wife of her lover in 1886; first woman to be executed by hanging at [[HM Prison Manchester|Strangeways Prison]] in [[Manchester]] in 1886 by executioner [[James Berry (executioner)|James Berry]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/stream/MyExperiencesAsAnExecutioner/Berry#page/n37/mode/1up |last=Berry |first=James |editor-first=H. Snowden |editor-last=Ward |date=1892 |title=My Experiences as an Executioner |location=London, UK |publisher=Percy Lund & Co |pages=74\u201376 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Bryan]]: [[Psychiatric hospital|institutionalized]] for fatal hammer attack on woman in 1993; re-apprehended for [[cannibalism|cannibalizing]] a friend in 2004, but able to batter a fellow patient to death months later.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2009/09/03/2009-09-03_series_of_blunders_frees_cannibal_peter_bryan.html |title=Series of blunders frees schizophrenic cannibal Peter Bryan, who kills two more people |last=Hazlett |first=Alexandra |date=3 September 2009 |newspaper=New York Daily News |accessdate=23 November 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905074132/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2009/09/03/2009-09-03_series_of_blunders_frees_cannibal_peter_bryan.html |archive-date=5 September 2009}}</ref>\n*[[George Chapman (murderer)|George Chapman]]: Polish-born poisoner who murdered three women between 1897 and 1902; suspected by some authors of being [[Jack the Ripper]]. Executed in 1903.<ref>{{cite book |first=Peter |last=De Loriol |title=Murder and Crime in London |year=2010 |publisher=History Press Limited |isbn=978-0-7524-5657-7 |pages=61\u201362}}</ref>\n*[[John Childs (murderer)|John Childs]]: known as the most prolific [[hit man]] in the United Kingdom, he was convicted in 1979 of six [[contract killing]]s, though none of the bodies have been found.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1946&dat=19791206&id=2DsyAAAAIBAJ&sjid=sqQFAAAAIBAJ&pg=4729,3210267 |title=British hired killer shocks Old Bailey |date=6 December 1979 |agency=UPI |newspaper=[[Montreal Gazette]] |accessdate=23 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[John Christie (murderer)|John Christie]]: gassed, raped and strangled at least five women from 1943 to 1953, hiding the bodies at his house in [[Notting Hill]], London; also strangled his wife Ethel, as well as the wife and baby daughter of neighbour [[Timothy Evans]], who was wrongfully executed for their murders.<ref>{{Cite book |title=John Christie |last=Marston |first=Edward |authorlink=Keith Miles |year=2007 |publisher=[[The National Archives (United Kingdom)|The National Archives]] |location=Kew, Surrey |isbn=978-1-90561-516-2 |page=[https://archive.org/details/johnchristie0000mars/page/108 108] |url=https://archive.org/details/johnchristie0000mars/page/108 }}</ref>\n*[[Robert George Clements]]: doctor who committed suicide when due to be arrested for poisoning his fourth wife; his other three wives all died suspiciously during the interwar period.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=-XvaAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Robert+George+Clements%22&dq=%22Robert+George+Clements%22 |title=The New Murderers' Who's Who |last1=Gaute |first1=J. H. H. |last2=Odell |first2=Robin |page=86 |date=1989 |location=London, UK |publisher=Harrap |isbn=978-0-245-54639-6}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Ann Cotton]]: [[Victorian era|Victorian]] killer; said to have poisoned more than twenty victims; hanged in 1873.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2016/10/31/dark-angel-joanne-froggatt-stars-in-the-gruesome-real-life-story/ |title=Dark Angel: the gruesome true story of Mary Ann Cotton, Britain's first serial killer |last1=Armstrong |first1=Neil |date=2016-10-31 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=31 October 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Neill Cream]]: also known as the \"[[Lambeth]] Poisoner\"; began his killing spree in the [[United States]] then moved to London; hanged in 1892.<ref>{{cite book |last=Edwards |first=Wallace |title=I am Jack The... |year=2013 |publisher=Absolute Crime |isbn=978-1484872215}}</ref>\n*[[Dale Cregan]]: sentenced to a whole life order in prison for four counts of homicide in 2012 involving the use of firearms, including killing two police officers, and three separate counts of attempted murder in [[Greater Manchester]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-22893157 |title=Dale Cregan trial: Police killer sentenced to whole of life in jail |date=13 June 2013 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Sarah Dazley]]: also known as the \"[[Potton]] Poisoner\"; poisoned her husband with arsenic; suspected of killing her first husband and child; hanged 1843.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM9BZB_The_Potton_Poisoner_Wrestlingworth_Beds_UK |title=The Potton Poisoner, Wrestlingworth, Beds, UK - Infamous Crime Scenes |website=Waymarking.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Frederick Bailey Deeming]]: in 1891 killed his wife and four children in Britain; remarried and moved to Australia, and then murdered his new wife.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article196998457 |title=The Windsor Tragedy: Search For the Murderer: Discovery of Clues |date=5 March 1892 |newspaper=[[The Age]] |issue=11553 |location=Melbourne, Victoria |accessdate=11 April 2018 |page=7 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[Peterborough ditch murders|Joanna Dennehy]]: stabbed three men to death and tried to kill two others selected at random in what would become known as the \"[[Peterborough]] Ditch Murders\" in 2013; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-24987953 |title=Peterborough ditch deaths: Joanna Dennehy pleads guilty |date=18 November 2013 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/serial-killer-joanna-dennehy-stuns-old-bailey-by-pleading-guilty-to-murdering-three-men-and-dumping-their-bodies-in-remote-ditches-8947023.html |title=Joanna Dennehy trial: Serial killer stuns Old Bailey by pleading guilty to murdering three men and dumping bodies in ditches |first=Rob |last=Williams |date=18 November 2013 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[John Duffy and David Mulcahy]]: also known as the \"Railway Killers\"; killed three women near railway stations in the 1980s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/954909.stm |title=Murder victims' fate 'revealed' |date=3 October 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Amelia Dyer]]: murdered infants in her care; executed by hanging at [[Newgate Prison]] in 1896.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thamesvalley.police.uk/aboutus-museum-baby-farmer |title=The Baby Farmer |website=Thames Valley Police |accessdate=17 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302213715/http://www.thamesvalley.police.uk/aboutus-museum-baby-farmer |archivedate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Kenneth Erskine]]: also known as the \"[[Stockwell]] Strangler\"; sentenced to life imprisonment in 1988 for murdering seven pensioners.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/8149050.stm |title='Strangler' wins murders appeal |date=14 July 2009 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Black Widows of Liverpool|Catherine Flannigan and Margaret Higgins]]: two [[Irish people|Irish]] women known as \"The Black Widows of [[Liverpool]]\"; killed at least four people by poisoning in the 1880s in order to obtain insurance money.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/liverpool-news/liverpool-murders/2010/01/07/mersey-murders-black-widows-margaret-higgins-and-catherine-flannagan-100252-25541424/ |title=Liverpool Murder Most Foul: Day 4: Black widows Margaret Higgins and Catherine Flannagan |first=Ben |last=Rossington |date=7 January 2010 |newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]] |accessdate=7 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Steven Grieveson]]: also known as \"The Sunderland Strangler\"; murdered four teenage boys in [[City of Sunderland|Sunderland]], [[Tyne and Wear]] between 1990 and 1994.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/gay-serial-killer-is-given-three-life-sentences-1321584.html |title=Gay serial killer is given three life sentences |date=29 February 1996 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bradford murders|Stephen Griffiths]]: also known as the \"Crossbow Cannibal\"; convicted of murdering three prostitutes in [[Bradford]] in 2009 and 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/may/27/bradford-murders-timeline |title=Bradford murders timeline |date=27 May 2010 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London, UK |accessdate=11 June 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Allan Grimson]]: [[Royal Navy]] petty officer convicted of two murders from 1997 to 1998; suspected of murdering up to twenty people across the UK, [[Gibraltar]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/police-search-gibraltar-for-sailor-missing-since-1986-109945.html |title=Police search Gibraltar for sailor missing since 1986 |last1=Bennetto |first1=Jason |date=23 June 2003 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=22 February 2017}}</ref>\n*[[John Haigh]]: also known as the \"Acid Bath Murderer\" and the \"Vampire of London\"; active in England during the 1940s; convicted of six murders, but claimed to have killed nine; executed in 1949.<ref>{{Cite journal |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_go1613/is_4_15/ai_n29310480/ |last=Ramsland |first=K. |title=John George Haigh: a malingerer's legacy |journal=The Forensic Examiner |volume=15 |issue=4 |year=2006 |via=[[FindArticles]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120629235153/findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_go1613/is_4_15/ai_n29310480/ |archive-date=29 June 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Anthony Hardy]]: also known as the \"[[Camden Town|Camden]] Ripper\"; convicted of three murders; suspected of at least four.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/may/14/camden-ripper-never-released-judge |title=Camden Ripper must never be released, judge rules |date=14 May 2010 |agency=Press Association |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=25 June 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Trevor Hardy]]: also known as \"The Beast of Manchester\"; killed three teenage girls in [[Manchester]] from 1974 to 1976.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/s/1053972_serial_killer_will_die_in_jail |title=Serial killer will die in jail |first=Chris |last=Osuh |date=13 June 2008 |newspaper=[[Manchester Evening News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Philip Herbert, 7th Earl of Pembroke|Philip Herbert]]: also known as the \"Infamous Earl of Pembroke\"; 17th century nobleman convicted of manslaughter but discharged; later killed the prosecutor and pardoned for a third murder.<ref>{{cite book |chapterurl=http://www.exclassics.com/newgate/ng37.htm |chapter=Philip, Earl of Pembroke and Montgomery, Tried for the Murder of Nathaniel Cony by his Brother Peers in 1678 and found guilty of Manslaughter later |editor1-first=J.L. |editor1-last=Rayner |editor2-first=G.T |editor2-last=Crook |date=1926 |title=The Complete Newgate Calendar |location=London, UK |publisher=Navarre Society |via=Ex-Classics.com |access-date=24 November 2019|title-link=The Newgate Calendar }}</ref>\n*[[Colin Ireland]]: also known as \"The Gay Slayer\"; killed five gay men in London in the early 1990s; died in prison in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.crimeandinvestigation.co.uk/crime-files/colin-ireland |title=Colin Ireland |date=June 30, 2017 |website=Crime + Investigation |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><!-- NOTE: Jack the Ripper is listed in the \"Unidentified serial killers\" section. Please do not add him to this section. -->\n*[[Theodore Johnson (serial killer)|Theodore Johnson]]: [[Jamaica]]n immigrant who murdered his wife and two girlfriends from 1981 to 2016; sentenced to 26 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/jan/05/man-theodore-johnson-on-conditional-release-who-killed-partner-lied-to-authorities-about-relationship |title=Killer on conditional release who murdered partner given life sentence |first=Jamie |last=Grierson |date=5 January 2018 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bruce George Peter Lee]]: serial killer and arsonist responsible for 26 deaths in the town of [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]] from 1973 to 1979.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://infotrac.galegroup.com/itw/infomark/531/644/115751697w16/purl=&dyn=11!pdy_3_0FFO-1981-JAN21-003-F?sw_aep=corlonli |title=Special hospital for young man who admitted killing 26 people and ten charges of arson |date=21 January 1984 |newspaper=The Times |page=3 |accessdate=7 July 2010}} ''(Library card access)''</ref>\n*[[Robin Ligus]]: drug addict convicted of robbing and bludgeoning three men to death with an iron bar in [[Shropshire]] in 1994.\n*[[Michael Lupo]]: also known as \"The Wolf Man\"; Italian-born man convicted of the murders of four men and two attempted murders in London in the 1980s; died in prison in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/serial-killer-with-hiv-virus-dies-in-jail-1573604.html |title=Serial killer with HIV virus dies in jail |last=Bennetto |first=Jason |date=18 February 1995 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Mackay]]: charged with the murders of five individuals in London and [[Kent]], convicted of three; confessed to killing eleven people from 1974 to 1975.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/mass/patrick_mackay/2.html |title=Patrick Mackay, psychopathic repeat killer |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |website=[[Crime Library]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080401002015/http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/mass/patrick_mackay/2.html |archive-date=1 April 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Maudsley]]: also known as \"Hannibal The Cannibal\"; killer of four; killed three in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2003/apr/27/ukcrime |title=The caged misery of Britain's real 'Hannibal the Cannibal' |last1=Thompson |first1=Tony |date=27 April 2003 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/tragic-life-led-hannibal-killings-3554260 |title=Tragic life that led to Hannibal killings |last=Shennan |first=Paddy |date=7 May 2003 |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Cannock Chase murders|Raymond Morris]]: also known as the \"[[A34 road|A34]] Killer\"; convicted of one murder, considered to have committed at least two more.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://static.expressandstar.com/millennium/1900/1950-1975/1969.html |title=Chase killer jailed for life |date=16 November 1968 |newspaper=[[Express & Star]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Hicks Murray]]: bigamist who murdered his first wife and three children, and then killed himself in a [[murder-suicide]] in 1912; posthumously connected to the killings of at least seven previous wives.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042373/1912-09-11/ed-1/seq-1/#date1=1789&sort=date&rows=20&words=Hicks+Murray+Robert&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=12&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=Robert+Hicks+Murray&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1 |title=Tragedy Reveals Modern Bluebeard Who Had Murdered Seven Wives |date=September 11, 1912 |page=1 |volume=7 |number=216 |newspaper=The Evening Times |location=[[Grand Forks]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Chronicling America}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Napper]]: also known as the \"[[South East London Green Chain|Green Chain]] Rapist\"; killed two women and a child in the 1990s.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/inside-the-mind-of-robert-napper-jlfxmbf7wr7 |title=Inside the mind of Robert Napper |first1=Sean |last1=O'Neill |first2=Adam |last2=Fresco |date=18 December 2008 |newspaper=The Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Donald Neilson]]: also known as the \"Black Panther\"; killed four people, including heiress [[Murder of Lesley Whittle|Lesley Whittle]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/black-panther-donald-neilsons-trail-8464470 |title=Black Panther Donald Neilson's trail of Terror and Murder of Lesley Whittle 40 Years ago Remembered by Top Cop |first=Mike |last=Lockley |date=17 January 2015 |newspaper=The Birmingham Mail |access-date=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Dennis Nilsen]]: also known as \"The [[Muswell Hill]] Murderer\"; killer of fifteen (possibly 16) men between 1978 and 1983 in North London.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nilsen given 25-year sentence |first=David |last=Nicholson |newspaper=[[The Times]] |location=London, UK |date=5 November 1983 |page=1 |issue=61682}}</ref>\n*[[Colin Norris]]: nurse convicted of killing four patients in [[Leeds]] hospitals between 2001 and 2002.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-15068743 |title=Colin Norris case: Murder convictions 'unsafe' |date=4 October 2011 |website=BBC News |accessdate=19 October 2011}}</ref>\n*[[William Palmer (murderer)|William Palmer]]: also known as \"Palmer the Poisoner\"; doctor suspected of numerous murders, convicted of one; hanged in 1856.<ref>{{cite book |title=Old Lamps For New Ones, And Other Sketches and Essays Hitherto Uncollected |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/oldlampsfornewon00dick#page/268/mode/2up |chapter=The Demeanor of Murderers |first=Charles |last=Dickens |author-link=Charles Dickens |year=1897 |page=269 |location=New York |publisher=New Amsterdam Book Company |accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Stephen Port]]: drugged, raped and murdered four men in [[Barking, London|Barking]], London between 2014 and 2015; convicted in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-38077859 |title=Stephen Port: Serial killer guilty of murdering four men |date=23 November 2016 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Elizabeth Ridgeway]]: poisoned her husband in 1684; after arrest, confessed to poisoning three more people starting from 1681; executed 1684.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A52275.0001.001/1:4?rgn=div1;view=fulltext |title=The penitent recognition of Joseph's brethren: a sermon occasion'd by Elizabeth Ridgeway, who for the petit treason of poysoning her husband, was, on March 24, 1683/4, according to the sentence of the Right Honourable Sir Thomas Street ... burnt at Leicester ... : to which is prefixed a full relation of the womans fact, tryal, carriage, and death |last=Newton |first=John |publisher=Printed for Richard Chiswel |year=1684 |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=University of Michigan University Library}}</ref>\n*[[Amelia Sach and Annie Walters]]: known as \"The [[East Finchley|Finchley]] Baby Farmers\"; baby farmers who used [[chlorodyne]] to poison an unknown number of infants; both hanged at the [[HM Prison Holloway]] in 1903.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1394309/Baby-killer-Amelia-Sach-Penninah-Ashers-family-Researching-background-popular--past-hide-horrific-secrets.html |title=The baby killer in my family: Researching your background has never been so popular... but the past can hide horrific secrets |first=Penninah |last=Asher |date=5 June 2011 |newspaper=Daily Mail |accessdate=14 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Harold Shipman]]: also known as \"Dr. Death\"; doctor convicted of fifteen murders; a later inquiry stated he had killed at least 215 and possibly up to 457 people over a 25-year period; committed suicide in 2004 in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/3391897.stm |title=Harold Shipman: The killer doctor |date=13 January 2004 |website=BBC News |accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>\n*[[George Joseph Smith]]: also known as \"The Brides in the Bath\" killer who murdered three women.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kentlive.news/news/kent-news/george-joseph-smith-notorious-brides-1219108 |title=George Joseph Smith and the notorious 'Brides in the Bath' murders |first=Adam |last=John |date=17 February 2018 |newspaper=[[Kent and Sussex Courier]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Rebecca Smith (infanticide)|Rebecca Smith]]: poisoned her infant son with arsenic in 1849, later confessing to doing the same to seven of her other children; executed 1849.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.academia.edu/9671973 |title=Religion, Community and the Infanticidal Mother: Evidence from 1840s Rural Wiltshire |first1=Katherine D. |last1=Watson |date=November 2008 |journal=Family & Community History |volume=11 |issue=2 |page=119 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[John Straffen]]: murdered three children between 1951 and 1952; Britain's longest-serving prisoner until his death in 2007.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2007/nov/19/ukcrime.prisonsandprobation |title=Longest-serving UK prisoner dies, aged 77 |first=Allegra |last=Stratton |date=19 November 2007 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Sutcliffe]]: also known as the \"[[Yorkshire]] Ripper\"; convicted in 1981 of murdering thirteen women and attacking seven more from 1975 to 1980.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/sutcliffe/mask_1.html |title=A Killer's Mask |first=Fiona |last=Steel |website=TruTV.com |accessdate=29 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090321003633/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/sutcliffe/mask_1.html |archivedate=21 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Griffiths Wainewright]]: artist considered to have poisoned four people.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Wainewright, Thomas Griffiths (1794\u20131847) |chapter-url=http://www.adb.online.anu.edu.au/biogs/A020509b.htm |first=V. W. |last=Hodgman |title=Australian Dictionary of Biography, Volume 2 |publisher=[[Melbourne University Press|MUP]] |year=1967 |pages=558\u2013559 |accessdate=2007-09-28|title-link=Australian Dictionary of Biography }}</ref>\n*[[Margaret Waters]]: baby farmer from [[Brixton]] who drugged and starved the infants in her care; believed to have killed at least nineteen children; executed on 11 October 1870.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA428 |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |publisher=Infobase Publishing |year=2006 |page=428 |isbn=978-0-81606-987-3 |accessdate=2012-06-20}}</ref>\n*[[Fred West]] and [[Rosemary West]]: also known as the \"House of Horrors\" murderers; she was convicted of ten murders; both are believed to have tortured and murdered at least twelve young women between 1967 and 1987, many at their home in [[Gloucester]]; he committed suicide in 1995 while awaiting trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eveyo.com/stories/world-news/54357-she-cut-heather-up-and-put-her-in-a-dustbin-our-daughter-in-a-dustbin-the-chilling-confession-of-serial-killer-fred-west-about-his-16-year-old-daughter-s-murder-to-be-heard-in-new-television-documenta.html |title=The Chilling Confession of Serial Killer Fred West about His 16-year-old Daughter's Murder to be Heard in New Television Documentary |first=Paul |last=Donnelley |date=2014-04-04 |website=Eveyo.com |accessdate=2018-03-14 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314110331/https://www.eveyo.com/stories/world-news/54357-she-cut-heather-up-and-put-her-in-a-dustbin-our-daughter-in-a-dustbin-the-chilling-confession-of-serial-killer-fred-west-about-his-16-year-old-daughter-s-murder-to-be-heard-in-new-television-documenta.html |archive-date=2018-03-14}}</ref>\n*[[Ada Williams (baby farmer)|Ada Williams]]: 19th-century baby farmer who strangled an infant in September 1899; suspected of more murders; executed 1900.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19000113.2.58.9 |title=Babies Slaughtered |date=13 January 1900 |newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=XXXVII |issue=11270 |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[Papers Past]]}}</ref>\n*[[Catherine Wilson]]: nurse considered to have poisoned seven people in the 19th century; executed in 1862.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.sonofthesouth.net/leefoundation/civil-war/1862/november/execution-catharine-wilson.htm |title=The Gallows |magazine=[[Harper's Weekly]] |date=22 November 1862 |page=743 |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Son of the South.net}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Elizabeth Wilson]]: also known as the \"Merry Widow of [[Windy Nook]]\"; convicted of murdering two husbands by poisoning and considered to have killed two others.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/history/dark-angel-look-another-north-12103801 |title=Dark Angel: We look at another North East woman serial killer - The Merry Widow of Windy Nook Case bears similarities to Dark Angel killer Mary Ann Cotton |first=Ian |last=Robson |date=31 October 2016 |newspaper=[[Evening Chronicle]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Steve Wright (serial killer)|Steve Wright]]: also known as \"The Suffolk Strangler\"; [[Ipswich 2006 serial murders|killed five women]] in six weeks around [[Ipswich]] in late 2006; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1579403/Steve-Wright-A-real-Jekyll-and-Hyde.html |title=Steve Wright: A real Jekyll and Hyde |last=Allen |first=Nick |date=21 February 2008 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London, UK |accessdate=27 September 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Graham Young]]: also known as \"The Teacup Poisoner\"; killed three people from 1962 to 1971; died in prison in 1990.<ref>{{cite book |last=Lane |first=Brian |date=1993 |title=The Murder Guide: 100 Extraordinary, Bizarre and Gruesome Murders |location=London, UK |publisher=Robinson |page=191 |isbn=1-85487-083-1}}</ref>\n\n====Northern Ireland====\n*[[Shankill Butchers]]: The Shankill Butchers was an Ulster loyalist gang\u2014many of whom were members of the [[Ulster Volunteer Force]] (UVF)\u2014that was active between 1975 and 1982 in Belfast, Northern Ireland. The gang was based in the Shankill area and were responsible for the deaths of at least twenty-three people, most of whom were [[Irish Catholic]]s killed in sectarian attacks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.politics.ie/history/18916-sectarianism-racism-one-same.html |title=Sectarianism \u2013 Racism \u2013 One and the Same? |author=Conuil |date=July 2007 |website=Politics.ie |access-date=21 December 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609160824/http://www.politics.ie/history/18916-sectarianism-racism-one-same.html |archive-date=2011-06-09}}</ref>\n\n====Scotland====\n*[[Robert Black (serial killer)|Robert Black]]: schoolgirl killer; convicted of four murders in [[Northern Ireland]], [[England]], and [[Scotland]] between 1981 and 1986, suspected of many more; died in prison in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/magazinearticle/death-of-a-serial-killer-robert-blacks-timeline-of-terror/ |title=Death of A Serial Killer \u2013 Robert Black's Timeline Of Terror |date=April 2016 |website=True Crime Library |accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-35296135 |title=Robert Black: Convicted child killer dies in prison |date=12 January 2016 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Burke and Hare murders|William Burke and William Hare]]: notorious [[body snatcher]]s in [[Edinburgh]] in the 19th century.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofScotland/Burke-Hare-infamous-murderers-graverobbers/ |title=The Story of Burke and Hare |first=Ben |last=Johnson |website=Historic UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Archibald Hall]]: also known as the \"Monster Butler\"; killed five in the 1970s, three with accomplice Michael Kitto.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/nostalgia/crimelibrary/archibaldthomsonhall/themurderousbutler/ |title=The Murderous Butler: Archibald Thomson Hall, alias Roy Fontaine |newspaper=[[Watford Observer]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Manuel]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Birkenshaw, North Lanarkshire|Birkenshaw]]\"; American-born murderer of seven, suspected of killing 15; executed in 1958.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Dv6G7xTW0FUC&pg=PT25&lpg=PT25&dq=capelrig+Anne+Kneilands#v=onepage&q=capelrig%20Anne%20Kneilands |first1=Hector |last1=MacLeod |first2=Malcolm |last2=McLeod |title=Peter Manuel, Serial Killer |date=2010 |edition=ebook |publisher=Mainstream Publishing |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-1-84596-883-0}}</ref>\n*[[Edward William Pritchard]]: English doctor who poisoned his wife and her mother in [[Glasgow]] in 1865; two years earlier their maid had died in a mysterious fire.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://heritage.scotsman.com/notoriouscriminalsfeatureseries/A-deadly-bedside-manner.2680240.jp |title=A deadly beside manner |first=Leighton |last=Bruce |date=21 November 2005 |newspaper=[[The Scotsman]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307062517/http://heritage.scotsman.com/notoriouscriminalsfeatureseries/A-deadly-bedside-manner.2680240.jp |archive-date=7 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[World's End Murders|Angus Sinclair]]: convicted of the murders of four young women, including the \"World's End Murders\" in [[Edinburgh]], believed to have murdered eight; died in prison in 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1309040/Child-killer-gets-life-for-1978-death-of-teenager.html |title=Child killer gets life for 1978 death of teenager |first=Tara |last=Womersley |date=14 June 2001 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London, UK |accessdate=5 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Tobin]]: rapist and killer of three women in Scotland and England between 1991 and 2006; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8132283.stm |title=Piecing together serial killer Peter Tobin's past |first=Mario |last=Cacciottolo |date=16 December 2009 |website=BBC News |access-date=9 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Wales====\n*[[John Cooper (serial killer)|John Cooper]]: also known as \"The Wildman\" and \"The Bullseye Killer\"; [[Pembrokeshire]] burglar responsible for the robbery and shotgun double-murders of a brother and sister in 1985 and a couple in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/the-moment-bullseye-revealed-killer-6025096 |title='The moment Bullseye revealed the killer': How shotgun killer John Cooper was caught |last=McCarthy |first=James |date=16 September 2013 |website=[[Wales Online]] |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Moore (serial killer)|Peter Moore]]: also known as \"The Man in Black\"; businessman who killed four men at random in [[North Wales]] in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.flintshirechronicle.co.uk/flintshire-news/local-flintshire-news//tm_headline=flintshire-murderer-peter-moore-in-european-court-of-human-rights-appeal-over-life-sentence%26method=full%26objectid=28267583%26siteid=51352-name_page.html |title=Flintshire murderer Peter Moore in European Court of Human Rights appeal over life sentence |first=Eleanor |last=Barlow |date=3 March 2011 |newspaper=[[Flintshire Chronicle]] |accessdate=13 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720013139/http://www.flintshirechronicle.co.uk/flintshire-news/local-flintshire-news//tm_headline=flintshire-murderer-peter-moore-in-european-court-of-human-rights-appeal-over-life-sentence%26method=full%26objectid=28267583%26siteid=51352-name_page.html |archive-date=20 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n===United States===\n{{main|List of serial killers in the United States}}\n\n===Uruguay===\n*[[Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez]]: Spanish-born murderer who killed tennis player [[Patricia Miller (tennis)|Patricia Miller]]'s half-sister and two other women; freed in 2016 but was arrested in 2017 in [[Paraguay]] for carrying an unregistered weapon and a quantity of cocaine.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.teledoce.com/telemundo/nacionales/pablo-goncalvez-en-libertad-salio-de-campanero-a-las-2357-del-jueves/ |title=Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez en libertad: sali\u00f3 de Campanero a las 23:57 del jueves 23 de junio |trans-title=Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez released: he left Campanero at 23:57 on Thursday, June 23 |date=24 June 2016 |website=[[Teledoce]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=23 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elpais.com.uy/informacion/paraguay-analiza-expulsion-goncalvez.html |title=Paraguay analiza la expulsi\u00f3n de Gonc\u00e1lvez |trans-title=Paraguay analyzes the expulsion of Gonc\u00e1lvez |date=27 June 2017 |newspaper=[[El Pa\u00eds (Uruguay)|El Pa\u00eds]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/bonomi-paraguay-pidio-informacion-pablo-goncalvez-n1089872\n|title=Bonomi: \"Paraguay pidi\u00f3 informacion\" sobre Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez |trans-title=Bonomi: \"Paraguay asked for information\" about Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez |date=26 June 2017 |newspaper=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.subrayado.com.uy/noticias/68137/la-historia-de-pablo-goncalvez-ahora-preso-en-paraguay |title=La historia de Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez, ahora preso en Paraguay |trans-title=The story of Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez, now imprisoned in Paraguay |date=25 June 2017 |website=[[Channel 10 (Uruguay)|Subrayado]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Uzbekistan===\n*[[Polatbay Berdaliyev]]: raped, murdered and robbed a total of eleven women in Uzbekistan and neighboring [[Kazakhstan]] with accomplice Abduseit Ormanov between 2011 and 2012; both sentenced to life imprisonment in both countries.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.kazpravda.kz/articles/view/taksi-na-tot-svet |title=\u0422\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u0442 \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0442 |trans-title=Taxi to the next world |first=Irina |last=Orlova |date=19 October 2018 |newspaper=[[Kazakhskaya Pravda]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Venezuela===\n*[[Dor\u00e1ngel Vargas]]: killed and cannibalized at least ten men between 1997 and 1999 in [[San Crist\u00f3bal, T\u00e1chira]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.absurddiari.com/s/llegir.php?llegir=llegir&ref=5673 |title=El can\u00edbal de los Andes confiesa: \"Comer gente es como comer peras\" |trans-title=The cannibal of the Andes confesses: 'Eating people is like eating pears' |date=19 November 2004 |website=L'absurd Diari |language=es |accessdate=10 September 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Yemen===\n*[[Abdallah al-Hubal]]: killed seven people in 1990 after the Yemeni reunion; fled prison and killed a young couple and three other people in 1998; killed in a shootout with the police.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tueursenserie.org/article.php?id_article=30 |title=Al-Hubal, Abdallah |first=Emily |last=Tibbatts |website=Tueurs en Serie.org |language=fr |access-date=2007-10-22 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120915095812/http://www.tueursenserie.org/article.php?id_article=30 |archive-date=2012-09-15}}</ref>\n*[[Mohammed Adam Omar]]: known as \"The Sana'a Ripper\"; [[Sudan]]ese morgue assistant who killed between two and 51 women across Yemen and other countries from 1975 to 1999; guilt has been questioned; executed 2001.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/14/world/sana-journal-a-fittingly-gory-finale-to-a-sordid-murder-case.html |title=Sana Journal; A Fittingly Gory Finale To a Sordid Murder Case |first=John F. |last=Burns |date=August 14, 2001 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191013081509/https://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/14/world/sana-journal-a-fittingly-gory-finale-to-a-sordid-murder-case.html |archive-date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Dhu Shanatir]]: 5th-century Yemeni (formerly Himyarite) serial killer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.paperstreetprod.com/compendium/archives/text/5intothe.txt |title=Into the Abyss |last=Horberg |first=Karl |date=8 May 1997 |website=Paper Street Productions |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050426080712/http://www.paperstreetprod.com/compendium/archives/text/5intothe.txt |archivedate=April 26, 2005}}</ref>\n\n===Zambia===\n*[[Mailoni Brothers]]: three brothers who killed at least twelve people from 2007 to 2013 in [[Central Province, Zambia|Central Province]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201306300093.html |title=Zambia: Mailoni Brothers - History of Serial Killers in Zambia |last=Kaluba |first=Austin |date=29 June 2013 |website=[[AllAfrica.com]] |accessdate=2014-04-15 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402135713/http://allafrica.com/stories/201306300093.html |archive-date=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Zimbabwe===\n*[[Richard McGown]]: also known as \"Dr. Death\"; Scottish doctor responsible for administering fatal doses of morphine to at least five patients in [[Harare]] from 1986 to 1992; convicted of two counts of [[culpable homicide]] and sentenced to a year in prison, after which he was released and returned to the UK.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/race-trial-doctor-guilty-of-homicide-1567492.html |title='Race-trial' doctor guilty of homicide |first=Angus |last=Shaw |date=11 January 1995 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Unidentified serial killers==\nThis is a list of unidentified serial killers. It includes circumstances where a suspect has been arrested, but not convicted.\n\n===Australia===\n*[[Bowraville Murders]]: murders of three [[Indigenous Australians|Aboriginal]] children in 1990 and 1991.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Truth be Told (transcript) |url=http://www.abc.net.au/austory/content/2006/s1733527.htm |access-date=24 November 2019 |series=Australian Story |series-link=Australian Story |first=Caroline |last=Jones |network=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |station=[[ABC Television]] |date=4 September 2006 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701073359/http://www.abc.net.au/austory/content/2006/s1733527.htm |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2004/02/07/1075854109819.html |title=Lone cop to tell inquest name of killer suspect |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=February 8, 2004 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Ghosts of Bowraville (transcript) |url=http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?http%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Frn%2Ftalks%2Fbbing%2Fstories%2Fs10587.htm |access-date=2019-02-21 |series=Background Briefing |first=Chris |last=Bullock |network=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |station=[[ABC Radio National]] |date=20 July 1997 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101001011/http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?http%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Frn%2Ftalks%2Fbbing%2Fstories%2Fs10587.htm |archive-date=2017-01-01}}</ref>\n*[[Claremont serial killings]]: murders of two young women and the disappearance of a third in 1996 and 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-02-22/bradley-edwards-charged-with-sarah-spiers-murder/9475258 |title=Claremont serial killings: Sarah Spiers murder charge for Bradley Robert Edwards |date=23 February 2018 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=27 February 2018}}</ref>\n*[[The Family Murders]]: murder and mutilation of five young men and boys from 1979 to 1983. [[Bevan Spencer von Einem]] was convicted of one murder.<ref>{{cite episode |title=The Butchered Boys |series=Crime Investigation Australia |series-link=Crime Investigation Australia |network=[[Crime & Investigation Network]] |series-no=1 |number=16}}</ref>\n*[[Tynong North and Frankston Murders]]: murders of six females in [[Tynong North, Victoria|Tynong North]] and Frankston in 1980 and 1981.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/retired-detectives-back-in-the-hunt-20051121-ge1a2c.html |title=Retired detectives back in the hunt |last=Silvester |first=John |date=2005-11-21 |newspaper=The Age |access-date=2018-09-14}}</ref>\n\n===Belgium===\n*[[Brabant killers]]: gang of serial killers who operated in the [[Brabant (province)|Brabant]] province from 1982 until 1985; murdered 28 people and injured 40.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.vice.com/article/police-are-running-out-of-time-to-catch-the-crazy-brabant-killers |title=Police Are Running Out of Time to Catch the 'Crazy Brabant Killers' |last=Dall'Armellina |first=Virgile |date=24 October 2014 |website=Vice.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*The [[Butcher of Mons]]: unidentified serial killer who committed five murders from January 1996 to July 1997 in [[Mons]]. Montenegrin murderer [[Smail Tulja]] is suspected of being the Butcher.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/08/magazine/hunt-for-a-serial-killer.html |title=On the Trail of an Intercontinental Killer |last=Schmidle |first=Nicholas |date=5 January 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Brazil===\n*[[Paturis Park murders]]: also known as the \"Rainbow Maniac\"; series of thirteen gunshot murders of gay men between July 2007 and August 2008 in Paturis Park in [[Carapicuiba]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2008/12/10/2442827.htm |title=Police hunt suspected serial killer in Brazil |last=Olle |first=Nick |authorlink=Nick Olle |date=10 December 2008 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |access-date=5 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Canada===\n*[[Highway of Tears murders|Highway of Tears]]: death and disappearance of around 40 young women in [[British Columbia]] since 1969.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/archives/entry/bcs-infamous-highway-of-tears |title=BC's infamous 'Highway of Tears' |last=Lee |first=Miyoung |date=November 17, 2009 |website=CBC Digital Archives |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] |accessdate=10 December 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Toronto hospital baby deaths]]: deaths of at least eight babies at Toronto's Hospital for Sick Children in 1980 and 1981 were initially alleged to be [[digoxin]] poisonings, a theory which was cast into doubt by new evidence in 2010-2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2011/03/06/dead-babies-remain-a-mystery |title=Dead babies remain a mystery |agency=[[QMI Agency]] |date=March 6, 2011 |newspaper=[[St. Catharines Standard]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225035344/http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2011/03/06/dead-babies-remain-a-mystery |archive-date=2017-12-25}}</ref>\n\n===Costa Rica===\n*[[El Psic\u00f3pata]]: killed nineteen people from 1986 to 1996 in [[Cartago, Costa Rica|Cartago]], [[Curridabat]] and [[Desamparados]]; suspected of other similar crimes.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.diarioextra.com/2001/febrero/13/sucesos03.html |title=De Jack el Destripador de Londres al Destripador de San Jos\u00e9 |trans-title=From Jack the Ripper of London to the Ripper of San Jos\u00e9 |last=Araya |first=Hugo |date=February 13, 2001 |newspaper=[[Diario Extra (Costa Rica)|Diario Extra]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101121031159/http://www.diarioextra.com/2001/febrero/13/sucesos03.html |archive-date=2010-11-21}}</ref>\n\n===Finland===\n*[[Murder of Susanne Lindholm#Serial killer theory|Helsinki cellar killer]]: suspected of raping and strangling three women in Helsinki cellars between 1979 and 1981, including Susanne Lindholm; the validity of this theory has been disputed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000000964453.html|title=Who killed them? 'The old thing can be reopened'|last=|first=|date=July 20, 2015|website=Ilta-Sanomat|language=fi-FI|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=August 25, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Hausj\u00e4rvi Gravel Pit Murders|J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4 Serial Killer]]: responsible for the so-called \"[[Hausj\u00e4rvi]] [[Gravel Pit]] Murders\"; killed a woman in 1991 and suspected in the disappearance of another in 1993; possibly responsible for other abductions and murders in the late 20th century.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://keski-uusimaa.fi/Uutiset/Arkisto/2008/07/15/Jarvenpaan-sarjamurhaaja-yrittanyt-ehka-uusia-tekonsa2 |title=Jarvenpaan sarjamurhaaja yrittanyt ehka uusia tekonsa |trans-title=J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4's serial killer perhaps tried new things |first=Malin |last=Jarkko |date=15 July 2008 |newspaper=[[Uusimaa (newspaper)|Uusimaa]] |language=fi |accessdate=22 April 2014}}{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Germany===\n{{Main|List of German serial killers}}\n\n===India===\n*Beer Man: murdered seven people in south [[Mumbai]] between October 2006 and January 2007.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/beer-man-acquitted-in-second-murder-case-too/story-yG21TyRav3e80e9SlETFlM.html |title='Beer Man' acquitted in second murder case too |last=Iyer |first=Vignesh |date=July 12, 2008 |newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=May 23, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Stoneman]]: responsible for thirteen murders in [[Kolkata]] in 1989.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/the-elusive-stoneman-of-kolkata/story-BQBcCHfk87WvoLp2LSCKRN.html |title=The elusive stoneman of Kolkata |first=Ritujay |last=Ghosh |date=December 30, 2006 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Italy===\n*[[Monster of Florence]]: committed eight murders of couples in a series of sixteen between 1968 and 1985. Giancarlo Lotti and Mario Vanni were convicted of four of the murders, but this conviction has been widely criticized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/predators/monster_florence/10.html |title=The Monster of Florence |first=David |last=Lohr |authorlink=David Lohr |website=[[Crime Library]] |page=10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403090508/http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/predators/monster_florence/10.html |archivedate=2014-04-03}}</ref>\n*[[Monster of Udine]]: killed at least four victims in the [[Province of Udine]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://messaggeroveneto.gelocal.it/udine/cronaca/2012/01/27/news/in-un-ventennio-14-omicidi-e-3-arresti-1.3113223 |title=In un ventennio 14 omicidi e 3 arresti |trans-title=In twenty years, 14 murders and 3 arrests |date=27 January 2012 |newspaper=[[Messaggero Veneto \u2013 Giornale del Friuli]] |language=it |accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Japan===\n*[[Paraquat murders]]: series of indiscriminate poisonings carried out in Japan in 1985 where twelve people were killed.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/12/10/world/japanese-puzzle-the-vending-machine-murders.html |title=Japanese Puzzle: The Vending Machine Murders |last1=Haberman |first1=Clyde |date=December 10, 1985 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Wednesday Strangler]]: killed 7 children and women in [[Saga Prefecture]] between 1975 and 1989, most of them on Wednesdays; a suspect was indicted for three of the murders, but later acquitted.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20071011104304/http://www.nishinippon.co.jp/news/wordbox/display/4796/ Kitamachi consecutive female murder case (West Japan Newspaper WORDBOX)]</ref>\n\n===Mexico===\n*[[Female homicides in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]]: also known as \"The dead women of Ju\u00e1rez\"; the violent deaths of hundreds of women since 1993 in the northern Mexican city of [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Violencia Femicida : Violence Against Women and Mexico's Structural Crisis |last=Olivera |first=Mercedes |journal=[[Latin American Perspectives]] |date=March 1, 2006 |volume=33 |issue=104 |pages=104\u2013114 |doi=10.1177/0094582X05286092|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/24615d971dc35c9dd58cfc0884cf7de0ea8f5029 }}</ref>\n\n===Namibia===\n*[[B1 Butcher]]: murdered at least five women between 2005 and 2007, with all murders related to the [[B1 road (Namibia)|National Road B1]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.namibian.com.na/40811/archive-read/B-1-Butcher-DNA-evidence-in-spotlight-REPORTS |title=B-1 Butcher: DNA evidence in spotlight |last=Menges |first=Werner |date=29 April 2008 |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Nicaragua===\n*[[San Juan del Sur Psychopath]]: murdered between two and ten men in the coastal town of [[San Juan del Sur]], from 2000 to 2002; a German [[alien (law)|illegal alien]] residing in [[Managua]] was arrested on suspicion, but later cleared of the murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2002/03/10/nacionales/829404-misterio-ronda-crmenes-de-san-juan-del-sur |title=Misterio ronda cr\u00edmenes de San Juan del Sur |trans-title=Mystery around crimes of San Juan del Sur |first=Noelia |last=S\u00e1nchez |date=March 10, 2002 |newspaper=[[La Prensa (Managua)|La Prensa]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Poland===\n*[[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a Gay Murderer]]: murdered seven homosexual men from 1988 to 1993 in \u0141\u00f3d\u017a.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://lodz.wyborcza.pl/lodz/1,35136,7956685,_Zdarzylo_sie_w_Lodzi___Mordowal_gejow_na_Fabrycznym.html |title=\"Zdarzy\u0142o si\u0119 w \u0141odzi\": Mordowa\u0142 gej\u00f3w na Fabrycznym |trans-title=\"It happened in \u0141\u00f3d\u017a\": He murdered gays on Fabryczny |first1=Marcin |last1=Mas\u0142owski |first2=Agnieszka |last2=Urazi\u0144ska |first3=Jerzy |last3=Walczyk |lastauthoramp=yes |date=May 31, 2010 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Wyborcza]] |language=pl |accessdate=15 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Portugal===\n*[[Lisbon Ripper]]: murdered three women in [[Lisbon]] between 1992 and 1993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/coldcases/lisbon.html |title=Unsolved Serial Killings; Portugal, Lisbon |date=October 27, 2009 |website=Serial Killer A-Z |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091027121656/http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/coldcases/lisbon.html |archive-date=2009-10-27}}</ref>\n\n===Russia===\n{{Main|List of Russian serial killers}}\n\n===South Africa===\n*[[Sleepy Hollow Killer]]: thought to be responsible for the murders of at least thirteen women in the late 1990s, including three more in 2007, around [[Pietermaritzburg]] and the surrounding area.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-in-pietermaritzburg-report-387211 |title=Serial killer in Pietermaritzburg: report |date=28 January 2008 |website=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===United Kingdom===\n*[[Bible John]]: thought to be responsible for the deaths of three women in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], in the late 1960s.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=v-NAAAAAIBAJ&sjid=3KYMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3021%2C2603615 |title=A Kiss Before Dying: 20 years on, the mystery of Bible John still haunts a city |last=Skelton |first=Douglas |date=10 February 1989 |newspaper=[[Evening Times]] |accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Jack the Ripper]]: murdered prostitutes in the East End of London in 1888.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.met.police.uk/history/ripper.htm |title=The Enduring Mystery of Jack the Ripper |website=[[Metropolitan Police]] |accessdate=31 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100204014147/http://www.met.police.uk/history/ripper.htm |archivedate=4 February 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Jack the Stripper]]: responsible for the London \"[[Hammersmith]] nude murders\" between 1964 and 1965.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/lifestyle/nostalgia/retro-mystery-jack-stripper-murders-5978691 |title=Retro: The mystery of the Jack the Stripper murders |first=James |last=Gates |date=12 March 2012 |work=[[Trinity Mirror|Get West London]] |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411025947/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/lifestyle/nostalgia/retro-mystery-jack-stripper-murders-5978691 |archive-date=April 11, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Thames Torso Murders|Thames Torso Murderer]]: thought to be responsible for the murder and dismemberment of four women in London between 1887 and 1889.<ref>{{cite book |first=R. Michael |last=Gordon |title=The Thames Torso Murders of Victorian London |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cbCzCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA1 |date=3 October 2015 |publisher=McFarland |location=London, UK |isbn=978-1-4766-1665-0}}</ref>\n\n===United States===\n{{main|List of serial killers in the United States}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of non-state terrorist incidents]] (includes Unabomber, [[Theodore Kaczynski]])\n*[[List of serial killers before 1900]]\n*[[List of serial killers by number of victims]]\n*[[Mass murder]]\n*[[Spree killer]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Active editnotice}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Serial Killers By Country}}\n[[Category:Death-related lists|serial killers]]\n[[Category:Lists of murderers|serial country]]\n[[Category:Serial killers by nationality]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\nThis is a list of '''notable [[serial killer]]s, by the country''' where most of the killings occurred.\n{{TOC right}}\n\n==Convicted serial killers by country==\n===Afghanistan===\n*[[Abdullah Shah]]: killed at least twenty travelers on the road from [[Kabul]] to [[Jalalabad]] serving under [[Zardad Khan]]; also killed his wife; executed on 20 April 2004.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/3662935.stm |title=Former Afghan commander executed |date=27 April 2004 |website=[[BBC News Online|BBC News]] |accessdate=20 August 2009}}</ref>\n\n===Antigua and Barbuda===\n*[[John Baughman]]: former American police officer who pushed his second wife from the roof of the Royal Antiguan Hotel in 1995; suspected of killing a close friend and first wife back in the USA; committed suicide in 2000.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-2000-06-02-0006020165-story.html |title=Family's Built-Up Pain Eased By Hanging In Antigua |first1=Marla |last1=Donato |first2=David |last2=Heinzmann |date=June 2, 2000 |newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Argentina===\n*[[Marcelo Antelo]]: also known as \"The [[San La Muerte]] Killer\"; drug addict who killed at least four people between February and August 2010, allegedly in the name of a pagan saint; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.clarin.com/crimenes/largo-prontuario-Marcelo-Antelo_0_SyXXJx2DXg.html |title=El largo prontuario de Marcelo Antelo |trans-title=The long record of Marcelo Antelo |first1=Horacio |last1=Ezcurra |first2=Rodrigo |last2=Ezcurra |first3=Marcelo |last3=Antelo |lastauthoramp=yes |date=September 9, 2012 |newspaper=[[Clar\u00edn (Argentine newspaper)|Clar\u00edn]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190910080104/https://www.clarin.com/crimenes/largo-prontuario-Marcelo-Antelo_0_SyXXJx2DXg.html |archivedate=September 10, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Florencio Fern\u00e1ndez]]: also known as \"The Argentine Vampire\"; killed fifteen women in his hometown of [[Monteros]] during the 1950s.\n*[[Cayetano Santos Godino]]: also known as \"Petiso Orejudo\" (\"Big Eared Midget\"); at 16, killed four children in 1912; died in prison in 1944.<ref name=CA>{{cite web |url=http://www.casoabierto.com/reportajes/cronica-negra/cayetano-santos-godino-la-historia-del-petiso-orejudo.html |title=Cayetano Santos Godino, la historia del Petiso Orejudo |last=Cabezas L\u00f3pez |first=Carlos |date=2007-09-16 |website=Caso Abierto |language=es |url-status=dead |accessdate=2008-09-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080801214210/http://www.casoabierto.com/reportajes/cronica-negra/cayetano-santos-godino-la-historia-del-petiso-orejudo.html |archivedate=2008-08-01}}</ref>\n*[[Cayetano Domingo Grossi]]: the first serial killer in Argentine history; Italian immigrant who murdered five of his newborn children between 1896 and 1898; executed 1900.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.acciontv.com.ar/soca/polis/enero13/grosi.htm |title=El fusilamiento de Cayetano Grossi (1900) |trans-title=The execution of Cayetano Grossi (1900) |website=Acci\u00f3nTV |language=es |access-date=12 November 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco Antonio Laureana]]: also known as \"The Satyr of [[San Isidro, Buenos Aires|San Isidro]]\"; murdered fifteen women from 1974 to 1975, raping thirteen of them; killed in a shootout with the police in 1975.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.diariopopular.com.ar/notas/182535-francisco-laureana-el-serial-san-isidro |title=Francisco Laureana, el serial de San Isidro |last=Kablan |first=Pablo |date=February 2, 2014 |newspaper=[[Diario Popular]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Yiya Murano]]: also known as \"The Poisoner of [[Monserrat, Buenos Aires|Monserrat]]\", poisoned three women in [[Buenos Aires]] in 1979.\n*[[Robledo Puch]]: also known as \"The Death Angel\" and \"The Black Angel\"; killed eleven people before his arrest in 1972; sentenced to [[life imprisonment]] in 1980.<ref name=\"lanacion\">{{cite news |url=https://www.lanacion.com.ar/lifestyle/robledo-puch-el-angel-negro-nid785598 |title=Robledo Puch: The Black Angel |first=Alvaro |last=Ab\u00f3s |date=5 March 2006 |newspaper=[[La Naci\u00f3n]] |accessdate=7 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Australia===\n*[[John Balaban (serial killer)|John Balaban]]: also known as the \"Romanian Maniac\"; Romanian emigrant who murdered at least five people in France and Australia from 1948 to 1953, including his wife and her family; executed 1953.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article49262393 |title=Murder Confession Alleged |date=4 May 1953 |newspaper=[[The Barrier Miner]] |volume=LXVI |issue=17445 |location=[[Broken Hill]], New South Wales |accessdate=12 November 2019 |page=1 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[David and Catherine Birnie]]: responsible for the \"Moorhouse Murders\"; couple from the [[Perth]] suburb of [[Willagee, Western Australia|Willagee]] who raped and murdered four women in 1986.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/partners/birnie/1_index.html |title=The Birnies - 2. A Serial Killer in Perth |last=Kidd |first=Paul B. |date=12 February 2007 |website=CourtTV CrimeLibrary |publisher=Courtroom Television Network, LLC. |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081123125648/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/partners/birnie/2.html |archivedate=23 November 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Gregory Brazel]]: [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] man who shot a woman to death in a 1982 armed robbery, and murdered two prostitutes in 1990.<ref name=killerpayout>{{cite news |url=http://www.theaustralian.news.com.au/story/0,20867,20409851-5006785,00.html |title=Killer gets compensation payout |first=Mark |last=Butler |date=14 September 2006 |newspaper=[[The Australian]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060915121802/http://www.theaustralian.news.com.au/story/0,20867,20409851-5006785,00.html |archive-date=2006-09-15}}</ref><ref name=killerlist>{{cite news |url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,21985,20673356-661,00.html |title=Killer caught with jail list |first=Mark |last=Butler |date=31 October 2006 |newspaper=[[Herald Sun|Sunday Herald Sun]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615104135/http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/killer-caught-with-jail-list/story-e6frf7kx-1111112443202 |archive-date=15 June 2011}}</ref>\n*[[John Bunting (serial killer)|John Bunting]], [[Robert Wagner (serial killer)|Robert Wagner]] and [[James Vlassakis]]: also known as the \"Bodies in the Barrels Murders\"; convicted of the [[Snowtown murders]] of twelve people between 1992 and 1999.<ref name=\"haydon trial\">{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/National/Bodiesinbarrels-trial-not-over/2004/12/19/1103391631199.html |title=Bodies-in-barrels trial not over |agency=[[Australian Associated Press|AAP]] |date=19 December 2004 |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |accessdate=11 January 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Francis Burns]]: confessed to eight killings; hanged in [[Ararat, Victoria|Ararat]] in 1883.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article198269401 |title=Burns's Confession Sustained |newspaper=[[Mount Alexander Mail]] |issue=7696 |location=[[Castlemaine, Victoria]] |date=3 December 1883 |access-date=24 November 2019 |page=3 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[Clarke brothers|Thomas and John Clarke]]: [[bushranger]] brothers who robbed railroad stations; killed five police officers; the Felons Apprehension Act of 1886, which allowed bushrangers to be killed on sight, was created because of them; both hanged 1867.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.anzlhsejournal.auckland.ac.nz/pdfs_2005/Eburn.pdf |title=Outlawry in Colonial Australia: The Felons Apprehension Acts 1865 \u20131899 |last=Eburn |first=Michael |date=2005 |website=Australian and New Zealand Law and History Society E-Journal |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110411043023/http://www.anzlhsejournal.auckland.ac.nz/pdfs_2005/Eburn.pdf |archive-date=April 11, 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Eric Edgar Cooke]]: also known as the \"Night Caller\"; killed at least eight people and attempted to kill many more in and around Perth between 1959 and 1963; last person to be hanged in [[Western Australia]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.postnewspapers.com.au/20030201/news/002.shtml |title=Police decoy used in killer hunt sting |last=Christian |first=Bret |date=February 1, 2003 |newspaper=[[Post Newspapers]] |location=[[Subiaco, Western Australia]] |accessdate=2006-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030202114507/http://www.postnewspapers.com.au/20030201/news/002.shtml |url-status=dead |archive-date=2 February 2003}}</ref>\n*[[John Leslie Coombes]]: killed two men in 1984 and one woman in 2009 around the Victoria area.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/triple-killer-to-die-in-jail-for-murder-that-ought-never-have-happened-20110826-1jddd.html |title=Triple killer to die in jail for murder that 'ought never have happened' |first1=Paul |last1=Millar |first2=Andrea |last2=Petrie |date=2011-08-26 |newspaper=[[The Age]] |location=[[Melbourne]] |access-date=2017-09-03}}</ref>\n*[[Bandali Debs]]: convicted of murdering two police officers and two prostitutes in the 1990s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2010-11-09/man-charged-15-years-after-prostitutes-murder/2330196 |title=Man charged 15 years after prostitute's murder |date=November 9, 2010 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Denyer]]: also known as the \"Frankston Killer\"; murdered three women in 1993 in the [[Melbourne]] suburb of [[Frankston, Victoria|Frankston]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/national/killers-family-dont-let-him-out/news-story/59e38892e8170309ccd633d1da3ffca4?sv=c839876f55e2e282e956202a2e18d4b5 |title=Family of Paul Denyer tell of killer's death threat |last=Deery |first=Shannon |date=July 21, 2011 |newspaper=[[Herald Sun]] |location=Melbourne |access-date=2018-01-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://aussiecriminals.com.au/high-profile-criminals/paul-charles-denyer-the-frankston-serial-killer/ |title=Paul Charles Denyer -The Frankston Serial Killer |author=Robbo |date=2012-04-20 |website=Aussie Criminals and Crooks |access-date=2018-01-28 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120709001907/http://aussiecriminals.com.au/high-profile-criminals/paul-charles-denyer-the-frankston-serial-killer/ |archive-date=July 9, 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Dupas]]: serving three life sentences for multiple murder and rape charges in Victoria.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/08/12/1092102597125.html?from=storylhs |title=Call for second life term for murderer Dupas |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=13 August 2004 |newspaper=The Age |location=Melbourne |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kathleen Folbigg]]: murdered four of her infants between 1991 and 1999.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2003/08/29/1062050669977.html |title=Killing them softly |first1=Julie |last1=Szego |first2=Stephen |last2=Cauchi |date=30 August 2003 |newspaper=The Age |location=Melbourne |accessdate=14 September 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Leonard Fraser]]: also known as the \"Rockhampton Rapist\"; convicted of killing four women in [[Rockhampton, Queensland]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.pansw.org.au/PolNews/Nov38-52.pdf |title=From Sexual Predator to Murderer |last=Bassingthwaighte |first=Ted |date=November 2006 |journal=Police News |publisher=[[Police Association of New South Wales]] |accessdate=2 January 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050615215035/http://pansw.org.au/PolNews/Nov38-52.pdf |archivedate=15 June 2005}}</ref>\n*[[John Wayne Glover]]: also known as the \"Granny Killer\"; killed six elderly women on Sydney's [[North Shore (Sydney)|North Shore]]; committed suicide in 2005.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/granny-killer-found-dead-in-cell/2005/09/09/1125772681493.html |title=Granny killer found dead in cell |last1=Gibson |first1=Jano |date=9 September 2005 |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/mystery-woman-pays-for-killers-funeral/2005/09/17/1126750168519.html |title=Mystery woman pays for killer's funeral |last1=O'Dwyer |first1=Erin |date=18 September 2005 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |accessdate=9 October 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Caroline Grills]]: also known as \"Auntie Thally\"; a serial [[Poison#Uses of poison|poisoner]] of five family members in [[New South Wales]] between 1947 and 1953.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/National/Murder-tried-and-true/2005/02/10/1107890341655.html |title=Murder, tried and true |date=11 February 2003 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |accessdate=2008-01-16}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Steven Haigh]]: sentenced to life imprisonment without parole for the murders of seven people in Victoria in the late 1970s.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/serial-killer-wins-right-to-seek-parole-20110419-1dml5.html |title=Serial killer wins right to seek parole |first=Belinda |last=Merhab |date=April 19, 2011 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Matthew James Harris]]: strangled a friend's brother, a female friend, and a male neighbor to death over five weeks in 1998 in [[Wagga Wagga]].<ref>{{cite AustLII|NSWSC|285|2000|litigants=R v Matthew James Harris|date=7 April 2000 |courtname=auto}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Jeffries]]: Tasmanian [[penal colony]] escapee responsible for the murders of five people; executed in 1826.<ref>Thomas Jeffries convict No. 3634, conduct record, State Archives of Tasmania.</ref>\n*[[Frances Knorr]]: also known as the \"Baby Farming Murderess\"; English-born baby farmer who killed three infants; executed 1894.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cv.vic.gov.au/stories/felon-families-/9300/felon-families-/ |title=Felon families: Stories of women prisoners and their families |last=Gardiner |first=Diane |date=2016 |website=National Trust of Australia (Victoria) |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Eddie Leonski]]: also known as the \"Brownout Strangler\"; United States Army soldier who killed three women in [[Melbourne]]; executed in 1942.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article231786070 |title=Melbourne Police Hunt \"Brownout\" Strangler |newspaper=[[The Sun (Sydney)|The Sun]] |issue=10100 |location=Sydney, New South Wales |date=20 May 1942 |accessdate=16 March 2017 |page=3 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article168972547 |title=Leonski, Enigma In Life And In Death, Carries His Secret To Grave |newspaper=[[Truth (Sydney newspaper)|Truth]] |issue=2758 |location=Sydney, New South Wales |date=15 November 1942 |accessdate=16 March 2017 |page=14 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article75783558 |title=Killed To Show His Strength |newspaper=[[The Mirror (Western Australia)|The Mirror]] |volume=29 |issue=1612 |location=Perth, Western Australia |date=19 April 1952 |accessdate=16 March 2017 |page=8 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/law-order/macabre-and-detailed-hangmans-journal-reproduced-in-detail-for-true-crime-scene/news-story/a98b17a1bc653a9f2e034ac32873781b?sv=c73ce64e6658e0bf838435a046bd3579 |title=Macabre and detailed hangman's journal reproduced in detail for True Crime Scene |last1=Robinson |first1=Russell |date=2012-06-03 |newspaper=[[Herald Sun]] |location=Melbourne |accessdate=26 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[John Lynch (serial killer)|John Lynch]]: also known as the \"[[Berrima, New South Wales|Berrima]] Axe Murderer\"; killed ten people from 1835 to 1841.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=nVJD6V0XAtwC&pg=PT32&lpg=PT32&dq=john+lynch+murderer#v=onepage&q=john%20lynch%20murderer |title=Australia's Serial Killers |last=Kidd |first=Paul B. |date=1 August 2011 |publisher=[[Pan Macmillan Australia]] |isbn=978-1-74262-798-4 |page=32}}</ref>\n*[[William MacDonald (serial killer)|William MacDonald]]: also known as the \"Mutilator\"; English immigrant who killed at least five men between June 1961 and April 1963 throughout Sydney.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/macdonald/monster_2.html |title=William \"The Mutilator\" Macdonald: The Making of a Monster |last=Kidd |first=Paul B. |accessdate=28 October 2010 |website=Turner Entertainment Networks |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811041741/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/macdonald/monster_2.html |archive-date=2011-08-11}}</ref>\n*[[John and Sarah Makin]]: late 19th century [[baby farming|baby farmers]] who killed and buried twelve children at a succession of their homes.<ref>{{cite dictionary |url=http://adbonline.anu.edu.au/biogs/AS10317b.htm |title=Makin, John (1845\u20131893) |first=Heather |last=Radi |date=2005 |dictionary=[[Australian Dictionary of Biography]] |publisher=National Centre of Biography, Australian National University |accessdate=20 December 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Malachi Martin (murderer)|Malachi Martin]]: convicted of killing [[Jane Macmanamin]] and suspected of murdering four additional people as well as being implicated in the suspicious death of his mother; hanged at the [[Adelaide Gaol]] in 1862.<ref>Martin's marriage certificate shows this spelling, while on that certificate he signed his name \"Malacky\" (1858 marriage certificate indexed by Births, Deaths and Marriages South Australia at Book 317, Page 541). On his petition to the Governor in December 1862 Martin signed his name \"Malaky Martin\" (Malachy Martin's petition to the Governor & Executive Council of South Australia, GRG 24/6/1862/1215). In oral tradition the name is pronounced in a way that indicates it should be spelt \"Malachy\" rather than the Biblical \"Malachi\". John Bowyer Bull, who had met Malachy, mentions him in his memoirs, and although he spells the name several ways, they are all closer to \"Malachy\" than to \"Malachi\" (J.B. Bull, unpublished manuscript ''The Life of John Bowyer Bull, The Australian Bushman & Explorer, 1838 \u20131894'', PGR 507/3, pp 62-65).</ref>\n*[[Backpacker Murders|Ivan Milat]]: killed at least seven tourists in [[Belanglo State Forest]], [[New South Wales]] between 1989 and 1993, which became known as the \"Backpacker Murders\"; suspected in similar disappearances in [[City of Newcastle|Newcastle]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/twenty-five-years-ago-the-first-victims-of-backpacker-killer-ivan-milat-were-found-in-belanglo-forest-twenty-five-years-ago-the-first-victims-of-backpacker-killer-ivan-milat-were-found-in-belanglo-forest/news-story/f4a31abad223faa68d8d73ca054d297e |title=Twenty five years ago the first victims of Backpacker Killer Ivan Milat were found in Belanglo Forest |last1=Lennon |first1=Troy |date=19 September 2017 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|The Daily Telegraph]] |location=Sydney |accessdate=26 January 2018 |url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n*[[Dan Morgan (bushranger)|Dan Morgan]]: also known as \"Mad Dog\"; violent bushranger who killed three people from 1864 to 1865; killed during a standoff with the Victoria police.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article80953125 |title=Bloodthirsty Morgan |newspaper=[[The Singleton Argus]] |location=Singleton, New South Wales |date=14 June 1924 |accessdate=16 April 2012 |page=3 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[Martha Needle]]: also known as the \"Black Widow of [[Richmond, Victoria|Richmond]],\" [[Poison#Uses of poison|poisoner]] of four family members and her boyfriend's brother; executed in 1894.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://newdiogenesmelbourne.wordpress.com/2016/04/17/martha-needles-headstone |title=Martha Needle headstone found |last=Hartley |first=M. George |date=2018-03-14 |website=New Diogenes Melbourne |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Alexander Pearce]]: Irish convict who escaped with seven other convicts from imprisonment; five of them were killed and cannibalised, leaving Pearce the only one left; hanged 1824.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.australianhistory.org/other-bushrangers.php |title=Other Bushrangers: Alexander Pierce |date=2006 |website=Australian History.org |access-date=2010-01-27 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101209021729/http://australianhistory.org/other-bushrangers.php |archive-date=9 December 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Derek Percy]]: murdered a child in 1969, but also linked to the deaths of eight other children in the 60s; died in prison from [[lung cancer]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-07-24/derek-percy-linked-to-deaths-of-9-children/4840556 |title=Child killer Derek Percy was linked to deaths of nine children |date=30 October 2014 |website=ABC News |accessdate=19 October 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Martha Rendell]]: killed three stepchildren with [[hydrochloric acid]] in 1907-08; last woman to be hanged in Western Australia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://policewahistory.org.au/HTML_Pages/Child_Murders.html |title=Martha Rendell Child Murders - 1909 |last=Skehan |first=Peter |website=Western Australia Police Historical Society |accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Lindsey Robert Rose]]: New South Wales serial and [[contract killer]] who murdered five people between 1984 and 1994.<ref>{{cite AustLII|NSWCCA|327|1999|litigants=R v Rose|date=11 October 1999 |courtname=auto}}</ref>\n*[[Murchison Murders|'Snowy' Rowles]]: also known as the \"[[Murchison (Western Australia)|Murchison]] Murders\"; stockman who murdered three people using a method from a then unpublished book of author [[Arthur Upfield]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thewest.com.au/news/wa/heritage-nod-for-site-of-grisly-outback-murders-ng-b88765025z |title=Heritage nod for site of grisly outback murders |last=Acott |first=Kent |date=6 March 2018 |newspaper=[[The West Australian]] |location=Perth |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Albert Schmidt (serial killer)|Albert Schmidt]]: also known as \"The Wagga Murderer\"; German immigrant who murdered at least three travelling companions from 1888 to 1890; executed for one murder in 1890.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article101894490 |title=The Late Wagga Murder |newspaper=[[The Wagga Wagga Advertiser]] |volume=XX |issue=2165 |location=Wagga Wagga, New South Wales |date=15 May 1890 |access-date=24 November 2019 |page=2 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[Arnold Sodeman]]: also known as the \"School-girl Strangler\"; killed four children in Melbourne in the 1930s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article1408956 |title=Sent To Reformatory |newspaper=[[The Argus (Melbourne)|The Argus]] |issue=22,491 |location=Melbourne |date=30 August 1918 |accessdate=2013-10-07 |page=3 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[John \"Rocky\" Whelan]]: [[Tasmania]]n [[penal colony]] escapee responsible for the murders of five people; executed in 1855.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.convictrecords.com.au/convicts/whelan/john/111127 |title=John Whelan |website=Convict Records |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Truro murders|Christopher Worrell and James Miller]]: also known as the \"[[Truro, South Australia|Truro]] Murderers\"; were convicted of killing seven people in 1976\u20131977.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/worrell/discover_2.html |title=The Truro Serial Murders: The Horrifying Discoveries |last=Kidd |first=Paul B. |date=2012 |website=[[TruTV]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927182522/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/worrell/discover_2.html |archive-date=2012-09-27}}</ref>\n\n===Austria===\n*[[Elfriede Blauensteiner]]: also known as the \"Black Widow\"; poisoner of three individuals; died in prison in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/austria/1316893/The-Black-Widow-is-guilty-of-two-more-murders.html |title=The Black Widow is guilty of two more murders |first=Michael |last=Leidig |date=2001-04-20 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Max Gufler]]: poisoned and drowned women; convicted of four murders and two attempted murders, but believed to have committed 18; died 1996.\n*[[Dariusz Kotwica]]: also known as the \"Euro Ripper\"; Polish vagrant who murdered at least three pensioners in Austria and [[Sweden]] in 2015; suspected of more murders in the [[Netherlands]], [[Czech Republic]] and the [[United Kingdom]]; sentenced to involuntary commitment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/623011/Euro-Ripper-Dariusz-Pawel-Kotwica-Britain-UK-detectives-DNA-pensioner-rapes-deaths |title=Did Euro Ripper strike in Britain? UK detectives trawl DNA over pensioner rapes and deaths |first=Anil |last=Dawar |date=30 November 2015 |newspaper=[[Daily Express]] |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Martha Marek]]: poisoned three family members and a lodger in her house with [[thallium]] between 1932 and 1937; executed 1938.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.bmi.gv.at/cms/BMI_OeffentlicheSicherheit/2007/05_06/files/Giftmorde.pdf |title=Ein fast perfekter Mord |trans-title=An almost perfect murder |last=Sabitzer |first=Werner |edition=May\u2013June |date=2007 |pages=47\u201354 |journal=\u00d6ffentliche Sicherheit |publisher==[[Directorate General for the Public Security]] |language=de |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211084043/http://www.bmi.gv.at/cms/BMI_OeffentlicheSicherheit/2007/05_06/files/Giftmorde.pdf |archive-date=December 11, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Wolfgang Ott]]: sex offender and suspected serial killer who kidnapped several women in 1995, killing two of them; sentenced to life imprisonment in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://noe.orf.at/news/stories/2839558/ |title=Doppelm\u00f6rder nach \u00dcberdosis im Spital |trans-title=Double murderer in hospital after overdose |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2017-04-27 |website=[[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]] |language=de |access-date=2018-01-29}}</ref>\n*[[Harald Sassak]]: [[gasworks]] employee who between 1971 and 1972 killed six people for the purpose of robbery; died from an undisclosed illness in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.noen.at/lokales/noe-uebersicht/gmuend/aktuell/Gaskassier-Sassak-starb-in-Weitra;art2511,480360 |title=\"Gaskassier\" Sassak starb in Weitra |trans-title=\"Gasman\" Sassak dies in Weitra |last=Lohninger |first=Markus |date=28 August 2013 |website=N\u00d6N.at |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Hugo Schenk]]: also known as the \"Viennese Housemaids Killer\"; swindler who killed four maids in 1883 with his accomplice Karl Schlossarek; suspected of more murders; executed 1884.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://serialkillercalendar.com/Hugo%20SCHENK.php |title=Hugo Schenk aka \"The Viennese Housemaids Killer\" |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Serial Killer Calendar.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jack Unterweger]]: author and [[Sadomasochism|sexual sadist]]; convicted of ten murders; believed to have killed twelve women; committed suicide in prison in 1994.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1994-06-30/local/me-10223_1_los-angeles |title=Austrian Slayer of L.A. Prostitutes Kills Self |last=Malnic |first=Eric |date=June 30, 1994 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lainz Angels of Death|Maria Gruber, Irene Leidolf, Stephanija Mayer and Waltraud Wagner]]: also known as the \"Lainz Angels of Death\"; nurses at the Lainz General Hospital in [[Vienna]] who admitted to murdering 49 patients between 1983 and 1989.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1989/04/18/world/killing-of-49-patients-by-4-nurse-s-aides-stuns-the-austrians.html |title=Killing of 49 Patients By 4 Nurse's Aides Stuns the Austrians |last=Protzman |first=Ferdinand |date=April 18, 1989 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=June 24, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Guido Zingerle]]: also known as the \"Monster of Tyrol\"; Italian who brutally raped women in Italy and Austria between 1946 and 1950, killing at least two by burying them under a pile of stones; died in prison from [[liver cancer]] in 1962.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.stol.it/Artikel/Kultur-im-Ueberblick/Literatur/Brav-sein-sonst-holt-dich-der-Zingerle-Die-Geschichte-des-Ungeheuers-von-Tirol |title=\"Brav sein, sonst holt dich der Zingerle\" - Die Geschichte des \"Ungeheuers von Tirol\" |trans-title=Be good, otherwise Zingerle will get you - The story of the \"Monster of Tyrol\" |date=October 27, 2009 |website=Stol.it |language=de |accessdate=August 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140718201116/http://www.stol.it/Artikel/Kultur-im-Ueberblick/Literatur/Brav-sein-sonst-holt-dich-der-Zingerle-Die-Geschichte-des-Ungeheuers-von-Tirol |archive-date=July 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===The Bahamas===\n*[[Cordell Farrington]]: killed four children and his homosexual lover from 2002 to 2003; sentenced to death and later commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2003/nov/10/richardluscombe |title=Serial murder police find remains |first=Richard |last=Luscombe |date=10 November 2003 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michaiah Shobek]]: also known as \"The Angels of Lucifer Killer\"; American emigrant who murdered three fellow US tourists from 1973 to 1974; executed 1976.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1976/10/19/archives/bahamas-to-execute-an-american-today-for-murder-of-3-tourists.html |title=Bahamas to Execute an American Today for Murder of 3 Tourists |date=19 October 1976 |agency=Associated Press |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Bangladesh===\n*[[Roshu Kha]]: enraged over rejection by his lover, Roshu killed at least eleven garment workers in [[Chandpur District]]. He pretended to love them, later killing them brutally.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://guardian.ng/news/confessed-serial-killer-sentenced-to-hang-in-bangladesh/ |title=Confessed serial killer sentenced to hang in Bangladesh |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=23 April 2015 |newspaper=[[The Guardian (Nigeria)|The Guardian]] |location=Lagos, Nigeria |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ershad Sikder]]: career criminal and corrupt politician responsible for the torture-murders of numerous people in the 1990s; convicted on seven counts of murder and executed in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/World/News/Bangladesh-killer-hanged-20040511 |title=Bangladesh killer hanged |date=2004-05-11 |website=[[News24]] |access-date=10 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Belarus===\n*[[Ivan Kulesh]]: drunkard who killed three saleswomen between 2013 and 2014 in the [[Grodno Region]]; executed 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://naviny.by/article/20161128/1480339538-ispolnen-ocherednoy-smertnyy-prigovor-rasstrelyan-ubiyca-lidskih |title=\u0418\u0441\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440. \u0420\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043b\u044f\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0430 \u043b\u0438\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0449\u0438\u0446 |trans-title=Another death sentence has been executed. The killer of Lida saleswomen was shot |first=Alexey |last=Alexandrov |date=November 28, 2016 |website=[[naviny.by]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Eduard Lykov]]: Russian immigrant who killed five people in drunken quarrels from 2002 to 2011; executed 2014.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.tut.by/society/395123.html |title=\u041b\u044b\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u043d\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0441\u0435\u0431\u044f \"\u043d\u0435\u0445\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\" \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b \u043b\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u044b. \u0421\u0443\u0434 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b \u0441\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0432 \u0441\u0438\u043b\u0435 (\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043e) |trans-title=Lykov called himself a \"non-christian\" and asked for imprisonment. The court upheld the death sentence (updated) |first=Katherine |last=Sinyuk |date=April 15, 2014 |website=[[Tut.By]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gennady Mikhasevich]]: [[Voluntary People's Druzhina|police volunteer]] who investigated his own mission-oriented murders of 36 women between 1971 and 1985; executed in 1987.<ref name=\"Newton_177\">{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA177 |date=February 2006 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3 |page=177}}</ref>\n*[[Igor Mirenkov]]: known as \"the [[Svietlahorsk]] Nightmare\"; child killer who murdered six boys from 1990 to 1993; executed in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.detektiv.by/svetlogorsk?page=9%2C2 |title=\u0421\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043a\u043e\u0448\u043c\u0430\u0440 |trans-title=Svetlogorsk nightmare |date=December 14, 2007 |website=Detectiv.by |language=ru |accessdate=2010-09-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68ZZxfQVK?url=http://www.detektiv.by/svetlogorsk?page=9,2 |archivedate=20 June 2012 }}</ref>\n*[[The Polotsk Four|Sergey Pugachev and Alexander Burdenko]]: leaders of the \"[[Polotsk]] Four\"; criminals responsible for killing two girls and two car enthusiasts from 2001 to 2002, as well as numerous robberies with two other accomplices; Pugachev was executed in 2005 and Burdenko was sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.sb.by/articles/bandity-poluchili-svoe.html |title=\u0411\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044b \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0435 |trans-title=Bandits got theirs |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=July 12, 2005 |newspaper=[[Sovetskaya Belorussiya \u2013 Belarus' Segodnya]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Alexander Sergeychik]]: killed six people from 2000 to 2006 in the [[Shchuchyn District|Shchuchyn]] and [[Grodno District]]s; confessed to twelve murders; executed 2007.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sb.by/articles/rasplata-vysshey-meroy.html |title=\u0420\u0430\u0441\u043f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0435\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0439 |trans-title=Reckoning with capital punishment |last=Charovskaya |first=Katerina |date=23 May 2007 |newspaper=Sovetskaya Belorussiya \u2013 Belarus' Segodnya |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Belgium===\n*[[Marie Alexandrine Becker]]: poisoned at least eleven people with [[Digitalis]]; sentenced to life imprisonment; died 1938.\n*[[Jan Caubergh]]: strangled his pregnant neighbour, his girlfriend and their child in 1979; sentenced to death but it was converted to life imprisonment; was the longest-serving prisoner in the country until his death in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gva.be/regio-antwerpen-noord/schoten/moordenaar-heeft-34-jaar-aan-mijn-hart-gevreten.aspx |title=Moordenaar heeft 34 jaar aan mijn hart gevreten |trans-title=Murder has eaten at my heart for 34 years |first=Kristin |last=Matthyssen |date=5 December 2013 |newspaper=[[Gazet van Antwerpen]] |language=nl |access-date=5 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/article/detail.aspx?articleid=GMU2QVK4K |title=77-jarige meervoudige moordenaar staat weer terecht |trans-title=77-year-old multiple murderer is on trial again |first=Steven |last=De Bock |date=2 June 2010 |newspaper=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |language=nl |access-date=2 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.standaard.be/cnt/dmf20131202_00868438 |title=Oudste gevangene van ons land overleden |trans-title=Oldest prisoner in our country dies |date=3 December 2013 |newspaper=[[De Standaard]] |language=nl |access-date=3 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/article/detail.aspx?articleid=dmf20131202_00868413 |title=Oudste Belgische moordenaar sterft in de cel |trans-title=The oldest Belgian serial killer dies in a cell |first=Pieter |last=Huyberechts |date=3 December 2013 |newspaper=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl |access-date=3 December 2013}}</ref>\n*[[\u00c9tienne Dedroog]]: known as the \"Lodgers' Killer\"; killed a [[Bed and breakfast|B&B]] owner in France and a couple in Belgium from October to November 2011; also suspected of a murder in Spain; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20170505_02867412 |title=B&B-moordenaar veroordeeld tot 25 jaar cel in Frankrijk |trans-title=B&B Murderer sentenced to 25 years imprisonment in France |date=5 May 2017 |newspaper=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Marc Dutroux]]: convicted of having kidnapped, tortured and sexually abused six girls ranging in age from 8 to 19, during 1995 and 1996. Four of his victims were murdered; the final two were rescued.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2002/jan/25/worlddispatch.dutroux |title=Belgium still haunted by paedophile scandal |first=Andrew |last=Osborn |date=25 January 2002 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=12 July 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Staf Van Eyken]]: also known as the \"Vampire of Muizen\"; raped and strangled three women from 1971 to 1972 in [[Muizen]] and [[Bonheiden]]; sentenced to death, commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.standaard.be/cnt/dmf20160216_02130945 |title=Vampier van Muizen wil zieke priester bezoeken |trans-title=Vampire van Muizen wants to visit a sick priest |first=Sarah |last=Vankersschaever |date=16 February 2016 |newspaper=[[De Standaard]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Renaud Hardy]]: also known as the \"Parkinson's Murderer\"; murdered between two and three women in the [[Flemish Community]] from 2009 to 2015; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hln.be/nieuws/binnenland/-topdokter-van-der-linden-quot-hardy-wordt-pas-seriemoordenaar-op-moment-dat-hij-parkinsonmedicatie-neemt-quot~ac84fd03/ |title='Topdokter' Van der Linden: \"Hardy wordt pas seriemoordenaar op moment dat hij parkinsonmedicatie neemt\" |trans-title='Top doctor' Van der Linden: \"Hardy only becomes a serial killer when he takes Parkinson's medication\" |first=Veronique |last=Coopmans |date=27 February 2018 |newspaper=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]] |language=nl |access-date=2018-03-08}}</ref>\n*[[Ronald Janssen]]: killed a woman in 2007 and later his neighbour and her boyfriend in 2010 in [[Flemish Brabant]]; admitted to five rapes committed in 1993, but is suspected of 20; sentenced to life imprisonment in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dhnet.be/actu/faits/ronald-janssen-les-aveux-du-tueur-en-serie-51b778f6e4b0de6db97d5cb4 |title=Ronald Janssen: les aveux du tueur en s\u00e9rie |trans-title=Ronald Janssen: the confessions of a serial killer |first=Gilbert |last=Dupont |date=17 September 2011 |newspaper=[[La Derni\u00e8re Heure]] |language=fr |access-date=20 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.7sur7.be/7s7/fr/1724/Meurtre-d-Annick/article/detail/1323107/2011/09/23/Ronald-Janssen-portrait-d-un-tueur-de-la-nuit.dhtml |title=Ronald Janssen, portrait d'un tueur de la nuit |trans-title=Ronald Janssen, portrait of a killer in the night |first=Micha\u00ebl |last=Bouche |date=23 October 2011 |website=7SUR7.be |language=fr |access-date=20 March 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Marie-Th\u00e9r\u00e8se Joniaux]]: poisoned three of her family members between 1894 and 1895; sentenced to death in 1895, but was commuted to life imprisonment; died in [[Antwerp]] in 1923.<ref>{{cite book |url=http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb31272691k |last=de Ryck\u00e8re |first=Raymond |date=1895 |title=L'affaire Joniaux, triple empoisonnement... |location=[[Lyon]] |publisher=A. Storck |via=[[Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France|BnF]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Andr\u00e1s P\u00e1ndy]]: also known as \"Vader Blauwbaard\" (Father Bluebeard); Hungarian immigrant convicted of the murder and rape of his two wives and four children in [[Brussels]] between 1986 and 1990 with the aid of his daughter, \u00c1gnes P\u00e1ndy; died in prison in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asp.gva.be/dossiers/-p/pandy/dossier.asp |title=De zaak Pandy: Chronologie van een familiedrama en een onderzoek |trans-title=The Pandy case: Chronology of a family drama and an investigation |website=De zaak Pandy |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228203527/http://asp.gva.be/dossiers/-p/pandy/dossier.asp |archive-date=28 December 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Nestor Pirotte]]: also known as the \"Crazy Killer\"; considered one of the worst Belgian criminals, responsible for the murders of up to seven people from 1954 to 1981, including his great-aunt; died from a heart attack in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.franceinfo.fr/faits-divers/histoires-criminelles/nestor-pirotte-le-faux-aristocrate-belge-qui-a-echappe-a-la-peine-capitale-691335-201 |title=Nestor Pirotte, le faux aristocrate belge qui a \u00e9chapp\u00e9 \u00e0 la peine capitale...deux fois! |trans-title=Nestor Pirotte, the false Belgian aristocrat who escaped the death penalty...twice! |last=Expert |first=Jacques |date=July 30, 2012 |website=[[France Info (radio network)|France Info]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120731012437/http://www.franceinfo.fr/faits-divers/histoires-criminelles/nestor-pirotte-le-faux-aristocrate-belge-qui-a-echappe-a-la-peine-capitale-691335-201 |archive-date=July 31, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Bolivia===\n*[[Ramiro Artieda]]: killed his brother in the early 1920s for monetary purposes; emigrated to the United States but later returned and killed seven women until 1938; was arrested in 1939, confessed and was executed by firing squad.<ref>{{cite book |first1=Amanda |last1=Howard |first2=Martin |last2=Smith |date=2004 |title=River of Blood: Serial Killers and Their Victims |publisher=Universal Publishers |page=27 |isbn=978-1-58112-518-4}}</ref>\n\n===Brazil===\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Augusto do Amaral]]: also known as \"Preto Amaral\"; first documented Brazilian serial killer; suspected of murdering and then raping the corpses of three young men in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] in 1926; died from [[tuberculosis]] while imprisoned before he could be put on trial.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.diarioinsano.com.br/2009/12/preto-amaral-o-1-serial-killer.html |title=Preto Amaral - O 1\u00ba serial killer brasileiro |trans-title=Preto Amaral - The 1st Brazilian serial killer |first=Karina |last=Ninni |date=1 December 2009 |website=Di\u00e1rio Insano |language=pt |accessdate=22 February 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222055627/http://www.diarioinsano.com.br/2009/12/preto-amaral-o-1-serial-killer.html |archive-date=2016-02-22}}</ref>\n*[[Marcelo Costa de Andrade]]: also known as \"The Vampire of [[Niter\u00f3i]]\"; raped and killed fourteen children.\n*[[Marcelo de Jesus Silva]]: also known as \"Chucky\"; [[Dwarfism|dwarf]] man convicted of twenty counts of murder, robbery, drug trafficking and death squad.\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Paz Bezerra]]: also known as \"The Morumbi Monster\"; sexually violated, tortured and murdered more than twenty women in S\u00e3o Paulo and [[Par\u00e1]] during the 1960s and 1970s; sentenced to 30 years imprisonment and released in 2001.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://oaprendizverde.com.br/2018/03/19/reportagem-retro-jose-paz-bezerra-o-monstro-estrangulador/ |title=Reportagem Retr\u00f4: Jos\u00e9 Paz Bezerra, o monstro estrangulador |trans-title=Retro Report: Jos\u00e9 Paz Bezerra, the strangling monster |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=19 March 2018 |website=O Aprendiz Verde |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Febr\u00f4nio \u00cdndio do Brasil]]: delusional religious maniac and habitual criminal who murdered at least six people from 1925 to 1927, mostly young boys and teens; acquitted by reason of insanity and sent to a mental institution, in which he died in 1989 from [[chronic obstructive pulmonary disease]].<ref>{{Cite journal |url=https://jus.com.br/artigos/1013/os-casos-de-pierre-riviere-e-febronio-indio-do-brasil-como-exemplos-de-uma-violencia-institucionalizada |title=Os casos de Pi\u00e9rre Rivi\u00e8re e Febr\u00f4nio \u00cdndio do Brasil como exemplos de uma viol\u00eancia institucionalizada |trans-title=The cases of Pi\u00e9rre Rivi\u00e8re and Febr\u00f4nio \u00cdndio do Brasil as examples of institutionalized violence |last=Wunderlich |first=Alexandre |date=1 July 2000 |volume=5 |number=43 |journal=Jus Navigandi |location=[[Teresina]] |language=pt |issn=1518-4862 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Abra\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 Bueno]]: [[Rio de Janeiro]] nurse who killed four child patients; sentenced to 110 years imprisonment in 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2008/05/16/ex_enfermeiro_que_matou_criancas_em_hospital_do_rio_e_condenado_a_110_anos_1315150.html |title=Ex-enfermeiro que matou crian\u00e7as em hospital do Rio \u00e9 condenado a 110 anos |trans-title=Former nurse who killed children in Rio hospital is sentenced to 110 years |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=16 May 2008 |website=\u00daltimo Segundo |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080619095227/http://ultimosegundo.ig.com.br/brasil/2008/05/16/ex_enfermeiro_que_matou_criancas_em_hospital_do_rio_e_condenado_a_110_anos_1315150.html |archive-date=June 19, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco das Chagas Rodrigues de Brito]]: pedophile who sexually abused, murdered and mutilated between 30 and 42 young boys from 1989 to 2003 in Maranh\u00e3o and Par\u00e1; sentenced to 217 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/100107/p_086.html |title=Ele matava, abusava, mutilava |trans-title=He killed, abused, mutilated |last=Teixeira |first=Jer\u00f4nimo |date=January 10, 2007 |magazine=[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331173827/http://veja.abril.com.br/100107/p_086.html |archive-date=March 31, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro Rosa da Concei\u00e7\u00e3o]]: Brazilian mass murderer who killed three people and wounded thirteen others on April 22, 1904. Killed his cellmate and a guard in 1911, and is said to have murdered a family of twelve people in an unspecified date and year. Died in 1919.\n*[[Pedro Rodrigues Filho]]: also known as \"Pedrinho Matador\"; convicted and sentenced to 128 years imprisonment for 70 murders; however, the maximum one can serve in Brazil is 30 years; claimed to have killed more than 100 victims, including 40 prison inmates.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://noticias.r7.com/videos/exclusivo-marcelo-rezende-entrevista-criminoso-que-matou-mais-de-cem-pessoas/idmedia/4fd5696f92bbcc410d415dd0.html |title=Exclusivo: Marcelo Rezende entrevista criminoso que matou mais de cem pessoas |trans-title=Exclusive: Marcelo Rezende interview with criminal that killed more than one hundred people |first=Marcelo |last=Rezende |authorlink=Marcelo Rezende |date=11 June 2012 |website=R7 News |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120615190337/http://noticias.r7.com/videos/exclusivo-marcelo-rezende-entrevista-criminoso-que-matou-mais-de-cem-pessoas/idmedia/4fd5696f92bbcc410d415dd0.html |archive-date=15 June 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Roneys Fon Firmino Gomes]]: known as the \"Tower Maniac\"; murdered at least six prostitutes in the city of [[Maring\u00e1]] between 2005 and 2015, disposing of their bodies under electric towers; sentenced to 21 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/pr/norte-noroeste/noticia/2019/03/15/maniaco-da-torre-e-condenado-a-21-anos-e-4-meses-de-prisao.ghtml |title='Man\u00edaco da Torre' \u00e9 condenado a 21 anos e 4 meses de pris\u00e3o |trans-title='Tower Maniac' is sentenced to 21 years and 4 months in prison |first=William |last=Souza |date=15 March 2019 |website=[[G1 (website)|G1]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco de Assis Pereira]]: rapist and serial killer, known as \"O Man\u00edaco do Parque\" (The Park Maniac); arrested for the torture, rape and death of eleven women and for assaulting nine in a park in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] during the 1990s.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/120898/p_106.html |title=Fui eu |trans-title=Was me |first=Laura |last=Capriglione |date=12 August 1998 |magazine=[[Veja (magazine)|Veja]] |accessdate=February 9, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071021024742/http://veja.abril.com.br/120898/p_106.html |archive-date=October 21, 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Tiago Henrique Gomes da Rocha]]: security guard who has claimed to have killed 39 people in the state of [[Goi\u00e1s]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-29654569 |title=Brazil man 'confesses to 39 murders' |date=16 October 2014 |website=BBC News |accessdate=17 October 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Edson Izidoro Guimar\u00e3es]]: nurse who killed four patients in the Rio de Janeiro neighborhood of [[M\u00e9ier]]; suspected of 131 deaths in total.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Serial Murder by Healthcare Professionals |first1=Beatrice Crofts |last1=Yorker |first2=Kenneth W. |last2=Kizer |first3=Paula |last3=Lampe |first4=A.R.W. |last4=Forrest |first5=Jacquetta M. |last5=Lannan |first6=Donna A. |last6=Russell |lastauthoramp=yes |date=November 2006 |journal=Journal of Forensic Sciences |volume=51 |number=6 |pages=1362\u20131371 |publisher=Wiley-Blackwell |doi=10.1111/j.1556-4029.2006.00273.x}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Vicente Matias]]: also known as \"Corumb\u00e1\"; former [[artisan]] who raped, murdered and dismembered six women between 1999 and 2005, cannibalizing one of them; sentenced to 23 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jornalpequeno.com.br/2008/6/4/Pagina79933.htm |title='Corumb\u00e1' condenado a 23 anos por matar estudante |trans-title='Corumb\u00e1' sentenced to 23 years for killing student |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=4 June 2008 |newspaper=[[Jornal Pequeno]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080609012441/http://www.jornalpequeno.com.br/2008/6/4/Pagina79933.htm |archive-date=June 9, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Florisvaldo de Oliveira]]: also known as \"Cabo Bruno\"; former police officer accused of more than 50 murders on the outskirts of S\u00e3o Paulo in 1982; murdered by unknown assailants in 2012.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://f5.folha.uol.com.br/saiunonp/2015/03/1607636-cabo-bruno-mata-50-e-morre-com-20-tiros.shtml |title=Cabo Bruno mata 50 e morre com 20 tiros |trans-title=Cabo Bruno kills 50 and dies with 20 shots |first=Luiz Carlos |last=Ferreira |date=25 March 2015 |newspaper=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] |language=pt |accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Sebasti\u00e3o Ant\u00f4nio de Oliveira]]: also known as \"The Monster of [[Bragan\u00e7a Paulista|Bragan\u00e7a]]\"; mentally-ill man who murdered five children and raped at least eight between 1953 and 1975; committed suicide before trial in 1976.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=http://memoria.bn.br/docreader/DocReader.aspx?bib=003581&pagfis=195392 |title=O monstro de Bragan\u00e7a |first=Edison |last=Torres |date=February 5, 1975 |magazine=[[O Cruzeiro]] |volume=XLVII |issue=6 |pages=28\u201333 |via=[[Biblioteca Nacional do Brasil]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Diogo Figueira da Rocha]]: also known as \"Dioguinho\"; career criminal responsible for at least 50 murders between 1894 and 1897 around S\u00e3o Paulo; supposedly killed in a shootout with the police in 1897.<ref>{{Cite journal |url=https://www.tjrs.jus.br/export/poder_judiciario/historia/memorial_do_poder_judiciario/memorial_judiciario_gaucho/revista_justica_e_historia/issn_1676-5834/v3n6/doc/05-Marilia_Schneider.pdf |title=Al\u00e9m Da Justi\u00e7a: O Homicida Dioguinho e Seus C\u00famplices |trans-title=Beyond Justice: The Murderer Dioguinho and His Accomplices |first=Mar\u00edlia |last=Schneider |date=2003 |journal=Revista de Jurisprud\u00eancia |publisher=Tribunal de Justi\u00e7a do Estado do Rio Grande do Sul |volume=3 |number=6 |issn=1676-5834 |language=pt |via=Biblioteca Digital Jur\u00eddica do [[Superior Tribunal de Justi\u00e7a]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Orlando Sabino]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Capin\u00f3polis]]\"; suspected of murdering twelve people in several municipalities around [[Minas Gerais]] and Goi\u00e1s; died from a heart attack in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portaldearaguari.com.br/2011/05/historia-do-monstro-de-capinopolis.html |title=A hist\u00f3ria do Monstro de Capin\u00f3polis ganha livro |trans-title=The story of the Monster of Capin\u00f3polis earns a book |date=25 May 2011 |website=Portal de Araguari |language=pt |access-date=July 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414082946/http://www.portaldearaguari.com.br/2011/05/historia-do-monstro-de-capinopolis.html |archive-date=2017-04-14}}</ref>\n*[[An\u00edsio Ferreira de Sousa]]: gynaecologist from [[Altamira, Par\u00e1|Altamira]] who was convicted of the murder of three children but linked to the disappearance of a total of 19.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hcnet.usp.br/ipq/nufor/pdf/meninos.pdf |title=Meninos Emasculados de Altamira: Resumo do Caso |trans-title=Emaculated Boys of Altamira: Case Summary |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Hospital das Cl\u00ednicas da Universidade de S\u00e3o Paulo]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070611153409/http://www.hcnet.usp.br/ipq/nufor/pdf/meninos.pdf |archive-date=11 June 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Jorge Luiz Thais Martins]]: former [[Military Firefighters Corps]] colonel who killed nine drug addicts from August 2010 and January 2011 to avenge the death of his son.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/cotidiano/866813-ex-comandante-dos-bombeiros-do-pr-e-suspeito-de-matar-9.shtml |title=Ex-comandante dos bombeiros do PR \u00e9 suspeito de matar 9 |trans-title=Former PR fire chief is suspected of killing 9 |first=Jean-Philip |last=Struck |date=27 January 2011 |newspaper=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] |language=pt |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Marcos Antunes Trigueiro]]: known as \"The Industrial Maniac\"; former taxi driver who killed five women from 2009 to 2010 in [[Contagem]] and [[Belo Horizonte]].\n\n===Burundi===\n*[[Ivomoku Bakusuba]]: confessed to having killed over 67 children. Committed suicide, \"probably in the late 1940s, or in the early 1950s\".\n\n===Bulgaria===\n*[[Hristo Georgiev (serial killer)|Hristo Georgiev]]: also known as \"The Sadist\"; former militiaman who murdered four women and one man in [[Sofia]] from 1974 to 1980; executed 1980.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://socbg.com/2015/09/%D0%BC%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%86%D0%B8%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B5%D1%80-%D1%81%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%B5%D1%86-%D1%85%D0%B2%D1%8A%D1%80%D0%BB%D1%8F-%D0%B2-%D1%83%D0%B6%D0%B0%D1%81-2.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0435\u0440-\u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0435\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0435\u0446 \u0445\u0432\u044a\u0440\u043b\u044f \u0432 \u0443\u0436\u0430\u0441 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437 70-\u0442\u0435 \u2013 II \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442 |trans-title=A serial killer plagues Sofia in the 1970s - Part II |first=Stoyan |last=G\u016dl\u016dbov |date=September 2015 |website=\u0421\u043f\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0442 \u041d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0440\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 [Memories of the Peoples Republic] |language=bg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Sokrat Kirshveng]]: also known as \"The Killer with the [[Adze]]\"; murdered two of his lovers in 1919, for which he was sentenced to death; commuted to 17 years imprisonment, and upon release in 1937, murdered his aunt and uncle-in-law; executed 1937.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://fakti.bg/life/300951-zloveshtata-istoria-na-parvia-serien-ubiec-v-balgaria-jestokia-sokrat-kirshveng |title=\u0417\u043bo\u0432e\u0449a\u0442a \u0438c\u0442o\u0440\u0438\u044f \u043da \u043f\u044a\u0440\u0432\u0438\u044f ce\u0440\u0438e\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438e\u0446 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433a\u0440\u0438\u044f - \u0436ec\u0442o\u043a\u0438\u044f Co\u043a\u0440a\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0448\u0432e\u043d\u0433 |trans-title=The creepy story of Bulgaria's first serial killer - the cruel Sokrat Kirshveng |first=Milena |last=Tracheva |date=4 May 2018 |website=Fakti.bg |language=bg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lenko Latkov]]: murdered three elderly women in [[Haskovo Province]] from 1999 to 2000 and raped two children; suspected in another three killings in [[Plovdiv Province]]; murdered by his cellmate in 2003.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://old.segabg.com/article.php?id=103720 |title=\u041e\u0441\u044a\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043d\u0430 8 \u0433. \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0438\u043b \u0434\u043e \u0441\u043c\u044a\u0440\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0435\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0435\u0446 \u043d\u0430 \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438 |trans-title=Man sentenced to 8 years in jail beats to death serial killer of women |first=Hristo |last=Dimitrov |date=16 September 2003 |website=Sega.bg |language=bg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mihail Leshtarski]]: also known as \"The Killer from the Cave\"; habitual thief who lived in the mountains, suspected of murdering at least five elderly pensioners from 2009 to 2011; convicted of one murder and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://btvnovinite.bg/kriminalno/dve-dozhivotni-prisdi-za-ubietsa-ot-peshcherata.html |title=\u0434\u0432\u0435 \u0434\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0434\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \"\u0443\u0431\u0438\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0435\u0448\u0447\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0430\" |trans-title=Two life sentences for \"The Killer from the Cave\" |date=21 March 2013 |website=[[bTV (Bulgaria)|bTV News]] |language=bg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ludwig Tolumov and Ivan Serafimov]]: also known as \"The Sour and The Sweet\"; criminal duo jointly responsible for three murders from May to July 2000; Serafimov, solely responsible for a 1996 murder, was later murdered by Tolumov, who was himself arrested and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimes.bg/%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B8/8310-%D1%81%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B9%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B5-%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%B9%D1%86%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B1%D1%8A%D0%BB%D0%B3%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8%D1%8F-%D1%83%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%B9%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B2%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%BE-%D0%B4%D1%83%D0%BE.html |title=\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f. \u0423\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0434\u0443\u043e |trans-title=Bulgaria's Serial Killers. The Deadly Duo |date=18 January 2015 |website=Crimes.bg |language=bg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Canada===\n*[[Gerald Thomas Archer]]: known as \"the London Chambermaid Slayer\"; killed three female hotel employees in his hometown of [[London, Ontario]]; died of a heart attack in 1995.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://london.ctvnews.ca/new-book-claims-london-was-once-serial-killer-capital-of-the-world-1.1726530 |title=New book claims London was once serial killer capital of the world |date=12 March 2014 |website=[[CTV News]] London |accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/19/serial-killer-london-ontario-canada |title=What turned one city in Canada into the 'serial killer capital' of the world? |last=Lindzon |first=Jared |date=19 August 2015 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Bernardo]]: also known as \"the [[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]] Rapist\"; a [[Toronto]] serial rapist who killed three teenage girls (including his wife's sister) with the aid of his wife [[Karla Homolka]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.cios.org/EJCPUBLIC/007/4/007415.HTML |title=Journalism Ethics and the Internet: Ethical Implications of Online Defiance of a Canadian Publication Ban |first=Eric B. |last=Easton |journal=The Electronic Journal of Communication / La Revue Electronique de Communication |volume=7 |number=4 |date=1997 |publisher=Communication Institute for Online Scholarship |accessdate=July 23, 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Wayne Boden]]: also known as \"the Vampire Rapist\" killed four women between 1968 and 1971; died in prison 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title=Doesn't Look Like a Killer |last=Noel |first=Albert |date=13 April 1972 |newspaper=[[Montreal Gazette]] |page=33}}</ref>\n*[[John Martin Crawford]]: convicted in 1996 for the murders of three women in [[Saskatoon]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.danielnpaul.com/SerialKiller-JohnMartinCrawford.html |title=Serial Killer - John Martin Crawford |first=Daniel N. |last=Paul |authorlink=Daniel N. Paul |website=danielnpaul.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[L\u00e9opold Dion]]: also known as \"Monster of [[Pont-Rouge]]\"; raped and killed four young boys in 1960;<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://archive.macleans.ca/article/1963/9/21/the-tragic-history-of-a-sex-criminal |title=The Tragic History of a Sex Criminal |last=Fulford |first=Robert |date=21 September 1963 |magazine=[[Maclean's]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> murdered in 1972 by a fellow prison inmate.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.erudit.org/revue/crimino/1976/v9/n1-2/017057ar.pdf |title=Litt\u00e9rature carc\u00e9rale qu\u00e9b\u00e9coise |trans-title=Qu\u00e9bec Prison Literature |last=Brunet-Aubry |first=Lise |date=1976 |journal=Criminologie |language=fr |volume=9 |number=1\u20132 |pages=191\u2013195 |doi=10.7202/017057ar |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[\u00c9rudit]]}}</ref>\n*[[William Patrick Fyfe]]: convicted of killing five women in [[Montreal]] between 1979 and 1999; suspect in several other murders.\n*[[Russell Maurice Johnson]]: also known as the \"Bedroom Strangler\"; convicted of raping and murdering three women in the 1970s; total number of victims later found to be higher.\n*[[Gilbert Paul Jordan]]: also known as the \"Boozing Barber\", killed between eight and ten women by alcohol poisoning in [[Vancouver]]; died in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/predator-back-in-jail-1.236346 |title='Predator' back in jail |date=31 August 2000 |website=CBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://justcriminals.info/2017/01/03/gilbert-paul-jordan-1965-1988/ |title=Gilbert Paul Jordan \u2013 1965-1988 |date=3 January 2017 |website=Criminal Encyclopedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Joseph LaPage]]: also known as the \"French Monster\"; murdered four women in Canada and the US from 1867 to 1875; executed 1878.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn86072143/1878-03-22/ed-1/seq-1/#date1=1878&sort=date&date2=1878&words=Joseph+JOSEPH+La+LaPage+PAGE&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=11&state=&rows=20&proxtext=Joseph+LaPage&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1 |title=Justice At Last: Joseph LaPage Expiates His Awful Crimes on the Gallows |newspaper=Burlington Weekly Free Press |location=[[Burlington, Vermont]] |volume=XXIV |number=39 |date=22 March 1878 |via=[[Chronicling America]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Cody Legebokoff]]: one of Canada's youngest serial killers, convicted of murdering three women and a teenage girl around [[Prince George, British Columbia|Prince George]], [[British Columbia]] between 2009 and 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nationalpost.com/opinion/christie-blatchford-cody-legebokoff-without-remorse-is-convicted-of-four-counts-of-first-degree-murder |title=Cody Legebokoff found guilty in murder of four B.C. women |last=Blatchford |first=Christie |author-link=Christie Blatchford |date=September 11, 2014 |newspaper=[[National Post]] |access-date=2018-05-13 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20140912132427/http://fullcomment.nationalpost.com/2014/09/11/christie-blatchford-cody-legebokoff-without-remorse-is-convicted-of-four-counts-of-first-degree-murder/ |archive-date=2014-09-12}}</ref>\n*[[Allan Legere]]: also known as \"Monster of the [[Miramichi]]\"; killer of five individuals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.douglaschristie.com/DHC/TommyRoss.htm |title=Profiles of 5 SHU Inmates: Canada's most dangerous cons |last=Cameron |first=Corey |date=November 25, 2001 |website=[[Canoe.com|Canoe News]] |access-date=March 22, 2014 |via=douglaschristie.com}}</ref>\n*[[2010\u20132017 Toronto serial homicides|Bruce McArthur]]: [[Toronto]] man who killed and dismemembered eight men between 2010 and 2017; sentenced to life in prison in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/02/08/us/bruce-mcarthur-toroto-serial-killer-sentencing/index.html |title=Toronto serial killer Bruce McArthur sentenced to life in prison |first=Ray |last=Sanchez |date=8 February 2019 |website=[[CNN]] |accessdate=8 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michael Wayne McGray]]: killed seven people, including a woman and child and a cellmate, claims to have killed eleven others.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/M/McGRAY_michael_wayne.php |title=McGray, Michael Wayne |first=Elisabeth |last=Wetsch |website=Serial Killer Crime Index |access-date=2018-05-13 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303230637/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/M/McGRAY_michael_wayne.php |archive-date=3 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/i-got-very-good-at-it-killer-says/article4162061/ |title='I got very good at it,' killer says |last=Anderssen |first=Erin |date=24 March 2000 |newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Dellen Millard and Mark Smich|Dellen Millard]]: convicted of murdering three people, including his father; two were killed with help from accomplice Mark Smich.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/dellen-millards-conviction-in-fathers-death-makes-him-canadas-latest-serial-killer |title=Dellen Millard's conviction in father's death makes him Canada's latest serial killer |first=Adrian |last=Humphreys |date=September 24, 2018 |newspaper=National Post |accessdate=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Clifford Olson]]: murdered eleven children in British Columbia in the early 1980s; died in prison 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060621/olson_parole_hearing_060621/20060621 |title=Parole hearing being planned for Clifford Olson |date=June 21, 2006 |website=[[CTV News]] |accessdate=September 21, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060701075918/http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060621/olson_parole_hearing_060621/20060621 |archivedate=July 1, 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Pickton]]: [[Port Coquitlam]], British Columbia man charged with the first degree murders of 26 women; allegedly confessed to 49 murders; convicted December 9, 2007 of six charges; reduced to second degree murder.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.missingpeople.net/2005/pickton_indictments.htm |title=Pickton Indictments, 27 first degree murders charges |date=May 25, 2005 |website=MissingPeople.net |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Yves Trudeau (biker)|Yves Trudeau]]: known as \"the Mad Bumper\"; former member of an [[outlaw motorcycle gang]] took part in 43 murders between 1973 and 1985; died of [[bone-marrow cancer]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=8a8cea7d-bcd5-43b3-bb16-f68c53506479 |title=He killed at least 43, now ex-biker faces death |last=Cherry |first=Paul |date=16 July 2008 |newspaper=[[Montreal Gazette]] |accessdate=9 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106084424/http://www.canada.com/montrealgazette/news/story.html?id=8a8cea7d-bcd5-43b3-bb16-f68c53506479 |archivedate=6 November 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Elizabeth Wettlaufer]]: registered nurse who murdered eight senior citizens in [[Ontario]] with fatal injections of [[insulin]], and gave non-fatal injections to six others, between 2007 and 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2016/10/29/from-caring-nurse-to-accused-serial-killer-who-is-elizabeth-wettlaufer.html |title=From caring nurse to accused serial killer: who is Elizabeth Wettlaufer? |last1=Gillis |first1=Wendy |last2=Siekierska |first2=Alicja |last3=Goffin |first3=Peter |lastauthoramp=yes |date=October 29, 2016 |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |accessdate=June 3, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Russell Williams (criminal)|Russell Williams]]: former Colonel of the [[Canadian Forces]]; killed two women and is suspected of murdering a third; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/article/873244--col-russell-williams-a-serial-killer-like-none-police-have-seen |title=Col. Russell Williams: A serial killer like none police have seen |first1=Jim |last1=Rankin |first2=Sandro |last2=Contenta |date=October 9, 2010 |newspaper=Toronto Star |accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Woodcock]]: murdered three children in 1956 and 1957 in Toronto and a fellow psychiatric institute patient in 1991; died while incarcerated in 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/ontario/article/776986--the-serial-killer-they-couldn-t-cure-dies-behind-bars#article |title=The serial killer they couldn't cure dies behind bars |first=Mark |last=Bourrie |date=March 9, 2010 |newspaper=Toronto Star |accessdate=July 22, 2010}}</ref>\n\n===Chile===\n*[[\u00c9mile Dubois (murderer)|\u00c9mile Dubois]]: French-born murderer and folk hero who's revered as \"The Chilean Robin Hood\" for killing alleged usurers; executed 1907.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias/site/artic/20070323/pags/20070323170038.html |title=Emile Dubois, el inmigrante franc\u00e9s que se convirti\u00f3 en mito |trans-title=Emile Dubois, the French immigrant who became a myth |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=24 March 2007 |newspaper=[[La Naci\u00f3n (Chile)|La Naci\u00f3n]] |location=Santiago, Chile |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090328140322/http://www.lanacion.cl/prontus_noticias/site/artic/20070323/pags/20070323170038.html |archive-date=28 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Catalina de los R\u00edos y Lisperguer]]: also known as \"La Quintrala\"; 17th century landowner tried for over 40 murders; died 1665.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.biografiadechile.cl/detalle.php?IdContenido=82&IdCategoria=8&IdArea=28&status=&TituloPagina=Historia%20de%20Chile |title=Catalina de los R\u00edos y Lisperguer: 1604-1665 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Biografia de Chile |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Julio P\u00e9rez Silva]]: also known as \"Psychopath from [[Alto Hospicio]]\", sentenced to life imprisonment for murdering fourteen women from 1998 to 2001.\n*[[Vi\u00f1a del Mar psychopaths|Jorge Sagredo and Carlos Topp]]: also known as the \"Vi\u00f1a del Mar Psychopaths\"; committed ten murders and four rapes from 5 August 1980 to 1 November 1981 in [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar]]; executed by firing squad on 29 January 1985; they were the last people executed in Chile.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sicopatasdevina.cl/caso/ |title=El Caso Completo |trans-title=The Complete Case |website=Sicopatas De Vi\u00f1a.cl |accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n\n===People's Republic of China===\n*[[Bai Baoshan]]: robber who attacked several police stations in three provinces; killed fifteen people; executed 1998.\n*[[Dong Wenyu]]: burglar-rapist who killed six people during break-ins between March and May 2006; also raped the female victims' corpses; executed 2007.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.163.com/07/1128/21/3UDSA31V00011229.html |title=Rapist-murderer Dong Wenyu is in Fufa, Zhejiang today |access-date=9 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071130182348/http://news.163.com/07/1128/21/3UDSA31V00011229.html |archive-date=30 November 2007 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Li Yijiang]]: killed seven people in the early 2000s; shot in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news3.xinhuanet.com/legal/2003-08/29/content_1053437.htm |title=\u5317\u4eac\u8fde\u73af\u6740\u4eba\u6848\u53d8\u6001\u7537\u5b50\u7684\u5b66\u751f\u65f6\u4ee3 |trans-title=The student life of the man in the Beijing serial killing case |date=2003-08-29 |website=[[Xinhua News]] |language=zh-hans |access-date=2018-08-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304211517/http://news3.xinhuanet.com/legal/2003-08/29/content_1053437.htm |archive-date=2016-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Liu Pengli]]: 2nd century BC Han prince; one of the earliest serial killers attested by historical sources.<ref>''[[Book of Han]]''</ref>\n*[[Long Zhimin]]: together with his wife Yan Shuxia, lured in and subsequently murdered 48 people in his home for various reasons between 1983 and 1985; both executed 1985.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cpd.com.cn/n10216060/n10216162/c25545632/content_1.html|title=The first major criminal case in New China was decrypted: Long Zhimin killed 48 people at home|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=China Police Network|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Gao Chengyong]]: nicknamed the \"Chinese Jack the Ripper\", killed eleven women between 1988 and 2002 in [[Baiyin]] and [[Inner Mongolia]]; executed 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/30/world/asia/china-jack-the-ripper-gao-chengyong.html |title=Man Thought to Be China's Jack the Ripper Is Arrested |last=Forsythe |first=Michael |date=2016-08-29 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=2018-03-30 |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n*[[Gong Runbo]]: found guilty of the murders of six children and teenagers in aged between 9 and 16 from 2005 to 2006 in [[Jiamusi]]; executed 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/R/RUNBO_gong.php |title=Runbo Gong |first=Elisabeth |last=Wetsch |website=Serial Killer Crime Index |accessdate=16 February 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140906023442/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/R/RUNBO_gong.php |archive-date=2014-09-06}}</ref>\n*[[Huang Yong (murderer)|Huang Yong]]: between September 2001 and 2003 killed at least seventeen teenage boys; executed in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/q-z/yong.html |title=Huang Yong |website=Serial Killers A-Z |accessdate=2010-12-08 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091027121734/http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/q-z/yong.html |archivedate=October 27, 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Shen Changyin and Shen Changping]]: found guilty of the murders of eleven prostitutes between 1999 and 2004 in [[Lanzhou]] and [[Taiyuan]]; sentenced to death in 2005.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2004/09/03/1093939117543.html |title=Brothers 'confess' to butchering 11 women: report |date=2004-09-03 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |accessdate=2008-09-09}}</ref>\n*[[Wang Qiang (serial killer)|Wang Qiang]]: 45 murder victims and ten rapes; executed on 17 November 2005.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.sohu.com/20030719/n224814133.shtml |title=\u8fbd\u7279\u5927\u7cfb\u5217\u6740\u4eba\u3001\u5f3a\u5978\u6848\u544a\u7834 \u767e\u65e5\u4f1a\u6218\u663e\u6210\u6548 |trans-title=A Series of Murders and Rapes in Liaoning Province solved: The Hundred Days Battle Proved Effective |date=2003-07-19 |website=[[Sohu]] |language=zh |accessdate=2010-07-30}}</ref>\n*[[Wang Zongfang and Wang Zongwei]]: known as \"Er Wang\"; murderers who killed soldiers using guns and grenades in [[Hunan]], [[Hubei]] and Jiangsu; killed by armed forces in 1983.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.jschina.com.cn/TodayJiangsu/201202/t964675.shtml |title=Killers ran, but they couldn't hide |website=JS China.com |accessdate=February 24, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109065851/http://english.jschina.com.cn/TodayJiangsu/201202/t964675.shtml |archive-date=November 9, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Yang Xinhai]]: also known as the \"Monster Killer\"; confessed to killing 65 people between 2000 and 2003; executed in 2004.<ref name=APN>{{cite news |url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Chinese+serial+killer+gets+death+sentence+for+slaying+67.-a0113064211 |title=Chinese serial killer gets death sentence for slaying 67 |date=2004-02-09 |newspaper=Asian Political News |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[The Free Library]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5azflHCF8?url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0WDQ/is_2004_Feb_9/ai_113064211/pg_1?tag=artBody;col1 |archivedate=21 September 2008 }}</ref>\n*[[Zhang Jun (serial killer)|Zhang Jun]]: robber who killed 28 people from 1993 to 2000 throughout China with accomplices; captured and executed in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://v.qq.com/x/page/x0185r4ugpa.html |title=\u6293\u6355\u5f20\u541b\uff01 |trans-title=Arrest Zhang Jun! |date=February 22, 2016 |website=[[Tencent]] |language=zh-hans |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Zhang Yongming]]: killed eleven males between March 2008 and April 2012; executed in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/news/world/2013-01-10-cannibal-killer-who-sold-human-flesh-is-executed/ |title=Cannibal killer who sold human flesh is executed |date=10 January 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sowetan]] |location=Johannesburg |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Zhao Zhihong]]: known as \"The Smiling Killer\"; raped and killed six women in Inner Mongolia between 1996 and 2005; confessed to a murder for which an innocent man was executed; executed 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://lenta.ru/news/2019/07/30/justice/ |title=\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043d\u0435\u0432\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u044b\u043c |trans-title=Serial killer executed following execution of innocent man |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=July 30, 2019 |website=[[Lenta.ru]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Zhou Kehua]]: former soldier who targeted ATM users; killed ten people in [[Jiangsu]] and [[Chongqing]] and evaded the law for 8 years, before being killed in 2012 in a shootout with police after a year-long manhunt.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.china.org.cn/china/2012-08/14/content_26226704.htm |title=Serial killer Zhou Kehua dead |date=2012-08-14 |website=[[China Internet Information Center]] |accessdate=2012-08-14}}</ref>\n\n===Colombia===\n*[[Andr\u00e9s Leonardo Achipiz]]: also known as \"The Fish\"; psychopathic hired killer who killed between 30 and 35 people in Bogot\u00e1 from 2009 to 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.elcolombiano.com/historico/pescadito-JBEC_240966 |title=Pescadito |last=Correa |first=Juan David Ram\u00edrez |date=6 May 2013 |newspaper=[[El Colombiano]] |location=[[Medell\u00edn]] |language=es |access-date=27 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Daniel Camargo Barbosa]]: also known as \"The Sadist of El Charquito\", who is believed to have raped and killed over 150 young girls in Colombia and Ecuador during the 1970s and 1980s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/cronologia-de-los-asesinatos-de-camargo-barbosa-26954-26954.html |title=Cronologia de los Asesinatos de Camargo Barbosa |trans-title=Timeline of the Murders of Barbosa Camargo |date=15 November 1994 |newspaper=[[Hoy (Ecuadorian newspaper)|Hoy]] |location=Ecuador |language=es |accessdate=31 March 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100529160106/http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/cronologia-de-los-asesinatos-de-camargo-barbosa-26954-26954.html |archivedate=29 May 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Manuel Octavio Berm\u00fadez]]: also known as \"El Monstruo de los Ca\u00f1aduzales\" (The Monster of the Cane Fields); confessed to raping and killing at least twenty-one children in remote areas of Colombia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kienyke.com/historias/manuel-octavio-bermudez-el-monstruo-de-los-canaduzales/ |title=La historia de cinco asesinos en serie de Colombia |trans-title=The story of five serial killers from Colombia |date=July 20, 2013 |website=KienyKe |language=es |accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Esneda Ruiz Cata\u00f1o]]: also known as \"The Predator\"; murdered three husbands for life insurance between 2001 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcnradio.com/colombia/capturada-mujer-acusada-de-asesinar-sus-esposos-para-cobrar-millonarios-seguros-de-vida |title=Capturada mujer acusada de asesinar a sus esposos para cobrar millonarios seguros de vida |trans-title=Captured woman accused of murdering her husbands to collect millions in life insurance |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=30 January 2013 |website=[[RCN Radio]] |language=es |access-date=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Tom\u00e1s Maldonado Cera]]: also known as \"The Satanist\"; murdered between seven and ten people in satanic rituals in Barranquilla.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/colombia/2019/02/14/los-macabros-detalles-del-asesino-serial-colombiano-que-le-rendia-tributo-al-diablo/ |title=Los macabros detalles del asesino serial colombiano que le rend\u00eda tributo al diablo |trans-title=The macabre details of the Colombian serial killer who paid tribute to the devil |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=14 February 2019 |website=[[Infobae]] |language=es |access-date=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Cristopher Ch\u00e1vez Cuellar]]: also known as \"The Soulless\"; killed six people, including four underage brothers, in 2015; suspected of at least fifteen murders dating back to the 1990s; sentenced to 40 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cambioin.com/featured-videos/el-asesino-de-los-4-ninos-del-caqueta-comenzo-su-carrera-criminal-en-ibague |title=El asesino de los 4 ni\u00f1os del Caqueta, comenz\u00f3 su carrera criminal en Ibagu\u00e9 |trans-title=The murderer of 4 children of in Caqueta, began his criminal career in Ibagu\u00e9 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=16 February 2015 |website=CambioIn |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528142539/https://www.cambioin.com/featured-videos/el-asesino-de-los-4-ninos-del-caqueta-comenzo-su-carrera-criminal-en-ibague |archive-date=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Luis Garavito]]: also known as \"The Beast\"; admitted to murder and rape of 140 young boys in the 1990s.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://benecke.com/pdf/serial_killer_bartsch_mark_benecke.pdf |title=Two Homosexual Pedophile Sadistic Serial Killers: J\u00fcrgen Bartsch (Germany, 1946\u20131976) and Luis Alfredo Garavito Cubillos (Colombia, 1957) |first1=M. |last1=Benecke |first3=M. |last2=Rodriquez |first4=A. |last3=Zabeck |first2=A. |last4=M\u00e4tzler |lastauthoramp=yes |journal=Minerva Medicolegale |volume=125 |number=3 |date=September 2005 |pages=153\u2013169 |publisher=Edizioni Minerva Medica S.p.A. |location=[[Turin]] |accessdate=20 June 2010 |issn=0026-4849}}</ref>\n*[[Rub\u00e9n Villalobos Herrera]]: also known as \"The Black Canes Monster\"; necrophile who raped and murdered nine women from 2012 to 2017; currently awaiting trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://diariodelsur.com.co/noticias/judicial/video-cayo-feminicida-y-violador-en-serie-que-aterrorizaba-311093 |title=Cay\u00f3 feminicida y violador en serie que aterrorizaba a Villavicencio |trans-title=Serial killer and rapist who terrorized Villavicencio captured |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=31 May 2017 |website=Diario del Sur |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mar\u00eda Concepci\u00f3n Ladino]]: also known as \"The Killer Witch\"; defrauded and murdered six people from 1994 to 1998; sentenced to 40 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://diariolavoz.net/2013/05/05/la-bruja-asesina/ |title=La bruja asesina |trans-title=The murderous witch |last=Pujadas |first=Edda |date=5 May 2013 |website=Diario La Voz |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro L\u00f3pez (serial killer)|Pedro L\u00f3pez]]: also known as \"The Monster of the Andes\"; claimed to have raped and killed more than 300 girls across South America between 1969 and 1980.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://users.erols.com/mwhite28/lopez_ap.htm |title=Who is Pedro Lopez? |date=20 February 2005 |website=Matthew White |accessdate=2013-08-25 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071021224003/http://users.erols.com/mwhite28/lopez_ap.htm |archivedate=21 October 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Jaime Iv\u00e1n Mart\u00ednez]]: also known as \"The Guarne Killer\"; killed at least four people in [[Guarne]] from 2005 to 2016, including his wife and two children; sentenced to 42 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcnradio.com/colombia/antioquia/condenan-42-anos-prision-al-llamado-asesino-serie-guarne |title=Condenan a 42 a\u00f1os de prisi\u00f3n al llamado \"asesino en serie\" de Guarne |trans-title=The \"serial killer\" of Guarne sentenced to 42 years in prison |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 January 2017 |website=[[RCN Radio]] |language=es |access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nepomuceno Matallana]]: also known as \"Doctor Mata\"; fraudster convicted of a 1947 murder of a merchant, but suspected of other murders; died 1960 from [[bronchitis]] combined with heart failure.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.banrepcultural.org/blaavirtual/revistas/credencial/enero2004/raro.htm |title=Doctor Mata, el tinterillo asesino |last=Aguilera Pe\u00f1a |first=Mario |date=January 2004 |journal=Credencial Historia |location=[[Bogot\u00e1]] |number=169 |issn=0121-3296 |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Biblioteca Virtual del Banco de la Rep\u00fablica}}</ref>\n*[[Luis Alberto Malag\u00f3n Su\u00e1rez]]: also known as \"The Sadist of Rinc\u00f3n\"; kidnapped, raped and killed five girls from 1995 to 1997 in [[Suba, Bogot\u00e1|Suba]]; imprisoned in 2012 for the 2001 murder of his wife.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/MAM-1336175 |title=Capturado Homicida de Ni\u00f1as de Suba |trans-title=Murderer of Suba girls captured |date=1 February 2002 |newspaper=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]] |language=es |accessdate=August 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[John Jairo Moreno Torres]]: also known as \"Johnny the Leper\"; gang leader who brutally murdered at least four people between 1997 and 1998 in [[Bogot\u00e1]]; murdered in prison by several inmates in 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://caracol.com.co/radio/1998/02/28/nacional/0888649200_088073.html |title=Sic\u00f3pata de 20 a\u00f1os ten\u00eda aterrorizados a los habitantes de Kennedy y Fontib\u00f3n |trans-title=20-year-old psychopath terrified the inhabitants of Kennedy and Fontib\u00f3n |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=28 February 1998 |website=[[Caracol Radio]] |language=es |access-date=10 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Yadira Narv\u00e1ez]]: also known as \"The Queen of Scopolamine\"; poisoned between five and six men with [[Carbofuran]] in 2011, but confessed to other murders; sentenced to 100 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.diariodelhuila.com/judicial/yadira:-la-asesina-en-serie-cdgint20140518101614109 |title=Yadira: la asesina en serie |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=18 May 2014 |newspaper=Diario del Huila |language=es |access-date=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Diego Fernando Ram\u00edrez]]: also known as \"The Butcher of Buga\"; cattle rancher who murdered two men in January 2007 in the rural town of [[Buga, Valle del Cauca|Buga]]; suspected in other similar disappearances from 2006.<ref>[https://www.semana.com/nacion/articulo/el-carnicero-buga/84112-3 The Butcher of Buga] [[Semana (Colombia)|''Semana'']]. Accessed February 22, 2020. (in Spanish)</ref>\n*[[Luis Gregorio Ram\u00edrez Maestre]]: killed 30 motorists in various municipalities; captured in 2012; expected to be released in 2032.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/CMS-12745082 |title=La macabra ruta del 'Monstruo de Tenerife' |trans-title=The macabre journey of the 'Monster of Tenerife' |first=Juli\u00e1n Espinos |last=Rojas |date=16 April 2013 |newspaper=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|El Tiempo]] |language=es |access-date=8 September 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Fredy Armando Valencia]]: also known as \"The Monster of [[Monserrate]]\"; raped and strangled at least nine drug-addicted women in the [[Eastern Hills, Bogot\u00e1|Eastern Hills]] region between 2012 and 2014; confessed to more murders; sentenced to 36 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcnradio.com/colombia/la-historia-del-monstruo-de-monserrate-asesino-en-serie-de-mujeres |title=La historia del 'Monstruo de Monserrate', asesino en serie de mujeres |trans-title=The story of the 'Monster of Monserrate', serial killer of women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 December 2015 |website=[[RCN Radio]] |language=es |access-date=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Costa Rica===\n*[[Adri\u00e1n Arroyo Guti\u00e9rrez]]: also known as \"The Southern Psychopath\"; raped and strangled between six and eleven drug-addicted prostitutes in [[San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica|San Jos\u00e9]]; sentenced to 110 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.diarioextra.com/Noticia/detalle/306803/psicopata-del-sur-acepta-6--asesinatos-y-2-violaciones |title=\"Psic\u00f3pata del Sur\" acepta 6 asesinatos y 2 violaciones |trans-title=\"Psycho of the South\" admits to 6 murders and 2 rapes |first=Carlos Castro |last=Gamboa |date=September 9, 2016 |newspaper=[[Diario Extra (Costa Rica)|Diario Extra]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Croatia===\n*[[Vinko Pintari\u0107]]: murdered five people, including his wife, between 1973 and 1990; escaped from custody three times, killed in a 1991 shootout with the police.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vjesnik.hr/Pdf/2003/01/08/21A21.PDF |title=Ako Baricu ne puste iz pritvora pobit \u0107u 30 ljudi |last=Lazarevi\u0107 |first=Branko |date=8 January 2003 |newspaper=[[Vjesnik]] |language=hr |accessdate=2010-04-04}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Czech Republic===\n*[[Oto Biederman]]: member of the \"Kol\u00ednsk\u00fd Gang\" who murdered five people from 1993 to 1995, including a former accomplice; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rozhlas.cz/dvojka/historiezlocinu/_zprava/pripad-apollo-aneb-pet-vrazd-kolinskeho-gangu--1661034 |title=P\u0159\u00edpad Apollo aneb p\u011bt vra\u017ed Kol\u00ednsk\u00e9ho gangu |trans-title=The Apollo case or the five murders of the Kol\u00ednsk\u00fd gang |last1=Taud |first1=Rostislav |last2=Vojtov\u00e1 |first2=Tereza |date=19 October 2016 |website=[[Czech Radio]] |language=cs |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jaroslava Fabi\u00e1nov\u00e1]]: murdered four men between 1981 and 2003 for financial reasons; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.securitymagazin.cz/krimi/krvava-blondyna-prostitutka-ktera-muze-uspavala-hypnotiky-a-pak-je-umlatila-kladivem-rozsekala-sekackem-na-maso-nebo-znetvorila-sidlem-1404059523.html?fb_comment_id=2346677882012613_2348173891863012 |title=Krvav\u00e1 blond\u00fdna: Prostitutka, kter\u00e1 mu\u017ee usp\u00e1vala hypnotiky a pak je uml\u00e1tila kladivem, rozsekala sek\u00e1\u010dkem na maso nebo znetvo\u0159ila \u0161\u00eddlem |trans-title=Bloody blonde: A prostitute who drugged her victims then beat, slashed or stabbed them |first=Petr |last=Duchoslav |date=25 March 2018 |website=Security Magazin |language=cs |accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Marie Fik\u00e1\u010dkov\u00e1]]: female nurse in [[Su\u0161ice]] who was executed by [[hanging]] in 1961 for the murders of ten babies.\n*[[Ladislav Hojer]]: sadist who raped and strangled at least five women from 1978 to 1981 around Czechoslovakia; executed 1986.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.odsouzeni.estranky.cz/clanky/co-prinesla-media/rozhovor-s-poslednim-ceskym-katem_-pred-popravou-rvacka_-po-ni-panak-rumu___.html |title=Rozhovor s posledn\u00edm \u010desk\u00fdm katem! |trans-title=Interview with the last Czech executioner! |date=30 July 2007 |website=P\u0159\u00edb\u011bhy odsouzen\u00fdch v \u010cR |language=cs |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701230140/http://www.odsouzeni.estranky.cz/clanky/co-prinesla-media/rozhovor-s-poslednim-ceskym-katem_-pred-popravou-rvacka_-po-ni-panak-rumu___.html |archive-date=1 July 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Kate\u0159ina z Kom\u00e1rova]]: 16th-century noblewoman who tortured and maimed between 14 and 30 serfs in [[Pi\u010d\u00edn]] and [[P\u0159\u00edbram]]; exiled to [[Prague Castle]], where she died in March 1534.<ref>DA\u010cICK\u00dd Z HESLOVA, Mikul\u00e1\u0161. Pam\u011bti. Praha: Akropolis, 1996. S. 280.</ref>\n*[[V\u00e1clav Mr\u00e1zek]]: convicted of the murders of seven women around [[Chomutov]]; executed in 1957.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/cerna-kronika/vrah-mrazek-poprava-60-let-soudruzi.A171215_123038_krimi_iri/foto/IRI7003c0_DSC09263.JPG |title=Fotogalerie: \u010c\u00e1st protokolu o poprav\u011b V\u00e1clava Mr\u00e1zka |trans-title=Photogallery: Part of the protocol on the execution of V\u00e1clav Mr\u00e1zek |first=Ji\u0159\u00ed |last=P\u00e1nek |website=[[Mlad\u00e1 fronta DNES|iDNES.cz]] |language=cs |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Leci\u00e1n]]: responsible for killing three policemen and a prison officer; executed in 1927.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zpravodajstvi.olomouc.cz/view2.php?cisloclanku=2005110808 |title=Martin Leci\u00e1n - postrach Moravy |trans-title=Martin Leci\u00e1n - the terror of Moravia |date=November 9, 2005 |website=Olomouc.cz |language=cs |accessdate=February 8, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203023030/http://zpravodajstvi.olomouc.cz/view2.php?cisloclanku=2005110808 |archive-date=December 3, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Hubert Pil\u010d\u00edk]]: killed at least five people whom he helped cross the border from [[Czechoslovakia]] into [[West Germany]]; committed suicide in prison in 1951.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://plzensky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/mohl-byt-vrah-pilcik-tajnym-agentem20080824.html |title=Mohl b\u00fdt vrah Pil\u010d\u00edk tajn\u00fdm agentem? |trans-title=Could the murderer Pil\u010d\u00edk be a secret agent? |first=Miroslava |last=Vejvodov\u00e1 |date=24 August 2008 |newspaper=[[Den\u00edk|Plze\u0148sk\u00fd den\u00edk]] |language=cs |accessdate=28 January 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Roh\u00e1\u010d]]: former soldier who robbed and killed 59 people between 1568 and 1571 with his accomplices; all were executed in 1571.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.detektorweb.cz/index.4me?s=show&i=3690&mm=1&vd=1&PHPSSIDW=90374151b234840f6ae124a7c9323cc2 |title=Brut\u00e1ln\u00ed vojensk\u00e1 loupe\u017en\u00e1 vra\u017eda |trans-title=A brutal military robbery |date=30 January 2006 |website=Detektorweb.cz |language=cs |accessdate=2018-05-20}}</ref>\n*[[Ivan Roubal]]: occultist who murdered five people from 1991 to 1994; sentenced to life imprisonment and died in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.securitymagazin.cz/krimi/chovatel-prasat-a-mystik-roubal-byl-odsouzen-za-pet-vrazd-ale-jich-ma-na-svedomi-kolem-patnacti-nebo-take-zadnou-spravedlnost-privital-samostrilem-1404059599.html |title=Chovatel prasat a mystik Roubal byl odsouzen za p\u011bt vra\u017ed... |trans-title=Pig-breeder and mystic Roubal was sentenced for five murders... |date=4 April 2018 |website=SecurityMagazin.cz |language=cs |access-date=5 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Jaroslav and Dana Stodolovi]]: couple who robbed and killed eight pensioners from 2001 to 2002; both sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ahaonline.cz/clanek/musite-vedet/22265/domy-hruzy-nikdo-je-nechce-mista-kde-zabijeli-stodolovi.html |title=Domy hr\u016fzy! Nikdo je nechce... M\u00edsta, kde zab\u00edjeli Stodolovi |trans-title=Houses of horror! No one wants them...The places where the Stodolovis killed |first=Iva |last=Kot\u0115\u0161ovcov\u00e1 |date=5 March 2008 |newspaper=[[Aha! (tabloid)|Aha!]] |language=cs |accessdate=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Petr Zelenka (serial killer)|Petr Zelenka]]: male nurse convicted of murdering seven patients in [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]] by lethal injections to \"test\" doctors; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.radio.cz/en/article/85964 |title=Nurse Committed Murders To \"Test\" Doctors |last=Velinger |first=Jan |date=5 December 2006 |website=[[Radio Prague]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Denmark===\n*[[Christina Aistrup Hansen]]: nurse who killed three patients at the [[Nyk\u00f8bing Falster]] Hospital; charges changed from three murders to four attempted manslaughter charges; initially sentenced to life imprisonment, changed to 12 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://politiken.dk/indland/art5627110/Anklagers-afsluttende-bem%C3%A6rkning-Sygeplejerske-dr%C3%A6bte-i-et-bizart-skuespil |title=Anklagers afsluttende bem\u00e6rkning: Sygeplejerske dr\u00e6bte i et bizart skuespil |trans-title=Prosecutor's closing remarks: Nurse killed in a bizarre acts |first=Kristian |last=Corfixen |date=9 June 2016 |newspaper=[[Politiken]] |language=da |access-date=9 March 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Lundin]]: killed his mother in the United States in 1991, then killed his mistress and her two children in Denmark 9 years later; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://finans.tv2.dk/nyheder/article.php/lundin-morderen-der-vidste-at-ligene-sladrer/?id=8173031 |title=Lundin: Morderen der vidste at ligene sladrer |trans-title=Lundin: The killer who knew that bodies will talk |first=Niels |last=Tradsfeldt |date=9 September 2007 |website=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV 2]] |language=da |accessdate=9 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Dagmar Overbye]]: childcare provider who killed between nine and twenty-five children; sentenced to death in 1921 then [[Clemency#Related concepts|reprieved]]; died in prison on 6 May 1929.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |url=http://www.kvinfo.dk/side/170/bio/904/ |title=Dagmar Overby (1887\u20131929) |first=Hanne Rimmen |last=Nielsen |encyclopedia=[[Dansk kvindebiografisk leksikon]] |year=2003 |publisher=[[KVINFO]] |language=da |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ecuador===\n*[[Gilberto Chamba]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Machala]]\"; murdered eight people in Ecuador and one in Spain; sentenced to 45 years in prison in Spain on 5 November 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/gilberto-chamba-alias-el-monstruo-de-machala-una-historia-real-a-lo-alfred-hitchcock-250160.html |title=Gilberto Chamba alias \"El Monstruo de Machala\": Una historia real a lo Alfred Hitchcock |trans-title=Gilberto Chamba alias the \"Moster of Machala\": A true story of Alfred Hitchcock |date=8 November 2006 |newspaper=[[Hoy (Ecuadorian newspaper)|Hoy]] |location=Quito |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222001443/http://www.hoy.com.ec/noticias-ecuador/gilberto-chamba-alias-el-monstruo-de-machala-una-historia-real-a-lo-alfred-hitchcock-250160.html |archive-date=22 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Juan Fernando Hermosa]]: also known as \"Ni\u00f1o del Terror\"; minor responsible for killing twenty-three people from 1991 to 1992 in [[Quito]], mostly taxi drivers and homosexuals; sentenced to four years imprisonment and then released, later murdered on his 20th birthday by unknown assailants.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/1/el-nino-del-terror-mataba-a-balazos-video |title=El 'Ni\u00f1o del terror' mataba a balazos |trans-title=The 'Child of Terror' shot to death |date=13 June 2014 |newspaper=[[El Tel\u00e9grafo (Ecuador)|El Tel\u00e9grafo]] |language=es |accessdate=26 March 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326210719/https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/1/el-nino-del-terror-mataba-a-balazos-video |archivedate=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Egypt===\n*[[Ramadan Abdel Rehim Mansour]]: also known as \"Al-Tourbini\"; gang leader who raped and murdered homeless children across Egypt by throwing them off trains in the 2000s, sometimes burying them alive; executed in 2010.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/insideegyptlando00brad/page/199 |title=Inside Egypt: The Land of the Pharaohs on the Brink of a Revolution |first=John R. |last=Bradley |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |year=2008 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/insideegyptlando00brad/page/199 199\u2013200] |isbn=978-1-4039-8477-7 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.mawared.org/english/files/Qatrannada11.pdf |title=Street Children: From Negligence to Confrontation |journal=Qatr An-Nada: Towards a Fair Start for Children in the Arab World |pages=2\u20133 |issue=11 |year=2007 |publisher=Arab Resource Collective |accessdate=January 20, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727072155/http://www.mawared.org/english/files/Qatrannada11.pdf |archivedate=July 27, 2011}}</ref><ref name=et>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.egypttoday.com/article.aspx?ArticleID=7119 |title=Killing Kids |first=Manal |last=el-Jesri |date=January 2007 |magazine=[[Egypt Today]] |accessdate=January 20, 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080113105035/http://www.egypttoday.com/article.aspx?ArticleID=7119 |archive-date=13 January 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Raya and Sakina]]: Egypt's most famous serial killers and the first Egyptian women to be executed by the modern state of Egypt; executed along with their husbands in 1921.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/434/chrncls.htm |title=The women killers |first=Yunan Labib |last=Rizk |date=23 June 1999 |newspaper=[[Al-Ahram Weekly]] |issue=434 |accessdate=20 April 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307042506/http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/1999/434/chrncls.htm |archivedate=7 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Estonia===\n*[[Johannes-Andreas Hanni]]: murderer, rapist, and cannibal who killed three people in 1982; committed suicide in police custody on 6 November 1982<ref>{{cite web |url=http://maaja.ee/andreas-hanni-tallinna-inimsooja/ |title=Andreas Hanni \u2013 Tallinna inims\u00f6\u00f6ja |trans-title=Andreas Hanni - Tallinn cannibal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=9 April 2007 |website=Maaja |language=et |access-date=29 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Bomb man of Pae street|M\u00e4rt Ringmaa]]: also known as the \"Bomb Man of Pae Street\"; killed seven people over the course of ten years in [[Tallinn]] using [[Improvised explosive device|IEDs]] that exploded in public places.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.epl.ee/uudised/370737 |title=Pae t\u00e4nava pommimees l\u00e4heb kohtusse |trans-title=Pae Street bomb man goes to court |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 January 2007 |newspaper=[[Eesti P\u00e4evaleht]] |language=et |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070123154734/http://www.epl.ee/uudised/370737 |archive-date=23 January 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Aleksandr Rubel]]: Ukrainian-born killer who was convicted the murderers of six people in [[Tallinn]] as a minor in the late 1990s; released from prison on 8 June 2006.\n*[[Yuri Ustimenko and Dmitry Medvedev]]: Russian duo who committed robberies, killing five people; Medvedev was killed by police, and Ustimenko was captured in Poland, extradited to Estonia and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.delfi.ee/a/50939117 |title=Sarim\u00f5rvar Ustimenko toodi Eestisse t\u00e4iendatud |trans-title=Serial killer Ustimenko brought to Estonia |first=Tanel |last=\u00d5unapuu |date=12 November 2002 |newspaper=Eesti P\u00e4evaleht |language=et |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Finland===\n* [[Juhani Aataminpoika]]: also known as \"Kerpeikkari\"; murdered twelve people in the span of two months in 1849, including his parents; sentenced to death, commuted to life imprisonment; died in 1854.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hs.fi/kulttuuri/a1477882673704 |title=Juhani Adaminpoika tappoi kaksitoista ihmist\u00e4 ja koki lopulta mestaustakin karmeamman kohtalon \u2013 elokuvan taustavoimina kaksi eturivin n\u00e4yttelij\u00e4\u00e4 |trans-title=Juhani Adaminpoika killed twelve people and finally suffered the brutal fate of casting - two front-line actors behind the film |first=Veli-Pekka |last=Lehtonen |date=1 November 2016 |newspaper=[[Helsingin Sanomat]] |language=fi |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Matti Haapoja]]: convicted murderer of three, but admitted to the killing of 18. Evidence suggests having killed as many as 22\u201325 people between 1867 and 1894 in Finland and [[Siberia]]. Sentenced to life imprisonment, but committed suicide by hanging in a prison cell.\n* [[Ismo Junni]]: killed his wife in 1980, then killed four people in arson attacks at the Kivinokka allotment garden in [[Helsinki]] from 1986 to 1989; committed suicide while in custody.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Suomalainen murha 1991\u20131994 |trans-title=Finnish murder 1991\u20131994 |first=Hannes |last=Markkula |date=1994 |pages=13\u201317 |publisher=Eurooppalainen kustannustalo |location=Helsinki |language=fi |isbn=951-96267-2-7}}</ref>\n* [[Ensio Koivunen]]: also known as \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enska\"; abducted and murdered three female hitchhikers between July and August 1971; sentenced for 25 years to prison, but released in the 1980s; died in 2003.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000005218663.html |title=Kolme liftaritytt\u00f6\u00e4 l\u00e4hti viimeiselle matkalleen \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enskan\" amerikanraudan kyydiss\u00e4 |trans-title=Three hitchhiking girls began their last journey in \"H\u00e4k\u00e4-Enska\"'s American car |date=20 May 2017 |newspaper=[[Ilta-Sanomat]] |language=fi |accessdate=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Jukka Lindholm]]: murdered three women from 1985 to 1993 in and around [[Oulu]] and one in Helsinki in 2018; sentenced to life imprisonment, and is currently appealing the decision. Has spent 25 years in prison between his crimes.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000005671206.html |title=Ep\u00e4ill\u00e4\u00e4n murhasta: N\u00e4in oululaisesta Jukka Lindholmista kasvoi sarjakuristajana tunnettu Michael Maria Penttil\u00e4 \u2013 ensimm\u00e4inen uhri oli oma \u00e4iti |trans-title=Suspected Murder: Jukka Lindholm from Oulu became Michael Maria Penttil\u00e4 a well-known serial killer - the first victim was his own mother |first1=Rami |last1=M\u00e4kinen |first2=Miika |last2=Viljakainen |date=2018-05-07 |newspaper=Ilta-Sanomat |accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>\n* [[Aino Nykopp-Koski]]: a female nurse convicted of five murders and five attempted murders between 2004 and 2009. Sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/finland/8220323/Finnish-nurse-gets-life-for-murdering-five-patients.html |title=Finnish nurse gets life for murdering five patients |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 December 2010 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Oulu child murders|Kaisa Vornanen-Karaduman]]: purposefully neglected her newborn children, starving them to death between 2005 and 2013; initially convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment, later reduced to 13 years imprisonment for manslaughter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kaleva.fi/uutiset/kotimaa/yllatyskaanne-vauvasurmajutun-tuomio-muuttui-rajusti-hovissa/730196/|title=The Surprise Turn: The verdict on the baby murder case changed dramatically|last=Kemppainen|first=Susanna|date=June 10, 2016|website=Kaleva|access-date=June 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===France===\n*[[Vincenzo Aiutino]]: also known as \"The Man with the Fifty Affairs\"; Swiss man who raped and strangled three women between 1991 and 1992 in [[Meurthe-et-Moselle]]; sentenced to life imprisonment without parole.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2013/09/10/le-tueur-de-femmes-du-pays-haut |title=Vincenzo Aiutino, le tueur de femmes du pays haut |trans-title=Vincenzo Aiutino, the country's top killer of women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 September 2013 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Patrice Al\u00e8gre]]: predator who killed five women from 1989 to 1997; suspected of more murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/societe/justice/l-homme-qui-aimait-tuer-les-femmes_494034.html |title=L'homme qui aimait tuer les femmes |trans-title=The man who loved to kill women |first=Marie |last=Huret |date=7 February 2002 |magazine=[[L'Express]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Madame de Brinvilliers|Marie-Madeleine-Marguerite d'Aubray, Marquise de Brinvilliers]]: aristocratic French poisoner of three individuals; executed in 1676.<ref>{{Cite book |url=http://www.intratext.com/IXT/ENG1175/_INDEX.HTM |title=The Marquise de Brinvilliers |first=Alexandre |last=Dumas |author-link=Alexandre Dumas |date=1850s |location=Paris |publisher=Marpon et Flammarion |via=IntraText CT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Brinvilliers, Marie Madeleine Marguerite d'Aubray, Marquise de |volume=4 |page=572}}</ref>\n*[[Jean-Charles-Alphonse Avinain]]: also known as \"The Terror of [[Gonesse]]\"; butcher who killed two people in March and June 1867 for robbery purposes; guillotined that same year.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan&tt=&titre=&auteur=&plan=&personne=&quand=&lieu=&publi=&annee=&parpage=&oper1=&oper2=&oper3=&oper4=&oper5=&oper6=&histo=&atri=&dtri=&offset=16801&nbmax=100 |title=Cour d'assises of Seine. The butcher of Avinain |website=Criminocorpus |language=fr |accessdate=12 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061117130149/http://www.criminocorpus.cnrs.fr/biblio/v3/b1.php?rech=avan |archive-date=17 November 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Marcel Barbeault]]: also known as \"The Shadow Killer\"; killed seven women and a man between 1969 and 1976 during night time or early morning; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.francesoir.fr/actualite/faits-divers/grands-crimes-du-xxe-siecle-marcel-barbeault-41340.html |title=Les grands crimes du XXe si\u00e8cle : Marcel Barbeault |trans-title=The great crimes of the 20th century: Marcel Barbeault |date=9 August 2009 |newspaper=[[France-Soir]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ludivine Chambet]]: also known as \"The Poisoner of [[Chamb\u00e9ry]]\"; nurse's aide who poisoned ten elderly people from 2012 to 2013 using antidepressants; sentenced to 25 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lindependant.fr/2017/05/23/13-personnes-agees-empoisonnees-l-aide-soignante-condamnee-a-25-ans,3017863.php |title=13 personnes \u00e2g\u00e9es empoisonn\u00e9es : l'aide-soignante condamn\u00e9e \u00e0 25 ans |trans-title=13 Poisoned seniors: caregiver sentenced to 25 years |date=23 May 2017 |newspaper=[[L'Ind\u00e9pendant (Pyr\u00e9n\u00e9es-Orientales)|L'Ind\u00e9pendant]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Chanal]]: soldier and military instructor who killed seventeen men and boys between 1980 and 1987 in [[Marne (department)|Marne]]; committed suicide in 2003.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/reunionfrance/1378581/Sadistic-sergeant-tries-to-escape-serial-killer-trial.html |title=Sadistic sergeant tries to escape serial killer trial |last=Jacobson |first=Philip |date=17 December 2000 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=2016-05-14}}</ref>\n*[[Dominique Cottrez]]: murdered eight of her newborn infants between 1989 and 2006 in her home in [[Villers-au-Tertre]]; sentenced to 9 years imprisonment in 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-10803080 |title=Details emerge in French baby killing case |date=29 July 2010 |website=BBC News |accessdate=21 April 2017}}</ref>\n*[[V\u00e9ronique Courjault]]: confessed to killing three of her babies, stuffing two of them in a freezer at their family home in South Korea; sentenced to 8 years imprisonment in 2009, released 2010.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://psmag.com/social-justice/the-babies-in-the-freezer-neonaticide-pregnancy-denial-mental-illness-95639 |title=The Babies in the Freezer |first=Nabeelah |last=Jaffer |date=8 December 2014 |magazine=[[Pacific Standard]] |accessdate=28 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Martin Dumollard]]: condemned to the guillotine after having been arrested and charged with the deaths of maids from 1855 to 1861.\n*[[Michel Fourniret]]: also known as \"The Ogre of [[Ardennes]]\"; confessed to nine murders of young girls; allegedly killed ten more between 1987 and 2001.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2018/02/16/le-tueur-en-serie-michel-fourniret-a-avoue-les-meurtres-de-deux-femmes_1630327 |title=Le tueur en s\u00e9rie Michel Fourniret a avou\u00e9 les meurtres de deux femmes |trans-title=Serial killer Michel Fourniret confessed to the murders of two women |date=16 February 2018 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] |language=fr |access-date=17 February 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Gilles Garnier]]: confessed to killing four children between October 1572 and January 1573.\n*[[Guy Georges]]: also known as the \"Beast of the [[Place de la Bastille|Bastille]]\"; serving a life sentence for seven murders between 1991 and 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.crimeandinvestigation.co.uk/crime-files/beast-of-bastille-guy-georges |title=Beast of Bastille: Guy Georges \u2013 Crime Files |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=[[Crime & Investigation Network]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jacquy Haddouche]]: delinquent who attacked six women from 1992 to 2002, killed three of them; sentenced to life imprisonment; died of [[intracerebral hemorrhage]] while incarcerated.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lobservateurdebeauvais.fr/2010/10/27/beauvais-mort-de-jacquy-haddouche-en-prison/ |title=Beauvais: mort de Jacquy Haddouche en prison |trans-title=Beauvais: death of Jacquy Haddouche in prison |first=Rapha\u00ebl |last=Thiollier |date=27 October 2010 |newspaper=L'Observateur de Beauvais |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Francis Heaulme]]: also known as the \"Criminal Backpacker\"; serving a life sentence for twenty murders between 1984 and 1992.\n*[[H\u00e9l\u00e8ne J\u00e9gado]]: [[domestic servant]] who poisoned at least twenty-three people between 1833 and 1851 in [[Brittany]]; executed in 1852.\n*[[Yvan Keller]]: also known as the \"Pillow Killer\"; killed and then robbed at least twenty-three old women from 1989 to 2006; confessed to 150 murders across France, Switzerland and Germany; committed suicide before trial in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/tueur-en-serie-l-affaire-yvan-keller-est-definitivement-close-27-05-2013-2840493.php |title=Tueur en s\u00e9rie: l'affaire Yvan Keller est d\u00e9finitivement close |trans-title=Serial Killer: The Yvan Keller affair is definitely closed |date=27 May 2013 |newspaper=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr |access-date=26 November 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Fran\u00e7ois Lacenaire]]: poet and army defector who killed two men between 1834 and 1835 with his accomplices; guillotined 1836.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bonjourparis.com/history/pierre-francois-lacenaire-murder-mystery-paris/ |title=Pierre Fran\u00e7ois Lacenaire: The Murderous Poet Dandy who Inspired \"Crime and Punishment\" |last=Brouwer |first=Marilyn |date=6 September 2017 |website=BonjourParis.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Henri D\u00e9sir\u00e9 Landru]]: killed eleven people; inspired the character of ''[[Monsieur Verdoux]]'' played by [[Charlie Chaplin]]; executed by guillotine on 25 February 1922.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=srw2DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT51&dq=henri+landru#v=onepage&q=henri%20landru |title=Serial Killers & Psychopaths |last1=Cawthorne |first1=Nigel |last2=Greig |first2=Charlotte |date=21 September 2017 |publisher=Arcturus Publishing |location=London, UK |isbn=978-1-78828-657-2 |page=51}}</ref>\n*[[Claude Lastennet]]: convicted of murdering five elderly women between August 1993 and January 1994 in [[\u00cele-de-France]]; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/societe/0101225965-il-a-fait-ce-qu-il-avait-a-faire-sans-sentiment-claude-lastenet-a-etrangle-cinq-femmes-agees-aujourd-hui-l-accuse-voudrait-que-ce-proces-l-aide-a-comprendre-pourquoi-cet-autre-lui-meme-qu-il-appelle-i |title=\"Il a fait ce qu'Il avait \u00e0 faire, sans sentiment\". Claude Lastenet a \u00e9trangl\u00e9 cinq femmes \u00e2g\u00e9es. Aujourd'hui l'accus\u00e9 voudrait que ce proc\u00e8s l'aide \u00e0 comprendre pourquoi cet autre lui-m\u00eame qu'il appelle \"Il\" l'a pouss\u00e9 \u00e0 tuer |trans-title=\"He did what He had to do, without feeling.\" Claude Lastenet strangled five elderly women. Today the accused would like this trial to help him understand why this other himself whom he calls \"He\" pushed him to kill |last=Henry |first=Michel |date=23 October 1997 |newspaper=[[Lib\u00e9ration]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Celine Lesage]]: suffocated and strangled six of her newborn infants between 2000 and 2007; sentenced to 15 years imprisonment in 2007.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/mar/19/french-woman-15-years-babies |title=French woman sentenced to 15 years for killing six babies |first=Lizzy |last=Davies |date=March 19, 2010 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[\u00c9mile Louis]]: preyed on young handicapped women (seven murders) in the 1970s in [[Yonne]]; died in prison in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/4045359.stm |title=French serial killer given life |date=26 November 2004 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Christine Mal\u00e8vre]]: nurse sentenced for the murders of at least 30 [[terminally ill]] patients in [[Mantes-la-Jolie]].<ref name=\"Sage\">{{cite news|title='Mercy killer' on murder charges|last=Sage|first=Adam|date=16 June 1999|newspaper=The Times|location=London, UK|via=[[Academic OneFile]]}}<!-- |access-date=7 March 2014 --></ref>\n*[[Albert Millet]]: also known as \"The Boar of the Moors\"; killed two girlfriends in 1954 and 1979; murdered his lover's friend in 2007; committed suicide to avoid apprehension.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/albert-millet-meurtrier-jusqu-a-son-dernier-jour-21-11-2007-3291377850.php |title=Albert Millet, meurtrier jusqu'\u00e0 son dernier jour |trans-title=Albert Millet, murderer until his last day |last=Boutry |first=Timoth\u00e9e |date=November 21, 2007 |newspaper=Le Parisien |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Catherine Monvoisin]]: also known as \"La Voisin\"; 17th century poisoner-for-hire who allegedly thousands of infants; burned at the stake in 1680.<ref>{{cite book |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |date=2005 |title=The Human Predator |location=New York |publisher=[[Berkley Books]] |isbn=978-0-42526-553-6}}</ref>\n*[[Rodica Negroiu]]: also known as the \"Poisoner of Max\u00e9ville\"; Romanian woman who poisoned two husbands in [[Nancy, France|Nancy]] in 1985 and 2004; suspected of the 1982 murder of her first husband in Romania; sentenced to 20 years imprisonment, released in 2017.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/actualite/2015/01/25/ils-m-ont-vole-ma-vie |title=Rodica Negroiu : \" Ils m'ont vol\u00e9 ma vie\u2026 \" |trans-title=Rodica Negroiu: \"They stole my life ...\" |first=\u00c9ric |last=Nicolas |date=25 January 2015 |newspaper=[[L'Est R\u00e9publicain]] |language=fr |access-date=28 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Yoni Palmier]]: also known as the \"Killer of [[Essonne]]\"; shot and killed four people from 2011 to 2012 during motorcycle drive-bys; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/2015/04/02/tueur-de-l-essonne-en-larmes-l-ex-petite-amie-raconte-sa-vie-avec-l-accuse-yoni-palmier-244471.html |title=Tueur de l'Essonne : en larmes, l'ex-petite amie raconte sa vie avec l'accus\u00e9, Yoni Palmier |trans-title=Killer of Essonne: in tears, the ex-girlfriend tells her life with the accused, Yoni Palmier |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 April 2015 |website=Outre-mer la 1\u00e8re |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Thierry Paulin]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Montmartre]]\"; preyed on the elderly in the 1980s and murdered twenty-one old women.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://moreas.blog.lemonde.fr/2009/01/27/le-complice-du-tueur-des-vieilles-dames-est-libere-mathurin-paulin/ |title=Le complice du tueur des vieilles dames est lib\u00e9r\u00e9 |trans-title=The accomplice of the killer of the old ladies is released |last=Mor\u00e9as |first=G. |date=27 January 2009 |newspaper=[[Le Monde]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michel Peiry]]: also known as the \"Sadist of [[Romont]]\"; Swiss soldier who sexually abused and killed at least five hitchhikers between 1981 and 1987 in Switzerland, France and the United States; suspected of more murders.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pipiou.over-blog.com/article-13989130.html |title=Michel Peiry \"Le sadique de Romont\" |trans-title=Michel Peiry \"The sadist of Romont\" |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=22 November 2007 |website=Meurtres en tout genre |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Albert Pel]]: also known as \"The Watchmaker of [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]]; watchmaker who poisoned his parents and lovers from 1872 to 1884; sentenced to penal labour in [[New Caledonia]], where he died in 1924.<ref>{{cite book |last=Brouardel |first=Paul |title=The Pel Affair |publisher=Bailli\u00e8re |date=1886 |page=48}}</ref>\n*[[Marcel Petiot]]: doctor who killed 63 would-be refugees in Paris who were fleeing from the [[Nazis]]; executed in 1946.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/history/petiot/5.html |title=Crime Library: Serial Killers: Dr. Marcel Petiot |first=Michael |last=Newton |website=TruTV.com |access-date=2013-06-11 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007230412/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/history/petiot/5.html |archive-date=2012-10-07}}</ref>\n*[[Louis Poirson]]: also known as \"Rambo\"; [[Madagascar|Malagasy]]-born stonemason who kidnapped women from 1995 to 2000, killing four of them; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/faits-divers/plongee-dans-le-terrible-passe-du-tueur-en-serie-30-05-2002-2003110943.php |title=Plong\u00e9e dans le terrible pass\u00e9 du tueur en s\u00e9rie |trans-title=Diving into the terrible past of the serial killer |last=Albouy |first=St\u00e9phane |date=30 May 2002 |newspaper=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Victor Pr\u00e9vost]]: also known as the \"Butcher of La Chapelle\"; former peacekeeper who murdered an acquaintance and his mistress between 1877 and 1879; suspected in two other disappearances; executed 1880.<ref>{{harvsp|La Lanterne|10/12/1880|p=1|id=LL}}</ref>\n*[[Gilles de Rais]]: 15th century satanist and child killer who is reputed to have killed 400; executed on 23 October 1440.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/rais/execution_13.html |title=Gilles de Rais: The Pious Monster |first=Mark |last=Gribben |website=The Crime Library |accessdate=17 November 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419115554/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/rais/execution_13.html |archive-date=April 19, 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Tommy Recco]]: killed his godfather in 1960; released in 1977, after which he killed a total of six cashiers in [[B\u00e9ziers]] and [[Carqueiranne]] from 1979 to 1980; also suspected of murdering a trio of German tourists; one of the oldest French prisoners.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lci.fr/faits-divers/corse-le-tueur-en-serie-tommy-recco-auteur-de-7-meurtres-demande-une-nouvelle-fois-sa-liberation-a-l-age-de-83-ans-2052546.html |title=Corse : Tommy Recco, auteur de 7 meurtres, demande une nouvelle fois sa lib\u00e9ration \u00e0 l'\u00e2ge de 83 ans |trans-title=Corsica: Tommy Recco, perpetrator of 7 murders, again requests release at the age of 83 |last=Mousset |first=L. |date=19 May 2017 |website=[[La Cha\u00eene Info]] |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Sid Ahmed Rezala]]: known as \"the Killer of the Trains\"; Algerian-born serial killer who killed three women in 1999; committed suicide in custody in 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/755008.stm |title='Confession' in Peake murder |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=19 May 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[R\u00e9my Roy]]: also known as the \"[[Minitel]] Killer\"; murdered three gay men after staged sadomasochistic acts from 1990 to 1991; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/france-archive/1996/06/29/le-tueur-du-minitel-condamne-a-perpetuite-remy-roy-etait-juge-pour-le-meurtre-de-trois-homosexuels-r_173025 |title=Le tueur du Minitel condamn\u00e9 \u00e0 perp\u00e9tuit\u00e9. R\u00e9my Roy \u00e9tait jug\u00e9 pour le meurtre de trois homosexuels rencontr\u00e9s par le biais de messageries |trans-title=The killer of Minitel sentenced to life. R\u00e9my Roy was tried for the murder of three homosexuals met through couriers |last=Vital-Durand |first=Brigitte |date=29 June 1996 |newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Giuseppe Sasia]]: known as the \"Shepherds' Killer\"; Italian criminal who killed at least four men in the span of a few months in 1934 in [[Draguignan]], also suspected of a 1930 murder; executed 1936.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.retronews.fr/journal/le-temps/9-decembre-1934/123/649815/3 |title=Faits-Divers: Les assassinats de bergers dans le Haut-Var |trans-title=News in brief: The murders of shepherds in the Haut-Var |date=9 December 1934 |page=3 |newspaper=[[Le Temps (Paris)|Le Temps]] |language=fr |access-date=23 November 2019 |via=RetroNews}}</ref>\n* [[Antoinette Scieri]]: nurse who confessed to killing twelve elderly patients, convicted on 27 April 1926 and died in prison.<ref>{{cite book |last=Nash |first=Jay Robert |title=Look for the Woman: A Narrative Encyclopedia of Female Prisoners, Kidnappers, Thieves, Extortionists, Terrorists, Swindlers and Spies from Elizabethan Times to the Present |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D9zaCQAAQBAJ |date=1 November 1986 |location=Lanham, Maryland |publisher=[[M. Evans and Company]] |isbn=978-1-4617-4772-7}}</ref>\n*[[Nadir Sedrati]]: also known as the \"Cutter of the Canal\"; murdered and dismembered three people in 1999, throwing the remains into the [[Marne-Rhine Canal]]; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/faits-divers/2013/09/06/nadir-sedrati-le-depeceur-du-canal |title=Nadir Sedrati, tueur machiav\u00e9lique |trans-title=Nadir Sedrati, Machiavellian killer |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=12 September 2013 |newspaper=L'Est R\u00e9publicain |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Alfredo Stranieri]]: also known as the \"Classified Ad Killer\"; Italian-born con man who committed two double murders in 1997 and 1999; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liberation.fr/societe/1999/07/21/quatre-cadavres-avec-preuves-d-achat-ce-sont-les-ex-proprietaires-des-commerces-rachetes-par-stranie_279306 |title=Quatre cadavres avec preuves d'achat. Ce sont les ex-propri\u00e9taires des commerces rachet\u00e9s par Stranieri |trans-title=Four corpses with proof of purchase. These are the former owners of the shops bought by Stranieri |last=Bertrand |first=Olivier |date=21 July 1999 |newspaper=Lib\u00e9ration |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Tissier]]: recidivistic rapist who killed three people from 1971 to 1993; sentenced to life imprisonment with a minimum of 30 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.la-croix.com/Archives/1998-02-02/Patrick-Tissier-est-condamne-a-la-reclusion-criminelle-a-perpetuite-_NP_-1998-02-02-451354 |title=Patrick Tissier est condamn\u00e9 \u00e0 la r\u00e9clusion criminelle \u00e0 perp\u00e9tuit\u00e9 |trans-title=Patrick Tissier is sentenced to life imprisonment |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 February 1998 |newspaper=[[La Croix]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Joseph Vacher]]: also known as \"The French Ripper\" and \"The South-East Ripper\"; 19th century serial killer of eleven people; executed by guillotine on 31 December 1898.<ref>{{cite book |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.V/v/vacher-joseph.htm |first1=Brian |last1=Lane |first2=Wilfred |last2=Gregg |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |date=1992 |location=London, UK |publisher=[[Headline Publishing Group|Headline]] |isbn=978-0-74723-731-0 |accessdate=7 January 2013 |quote=Yes, I committed the crimes... I committed them all in moments of frenzy. |via=Murderpedia}}</ref>\n*[[Denis Waxin]]: pedophile who raped six children from 1985 to 1992 in the [[Nord (French department)|Nord department]], killing three of them; sentenced to life imprisonment for a minimum of 29 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nordeclair.fr/Locales/Lille/2009/08/04/le-cauchemar-du-pompiste-pedophile.shtml |title=Le cauchemar du pompiste p\u00e9dophile |trans-title=The nightmare of the pedophile pump attendant |last=Renoul |first=Bruno |date=4 August 2009 |newspaper=[[Nord \u00e9clair]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001200459/http://www.nordeclair.fr/Locales/Lille/2009/08/04/le-cauchemar-du-pompiste-pedophile.shtml |archive-date=1 October 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Jeanne Weber]]: convicted of the strangulation murders of ten children; committed suicide in custody in 1918.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://28rueaffre.eklablog.com/jeanne-weber-l-ogresse-de-la-goutte-d-or-a113380782 |title=Jeanne Weber, l'Ogresse de la Goutte d'Or |trans-title=Jeanne Weber, the Ogress of the [[Goutte d'Or]] |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=27 November 2014 |website=28 rue Affre |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Eugen Weidmann]]: German who strangled and robbed American dancer [[Jean de Koven]], shot a former accomplice, and shot dead and robbed four other people around Paris in 1937.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/1938/02/05/american-in-paris |title=American in Paris |last=Flanner |first=Janet |date=29 January 1938 |magazine=[[The New Yorker]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Germany===\n{{Main|List of German serial killers}}\n\n===Ghana===\n*[[Charles Quansah]]: known as the \"Accra Strangler\"; convicted of the [[strangulation]] deaths of nine women in [[Accra]]; suspected of killing 34; sentenced to death in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.modernghana.com/GhanaHome/NewsArchive/news_details.asp?id=VFhwck1VNUVZejA9&type=&section=&gender=General_News&menu_id=1&menu_id2=0&sub_menu_id=0 |title=Serial Killer Speaks Out |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=20 August 2003 |website=The Ghana Resource Center |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927025650/http://www.modernghana.com/GhanaHome/NewsArchive/news_details.asp?id=VFhwck1VNUVZejA9&type=&section=&gender=General_News&menu_id=1&menu_id2=0&sub_menu_id=0 |archive-date=27 September 2007}}</ref>\n\n===Greece===\n*[[Antonis Daglis]]: also known as the \"[[Athens]] Ripper\"; convicted in 1997 of the strangulation murder and dismemberment of three women and the attempted murder of six others; committed suicide in police custody in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hri.org/news/greek/ana/1996/96-01-26.ana.html |title=Police charge 21-year-old with murder of two prostitutes |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=26 January 1996 |website=Athens News Agency Bulletin |number=797 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Hermann Duft and Hans Wilhelm Bassenauer]]: Germans who murdered six persons in Greece, within a short period in 1969, were captured, tried, sentenced to death and executed in 1969.<ref name=palm>{{cite web |url=http://www.palmografos.com/permalink/20902.html#ixzz2z8BylBnB |title=\u0397 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c6\u03c4 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u039c\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03b5\u03bd\u03ac\u03bf\u03c5\u03b5\u03c1 |trans-title=The execution of Duft and Basenauer |last=Kontogiannidis |first=T\u00e1sou |date=16 December 2013 |website=Palmographos |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Aristidis Pagratidis]]: also known as the \"Ogre of Seikh Sou\"; allegedly attacked couples in the forested area of Seikh Sou in suburban [[Thessaloniki]] from 1958 to 1959, killing three people; executed 1968, and since then his guilt has been questioned.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.athensmagazine.gr/article/news/36593-oi-thewries-synwmosias-gia-ton-laquo-drako-raquo-toy-seix-soy-h-skoteinh-ypothesh-kai-ta-fonika-poy-anatrixiazoyn-akoma-kai-miso-aiwna-meta |title=\u039f\u03b9 \u03b8\u03b5\u03c9\u03c1\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c9\u03bc\u03bf\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \"\u03b4\u03c1\u03ac\u03ba\u03bf\" \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a3\u03ad\u03b9\u03c7 \u03a3\u03bf\u03c5! \u0397 \u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03c4\u03b5\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae \u03c5\u03c0\u03cc\u03b8\u03b5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c6\u03bf\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03c7\u03b9\u03ac\u03b6\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bc\u03b9\u03c3\u03cc \u03b1\u03b9\u03ce\u03bd\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03ac!!! |trans-title=The conspiracy theories about the \"dragon\" of the Sheikh Shu! The dark affair and the killings that shake even half a century later!!! |last=\u0391\u03b4\u03b1\u03bc\u03bf\u03c5 |first=\u039d\u03c4\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03bb\u03bb\u03b1\u03c3 |date=2013-04-11 |website=Athens Magazine |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kyriakos Papachronis]]: also known as the \"Ogre of [[Drama, Greece|Drama]]\"; murdered three women from 1981 to 1982, committing other crimes as well; sentenced to life imprisonment, released on bail in 2004.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.kathimerini.gr/202903/article/epikairothta/ellada/eley8eros-o-papaxronhs-poy-apokhry3e-ton-ewsforo |title=\u0395\u03bb\u03b5\u03cd\u03b8\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u03a0\u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03bf\u03ba\u03ae\u03c1\u03c5\u03be\u03b5 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0395\u03c9\u03c3\u03c6\u03cc\u03c1\u03bf |last=\u039a\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03c3\u03b7 |first=\u0395\u03bb\u03b5\u03bd\u03b1 |date=9 December 2004 |newspaper=[[Kathimerini]] |language=el |access-date=2018-05-19}}</ref>\n*[[Mariam Soulakiotis]]: also known as the \"Woman Rasputin\"; convent abbot who lured, tortured and killed 177 wealthy women and children from 1939 to 1951; died 1954.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.reporter.com.cy/greece/article/61972/i-monachi-serial-killer-mariam-tis-kerateas |title=\u0397 \u03bc\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03c7\u03ae serial killer \u039c\u03b1\u03c1\u03b9\u03ac\u03bc \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1\u03c4\u03ad\u03b1\u03c2 |trans-title=The serial killer nun Mariam of Keratea |first=\u0395\u03bb\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 |last=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 |date=2016-05-09 |website=\u03a1\u03b5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1 |language=el |access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref>\n*[[Dimitris Vakrinos]]: killed five people and attempted seven more murders for minor quarrels between 1987 and 1996; hanged himself in the prison showers in 1997.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tovima.gr/relatedarticles/article/?aid=87285 |title=\u03a4\u03bf\u2026 \u03b2\u03c1\u03bf\u03c5\u03b2\u03ac\u03ba\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c7\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03cd |first=\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b3\u03b9\u03c9\u03c4\u03b1 |last=\u039c\u03c0\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b9\u03ba\u03b1 |date=13 April 1997 |newspaper=[[To Vima]] |language=el |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Hong Kong===\n*[[Lam Kor-wan]]: sexual sadist who murdered and dismembered four women in the 1980s; sentenced to death (commuted to life imprisonment as per tradition at that time).<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scmp.com/magazines/post-magazine/short-reads/article/2106303/our-archives-capture-hong-kongs-jars-killer |title=From our archives: the capture of Hong Kong's Jars Killer |first=Jessica |last=Li |date=August 13, 2017 |newspaper=[[South China Morning Post]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lam Kwok-wai]]: murdered three women, apprehended in 1993 and sentenced to life imprisonment (capital punishment already abolished).<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/article/128162/tuen-mun-rapist-loses-plea |title=Tuen Mun rapist loses plea |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=17 August 1995 |newspaper=South China Morning Post |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Hungary===\n*[[Angel Makers of Nagyr\u00e9v]]: group of women led by Susanna Fazekas who poisoned around 300 people in the village of [[Nagyr\u00e9v]] between 1914 and 1929.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/3567679.stm |title=Unearthing Hungary husband murders |last1=Fish |first1=Jim |accessdate=10 December 2016 |website=BBC News |date=29 March 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/articles/199911/bad-girls |title=Bad Girls |first=Barry |last=Yeoman |magazine=[[Psychology Today]] |date=1 November 1999 |publisher=Sussex Publishers, LLC |accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Erzs\u00e9bet B\u00e1thory]]: [[countess]] who killed servant girls; rumored to have killed more than 600.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/bathory/7.html |title=Countess Elizabeth Bathory \u2013 The Blood Countess |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |website=The Crime Library |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815205239/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/bathory/7.html |archive-date=2011-08-15}}</ref>\n*[[Alad\u00e1r Don\u00e1szi]]: robber who killed four people from 1991 to 1992 with his accomplice L\u00e1szl\u00f3 Bene; committed suicide in prison in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.kisalfold.hu/szieszta/irnoka_volt_donaszi_a_hirhedt_gyilkos/1164138/ |title=\u00cdrnoka volt Don\u00e1szi, a h\u00edrhedt gyilkos |trans-title=Clerk was Don\u00e1szi, the notorious killer |date=25 March 2006 |website=Kisalf\u00f6ld |language=hu |accessdate=23 September 2015}}</ref>\n*[[B\u00e9la Kiss]]: murdered at least twenty-four women, escaped justice in the confusion of [[World War I]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/justice-story/killer-murdered-24-pickled-corpses-barrels-article-1.1607445 |title=Hungarian man murdered 24, pickled each corpse in barrels of alcohol in early 1900s |first=Mara |last=Bovsun |date=9 February 2014 |newspaper=[[New York Daily News]] |access-date=20 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302235328/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/justice-story/killer-murdered-24-pickled-corpses-barrels-article-1.1607445 |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[P\u00e9ter Kov\u00e1cs (serial killer)|P\u00e9ter Kov\u00e1cs]]: also known as the \"[[Martf\u0171]] Monster\"; truck driver who raped and killed between four and five women from 1957 and 1967, possibly responsible for more murders; executed 1968.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nol.hu/mozaik/hatodik_tipusu_sorozatgyilkossag-333179 |title=Hatodik t\u00edpus\u00fa sorozatgyilkoss\u00e1g |trans-title=Sixth type serial killer |date=17 May 2009 |newspaper=[[N\u00e9pszabads\u00e1g]] |language=hu |accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Guszt\u00e1v Nemesk\u00e9ri]]: also known as the \"Kat\u00f3ka Street Killer\"; killed four people between 1996 and 1999 to settle his debts, including his half-brother; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://index.hu/bulvar/gyilkos1009/ |title=T\u00e9nyleges \u00e9letfogytiglant kapott a n\u00e9gyszeres gyilkos |trans-title=The four-time killer got life imprisonment |date=9 October 2003 |website=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |language=hu |accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Zolt\u00e1n Szab\u00f3 (serial killer)|Zolt\u00e1n Szab\u00f3]]: also known as the \"Bal\u00e1stya Monster\"; killed and mutilated at least four women on his farm in [[Bal\u00e1stya]] between 1998 and 2001; committed suicide while imprisoned in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ma.hu/tart/rcikk/a/0/65744/1 |title=\u00c9letfogytiglani fegyh\u00e1z a \"bal\u00e1styai r\u00e9m\" meg\u00e9rdemelt b\u00fcntet\u00e9se |trans-title=Life imprisonment is a well-deserved punishment for \"Bal\u00e1stya's Nightmare\" |date=20 November 2003 |website=Ma.hu |language=hu |accessdate=2 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Iceland===\n*[[Axlar-Bj\u00f6rn|Bj\u00f6rn P\u00e9tursson]]: also known as \"Axlar-Bj\u00f6rn\"; killed at least nine travellers in the 16th century.\n\n===India===\n*[[Thug Behram]] (ca. 1765\u20131840): alleged to have killed over 900 people; executed in 1840.<ref>{{cite book |last=Dash |first=Mike |author-link=Mike Dash |date=2005 |title=Thug: The True Story of India's Murderous Cult |location=London, UK |publisher=Granta Books |pages=283\u2013289 |isbn=1-86207-604-9}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Ash |first=Russell |date=1995 |title=The Top Ten of Everything 1996 |location=London, UK |publisher=[[Dorling Kindersley]] |page=[https://archive.org/details/toptenofeverythi00russ_0/page/65 65] |isbn=0-7894-0196-7 |url=https://archive.org/details/toptenofeverythi00russ_0/page/65 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Rubinstein |first=William D. |author-link=William Rubinstein |date=2004 |title=Genocide: A History |location=Harlow, Essex |publisher=[[Pearson Education Limited]] |page=83 |isbn=978-0-58250-601-5}}</ref>\n*[[Seema Gavit and Renuka Shinde]] (born 1975 and 1973): sisters who kidnapped and murdered five children between 1990 and 1996.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/thieves-who-kidnapped-used-and-killed-babies |title=Thieves who kidnapped, used and killed babies |first=Atikh |last=Rashid |date=18 August 2014 |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[M. Jaishankar]] (born 1977): also known as \"Psycho Shankar\", involved in about 30 rapes, murders and robbery cases around [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref name=\"IT_how_2013\">{{cite magazine |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/psycho-shankar-how-serial-rapist-killer-was-nabbed/1/308631.html |title=Psycho Shankar \u2013 How the serial rapist and killer was nabbed |first1=T. S. |last1=Sudhir |first2=Rohini |last2=Swamy |first3=Shreesha |last3=Reddy |lastauthoramp=yes |date=6 September 2013 |magazine=[[India Today]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710200427/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/psycho-shankar-how-serial-rapist-killer-was-nabbed/1/308631.html |archivedate=10 July 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Chandrakant Jha]] (born 1967): befriended and murdered seven male migrants from 1998 to 2007; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/north/story/rohini-court-death-sentence-to-serial-killer-chandrakant-jha-153306-2013-02-05 |title=Rohini Court awards death sentence to serial killer Chandrakant Jha |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=5 February 2013 |magazine=India Today |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Joshi-Abhyankar serial murders]]: series of ten murders committed by four art students in [[Pune]]; all were executed on 27 November 1983.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.rahulchandawarkar.com/news/general/general03float.htm |title=The Evil and the Dead |first=Rahul |last=Chandawarkar |date=September 6, 1998 |newspaper=[[Sunday Mid-Day]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=rahulchandawarkar.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715150717/http://www.rahulchandawarkar.com/news/general/general03float.htm |archivedate=15 July 2011}}</ref>\n*[[KD Kempamma]] (born 1970): also known as \"Cyanide Mallika\"; poisoned six women from 1999 to 2007 with cyanide; India's first convicted female serial killer; sentenced to death, commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/First-woman-serial-killer-nabbed/articleshow/2665976.cms |title=First woman serial killer nabbed |date=1 January 2008 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailyo.in/variety/cyanide-mallika-serial-killers-women-crime/story/1/21649.html |title=Women who kill: The story behind India's first woman serial killer |last=Anand |first=Pinky |date=10 January 2018 |website=Daily O |accessdate=10 May 2018}}</ref>\n*[[2006 Noida serial murders|Surendra Koli]] (born 1970-71): convicted of raping and murdering four children in [[Delhi]] in 2005 and 2006 with another twelve cases pending.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rediff.com/news/report/how-indira-jaising-got-midnight-reprieve-for-convict-koli/20140908.htm |title=How Indira Jaising got midnight reprieve for convict Koli |date=September 8, 2014 |website=[[Rediff]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://scroll.in/article/679297/nine-reasons-not-to-hang-alleged-nithari-serial-killer-surendra-koli |title=Nine reasons not to hang alleged Nithari serial killer Surendra Koli |first=Shivam |last=Vij |date=17 September 2014 |website=[[Scroll.in]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mohan Kumar (serial killer)|Mohan Kumar]] (born 1963): also known as \"Cyanide Mohan\"; killed twenty female victims with cyanide, claiming they were contraceptive pills; sentenced to death in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=67282 |title=Mangalore: Neighbours, Family, Refuse to Accept Mohan as Serial Killer |date=23 October 2009 |website=[[Daijiworld Media|Daijiworld.com]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ravinder Kumar (serial killer)|Ravinder Kumar]] (born 1991): killed the children of poor families from 2008 until his arrest in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/delhi-serial-rapist-ravinder-kumar-admits-killing-30-children-2355078.html |title=Delhi serial rapist Ravinder Kumar admits to killing more than 30 children |date=21 July 2015 |website=[[Firstpost]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Motta Navas]] (born 1966): killed pavement dwellers in their sleep during a three-month period in 2012 in [[Kollam]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/man-held-on-charge-of-five-murders/article4060891.ece |title=Man held on charge of five murders |date=3 November 2012 |newspaper=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Santosh Pol]] (born 1974): also known as \"Dr. Death\"; killed six people with [[succinylcholine]] in the town of Dhom.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/maharashtra-doctor-death-six-murders/1/741281.html |title=Maharashtra's 'Dr Death' confesses to 6 murders, five of them women |date=August 16, 2016 |magazine=India Today |accessdate=2016-08-17}}</ref>\n*[[Raman Raghav]] (1929\u20131995): also known as \"Psycho Raman\"; [[Mumbai]] man who killed homeless people and others in their sleep.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/life-style/the-monsoon-murders |title=The real man behind Raman Raghav 2.0: Mumbai's first big-ticket serial killer |first=Smita |last=Nair |date=2016-06-26 |newspaper=The Indian Express |access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/inside-the-mind-of-raman-raghav-mumbai-s-serial-killer-of-the-60s/story-LaA01MtT0wrAM0ZprCoLYJ.html |title=Inside the mind of Raman Raghav, Mumbai's serial killer of the 1960s |first=Poonam |last=Saxena |date=2016-06-11 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref>\n*[[Umesh Reddy]] alias BA Umesh (born 1969): confessed to eighteen rapes and murders, convicted in nine cases.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1091108/jsp/7days/story_11713568.jsp |title=Murders most foul |first=Varun |last=Verma |date=2009-11-08 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (Kolkata)|The Telegraph]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ripper Jayanandan]] (born 1968): also known as the \"Singing Serial Killer\"; killed seven people during robberies.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/Ripper-Jayanandan-gets-life-sentence/articleshow/11228173.cms |title=Ripper Jayanandan gets life sentence |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=24 December 2011 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Satish (Bahadurgarh baby killer)|Satish]] (born c. 1973): also known as the \"[[Bahadurgarh]] Baby Killer\"; confessed to and convicted for ten murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Serial-killers-life-spared/articleshow/2722792.cms |title=Serial killer's life spared |date=22 January 2008 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Auto Shankar]] (1954\u20131995): murdered nine teenage girls in [[Thiruvanmiyur]], [[Chennai]] during a six-month period in 1988; executed in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=EoZlAAAAIBAJ&sjid=mZ4NAAAAIBAJ&dq=auto%20shankar&pg=1032%2C3469058 |title=The mass murderer of Madras |first1=K. M. |last1=Thomas |date=9 September 1990 |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PIxlAAAAIBAJ&sjid=q54NAAAAIBAJ&pg=817%2C2582855 |title=Auto Shankar, two others sentenced to death |date=1 June 1991 |newspaper=The Indian Express |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Kampatimar Shankariya]] (1952\u20131979): killed at least 70 people with hammer in 1977-78; hung in Jaipur.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA239&lpg=PA239&dq=kampatimar+shankariya#v=onepage&q=kampatimar%20shankariya&f=false|title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers|last=Newton|first=Michael|publisher=Infobase Publishing|year=2006|isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3|location=|pages=239|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Darbara Singh (murderer)|Darbara Singh]] (born 1952): convicted for two murders, seventeen suspected victims.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/india-s-cruel-serial-baby-killer-darbara-singh-who-murdered-2674.html |title=India's cruel serial baby killer Darbara Singh, who murdered seventeen babies |date=2013-02-17 |website=[[India TV]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> Singh had three children; his wife expelled him from their house, because of his \"bad habits\".\n*[[Charles Sobhraj]] (born 1944): killed at least twelve Western tourists in [[Southeast Asia]] during the 1970s; imprisoned in [[India]] (released) and [[Nepal]] (in prison).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/story/international-serial-killer-charles-sobhraj-64-engaged-to-woman-20 |title=International Serial Killer Charles Sobhraj, 64, Engaged to Woman, 20 |date=5 July 2008 |website=[[Fox News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/famous/charles_sobraj/1.html |title=Charles Sobhraj |first=Mark |last=Gribben |website=[[Crime Library]] |accessdate=20 February 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224131111/http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/famous/charles_sobraj/1.html |archivedate=24 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Akku Yadav]] (died 2004): murdered at least three people and dumped their bodies on the railroad tracks; lynched by a mob of around 200 women in [[Nagpur]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-23/nagpur/34679336_1_murder-case-akku-yadav-panch-witness |title=Trial in Akku Yadav murder case begins |date=22 October 2012 |newspaper=The Times of India |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2005/sep/16/india.gender |title='Arrest us all': the 200 women who killed a rapist |first=Raekha |last=Prasad |date=16 September 2005 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/01/15/opinion/in-india-one-womans-stand-says-enough.html |title=In India, One Woman's Stand Says 'Enough' |first=Nicholas D. |last=Kristof |date=15 January 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Indonesia===\n*[[Baekuni]]: also known as \"Babe\"; pedophile who killed between four and fourteen boys from 1993 to 2010; sentenced to life imprisonment, later changed to the death sentence.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2010/01/17/07262786/Mutilasi.Baekuni.Lebih.Keji.Ryan.Henyansah.Lebih.Rumit |title=Mutilasi, Baekuni Lebih Keji, Ryan Henyansah Lebih Rumit |trans-title=Mutilation, Baekuni more vile, Ryan Henyansah more complex |date=17 January 2010 |newspaper=[[Kompas]] |language=id |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Very Idham Henyansyah]]: also known as \"Ryan\" and the \"Singing Serial Killer\"; convicted and sentenced to death in 2008 for the killing of eleven people.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/03/24/2525127.htm |title=Indonesia seeks death for singing serial killer |date=24 March 2009 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=2011-01-10}}</ref>\n*[[Ahmad Suradji]]: admitted to killing 42 women around [[Medan]]; sentenced to death and executed by firing squad on 10 July 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/indonesia/2286216/Black-Magic-Killer-executed-for-42-murders.html |title=Black Magic Killer executed for 42 murders |first=Thomas |last=Bell |date=11 July 2008 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\n*[[Asghar the Murderer|Ali Asghar Borujerdi]]: also known as \"Asghar the Murderer\"; killed 33 young adults in Iraq and Iran; executed on 26 June 1934.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://ulib.aub.edu.lb/data/hist258k-cs-47/Schayegh-Serial_murder_in_Tehran.pdf |title=Serial Murder in Tehran: Crime, Science, and the Formation of Modern State and Society in Interwar Iran |last=Schayegh |first=Cyrus |date=2005 |journal=Comparative Studies in Society and History |publisher=Cambridge University Press |volume=47 |issue=4 |pages=836\u2013862 |doi=10.1017/S001041750500037X |issn=0010-4175 |jstor=3879345 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160520022651/http://ulib.aub.edu.lb/data/hist258k-cs-47/Schayegh-Serial_murder_in_Tehran.pdf |archive-date=20 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Louay Omar Mohammed al-Taei]]: medical doctor found to have killed 43 wounded policemen, soldiers and officials in [[Kirkuk]]; was a member of an [[Insurgency|insurgent cell]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/insurgent-doctor-killed-dozens-of-wounded-soldiers-6105814.html |title=Insurgent doctor killed dozens of wounded soldiers |last=Cockburn |first=Patrick |date=23 March 2006 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Iran===\n*[[Mohammed Bijeh]]: also known as the \"Tehran Desert Vampire\"; killed at least sixteen young boys near [[Tehran]]; executed in 2005.\n*[[Saeed Hanaei]]: also known as \"The Spider Killer\"; killed at least sixteen women around [[Mashhad]]; executed in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/04/18/world/iran-executes-worker-who-strangled-16-women-over-2-years.html |title=Iran Executes Worker Who Strangled 16 Women Over 2 Years |first=Nazila |last=Fathi |date=April 18, 2002 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Esmail Jafarzadeh]]: murdered a young girl in 2017, confessing to the murder of two women in 2012 and 2014 after his arrest; executed 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fararu.com/fa/news/324976/%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84-%D8%A2%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D9%88-%D8%B2%D9%86-%D8%AF%D9%8A%DA%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D9%87%D9%85-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title=\u0642\u0627\u062a\u0644 \u0622\u062a\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0648 \u0632\u0646 \u062f\u064a\u06af\u0631 \u0631\u0627 \u0647\u0645 \u06a9\u0634\u062a\u0647\u200c \u0627\u0633\u062a |trans-title=Athena's killer has also killed two other women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=6 August 2008 |website=[[Fararu]] |language=fa |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gholamreza Khosroo Kurdieh]]: also known as \"The Night Bat\"; murdered nine women in Tehran in 1997, burning the bodies afterwards; executed 1997.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://images.hamshahrionline.ir/hamnews/1376/760523/HAVAD30.HTM |title=\u0634\u062f\u061f 214 \u0627\u0639\u062f\u0627\u0645\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0686\u06af\u0648\u0646\u0647\u200c\u200f\u200e \u062f\u062e\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0646\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0648\u200f\u200e \u0632\u0646\u0627\u0646\u200c\u200f\u200e \u0642\u0627\u062a\u0644\u200c\u200f\u200e |trans-title=214 was it? Execution of killer of girls and women |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=23 August 1997 |newspaper=[[Hamshahri]] |language=fa |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Majid Salek Mohammadi]]: murdered twenty-four people from 1981 to 1985, primarily women he considered unfaithful to their husbands; committed suicide in prison before he could be sentenced.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.isna.ir/news/95050119135/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%84-%D8%B3%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%84%DB%8C-%D8%B2%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86 |title=White rope murders |date=2016-08-20 |website=[[Iranian Students News Agency]] |language=fa |accessdate=25 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Republic of Ireland===\n*[[Geoffrey Evans|Geoffrey Evans and John Shaw]]: Englishmen who traveled to Ireland in 1976 and vowed to murder a woman once a week, killing two; both apprehended and sentenced. Until his 2012 death, Evans was one of Ireland's longest-serving prisoners.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.wicklownews.net/Post/2012/5/1911/brittas-bay-killer-geoffrey-evans-dies |title=Brittas bay killer Geoffrey Evans dies |date=21 May 2012 |newspaper=Wicklow News |accessdate=21 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120524044621/http://www.wicklownews.net/Post/2012/5/1911/brittas-bay-killer-geoffrey-evans-dies |archivedate=24 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Darkey Kelly]]: [[brothel]]-keeper who killed six men in the 18th century; accused of witchcraft and was [[death by burning|burned at the stake]] in 1761.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/was-irish-witch-darkey-kelly-really-irelands-first-serial-killer-113340849-237364711.html |title=Was Irish witch Darkey Kelly really Ireland's first serial killer? |first=Cathy |last=Hayes |date=2011-01-12 |website=IrishCentral.com |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite podcast |url=https://www.podomatic.com/podcasts/nosmokewithouthellfire1/episodes/2011-01-19T14_46_14-08_00 |title=No Smoke Without Hellfire Part I |host=McLoughlin, Eamonn |date=2011-01-19 |website=PodOmatic |access-date=2015-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Alice Kyteler]]: also known as \"The Witch of [[Kilkenny]]\"; alleged witch who poisoned four husbands in the 14th century; fled to England, fate unknown.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Chapter II: \"Dame Alice Kyteler, the Sorceress of Kilkenny |title=Irish Witchcraft and Demonology |first=St. John D., B.D. |last=Seymour |date=1913 |pages=25\u201326 |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/irishwitchcraftd00seymrich#page/24/mode/2up |location=Dublin |publisher=Hodges, Figgs}}</ref>\n\n===Israel===\n*[[Yahya Farhan]]: [[Bedouin]] serial killer, who murdered between two and four people from 1994 to 2004, including [[Murder of Dana Bennett|Dana Bennett]]; sentenced to three consecutive life sentences, and later acquitted of one murder.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mako.co.il/news-law/legal/Article-cec7b38cde5f921004.htm |title=See: Farhan reconstructs Bennett's murder |first=Yossi |last=Mizrahi |date=July 21, 2010 |website=Mako |language=he |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nicolai Bonner]]: killed four people in 2005 in [[Haifa]], three of them homeless; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/homeless-man-found-guilty-of-haifa-serial-murders-1.204551 |title=Homeless Man Found Guilty of Haifa Serial Murders |date=2006-11-07 |newspaper=[[Haaretz]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Italy===\n*[[Wolfgang Abel and Marco Furlan]]: German-Italian duo found guilty of ten of 27 counts of murder in 1987.\n*[[Beasts of Satan]]: Satanic cult members who committed three notorious ritual murders from 1998 to 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/this_world/4446342.stm |title=Investigating the 'death metal' murders |last=Bagnall |first=Sam |date=23 November 2005 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Marco Bergamo (serial killer)|Marco Bergamo]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Bolzano]]\"; murdered five women in Bolzano from 1985 to 1992; died from a lung infection in 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/17_ottobre_17/morto-margo-bergamo-mostro-bolzano-che-aveva-ucciso-5-donne-8368d79c-b35d-11e7-9cef-7c546dada489.shtml |title=Morto Marco Bergamo, il \"mostro di Bolzano\" che aveva ucciso 5 donne |trans-title=Marco Bergamo, the \"Monster of Bolzano\" who had killed 5 women, is dead |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=17 October 2017 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Donato Bilancia]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Liguria]]\" murdered seventeen people in seven months between 1997 and 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.occhirossi.it/biografie/DonatoBilancia.htm |title=Donato Bilancia |last=Del Frate |first=Daniele |date=31 October 2004 |website=Occhi Rossi |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Antonio Boggia]]: also known as the \"Monster of Milan\"; first documented Italian serial killer; murdered four people for monetary purposes between 1849 and 1859; hanged 1862.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cultura/storia-primo-serial-killer-italiano-944632.html |title=Storia del primo serial killer italiano |trans-title=History of the first Italian serial killer |first=Luca |last=Crovi |date=22 August 2013 |newspaper=[[Il Giornale]] |language=it |accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Ralph Brydges]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Rome]]\"; English pastor who is widely believed to have murdered five girls in Rome in the 1920s, and four in other countries; never convicted of his crimes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/genova/mostro-e-commissario-che-bracc-fino-genova.html |title=Il mostro e il commissario che lo bracc\u00f2 fino a Genova |trans-title=The monster and the commissioner who chased him to Genoa |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=9 May 2012 |newspaper=Il Giornale |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Sonya Caleffi]]: nurse who poisoned terminally ill patients between 2003 and 2004, killing 5 of them; sentenced to 20 years of imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ildue.it/Notizie/SVittore/Dettaglio.asp?ID=537 |title=Sonya Caleffi a 'Grazia': 'Non sono un'assassina' |trans-title=Sonya Caleffi to 'Grazia': 'I am not a murderer' |date=28 March 2006 |website=IlDue.it |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514001944/http://www.ildue.it/Notizie/SVittore/Dettaglio.asp?ID=537 |archive-date=May 14, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Luigi Chiatti]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Foligno]]\"; kidnapped and killed two children in 1992 and 1993; sentenced to two life sentences, but he was found unfit to stand trial and was reduced to 30 years in a mental hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.umbria24.it/cronaca/lavvocato-bacino-%c2%abchiatti-non-e-uscito-dal-carcere-ne-ha-mai-chiesto-la-semiliberta%c2%bb |title=Luigi Chiatti non \u00e8 uscito dal carcere n\u00e9 ha mai chiesto la semilibert\u00e0 |trans-title=Luigi Chiatti was not released from prison and has never asked for parole |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=18 November 2010 |website=Umbria24 |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Leonarda Cianciulli]]: also known as the \"Soap-Maker of [[Correggio]]\"; murderer of three women between 1939 and 1940; died in a women's criminal asylum in 1970.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.museocriminologico.it/correggio_uk.htm |title=The Correggio soap-maker |website=Museo Criminologico |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060912155116/http://www.museocriminologico.it/correggio_uk.htm |archivedate=2006-09-12}}</ref>\n*[[Ferdinand Gamper]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Merano]]\"; killed six people in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.italiacriminale.it/ferdinand-gamper-il-mostro-di-merano/ |title=Ferdinand Gamper: the monster Merano |website=Italia Criminale |language=it |access-date=17 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330223112/http://www.italiacriminale.it/ferdinand-gamper-il-mostro-di-merano/ |archive-date=2016-03-30}}</ref>\n*[[Pier Paolo Brega Massone]]: murdered at least four people in [[Milan]] and maimed other dozens of victims through unnecessary surgeries to illegally obtain a large amounts of money refunds; convicted and given a life sentence.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://milano.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/14_aprile_09/clinica-orrori-condanna-all-ergastolo-brega-massone-80c798e6-c006-11e3-a6b2-109f6a781e55.shtml |title=Clinica degli orrori: Ergastolo per Brega Massone, arresto in aula |trans-title=Clinic of horrors: life imprisonment for Brega Massone, arrest in court |date=2014-04-09 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Andrea Matteucci]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Aosta]]\"; murdered a merchant and three prostitutes in Aosta from 1980 to 1995; sentenced to 28 years imprisonment and three years in a mental institution.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.gqitalia.it/underground/2015/06/05/andrea-matteucci-il-mostro-di-aosta/ |title=L'inquietante parabola di Andrea Matteucci, il mostro di Aosta |trans-title=The disturbing parable of Andrea Matteucci, the monster of Aosta |first=Edoardo |last=Montolli |date=5 June 2015 |magazine=[[GQ|GQ Italia]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Maurizio Minghella]]: killed five women in his hometown of [[Genoa]] in 1978; imprisoned and released, after which he murdered at least four more and is suspected of other murders between 1997 and 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lastampa.it/Torino/cmsSezioni/cronaca/200810articoli/8420girata.asp |title=Il pugile schizofrenico che strangola e dimentica; Diciotto anni di prigione Liberato, torna a uccidere |trans-title=The schizophrenic boxer who strangles and forgets; freed after eighteen years in prison to kill again |first=Massimo |last=Numa |date=22 October 2008 |newspaper=[[La Stampa]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081022213240/http://www.lastampa.it/Torino/cmsSezioni/cronaca/200810articoli/8420girata.asp |archive-date=22 October 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Giorgio Orsolano]]: also known as the \"Hyena of [[San Giorgio Canavese|San Giorgio]]\"; raped, killed and dismembered three girls from 1834 to 1835 in his hometown of San Giorgio Canavese; executed 1835.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.torinoscienza.it/anatomia/le_collezioni/aprieed6eed6.html?obj_id=2375 |title=Death mask of Giorgio Orsolano |access-date=2018-11-24 |website=Torino Museo di Anatomia |language=it |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210191624/http://www.torinoscienza.it/anatomia/le_collezioni/aprieed6eed6.html?obj_id=2375 |archivedate=2015-02-10}}</ref>\n*[[Ernesto Picchioni]]: also known as \"The Monster of [[Nerola]]\"; murdered people around his home; died of cardiac arrest in 1967.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.P/p/picchioni-ernesto.htm |title=Ernesto Picchioni A.K.A.: \"The Monster of Nerola\" |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Milena Quaglini]]: murdered her husband and two men who tried to rape her from 1995 to 1999; committed suicide while imprisoned in 2001.<ref name=Milena>{{Cite web |url=http://www.misteriditalia.it/cn/?page_id=5150 |title=1995-1998: Milena Quaglini, La Donna Che Uccideva gli Uomini Violenti |trans-title=Milena Quaglini, The Woman Who Killed Violent Men |website=Misteri d'Italia |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gianfranco Stevanin]]: also known as the \"Monster of [[Terrazzo]]\"; raped and murdered prostitutes after violent sex games between 1993 and 1994; violated the corpse of one victim; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1996/08/25/sono-morte-dopo-un-gioco-di.html |title=Sono Morte Dopo Un Gioco Di Sesso Estremo ... |trans-title=I Died After An Extreme Sex Game ... |date=1996-08-25 |newspaper=[[la Repubblica]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Roberto Succo]]: murdered at least five people, including his parents, committed suicide while in prison in 1988.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/c-dric-kahn-inside-the-mind-of-a-killer-178982.html |title=C\u00e9dric Kahn: Inside the mind of a killer |last=Romney |first=Jonathan |date=2 June 2002 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Giulia Tofana]]: leader of a group of female poisoners in the 17th century; died in her bed, never been arrested.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mikedashhistory.com/2015/04/06/aqua-tofana-slow-poisoning-and-husband-killing-in-17th-century-italy/ |title=Aqua Tofana: Slow-Poisoning and Husband-Killing in 17th Century Italy |first=Mike |last=Dash |date=6 April 2015 |website=A Blast From the Past |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Giorgio Vizzardelli]]: shot and killed five people around [[Sarzana]] from 1937 to 1939; sentenced to life imprisonment; committed suicide by slitting his throat with a kitchen knife in 1973.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/genova/mostro-sarzana-80-anni-906542.html |title=Il mostro di Sarzana 80 anni dopo |trans-title=The monster of Sarzana 80 years later |date=14 April 2013 |newspaper=[[Il Giornale]] |language=it |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Jamaica===\n*[[Lewis Hutchinson]]: Scottish immigrant convicted of shooting dozens of people in the 18th century; executed in 1773.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/history/story0036.htm |title=Pieces of the Past \u2013 Lewis Hutchinson: The Mad Master |last=Tortello |first=Rebecca |date=6 November 2002 |newspaper=[[The Gleaner (newspaper)|Jamaica Gleaner]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150127042527/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/history/story0036.htm |archivedate=27 January 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Japan===\n*[[Ryuun Daimai]]: also known as the \"Nun Slayer\"; former monk who raped and killed at least five people in several cities between 1905 and 1915; executed 1916.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www5b.biglobe.ne.jp/~madison/murder/text_japan/ryuun.html|title=Daimai Ryuun|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=December 25, 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Sachiko Eto]]: also known as the \"Drumstick Killer\"; cult leader who murdered six of her followers with [[Taiko]] sticks from 1994 to 1995; executed 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201904/20190414_13031.html|title=<Retrospective of the Heisei Era> (6) Sukagawa Prayer Murders (7 years)|last=|first=|date=April 14, 2019|work=[[Kahoku Shimp\u014d]]|access-date=2019-04-16|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416041418/https://www.kahoku.co.jp/tohokunews/201904/20190414_13031.html|archive-date=16 April 2019|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Satar\u014d Fukiage]]: raped and killed at least seven girls in the early 20th century; executed 1926.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www8.ocn.ne.jp/~moonston/child.htm |title=Child Killers: \u5439\u4e0a\u4f50\u592a\u90ce |website=Monsters |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071117231639/http://www8.ocn.ne.jp/~moonston/child.htm |archivedate=2007-11-17}}</ref>\n*[[Sokichi Furuya]]: murdered eight elderly people in several western Japanese cities for more than a month in 1965; suspected of four earlier murders, for two of which an accomplice was executed; executed 1985.<ref>[[Asahi Shimbun]] (June 1, 1985) Tokyo morning newspaper, p. 23 \"Robbery murderer, execution of Furuya at Osaka Detention Center\"</ref>\n*[[Hiroaki Hidaka]]: killed four prostitutes in [[Hiroshima]] in 1996; executed 25 December 2006.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/02/09/news/lawyer-to-sue-after-prison-bars-meeting-before-inmate-is-executed/ |title=Lawyer to sue after prison bars meeting before inmate is executed |date=2007-02-09 |newspaper=[[The Japan Times]] |accessdate=2008-02-23}}</ref>\n*[[Miyuki Ishikawa]]: [[midwife]] who murdered an estimated 103 infants, but could have been up to 169, in the 1940s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://homepage3.nifty.com/koseki-t/yougo2.html |script-title=ja:\u990a\u8b77\u65bd\u8a2d\u306e\u5b50\u3069\u3082\u305f\u3061\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\u5150\u7ae5\u3068\u798f\u7949\u306b\u95a2\u9023\u3059\u308b\u3067\u304d\u3054\u3068 |first=Takashi |last=Koseki |website=Koseki-t |language=ja |accessdate=2008-02-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070211225216/http://homepage3.nifty.com/koseki-t/yougo2.html |archivedate=February 11, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://homepage2.nifty.com/kousinren/nenhyo/nenpyo4/1948.htm |title=15 March 1948 |website=Kousinren |language=ja |accessdate=2008-02-24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120713061748/http://homepage2.nifty.com/kousinren/nenhyo/nenpyo4/1948.htm |archive-date=2012-07-13}}</ref>\n*[[Chisako Kakehi]]: poisoned her husband and two other men to death, attempted to kill a fourth man, and is a suspect in another seven deaths; sentenced to death in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/japans-black-widow-given-death-penalty-for-murders/news-story/a2c64e7c3f304991462bed828274a8f7 |title=Japan's 'Black Widow' given death penalty for murders |last=Palin |first=Megan |date=7 November 2017 |website=[[News.com.au]] |access-date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Kiyotaka Katsuta]]: [[firefighter]] who shot and strangled at least eight people, some during robberies, between 1972 and 1982.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2000/12/01/national/serial-killer-two-other-murderers-hanged/ |title=Serial killer, two other murderers hanged |date=December 1, 2000 |newspaper=The Japan Times |accessdate=2008-03-01}}</ref>\n*[[Kanae Kijima]]: also known as \"The Konkatsu Killer\"; marriage fraudster who poisoned between three and seven men for money, from 2007 to 2009; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20170414/k10010948561000.html|title=Kanae Kijima, accused of killing three men in staged accidents, on death row|last=|first=|date=April 14, 2017|work=NHK|access-date=April 15, 2017|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415103815/http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20170414/k10010948561000.html|archive-date=15 April 2017|publisher=[[NHK]]}}</ref>\n*[[Yoshio Kodaira]]: rapist thought to have killed eleven people in Japan and China as a soldier; executed on 5 October 1949.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,853940-2,00.html |title=Peace, It's Wonderful |date=1949-10-17 |magazine=TIME |accessdate=2008-02-09}}</ref>\n*[[Genzo Kurita]]: killed six women and two children and engaged in rape and [[necrophilia]]; executed on 16 January 1959.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kokkai.ndl.go.jp/SENTAKU/sangiin/024/0640/02405100640002c.html |title=\u7b2c024\u56de\u56fd\u4f1a \u6cd5\u52d9\u59d4\u54e1\u4f1a\u516c\u8074\u4f1a \u7b2c2\u53f7 |trans-title=The 24th Diet Legal Committee Hearing No.2 |date=1956-05-10 |website=[[National Diet Library]] |language=ja |accessdate=2008-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023230218/http://kokkai.ndl.go.jp/SENTAKU/sangiin/024/0640/02405100640002c.html |archive-date=23 October 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Hiroshi Maeue]]: also known as \"Suicide Website Murderer\"; [[Osaka]] man who lured people from suicide clubs promising to kill himself with his victims.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2007/03/29/national/man-gets-death-for-murdering-suicidal-trio/ |title=Man gets death for murdering suicidal trio |date=2007-03-29 |newspaper=The Japan Times |accessdate=2008-02-23}}</ref>\n*[[Futoshi Matsunaga]] and [[Junko Ogata]]: also known as \"House of Horror\"; tortured and killed at least seven people between 1996 and 1998, including Ogata's family.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/weekly/news/nn2005/nn20050312a5.htm |title=Pair accused of slaying 7 face gallows |date=2005-03-03 |newspaper=The Japan Times Weekly |accessdate=2008-02-10 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121227215212/search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/nn20050303a1.html |archive-date=27 December 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Tsutomu Miyazaki]]: also known as \"The [[Otaku]] Murderer\", \"The Little Girl Murderer\" and \"Dracula\"; killed four pre-school-age girls and ate the hand of a victim; executed in 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/national/20080618TDY02306.htm |title=Miyazaki unrepentant to the last / Serial child killer goes to execution without apologizing or explaining his thinking |date=2008-06-18 |newspaper=[[Yomiuri Shimbun]] |location=Tokyo |accessdate=2008-06-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20080621044230/http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/national/20080618TDY02306.htm |archivedate=2008-06-21}}</ref>\n*[[Seisaku Nakamura]]: also known as the \"[[Hamamatsu]] Deaf Killer\", murdered at least nine people; executed in 1943.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kangaeru.s59.xrea.com/senzen.htm |first=Eruo |last=Kanga |script-title=ja:\u6226\u524d\u306e\u5c11\u5e74\u72af\u7f6a |website=Juvenile crime database |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-22}}</ref>\n*[[Akira Nishiguchi]]: killed five people and engaged in fraud; executed on 11 December 1970.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alpha-net.ne.jp/users2/knight9/nisiguti.htm |script-title=ja:\u897f\u53e3\u5f70\u9023\u7d9a\u5f37\u76d7\u6bba\u4eba\u4e8b\u4ef6 |website=\u7121\u9650\u56de\u5eca |language=ja |accessdate=2007-11-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071201122525/http://www.alpha-net.ne.jp/users2/knight9/nisiguti.htm |archivedate=2007-12-01}}</ref>\n*[[Kiyoshi \u014ckubo]]: also known as \"Tanigawa Ivan\"; raped and murdered eight young women over a period of 41 days in 1971.\n*[[Miyuki Ueta]]: former snack hostess who murdered between two and six men she dated in [[Tottori (city)|Tottori]], from 2004 to 2009; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/170826/afr1708260002-n1.html|title=Tottori Consecutive Suspicious Deaths Case: former snack hostess, defandant Ueta on death row|last=|first=|date=August 26, 2017|work=Sankei Shimbun|access-date=September 26, 2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926113636/http://www.sankei.com/affairs/news/170826/afr1708260002-n1.html|archive-date=September 26, 2017|publisher=Sankei Shimbun}}</ref>\n*[[Yukio Yamaji]]: murdered his own mother in 2000, and then murdered a 27-year-old woman and her 19-year-old sister in 2005.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2006/12/14/national/man-to-hang-for-sisters-murders/ |title=Man to hang for sisters' murders |date=14 December 2006 |newspaper=The Japan Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Kazakhstan===\n*[[Nikolai Dzhumagaliev]]: also known as \"Metal Fang\"; raped and hacked seven women to death with an axe in [[Almaty]] in 1980, then cannibalised them using his unusual false teeth.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/blog/2012/05/17/modern-cannibalism-six-killers-with-a-taste-for-human-flesh/index.html |title=Modern cannibalism: Six killers with a taste for human flesh |first=Michael |last=Washburn |date=2012-05-17 |website=TruTV.com |accessdate=2014-01-18 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626165904/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/blog/2012/05/17/modern-cannibalism-six-killers-with-a-taste-for-human-flesh/index.html |archive-date=26 June 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Yuri Ivanov (serial killer)|Yuri Ivanov]]: also known as the \"Ust-Kamenogorsk Maniac\"; raped and killed sixteen girls and young women who spoke badly of men in [[Ust-Kamenogorsk]] from 1974 to 1987; executed 1987.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://meta.kz/novosti/kazakhstan/814276-gromkie-prestupleniya-sovetskogo-vremeni-ust-kamenogorskiy-manyak.html |title=\u0413\u0440\u043e\u043c\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0441\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438: \u0423\u0441\u0442\u044c-\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a |trans-title=High-profile crimes of the Soviet era: Ust-Kamenogorsk maniac |date=29 July 2013 |website=Novosti Kazakhstana |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Latvia===\n*[[Ansis Kaup\u0113ns]]: army deserter who committed 30 robberies and 19 murders from 1920 to 1926; executed 1927 in [[Vircava Parish]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vietas.lv/index.php?p=10&id=481 |title=Ansis Kaup\u0113ns (1895-1927) |first=Zemgales |last=Zi\u0146as |date=11 November 2005 |website=Vietas.lv |language=lv |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180823042154/http://www.vietas.lv/index.php?p=10&id=481 |archive-date=2018-08-23}}</ref> \n*[[Kaspars Petrovs]]: convicted of murdering thirteen elderly [[Riga]] women in 2005; confessed to killing 38.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://newsfromrussia.com/hotspots/2005/05/12/59725.html |title=Latvian serial killer sentenced to life in prison for 13 murders |date=2005-05-12 |website=[[Pravda.ru]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060327205411/http://newsfromrussia.com/hotspots/2005/05/12/59725.html |archivedate=March 27, 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Stanislav Rogolev]]: also known as \"Agent 000\"; robbed, raped and killed ten women from 1980 to 1982; suspected of having inside information for the investigation on him; executed 1984.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kriminal.lv/news/retrodetektiv-delo-rogaleva-manyyak-byl-lichnym-agentom-generala-kavalierisa |title=\u0420\u0435\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432. \u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0420\u043e\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430: \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a \u0431\u044b\u043b \u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0430\u0433\u0435\u043d\u0442\u043e\u043c \u0433\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u041a\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0430 |trans-title=Retrodetective. The case of Rogalev: the maniac was a personal agent of General Cavalieris |first=\u0418\u0433\u043e\u0440\u044c |last=\u0418\u0449\u0443\u043a |date=13 May 2010 |website=Kriminal.lv |language=lv |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Lebanon===\n*[[George and Michel Tanielian]]: also known as the \"Taxi Driver Killers\"; [[Syria]]n brothers who killed and robbed mostly taxi drivers in the [[Matn District]] from July to November 2011; both sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lbcgroup.tv/news/d/lebanon-news/10173/beirut-serial-killer-mystery-solved/en |title=Beirut serial killer mystery solved |date=November 15, 2011 |website=Lebanon News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Lithuania===\n*[[Antanas Varnelis]]: murdered and robbed six pensioners between July and December 1992 around several municipalities; first known serial killer in Lithuania; executed 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.delfi.lt/news/daily/lithuania/ivykiai-sukrete-lietuva-a-varnelio-istorija-danu-tv-pranese-lietuvoje-psichopatai-saudomi-teismo-nuosprendziu.d?id=34684635|title=\"Events that shocked Lithuania\" The Story of A. Varnelis. Danish TV reported: Lithuanian psychopath executed|last=Knispeliu|first=Egidijumi|date=July 21, 2010|website=DELFI|access-date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Malta===\n*[[Silvio Mangion]]: only known serial killer in Malta; murdered three elderly pensioners during robberies between 1984 and 1998; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2012-07-04/local-news/Man-On-trial-for-third-murder:-Mangion-made-%E2%80%98serial-killer%E2%80%99-joke-about-his-tattoos-312479|title=Man On trial for third murder: Mangion made 'serial killer' joke about his tattoos|publisher=[[The Malta Independent]]|date=July 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Mexico===\n*[[Macario Alcala Canchola]]: also known as \"Jack Mexicano\" (\"Mexican Jack\"), was a [[Jack the Ripper]] copycat active in the 1960s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://enciclopediadelosasesinosenserie.blogspot.mx/2010/02/macario-alcala-canchola-jack-el.html |title=Macario Alcala Canchola. \"Jack el Mexicano\" (M\u00e9xico) |trans-title=Macario Alcala Canchola. \"Mexican Jack\" (Mexico) |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=February 10, 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los Asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=April 24, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Sara Aldrete]]: also known as \"La Madrina\"; cult follower of Adolfo Constanzo; convicted in 1994 of murdering several individuals during her association with Constanzo.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DEEDA103AF93BA35756C0A96F948260 |title=Leader in Cult Slayings Ordered Own Death, Two Companions Say |date=May 8, 1989 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |quote=The leader of a drug-smuggling cult that is believed to have killed fifteen people and buried their bodies along the United States-Mexican border ordered his own killing when the police closed in on him, two of his companions said today. |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[David Avenda\u00f1o Ballina]]: also known as \"The Hamburger\"; alleged leader of a sex servant gang who robbed and poisoned their clients from 1997 to 2007; arrested in 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n592543.htm |title=Cay\u00f3 El Hamburguesa, l\u00edder de la banda de \"Las Goteras\" |trans-title=The fall of 'El Hamburguesa', leader of the band of \"Las Goteras\" |first=Manuel |last=Olmos |date=13 February 2008 |website=[[Organizaci\u00f3n Editorial Mexicana]] |language=es |accessdate=18 August 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305022326/http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n592543.htm |archive-date=5 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Juana Barraza]]: also known as \"Mataviejitas\" (\"Old Lady Killer\"); operated within the metropolitan area of [[Mexico City]] until 25 January 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/7323821.stm |title=Life for Mexico's Old Lady Killer |date=2008-04-01 |website=BBC News |accessdate=2009-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/latestCrisis/idUKN3122188820080401 |title=Mexico's \"Little Old Lady Killer\" gets life term |date=2008-04-01 |website=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=2009-03-31}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Luis Calva]]: cannibal; police found the remains of multiple female victims in his house; committed suicide on 11 December 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/americas/12/11/mexico.suicide.ap/ |title='Cannibal' killer commits suicide |date=11 December 2007 |website=[[CNN]] |accessdate=2007-12-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215011523/http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/americas/12/11/mexico.suicide.ap/ |archivedate=2007-12-15}}</ref>\n*[[Gregorio C\u00e1rdenas Hern\u00e1ndez]]: known as \"the Strangler of Tacuba\"; strangled four women in the [[Tacuba (Mexico)|Tacuba]] neighbourhood in 1942; died in 1999 of natural causes.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/english/2016/11/16/el-goyo-cardenas-one-mexicos-most-infamous-serial-killers |title=El Goyo C\u00e1rdenas, one of Mexico's most infamous serial killers |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=16 November 2016 |newspaper=[[El Universal (Mexico City)|El Universal]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Andr\u00e9s Ulises Castillo Villarreal]]: known as the \"Chihuahua Ripper\"; drugged, raped, killed and mutilated three men in [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] in 2015; confessed to twelve more murders, but suspected of twenty overall; sentenced to 120 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.milenio.com/opinion/jose-luis-duran-king/vidas-ejemplares/el-descuartizador-de-chihuahua |title=El Descuartizador de Chihuahua |trans-title=The Chihuahua Ripper |last=Dur\u00e1n King |first=Jos\u00e9 Luis |date=9 January 2016 |newspaper=[[Milenio]] |language=es |access-date=1 December 2018}}</ref>\n*[[The Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez Rebels]]: gang of serial killers who killed women in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez from 1995 to 1996; convicted of eight murders, suspected of killing from ten to 14; claimed to have worked for Abdul Latif Sharif.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2009/09/el-depredador-de-ciudad-juarez-mexico.html |title=El Depredador De Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez |trans-title=The Predator of Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez |last=Rivera |first=Horacio B. |date=29 September 2009 |website=Encyclopedia of serial killers |accessdate=4 January 2013 |quote=... the detainees were: Sergio Armendariz Diaz \"El Diablo\", Jose Luis Rosales, Fernando Germes Aguirre, Juan Jose Contreras Jurado, Gerardo Fernandez Molina, Carlos Hernandez Molina Mariscal, Carlos Barrientos Vidales, Hector Raymundo Olivares, Romel Omar Ceniceros Garcia and Ericka Fierro, the majority were released due to lack of incriminating evidence ...}}</ref>\n*[[Adolfo Constanzo]]: also known as \"The Godfather of Matamoros\"; serial killer and cult leader in Mexico; committed suicide in 1989.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE0D71F3FF930A25757C0A96F948260 |title=Drugs, Death and the Occult Meet In Grisly Inquiry at Mexico Border |first=Peter |last=Applebome |date=April 13, 1989 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=2008-07-28}}</ref>\n*[[Feminicides of the cotton field|Edgar \u00c1lvarez Cruz and Francisco Granados]]: responsible for the so-called \"Feminicides of the cotton field\"; Cruz, with the help of the drugged Granados, kidnapped, raped, tortured and killed at least 8-10 young women in satanic rituals between 1993 and 2003; suspected of committing a total of fourteen murders.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n911023.htm |title=Vinculan feminicidios con actos sat\u00e1nicos |trans-title=They link feminicides with satanic acts |first=Adri\u00e1n |last=S\u00e1nchez |website=Organizaci\u00f3n Editorial Mexicana |language=es |accessdate=23 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141216214811/http://www.oem.com.mx/esto/notas/n911023.htm |archive-date=December 16, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Pedro Padilla Flores]]: also known as \"El Asesino de Rio Bravo\"; killed three women in 1986; escaped to the US but was deported back to Mexico; suspect in the Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez murders.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2011/02/pedro-padilla-flores-el-asesino-del-rio.html |title=Pedro Padilla Flores \"El Asesino del R\u00edo Bravo\" (M\u00e9xico) |first=Horacio B. |last=Rivera |date=3 February 2011 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |access-date=15 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Gabriel Garza Hoth]]: also known as \"The Black Widower\"; killed three women in Mexico City between 1991 and 1998, his victims were wives and lovers.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt |url-access=registration |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt/page/346 346] |quote=gabriel garza hoth. |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |date=February 2006 |location=New York |publisher=Facts On File, Inc. |isbn=0-8160-6195-5 |accessdate=November 2, 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Delfina and Mar\u00eda de Jes\u00fas Gonz\u00e1lez]]: also known as \"Las Poquianchis\"; killed a total of 91 in [[Guanajuato]]; arrested and sentenced to 40 years in prison in 1964.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/most-prolific-murder-partnership |title=Most prolific murder partnership |website=[[Guinness World Records]] |accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco Guerrero P\u00e9rez]]: also known as \"El Chalequero\" (\"The man of the vests\"); the first documented serial killer in Mexico; committed approximately twenty murders in Mexico City between 1880 and 1888 plus one more in 1908.<ref>{{cite book |title=The Sausage Rebellion: Public Health, Private Enterprise, and Meat in Mexico City, 1890\u20131917 |first=Jeffrey M. |last=Pilcher |chapter=2. The Porfirian Jungle |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GHgF0Xz2fcYC&pg=PA63&dq=francisco+guerrero+chalequero#v=onepage&q=francisco%20guerrero%20chalequero |year=2006 |edition=1st |publisher=University of New Mexico Press |location=Albuquerque, New Mexico |pages=62\u201365 |isbn=978-0-8263-3796-2 |accessdate=2012-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Libro Rojo, Vol. 1 |last=Vi\u00f1as |first=Gerardo Villadel\u00e1ngel |chapter=13. El Chalequero |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hTkS8dDnorQC&pg=PA129&dq=francisco+guerrero+el+chalequero#v=onepage&q=francisco%20guerrero%20el%20chalequero |language=es |edition=1st |year=1888 |publisher=Fondo de Cultura Econ\u00f3mica |location=Mexico City, Mexico |pages=128\u2013145 |isbn=9681686152 |accessdate=2012-07-20}}</ref>\n*[[Fernando Hern\u00e1ndez Leyva]]: convicted of 33 murders in 1986, suspected of 137 killings.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/L/LEYVA_fernando_hernandez.php |title=Fernando Hern\u00e1ndez Leyva |last=Wetsch |first=Elisabeth |website=Serial Killer Crime Index |accessdate=24 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923211212/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkillers/L/LEYVA_fernando_hernandez.php |archive-date=23 September 2015 }}</ref>\n*[[Monsters of Ecatepec|Juan Carlos Hern\u00e1ndez and Patricia Mart\u00ednez]]: pair from [[Ecatepec]], [[State of Mexico]], known as \"The Monsters of Ecatepec\", who raped, murdered and cannibalized between ten and twenty women. Active between 2012 and 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/killers-confess-to-eating-remains/ |title=Serial killers of Ecatepec confess to eating the remains of their victims |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 October 2018 |website=Mexico News Daily |access-date=19 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Luis Oscar Jim\u00e9nez Herrera]]: also known as \"The Tinaco Killer\"; murdered sixteen women in Nuevo Le\u00f3n between 2013 and 2016, but also suspected of a 2010 murder in San Luis Potos\u00ed; sentenced to 123 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://elmanana.com.mx/noticia/162970/Dan-123-aos-por-homicidios-y-secuestros.html |title=Dan 123 a\u00f1os por homicidios y secuestros |trans-title=Given 123 years for homicides and kidnappings |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=March 10, 2018 |newspaper=[[El Ma\u00f1ana (Nuevo Laredo)|El Ma\u00f1ana]] |location=[[Nuevo Laredo]] |language=es |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[C\u00e9sar Armando Librado Legorreta]]: also known as \"El Coqueto\"; raped and killed six women in the [[Greater Mexico City]] between 2011 and 2012; sentenced to 240 years in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portal2.edomex.gob.mx/pgjem/seguridad_delicuencia/buscados/prioridad1/groups/public/documents/edomex_archivo/pgjem_pdf_media_librado_l.pdf |title=C\u00e9sar Armando Librado Legorreta alias \"El Coqueto\" |date=2012 |website=Procuradur\u00eda General de Justicia del Estado de M\u00e9xico |language=es |access-date=3 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022001612/http://portal2.edomex.gob.mx/pgjem/seguridad_delicuencia/buscados/prioridad1/groups/public/documents/edomex_archivo/pgjem_pdf_media_librado_l.pdf |archive-date=22 October 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Los Huipas]]: gang of four indigenous homosexual men, led by Eusebio Yocupicio Soto, who murdered seven men who made fun of them between 1949 and 1950; initially sentenced to death, later commuted to 30 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elgrafico.mx/especiales/asesinos-seriales/11-03-2016/huipas-desollaron-siete-por-burlas-homofobicas|title=Huipas: seven were skinned for homophobic ridicule|last=|first=|date=|website=www.elgrafico.mx|language=es|access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Rudolfo Infante and Anna Villeda]]: couple from [[Matamoros, Tamaulipas|Matamoros]] responsible for the murders of eight women. Apprehended in 1991.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt |url-access=registration |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofse0000newt/page/447 447] |quote=the encyclopedia of serial killers villeda. |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |date=February 2006 |location=New York, USA |publisher=Facts On File, Inc. |isbn=0-8160-6195-5 |accessdate=2013-11-24}}</ref>\n*[[Abdul Latif Sharif]]: also known as \"The Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez Predator\"; Egyptian man responsible for murdering an unknown number of women in [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/ciudad_juarez/4.html |title=Ciudad Juarez:The Serial Killer's Playground |first=Michael |last=Newton |website=TruTV.com |page=4 |accessdate=2012-07-22 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505045358/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/ciudad_juarez/4.html |archive-date=2012-05-05}}</ref> possibly as many as fifteen but convicted of only one; died in prison.\n*[[Daniel Audiel L\u00f3pez Mart\u00ednez]]: killed five women in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez between 2007 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.excelsior.com.mx/node/700670 |title=Detienen a asesino serial de mujeres de Ciudad Juarez |trans-title=Serial killer of women captured in Ciudad Juarez |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=January 3, 2011 |website=Excelsior |language=es |accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Ra\u00fal Osiel Marroqu\u00edn]]: also known as \"El Gato Imperial\"; killed four gay men in Mexico City.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pgr.gob.mx/cmsocial/coms06/260106.htm |title=Conferencia de Prensa que ofreci\u00f3 Genaro Garc\u00eda Luna, titular de la Agencia Federal de Investigaci\u00f3n para anunciar la detenci\u00f3n del presunto asesino serial y secuestrador Ra\u00fal Marroqu\u00edn Reyes |trans-title=Press conference held by Genaro Garc\u00eda Luna, head of the Federal Investigation Agency, to announce the capture of the serial killer Ra\u00fal Marroqu\u00edn Reyes |date=January 26, 2006 |website=Procuradur\u00eda General de Justicia |language=es |accessdate=18 July 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226070959/http://www.pgr.gob.mx/cmsocial/coms06/260106.htm |archivedate=26 February 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Filiberto Hern\u00e1ndez Mart\u00ednez]]: killed six people between 2010 and 2013 in [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.omahasuntimes.com/2014/07/filiberto-hernandez-child-serial-killer-suspect-confesses-to-5-murders-cops/ |title=Filiberto Hernandez, Child Serial Killer Suspect, Confesses To 5 Murders: Cops |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=5 July 2014 |newspaper=Omaha Sun Times |location=[[Omaha, Nebraska]] |accessdate=17 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402191055/http://www.omahasuntimes.com/2014/07/filiberto-hernandez-child-serial-killer-suspect-confesses-to-5-murders-cops/ |archive-date=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Jorge Humberto Mart\u00ednez C\u00f3rtez]]: also known as \"El Matanovias\"; killed between two and three of his romantic partners from 2011 to 2014; currently awaiting sentencing.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.proceso.com.mx/508643/interpol-captura-en-guatemala-al-matanovias-la-pgj-cdmx-solicitara-traslado |title=Interpol captura en Guatemala al \"Matanovias\"; la PGJ-CDMX solicitar\u00e1 su traslado |trans-title=Interpol captures the \"Matanovias\" in Guatemala; the PGJ-CDMX requests his transfer |date=24 October 2017 |magazine=[[Proceso (magazine)|Proceso]] |language=es |publisher=Comunicaci\u00f3n e Informaci\u00f3n S.A. de C.V |accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/entregan-el-matanovias-pgr-en-guatemala |title=Entregan a \"El Matanovias\" a PGR en Guatemala |trans-title=They deliver \"El Matanovias\" to PGR in Guatemala |first=Jos\u00e9 |last=Mel\u00e9ndez |date=15 October 2017 |newspaper=El Universal |language=es |accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Alejandro M\u00e1ynez]]: may have killed over 50 women with accomplices.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pr5HAAAAYAAJ&q=alejandro+maynez&dq=alejandro+maynez |title=Cosechja de mujeres: safar\u00ed en el desierto mexicano |first=Diana |last=Washington V\u00e1ldez |publisher=University of Texas |year=2005 |isbn=9706519882 |pages=168\u2013170}}</ref>\n*[[House of Laments|Tadeo Fulgenc\u00edo Mej\u00eda]]: responsible for several murders during the 1890s and 1900s, motivated by delirious idea of contacting his deceased wife. Now the house in [[Guanajuato]], where he committed the crimes, is known as \"The House of Laments\" (''Casa de los lamentos''), and according to legend is haunted.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aztecaamerica.com/notas/extranormal/59060/tragedia-en-casa-de-los-lamentos |title=Tragedia en Casa de los Lamentos |last=Enciso |first=Alejandra |date=2011-06-16 |website=[[TV Azteca]] |language=es |accessdate=2013-11-18}}</ref>\n*[[Silvia Meraz]]: [[Sonora]] woman involved in an occult sect, killed three persons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/centralamericaandthecaribbean/mexico/9177633/Children-sacrificed-to-Mexicos-cult-of-Saint-Death.html |title=Children 'sacrificed' to Mexico's cult of Saint Death |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=31 March 2012 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Agust\u00edn Salas del Valle]]: also known as \"Jack the Strangler\"; killed more than twenty women in Mexico City's Central Zone.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2010/01/agustin-salas-del-valle-el.html |title=Agust\u00edn Salas del Valle, \"El Estrangulador de mujeres\" (M\u00e9xico) |first=Horacio B. |last=Rivera |date=19 January 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |access-date=10 July 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Fel\u00edcitas S\u00e1nchez Aguill\u00f3n]]: named \"The Ogress of [[Colonia Roma]]\" was a nurse, midwife and baby farmer responsible for an unknown number of murders during the 1930s, possibly 50 victims, in [[Mexico City]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://enciclopediadelosasesinosenserie.blogspot.mx/2010/12/felicitas-sanchez-aguillon-la.html |title=Fel\u00edcitas S\u00e1nchez Agill\u00f3n. \"La Descuartizadora de la Colonia Roma\". (M\u00e9xico) |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=6 December 2010 |website=Enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=25 December 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Cristina Soledad S\u00e1nchez Esquivel]]: also known as \"La Matataxistas\"; killed between five and six taxi drivers in [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]] in 2010 with her accomplice Aar\u00f3n Herrera Hern\u00e1ndez; sentenced to 130 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.info7.mx/seccion/la-matataxistas-actuo-por-venganza-contra-los-hombres/477032 |title=La matataxistas actu\u00f3 por venganza contra los hombres |trans-title=La Matataxistas acted for revenge against men |first=Badillo |last=Victor |date=2010-06-17 |website=INFO7 |language=es |accessdate=26 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Magdalena Sol\u00eds]]: religious fanatic, proclaimed \"The High Blood's Priestess\", killed eight persons in ritual sacrifices<ref name=\"TrueTv's Crime Library\">{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/vampires/4.html |title=Crime Library: The Vampire Killers |first=Katherine |last=Ramsland |website=TruTv |access-date=July 21, 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014144507/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/weird/vampires/4.html |archive-date=2012-10-14}}</ref>\n*[[Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9]]: killed three young girls between 2007 and 2008 in [[M\u00e9rida, Yucat\u00e1n]]; later died in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asesinosenseriebios.blogspot.mx/2010/02/mario-alberto-sulu-canche-el.html |title=Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9. El Matachavitas. (M\u00e9xico) |trans-title=Mario Alberto Sul\u00fa Canch\u00e9. The Young-Girls-Killer |last1=Rivera |first1=Horacio B. |date=19 February 2010 |website=La enciclopedia de los asesinos en serie |language=es |accessdate=14 May 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Moldova===\n*[[Alexander Skrynnik]]: also known as the \"Moldavian Chikatilo\"; killed and then mutilated three women in [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]] and [[Yakutia]] from the mid\u20131970s to 1980; executed 1981.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://brw.md/moldavskii-maniac-aleksander-skrynnikov/ |title=\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043a \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 2. \u0414\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0421\u043a\u0440\u044b\u043d\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 |trans-title=Handwriting of the criminal 2. The case of Skrynnik |date=October 25, 2017 |website=BRW \u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Morocco===\n*[[Hadj Mohammed Mesfewi]]: also known as the \"[[Marrakesh]] Arch-Killer\"; drugged and killed 36 women; died 1906.\n\n===Netherlands===\n*[[Klaas Annink]]: also known as \"Huttenkloas\"; robber and murderer who killed along with his wife Anna and son Jannes; both he and his wife were executed in 1775.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.molenaarshuis.nl/huttenkloas.htm |title=Huttenkloas |website=Molenaarshuis |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060620072915/http://www.molenaarshuis.nl/huttenkloas.htm |archivedate=June 20, 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Hendrikje Doelen]]: 19th century farm-wife who poisoned several people in a [[poorhouse]] from 1845 to 1846, killing three of them; died of natural causes in 1847.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.drenlias.nl/index.html?option=com_familias&task=zoeken&bron=na1811&lname1=DOELEN&fname1=HENDRIKJE&header=advanced&plaats=&van=1848&tot=1848&methode=exact&submit.x=21&submit.y=14&submit=Zoeken |title=Hendrikje Doelen |website=Drenlias.nl |access-date=24 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180827044030/http://www.drenlias.nl/index.html?option=com_familias&task=zoeken&bron=na1811&lname1=DOELEN&fname1=HENDRIKJE&header=advanced&plaats=&van=1848&tot=1848&methode=exact&submit.x=21&submit.y=14&submit=Zoeken |archive-date=27 August 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Willem van Eijk]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Harkstede]]\"; convicted of the murders of five women between 1971 and 2001.\n*[[Koos Hertogs]]: convicted of the murders of three women between 1979 and 1980.\n*[[Aalt Mondria]]: escaped mental patient who murdered a family of three in 1978; after release, murdered his girlfriend's son in 1997; died 2011 from untreated [[Hepatitis C]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.destentor.nl/hardenberg/seriemoordenaar-aalt-mondria-overleden~ae72d3fa/ |title=Seriemoordenaar Aalt Mondria overleden |trans-title=Serial killer Aalt Mondria dies |date=28 September 2011 |newspaper=[[De Stentor]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gustav M\u00fcller (serial killer)|Gustav M\u00fcller]]: German watchmaker who murdered his wife and son in [[Rotterdam]] in 1897; surrendered and subsequently confessed to killing his parents and at least fourteen other wives around the world; acquitted by reason of insanity and confined to an asylum.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/2016270503/1897-11-09/ed-1/seq-6/#date1=1897&sort=date&rows=20&words=Gustav+Muller&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=12&state=&date2=1898&proxtext=Gustav+Muller&y=19&x=19&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=2 |title=Slew Fourteen Wives |date=November 9, 1897 |newspaper=Waterbury Evening Democrat |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Chronicling America}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Soultana]]: strangled two women in 2010, suspected of three more murders; sentenced to 25 years plus provision in 2014.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2686/Binnenland/article/detail/3600023/2014/02/19/Patrick-S-bekent-betrokkenheid-bij-moord-op-Farida-Zargar.dhtml |title=Patrick S. bekent betrokkenheid bij moord op Farida Zargar |trans-title=Patrick S. confesses involvement in the murder of Farida Zargar |date=24 March 2017 |newspaper=de Volkskrant |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michel Stockx]]: murdered three children around [[Assen]] in 1991; sentenced to 20 years in prison in 1992; died of severe burns from an incident during his work therapy in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.misdaadjournalist.nl/rapportages/michelstockxendedodekinderen.html |title=Michel Stockx en de dode kinderen |trans-title=Michel Stockx and the dead children |first=Hendrik Jan |last=Korterink |website=Misdaad Journalist |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Maria Swanenburg]]: suspected of killing between 27 and 90 people with [[arsenic]] in [[Leiden]] in the 1880s; died in prison in 1915.\n*[[Hans van Zon]]: murdered three people from April to August 1967, including a former lover; suspected of several other murders; died 1998 from [[alcohol poisoning]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/gentleman-killer-hans-van-z-vast-voor-poging-tot-doodslag-buurman~b84f4d0a/ |title='Gentleman-killer' Hans van Z. vast voor poging tot doodslag buurman |trans-title='Gentleman-killer' Hans van Z. charged with attempted homicide of neighbor |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=12 March 1997 |newspaper=[[Trouw]] |language=nl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===New Zealand===\n*[[Robert Butler (criminal)|Robert Butler]]: Irish highwayman who allegedly killed a family of three in [[Dunedin]] in 1880; acquitted, but was later hanged for shooting a man in Australia.<ref>{{DNZB |title=Robert Butler |first=Brian |last=O'Brien |id=2b53 |accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Daniel Cooper (murderer)|Daniel Cooper]]: also known as \"The [[Newlands, New Zealand|Newlands]] Baby Farmer\"; killed two infants and supposedly his first wife; executed 1932.<ref>{{cite book |first=C. A. L. |last=Treadwell |title=Notable New Zealand Trials |location=New Plymouth |publisher=Thomas Avery |date=1936}}</ref>\n*[[Minnie Dean]]: Scottish immigrant [[Baby farming|baby farmer]] who killed at least three children by [[Laudanum]] poisoning and suffocation in the 1890s; executed by hanging in 1895.<ref>{{cite book |first=Graham |last=Hutchins |title=Bad: Crooks, Creeps and Killers in New Zealand |location=Auckland |publisher=Hodder Moa |date=2010 |isbn=978-1-86971-174-0}}</ref>\n\n===North Macedonia===\n*[[Viktor Karamarkov]]: known as \"The Macedonian [[Rodion Raskolnikov|Raskolnikov]]\"; drug addict who murdered four elderly women in [[Skopje]] from March to October 2009; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://makfax.com.mk/makedonija/109986/ |title=\u0414\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043d \u0437\u0430\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0440 \u0437\u0430 \u0412\u0438\u043a\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0430\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432 |trans-title=Life imprisonment for Viktor Karamarkov |date=June 16, 2010 |website=[[Makfax]] |language=mk |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Vlado Taneski]]: crime reporter arrested in June 2008 for the murder of three elderly women on whose deaths he had written articles; committed suicide in police custody; suspected of killing another woman.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/jun/24/pressandpublishing.internationalcrime |title=The shocking story of the newspaper crime reporter who knew too much |last=Smith |first=Helena |date=2008-06-24 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |location=London, UK |accessdate=2008-06-24}}</ref>\n\n===Norway===\n*[[Arnfinn Nesset]]: manager of a [[geriatric]] nursing home who poisoned twenty-two residents at the [[Orkdal]] Alders-og Sjukeheim institution over a period of years before being convicted in 1983.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=U7QSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=cfkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=2293,1624213&dq=arnfinn-nesset |title=Slayer of 22 sentenced |date=19 March 1983 |newspaper=[[Spokane Chronicle]] |accessdate=12 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Pakistan===\n*[[Javed Iqbal (serial killer)|Javed Iqbal]]: believed to have raped and killed 100 boys, committed suicide while in prison in 1991.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/serial-killer-javed-iqbal-who-sexually-abused-and-killed-2733.html |title=Serial killer Javed Iqbal who sexually abused and killed 100 children in Pakistan |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=25 February 2013 |website=[[India TV]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6PqlVwKyg?url=http://www.indiatvnews.com/crime/news/serial-killer-javed-iqbal-who-sexually-abused-and-killed-2733.html |archive-date=26 May 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Amir Qayyum]]: also known as the \"Brick Killer\"; murdered fourteen homeless men in [[Lahore]] with rocks or bricks when they were asleep and was sentenced to death in May 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.turkishweekly.net/news/31571/-death-for-lahore-brick-killer.html |title=Death for Lahore 'brick killer' |date=May 11, 2006 |website=Turkish Weekly |accessdate=February 26, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302140823/http://www.turkishweekly.net/news/31571/-death-for-lahore-brick-killer.html |archive-date=March 2, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Panama===\n*[[Silvano Ward Brown]]: known as \"The Panam\u00e1 Strangler\"; first serial killer in Panamanian history; strangled three women from 1959 to 1973 in the [[Panam\u00e1 Province]]; released in 1993 after serving a 20-year sentence.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://impresa.prensa.com/mas_de_la_prensa/muertes-prostitutas_0_966653491.html |title=Las muertes de las prostitutas |trans-title=The deaths of prostitutes |date=July 13, 2003 |newspaper=[[La Prensa (Panama City)|La Prensa]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> \n*[[Gilberto Ventura Ceballos]]: [[Dominican Republic|Dominican]] man who murdered five Panamanian youths of Chinese descent in [[La Chorrera, Panama|La Chorrera]] from 2010 to 2011; sentenced to 50 years imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Condenan-Ventura-Ceballos-asesinato-chorreranos_0_1152485117.html |title=Dictan 50 a\u00f1os de prisi\u00f3n para Ventura Ceballos y M\u00e9ndez por asesinato de 5 j\u00f3venes chorreranos |trans-title=Ventura Ceballos and M\u00e9ndez setenced to 50 years in prison for the murder of 5 young chorreranos |first=Nimay |last=Gonz\u00e1lez |date=9 July 2018 |website=[[Telemetro]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709183020/http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Condenan-Ventura-Ceballos-asesinato-chorreranos_0_1152485117.html |archive-date=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n*[[William Dathan Holbert]]: also known as \"Wild Bill\"; American expatriate who had the bodies of five other Americans buried on his property; he would kill people to get their money and properties; his wife, Laura Michelle Reese, was also arrested.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Desmienten-Wild-Bill-designado-capellan_0_731627270.html |title=Desmienten que \"Wild Bill\" haya sido designado como capell\u00e1n |trans-title=They deny that \"Wild Bill\" has been appointed as chaplain |website=Telemetro |language=es |accessdate=5 September 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908004447/http://www.telemetro.com/nacionales/Desmienten-Wild-Bill-designado-capellan_0_731627270.html |archive-date=8 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/08/05/william-holbert-panama-mu_n_671658.html |title=William Holbert Panama Murders: More Bodies Found at Hostel of U.S. Man Accused of Serial Killings |first=Nicholas |last=Sabloff |date=August 5, 2010 |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=28 March 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===Peru===\n\n*[[Pedro Pablo Nakada Lude\u00f1a]]: also known as \"The Apostle of Death\"; convicted of seventeen murders and claimed 25; sentenced to 35 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eltelegrafo.com.ec/noticias/judicial/13/pedro-pablo-nakada-el-mayor-asesino-en-serie-del-peru |title=Pedro Pablo Nakada, el mayor asesino en serie del Per\u00fa |trans-title=Pedro Pablo Nakada, the greatest serial killer of Peru |date=1 November 2013 |newspaper=[[El Tel\u00e9grafo (Ecuador)|El Tel\u00e9grafo]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Philippines===\n*[[Edgar Matobato]]: self-confessed hitman and serial killer who claims to have killed hundreds of people as part of the [[Davao Death Squad]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/in-depth/147414-edgar-matobato-liar-truth-teller |title=Edgar Matobato: Liar or truth-teller? |first=Chay F. |last=Hofile\u00f1a |date=27 September 2016 |website=[[Rappler]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Poland===\n*[[Bogdan Arnold]]: murdered four women in [[Katowice]] from 1966 to 1967; also attempted to poison his third wife; executed 1968.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://wiadomosci.onet.pl/na-tropie/bestia-z-katowic-horror-na-poddaszu/xr1mw |title=Bestia z Katowic. Horror na poddaszu |trans-title=The beast from Katowice. Horror in the attic |first=Joanna |last=Zaj\u0105czkowska |date=30 December 2011 |website=[[Wiadomo\u015bci]] |language=pl |accessdate=22 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Baczy\u0144ski]]: killed a woman and three men in Wroc\u0142aw and Bytom from 1946 to 1957; executed 1960.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://wroclaw.wyborcza.pl/wroclaw/7,142076,22437163,morderca-strzela-w-ciemnosciach-o-seryjnym-zabojcy-we-wroclawiu.html |title=Seryjny zab\u00f3jca strzela\u0142 do ludzi we Wroc\u0142awiu lat 50. Milicja Obywatelska by\u0142a bezradna |trans-title=The serial killer shot people in Wroc\u0142aw in the 1950s. Citizens' Militia was helpless |first=Karolina |last=Kijek |date=1 October 2017 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Wyborcza]] |language=pl |accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[J\u00f3zef Cyppek]]: also known as \"The Butcher of [[Niebuszewo]]\"; dismembered his neighbour in 1952; was sentenced to death and executed that same year; suspected of other murders.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://poczciarz.home.pl//wydarzenia/index.php?artikle=245 |title=Rze\u013dnik z Niebuszewa- J\u00f3zef Cyppek |trans-title=The butcher of Niebuszewo \u2013 J\u00f3zef Cyppek |first=Moniki |last=Adamowskiej |website=Poczciarz |language=pl |accessdate=28 April 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Ensztajn]]: also known as \"Vampire of \u0141owicz\"; raped and killed seven women in [[\u0141owicz]] and the surrounding areas in 1933; sentenced to 15 years in prison in 1934.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-wCXJ7aVNtcY/UEiwHUUF7VI/AAAAAAAABUQ/RNF0zgSYBDs/s1600/G%C5%82os+Poranny+22.+VII+1934.jpg |title=The story of a descendant of a rapist |website=Voice of the Morning |language=pl |access-date=19 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Krzysztof Gawlik]]: also known as \"Scorpio\"; murdered five people with a silenced machine gun in 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/pozwroc2001.htm |title=Morderstwa pi\u0119ciu os\u00f3b z Poznania i Wroc\u0142awia |trans-title=Murders of five people from Pozna\u0144 and Wroc\u0142aw |date=1 March 2003 |website=Karasmierci |language=pl |access-date=28 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080105102625/http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/pozwroc2001.htm |archive-date=5 January 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Grzesik]]: leader of the so-called \"Bureaucrats Gang\"; killed between eight and twenty people in several Polish voivodeships with his gang, mainly owners of exchange offices; suspected of more murders; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/krakow/krakow-kolejne-zarzuty-dla-gangu-kantorowcow/1dtbz3h |title=Hodowca truskawek ze swoim gangiem mordowa\u0142 w\u0142a\u015bcicieli kantor\u00f3w. Kolejne zarzuty |trans-title=Strawberry grower and his gang murdered the owners of money exchange offices. Further allegations |date=8 April 2017 |newspaper=[[Fakt]] |language=pl |accessdate=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Joachim Knycha\u0142a]]: also known as \"The Vampire of [[Bytom]]\" or \"Frankenstein\", who murdered five women between 1975 and 1982.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.zyciebytomskie.pl/artykul.php?id=1886&glowny=0 |title=Wampir z Bytomia |date=7 February 2011 |newspaper=\u017bycie Bytomskie |language=pl |accessdate=24 May 2012}}{{Dead link |date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wiadomosci.onet.pl/wiadomosci/slaski-frankenstein,1,3488062,wiadomosc.html |title=\u015al\u0105ski Frankenstein |trans-title=Silesian Frankenstein |first=Erika |last=Sjoblom |date=12 November 2008 |website=[[Onet.pl]] |language=pl |accessdate=24 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120716065047/http://wiadomosci.onet.pl/wiadomosci/slaski-frankenstein,1,3488062,wiadomosc.html |archive-date=16 July 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Edmund Kolanowski]]: necrophile who murdered three women from 1970 to 1982; also mutilated and desecrated corpses he excavated from chapels; executed 1986.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://poznan.wyborcza.pl/poznan/1,109268,11163581,Zanim_znow_zaatakuje____Historia_nekrofila.html |title=Zanim zn\u00f3w zaatakuje... Historia nekrofila |trans-title=Before he attacks again ... History of the necrophile |first=Piotr |last=\u017bytnicki |date=18 February 2012 |newspaper=Gazeta Wyborcza |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Karol Kot]]: killed two people from 1964 to 1966 in his native [[Krak\u00f3w]], attempted to murder many more; executed 1968.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://killer.radom.net/~sermord/zbrodnia.php?dzial=mordercy&dane=KotKarol |title=Mordercy: Kot Karol |trans-title=Killers: Kot Karol |year=1999 |website=Killer.radom.net |language=pl |accessdate=4 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040110182847/http://killer.radom.net/~sermord/zbrodnia.php?dzial=mordercy&dane=KotKarol |archive-date=January 10, 2004}}</ref>\n*[[Henryk Kuku\u0142a]]: also known as \"The Monster from [[Chorz\u00f3w]]\"; pedophile who murdered four children from 1980 to 1990; sentenced to 28 years in prison, expected to be released in 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/slask/henryk-kukula-monstrum-z-chorzowa-pedofil-ktory-mordowal-dzieci/ty7qzxe |title=Fakt24 ujawnia histori\u0119 monstrum z Chorzowa |trans-title=Fakt24 reveals the history of the monster from Chorz\u00f3w |first=Maciej |last=Molenda |date=2017-06-10 |newspaper=Fakt |language=pl |accessdate=2017-06-20}}</ref>\n*[[Tadeusz Kwa\u015bniak]]: also known as the \"Towel Strangler\"; violent pedophile who raped and murdered five boys from 1990 and 1991; also responsible for numerous robberies; hanged himself in his prison cell before he could be sentenced.\n*[[Zdzis\u0142aw Marchwicki]]: also known as the \"[[Zag\u0142\u0119bie D\u0105browskie|Zag\u0142\u0119bie]] Vampire\"; convicted of murdering fourteen women; executed in 1976.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.murderpedia.org/male.M/m/marchwicki-zdzislaw.htm |title=Zdislaw Marchwicki |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nikifor Maruszeczko]]: criminal who killed four men for the purpose of robbery; executed 1938.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.focus.pl/artykul/kilka-smiertelnych-miesiecy |title=Kilka \u015bmiertelnych miesi\u0119cy |trans-title=A few deadly months |first=Damian |last=Szymczak |date=27 June 2013 |magazine=[[Focus (Polish magazine)|Focus]] |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz (serial killer)|W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz]]: also known as \"The Gentleman Killer\"; killed up to 30 women; executed by hanging in 1957.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://gazetakrakowska.pl/skazani-na-smierc-wladyslaw-mazurkiewicz-elegancki-morderca/ar/1049152?_d=byfUiRFGfv8ZmwkkNJ0vtk7Il0S9kEOuJ9qVGrpQfRVtAPMbhiUElfZQFTpx50jZOplusplusUioHcPEGnxKi77pUJIA |title=Skazani na \u015bmier\u0107: W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz. Elegancki morderca |trans-title=Condemned to death: W\u0142adys\u0142aw Mazurkiewicz. An elegant killer |first=Artur |last=Dro\u017cd\u017cak |date=23 November 2013 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Krakowska]] |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160430132526/http://www.gazetakrakowska.pl/artykul/1049152,skazani-na-smierc-wladyslaw-mazurkiewicz-elegancki-morderca,id,t.html?_d=byfUiRFGfv8ZmwkkNJ0vtk7Il0S9kEOuJ9qVGrpQfRVtAPMbhiUElfZQFTpx50jZOplusplusUioHcPEGnxKi77pUJIA |archive-date=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Stanis\u0142aw Modzelewski]]: murdered seven women in [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] during the 1960s; executed in 1970.\n*[[Henryk Moru\u015b]]: killed seven people in the [[Piotrk\u00f3w Voivodeship]] from 1986 to 1992; sentenced to 25 years imprisonment; died of probable heart failure in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dzienniklodzki.pl/artykul/986609,bezwgledny-morderca-z-sulejowa-nie-zyje-henryk-morus-zmarl-w-wiezieniu,id,t.html |title=Bezwgl\u0119dny morderca z Sulejowa nie \u017cyje. Henryk Moru\u015b zmar\u0142 w wi\u0119zieniu |trans-title=The ruthless murderer from Sulej\u00f3w is dead. Henryk Moru\u015b died in prison |first=Marek |last=Okolny |date=6 September 2013 |newspaper=Dziennik Lodzki |language=pl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://piotrkowtrybunalski.naszemiasto.pl/wydarzenia/865547.html |title=Morderca z Sulejowa bez \u0142aski |trans-title=A murderer from Sulej\u00f3w without grace |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=19 June 2008 |website=Piotrk\u00f3w Trybunalski |language=pl |access-date=19 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091030054216/http://piotrkowtrybunalski.naszemiasto.pl/wydarzenia/865547.html |archive-date=30 October 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Grzegorz Musiatowicz]]: violent criminal who killed three men between 2002 and 2014; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://wyborcza.pl/7,90535,24746795,dozywotniacy-kim-sa-wiezniowie-skazani-na-najwyzszy-wymiar.html |title=Do\u017cywotniacy: \"Kim s\u0105 wi\u0119\u017aniowie skazani na najwy\u017cszy wymiar kary?\" Lizut: \"W ka\u017cdym z nich jest inna historia\" |trans-title=Do\u017cywotniacy: \"Who are the prisoners sentenced to the highest sentence?\" Lizut: \"Each of them has a different story\" |first=Marta |last=Bratkowska |date=8 May 2019 |newspaper=Gazeta Wyborcza |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Leszek P\u0119kalski]]: also known as the \"Vampire of [[Byt\u00f3w]]\"; killed up to seventeen women.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA321&dq=Leszek+Pekalski&cd=7#v=onepage&q=Leszek%20Pekalski |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |first=Eric W. |last=Hickey |date=2009-06-23 |publisher=Cengage Learning |edition=5th |page=321 |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7}}</ref>\n*[[Kazimierz Polus]]: pedophile who killed two boys and one man from 1971 to 1982; executed 1985.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.poznan.pl/mim/necropolis/plan.html?urlAnchor=OpenMap&mtype=cemeteries&cm_id=1&surname=Polus&name=Kazimierz&id=22986 |title=Kazimierz Polus - burial place in Mi\u0142ost\u00f3w in Pozna\u0144 |access-date=7 July 2017 |language=pl}}</ref>\n*[[Skin Hunters]]: Karol Bana\u015b, Andrzej Nowocie\u0144, Dr. Janusz Kuli\u0144ski and Dr. Pawe\u0142 Wasilewski; paramedics and doctors in [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] who killed patients for profit; all four were convicted and officials are investigating possible accomplices.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/3323663.stm |title=Paramedic held in funeral scam |first=Adam |last=Easton |date=2003-12-16 |website=[[BBC News Online|BBC News]] |accessdate=2010-05-23}}</ref>\n*[[Mariusz Sowi\u0144ski]]: also known as \"The [[Stefankowice]] Vampire\"; raped and killed four women from 1994 to 1997; sentenced to 50 years in prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/hrub1997.html |title=Wampir ze Stefankowic (Hrubieszowskie) - 4 morderstwa i gwa\u0142ty |trans-title=Vampire from Stefankowice (Hrubieszowskie) - 4 murders and rapes |website=Krasmierci |language=pl |date=26 June 2000 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070630083700/http://www.karasmierci.info.pl/hrub1997.html |archive-date=June 30, 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Pawe\u0142 Tuchlin]]: also known as \"Scorpion\"; killed nine women and attempted to kill eleven more to feel better; executed 1987.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.wprost.pl/tygodnik/2429/lowcy.html |title=\u0141owcy |trans-title=Hunters |first=Ewa |last=Ornacka |date=3 January 1999 |magazine=[[Wprost]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mieczys\u0142aw Zub]]: also known as \"Fantomas\"; killed four women the area of [[Ruda \u015al\u0105ska]]; committed suicide in 1985.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/slask/mieczyslaw-zub-fantomas-nieuchwytny-psychopata-ktory-terroryzowal-slask/986ydes |title=Nieuchwytny psychopata terroryzowa\u0142 \u015al\u0105sk |trans-title=An elusive psychopath terrorized Silesia |first=Maciej |last=Molenda |date=2017-04-06 |newspaper=Fakt |access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref>\n\n===Portugal===\n*[[Diogo Alves]]: also known as the \"Aqueduct Murderer\"; Spanish man who robbed and threw poor people off [[Lisbon]]'s [[\u00c1guas Livres Aqueduct]] between 1836 and 1840; executed 1841.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://pereulki.com/2015/06/ubijtsa-s-akveduka-istoriya-diogo-alvesha-samogo-izvestnogo-prestupnika-portugalii/ |title=\u0423\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0430 \u0441 \u0410\u043a\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0443\u043a\u0430: \u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0414\u0438\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0410\u043b\u0432\u0435\u0448\u0430, \u0421\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0418\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0443\u0433\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438 |trans-title=Aqueduct Killer: The Story of Diogo Alves, Portugal's Most Famous Criminal |date=June 22, 2015 |website=\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0443\u043b\u043a\u0438 \u041b\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043d\u0430 |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ant\u00f3nio Lu\u00eds Costa]]: ex-[[Portuguese National Republican Guard|GNR]] officer from [[Santa Comba D\u00e3o]] who murdered three women between 2005 and 2006; sentenced to 25 years in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://expresso.sapo.pt/dossies/diario/os-vizinhos-de-socrates-na-prisao=f899794 |title=Os vizinhos de S\u00f3crates na pris\u00e3o |trans-title=S\u00f3crates's prison neighbours |last1=Franco |first1=Hugo |last2=Moleiro |first2=Raquel |last3=Gustavo |first3=Rui |lastauthoramp=yes |date=25 November 2014 |newspaper=[[Expresso (newspaper)|Expresso]] |language=pt |access-date=13 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Romania===\n\n*[[Vera Renczi]]: poisoned two husbands, one son and 32 of her suitors in the 1920s and 1930s.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://adevarul.ro/locale/calarasi/sfarsitul-cumplit-celei-mai-sadice-criminale-vaduva-neagra-femeia-misterioasa-ucis-35-barbati-1_57372ef05ab6550cb8eef23c/index.html |title=Sf\u00e2r\u015fitul cumplit al celei mai sadice criminale. V\u0103duva Neagr\u0103, femeia misterioas\u0103 care a ucis 35 de b\u0103rba\u0163i |trans-title=The terrible end of the most sadistic criminal. The Black Widow, the mysterious woman who killed 35 men |first=Ionela |last=St\u0103nil\u0103 |date=1 June 2016 |newspaper=[[Adev\u0103rul]] |language=ro |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.descopera.ro/cultura/3470508-vaduva-neagra-sau-castelana-din-berkerekul |title=Vaduva Neagra sau Castelana din Berkerekul |trans-title=Black Widow or Chatelaine of Berkerekul |first=Adrian |last=Nicolae |date=11 October 2008 |website=Descoper\u0103 |language=ro |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ion R\u00eemaru]]: murdered and raped young women in [[Bucharest]] from 1970 to 1971; executed in 1971.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://adevarul.ro/locale/alexandria/secretele-faimosului-criminal-ramaru-vampirul-bucuresti-sugea-sangele-victimelor-sfasia-organele-genitale-dintii-1_56602b4f7d919ed50ed9e3a3/index.html |title=Secretele faimosului criminal R\u00e2maru, \"vampirul din Bucure\u015fti\": sugea s\u00e2ngele victimelor \u015fi le sf\u00e2\u015fia organele genitale cu din\u0163ii |trans-title=Secrets of the famous criminal R\u00e2maru, \"the vampire from Bucharest\": sucked the blood of his victims and ripped their genitals with his teeth |first=Elisabeth |last=Bouleanu |date=4 December 2015 |newspaper=Adev\u0103rul |language=ro |access-date=4 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Vasile Tcaciuc]]: also known as \"The Butcher of [[Ia\u0219i]]\": murdered victims with an axe and confessed to have committed at least 26 murders; shot dead by a policeman while trying to escape from prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.procuror.ro/article/8791/Vasile-Tcaciuc-ndash-Macelarul-din-Iasi |title=Vasile Tcaciuc \u2013 Macelarul din Iasi |trans-title=Vasile Tcaciuc - Butcher from Iasi |date=2009 |website=Procuror |language=ro |accessdate=February 20, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140225183013/http://www.procuror.ro/article/8791/Vasile-Tcaciuc-ndash-Macelarul-din-Iasi |archive-date=2014-02-25}}</ref>\n*[[Romulus Vere\u0219]]: convicted of five murders in the 1970s; sent to a mental institution; died in 1993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clujeanul.ro/cluj/citeste-povestea-celui-mai-temut-criminal-al-clujului-omul-cu-ciocanul-2394295 |title=Cite\u015fte povestea celui mai temut criminal al Clujului: \"Omul cu ciocanul\" |trans-title=Read the story of the most feared criminal in Cluj: \"The man with the hammer\" |date=2008-02-17 |website=Clujeanul |language=ro |accessdate=2008-03-12 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080301111548/http://www.clujeanul.ro/cluj/citeste-povestea-celui-mai-temut-criminal-al-clujului-omul-cu-ciocanul-2394295 |archive-date=2008-03-01}}</ref>\n\n===Russia===\n{{Main|List of Russian serial killers}}\n\n===Serbia===\n*[[Baba Anujka]] (also known as Anna Pistova, Ana di Pi\u0161tonja, Anuyka Dee, \"The Banat Witch\" and \"The Witch of [[Vladimirovac]]\"); professional poisoner who poisoned between 50 and 150 people until apprehended in 1928.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/reportaze/aktuelno.293.html:792782-BANATSKA-VESTICA-ZAVILA-VLADIMIROVAC-U-CRNO-Baba-Anujka-je-bila-prvi-serijski-ubica-u-Srbiji-ubila-150-ljudi |title=Baba Anujka je bila prvi serijski ubica u Srbiji, ubila 150 ljudi |trans-title=Baba Anujka was the first serial killer in Serbia, killing 150 people |date=5 May 2019 |newspaper=[[Ve\u010dernje novosti]] |language=sr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Slovakia===\n*[[Matej \u010curko]]: also known as the \"Slovak Cannibal\"; killed and cannibalized two willing victims in 2010 in [[Kysak]], suspected of another 28 such cases from 2009 to 2011; killed by police in 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.corriere.it/english/11_agosto_02/cannibal-victims_fa52f944-bcf3-11e0-b530-d2ad6f731cf9.shtml |title=Slovak Cannibal's Possible Italian Victims \u2013 Thirty Missing Women Profiled |first=Massimo |last=Sideri |translator-first=Giles |translator-last=Watson |date=August 2, 2011 |newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]] |edition=English |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Juraj Lupt\u00e1k]]: also known as the \"Strangler from [[Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica]]\"; shepherd who raped and strangled three women from 1978 to 1982; executed 1987 in Bratislava.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://korzar.sme.sk/c/5770728/dievca-vymodelovalo-tvar-svojho-vraha-bol-nim-krvavy-baca.html#axzz4krXbYeYQ |title=Diev\u010da vymodelovalo tv\u00e1r svojho vraha. Bol n\u00edm \"krvav\u00fd ba\u010da\" |trans-title=The girl modeled the face of her killer. He was \"bloody shepherd\" |first=Eva |last=Bombov\u00e1 |date=18 February 2011 |newspaper=[[Korz\u00e1r]] |language=sk |accessdate=2017-06-24}}</ref>\n*[[Ondrej Rigo]]: killed, raped and mutilated nine women in [[Amsterdam]], [[Munich]] and [[Bratislava]], always wearing socks on his hands; he remains the [[Slovaks|Slovak]] murderer with the highest number of victims and he is also the most prolific serial killer in modern Slovak history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://refresher.sk/33850-Ondrej-Rigo-Na-svedomi-ma-9-zivotov-a-vysluzil-si-titul-najbrutalnejsi-seriovy-vrah-Slovenska?gdpr-accept=1 |title=Ondrej Rigo: Na svedom\u00ed m\u00e1 9 \u017eivotov a vysl\u00fa\u017eil si titul najbrut\u00e1lnej\u0161\u00ed s\u00e9riov\u00fd vrah Slovenska |trans-title=Ondrej Rigo: He killed 9 and is Slovakia's most brutal serial killer |first=Franti\u0161ek |last=Kulh\u00e1nek |date=4 June 2016 |website=Refresher.sk |language=sk |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jozef Slov\u00e1k]]: after serving just 8 years for his first murder from 1978, Slov\u00e1k killed at least four other women in [[Slovakia]] and [[Czech Republic]] in the early 1990s; highly intelligent, holder of numerous patents in electronics.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.pluska.sk/slovensko/vrah-genius.html |title=Vrah g\u00e9nius! |trans-title=Killer genius! |date=9 June 2008 |newspaper=[[Plus JEDEN DE\u0147]] |language=sk |accessdate=20 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Slovenia===\n*[[Silvo Plut]]: killed three women in Slovenia and Serbia from 1990 until 2006; committed suicide in prison in 2007.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.si/204085 |title=Silvo Plut obsojen na 30 let zaporne kazni |trans-title=Silvo Plut sentenced to 30 years in prison |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2 October 2006 |newspaper=[[Dnevnik (Slovenia)|Dnevnik]] |language=sl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Metod Trobec]]: raped and killed at least five women between 1976 and 1978; committed suicide in prison in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.slovenskenovice.si/crni-scenarij/doma/dolenja-vas-kraj-nesrecnega-imena |title=Dolenja vas, kraj nesre\u010dnega imena |trans-title=Dolenja Vas, a place of unlucky name |first=Vojko |last=Zakraj\u0161ek |date=January 5, 2012 |newspaper=[[Slovenske novice]] |language=sl |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===South Africa===\n{{as of|2014|October}}, South Africa had 160 recorded serial killers since 1950. A disproportionately large number of them were white males, although no racial group was more likely to be a victim.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/crime-courts/most-sa-serial-killers-are-white-males-1.1766044 |title=Most SA serial killers are white males |last=Geach |first=Chelsea |date=16 October 2014 |newspaper=[[Cape Argus]] |via=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |accessdate=29 October 2014}}</ref>\n\n*[[Asande Baninzi]]: killed eighteen people in the span of three months in 2001 with accomplice Mthutuzeli Nombewu; was given 19 life sentences and 189 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/B/BANINZI_asande.php |title=Asande Baninzi |last=Wetsch |first=Elisabeth |date=2005 |website=Serial Killer News |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008070518/http://www.crimezzz.net/serialkiller_news/B/BANINZI_asande.php |archive-date=2015-10-08}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Basson]]: first documented South African serial killer; killed nine people in [[Claremont, Cape Town|Claremont]] between 1903 and 1906 and buried them in his backyard; committed suicide to avoid arrest.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.africacrime-mystery.co.za/books/fsac/chp1.htm |title=Murdering for money, Pierre Basson: 1903 |last=Marsh |first=Rob |date=2009 |website=AfricaCrime-Mystery.co.za |access-date=19 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Sibusiso Duma]]: murdered seven people in the [[Pietermaritzburg]] area of [[KwaZulu Natal]] in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Life-in-jail-for-serial-killer-20090817 |title=Life in jail for Serial Killer |date=2009-08-17 |website=[[News24]] |access-date=2010-04-10 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920180328/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Life-in-jail-for-serial-killer-20090817 |archive-date=2012-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Gamal Lineveldt]]: responsible for the \"[[Cape Flats]] Murders\"; murdered four European women from October to November 1940; executed 1942.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://murderpedia.org/male.L/l/lineveldt-gamal.htm |title=Gamal Salie Lineveldt |first=Juan Ignacio |last=Blanco |website=Murderpedia |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Cedric Maake]]: also known as the \"[[Wemmer Pan]] Killer\"; serial rapist; murdered at least 27 people from 1996\u20131997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/679141.stm |title=Serial killer jailed for 1,340 years |date=16 March 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bulelani Mabhayi]]: also known as \"The Monster of Tholeni\"; killed twenty women and children from 2007 to 2012 in the village of Tholeni in the [[Eastern Cape]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Serial-killer-pleads-guilty-to-20-murders-20130828 |title=Serial killer pleads guilty to 20 murders |date=2013-08-28 |website=News24 |accessdate=5 April 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Simon Majola]]: together with accomplice Themba Nkosi, known as \"The Bruma Lake Killers\"; robbed and drowned at least eight men in Bruma Lake from 2000 to 2001; both sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.iol.co.za/saturday-star/dredging-up-the-lake-serial-killers-1136700 |title=Dredging up the lake serial killers |first=Hanlie |last=Retief |date=13 September 2011 |newspaper=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Saturday Star]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]]}}</ref>\n*[[Fanuel Makamu]]: also known as \"The [[Mpumalanga]] Serial Rapist\"; along with accomplice Henry Maile, robbed, raped and murdered six six women from February to September 2000; Maile was shot by police on September 14, while Makamu was captured and sentenced to 165 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Serial-killer-gets-165-years-20040727 |title=Serial killer gets 165 years |first1=Zenzele |last1=Kuhlase |first2=Oris |last2=Mnisi |date=27 July 2004 |website=[[News24]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jimmy Maketta]]: also known as \"The Jesus Killer\" convicted on sixteen counts of murder, nineteen counts of rape from 1996\u20131999.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-guilty-on-47-counts-351242 |title=Serial killer guilty on 47 counts |first=Caryn |last=Dolley |date=2007-05-03 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2009-08-19}}</ref>\n*[[Johannes Mashiane]]: also known as \"The Beast of [[Atteridgeville]]\" thirteen counts of murder, twelve counts of sodomy from 1982\u20131989.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |title=Serial Killers |website=A History of Madness: An Index of Serial Killers and Murderers |access-date=2010-04-09 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003172900/http://ajas29.tripod.com/stats.html |archive-date=2011-10-03}}</ref>\n*[[Daisy de Melker]]: poisoner; killed two husbands and one son between 1923\u20131932; executed in 1932.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimemagazine.com/daisy-de-melker-south-africas-first-serial-killer-0 |title=Daisy de Melker: South Africa's First Serial Killer |first=Marilyn Z. |last=Tomlins |date=13 October 2009 |website=Crime Magazine.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Samuel Bongani Mfeka]]: strangled six women from 1993 to 1996 in KwaZulu-Natal.<ref>{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA381&lpg=PA381&dq=Samuel+Bongani+Mfeka#v=onepage&q=Samuel%20Bongani%20Mfeka |date=February 2006 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3 |page=381}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Schechter |first=Harold |title=The A to Z Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=zM7ROzJPK2MC&pg=PA341&lpg=PA341&dq=%22Samuel+Bongani+Mfeka%22#v=onepage&q=%22Samuel%20Bongani%20Mfeka%22 |date=27 November 2012 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-1-4391-3885-4 |page=341 }}</ref>\n*[[Jack Mogale]]: also known as the \"West-End serial killer\"; convicted of raping and murdering sixteen women in [[Johannesburg]] in 2008 and 2009.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316 |title=West-End killer awaits sentencing |date=2011-03-16 |website=News24 |access-date=2011-03-17 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629051305/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/West-End-killer-awaits-sentencing-20110316 |archive-date=2011-06-29}}</ref>\n*[[Elifasi Msomi]]: also known as \"The Axe Killer\" murdered fifteen people from 1953-1955, claiming that he was under the influence of the [[Tokoloshe]].<ref name=\"LeandiLouw\">{{cite web |url=https://medium.com/@LeandiLouw/south-africas-3-most-memorable-serial-killers-560c5b7a6f1a |title=South Africa's 3 Most Memorable Serial Killers |first=Leandi |last=Louw |date=6 August 2018 |website=[[Medium.com]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mukosi Freddy Mulaudzi]]: also known as \"The [[Limpopo]] Serial Killer\"; escaped convict, originally responsible for two murders in 1990, who murdered eleven more people between 2005 and 2006; given 11 life sentences.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/limpopo-serial-killer-case-postponed-297239 |title=Limpopo serial killer case postponed |date=11 October 2006 |website=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Nicholas Lungisa Ncama]]: murdered six people in the [[Eastern Cape]] in 1997; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dispatch.co.za/1997/12/09/page%201.htm |title=Serial Killer Suspect in Court |first=Stan |last=Mzimba |date=9 December 1997 |newspaper=[[Daily Dispatch]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080501154307/http://www.dispatch.co.za/1997/12/09/page%201.htm |archivedate=May 1, 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Velaphi Ndlangamandla]]: also known as \"The Saloon Killer\"; robber who murdered nineteen people around Mpumalanga from April to September 1998; sentenced to 137 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/saloon-killer-gets-137-years-for-19-murders-42926 |title='Saloon killer' gets 137 years for 19 murders |date=19 September 2000 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[David Randitsheni]]: also known as \"[[Modimolle]] Serial Killer\" raped and murdered ten children (kidnapped and raped more) from 2004\u20132008.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-found-hanging-by-a-sheet-456838 |title=Serial killer found hanging by a sheet |date=2009-08-31 |agency=SAPA |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2009-08-31}}</ref>\n*[[Gert van Rooyen]]: allegedly abducted and murdered at least six girls from across [[South Africa]] from 1988\u20131989.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/he-feared-god-but-loved-young-girls-1.322079 |title=Feared God but 'loved' young girls |last=Gallagher |first=Christina |date=7 April 2007 |newspaper=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Star]] |via=Independent Online |access-date=10 June 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918005419/http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/he-feared-god-but-loved-young-girls-1.322079 |archive-date=18 September 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Louis van Schoor]]: former security guard who confessed to murdering 100 people; released on parole.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-freed-after-12-years-in-prison-1.225629 |title=Serial killer freed after 12 years in prison |first=Barbara |last=Hollands |date=2004-10-31 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=2015-12-09}}</ref>\n*[[Khangayi Sedumedi]]: also known as the \"Century City Killer\"; raped, robbed and murdered between four and six women in [[Century City, Cape Town|Century City]] from 2011 to 2015; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/century-city-killers-modus-operandi-revealed-2032665 |title=Century City killer's modus operandi revealed |first=Catherine |last=Rice |date=June 9, 2016 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Samuel Sidyno]]: also known as \"Capital Hill Serial Killer\"; murdered seven people in [[Pretoria]] from 1998\u20131999.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/sadistic-serial-killer-gets-seven-life-terms-45868 |title=Sadistic serial killer gets seven life terms |date=5 September 2000 |website=Independent Online |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Norman Afzal Simons]]: also known as \"Station Strangler\" raped, sodomised and murdered twenty-two children on the [[Cape Flats]] from 1986\u20131994.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/revisiting-the-station-strangler-cases-1.250970 |title=Revisiting the Station Strangler cases |last1=Bailey |first1=Candice |date=16 August 2005 |website=Independent Online |accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Moses Sithole]]: also known as the \"ABC Killer\" and the \"South African Strangler\"; raped and killed at least 38 young women in [[Atteridgeville]], [[Boksburg]] and Cleveland from 1994\u20131995.<ref name=\"LeandiLouw\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.iafrica.com/features/827627.htm |title=Worst criminals of SA |last=Kendal |first=Rebekah |date=3 May 2007 |website=iAfrica.com |accessdate=3 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720084655/http://news.iafrica.com/features/827627.htm |archive-date=20 July 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Thozamile Taki]]: also known as the \"[[Sugarcane]] Serial Killer\"; robbed and killed ten women in [[KwaZulu Natal]] and three in [[Eastern Cape]], dumping their bodies in sugarcane and tea [[plantation]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Sugarcane-killer-Release-her-20100302 |title=Sugarcane killer : Release her |date=2010-03-02 |website=News24 |access-date=2010-04-10 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120920180212/http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Sugarcane-killer-Release-her-20100302 |archive-date=2012-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Sipho Thwala]]: also known as the \"[[Phoenix, Durban|Phoenix]] Strangler\"; raped and murdered nineteen women in the sugarcane fields of [[KwaZulu Natal]] from 1996 to 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.discoverychannel.co.uk/crime/serialkillers/phoenixstrangler/index.shtml |title=Crimes That Shook The World: The Phoenix Strangler |date=2009 |website=Discovery Channel: Crimes and Forensics |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091208090320/http://www.discoverychannel.co.uk/crime/serialkillers/phoenixstrangler/index.shtml |archive-date=2009-12-08}}</ref>\n*[[Stewart Wilken]]: also known as \"Boetie Boer\"; raped, sodomised and murdered at least seven victims in and around [[Port Elizabeth]] from 1990\u20131997.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA344 |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |last=Hickey |first=Eric W. |date=23 June 2009 |publisher=Cengage Learning |page=344 |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=s7cEAQAAIAAJ |title=Strangers on the Street: Serial Homicide in South Africa |last=Pistorius |first=Micki |authorlink=Micki Pistorius |year=2002 |publisher=Penguin |isbn=978-0-14-100356-6 |accessdate=5 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/local-news/north-harbour-news/696177 |title=Story of a Serial Killer |date=30 October 2008 |newspaper=North Harbour News |accessdate=5 April 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Elias Xitavhudzi]]: also known as \"Pangaman\" murdered sixteen people in [[Atteridgeville]] in the 1960s.<ref>{{cite book |last=Newton |first=Michael |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC |date=February 2006 |publisher=Infobase Publishing |pages=207 & 246 |isbn=978-0-8160-6987-3}}</ref>\n*[[Christopher Mhlengwa Zikode]]: also known as \"Donnybrook Serial Killer\"; murdered eighteen people in [[Donnybrook, KwaZulu-Natal]] from 1994\u20131995.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=oN_QKBYvSloC&pg=PA341&lpg=PA341&dq=christopher+zikode,+serial+killer#v=onepage&f=false |title=Serial Murderers and their Victims |first=Eric W. |last=Hickey |date=June 23, 2009 |page=341 |publisher=Cengage Learning |isbn=978-0-495-60081-7 |via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n===South Korea===\n*[[Chijon family]]: gang of cannibals that was sentenced to death for killing five people; sentenced to death in 1994; all members were [[executed by hanging]] on November 2, 1995.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://news.joins.com/article/3684096 |title=\uc0b4\uc778\ub9c8 \uc9c0\uc874\ud30c \uc6d0\ub798 \uc870\uc9c1\uba85\uc740 \ub9c8\uc2a4\uce78 |trans-title=Murderer tribe originally named Maskan |date=2009-07-12 |newspaper=[[JoongAng Ilbo]] |language=ko |access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref>\n*[[Crown Prince Sado]]: [[Joseon]] prince who raped and killed his palace staff; sealed in a rice chest and died.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3010313 |title=The ever-changing history of Prince Sado |author=Jin Eun-Soo |date=15 October 2015 |newspaper=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jeong Du-yeong]]: killed an officer in 1986; after release, killed eight other people in robberies from 1999 to 2000; sentenced to death.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.donga.com/fbin/output?f=eA_&n=200004160101 |title=\uc5f4\ub2ec\uc0c8 9\uba85 \uc8fd\uc600\ub2e4\u2026\ubd80\uc0b0 \u4e2d\u4f01\ud68c\uc7a5\ubd80\ubd80 \uc0b4\ud574\ubc94 \uc790\ubc31 |trans-title=Killed nine people in ten months ... confessed to murder of husband and wife |date=16 April 2000 |newspaper=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]] |language=ko |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Jeong Nam-gyu]]: sexually assaulted and killed fourteen people from 2004 to 2006; died in hospital after failing to hang himself the previous day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LPOD&mid=sec&sid1=001&sid2=140&oid=001&aid=0002987292&isYeonhapFlash=Y |title=\uc5f0\uc1c4\uc0b4\uc778\ubc94 \uc815\ub0a8\uaddc \uc11c\uc6b8\uad6c\uce58\uc18c\uc11c \uc790\uc0b4 |trans-title=Serial Killer Chung Nam-gyu commits suicide at Seoul detention center |date=2009-11-22 |agency=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |website=[[Naver]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kang Ho-sun]]: sentenced to death in 2010 for killing ten women, including his wife and mother-in-law.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking_news_detail.asp?id=13851 |title=Death sentence for South Korean serial killer |date=10 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Standard (Hong Kong)|The Standard]] |accessdate=2013-11-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110003435/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking_news_detail.asp?id=13851 |archivedate=2013-11-10}}</ref>\n*[[Kim Hae-sun]]: violent drunkard who raped and killed three children in 2000; executed 2001.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://media.daum.net/culture/art/view.html?cateid=1021&newsid=20060323092612574&p=tvreport |title=\uc5b4\uc774\uc5c6\uace0 \ud574\uad34\ud55c \ubc94\uc8c4 '\uc0ac\uc774\ucf54\ud328\uc2dc'\uc871\ub4e4! |trans-title=A ridiculous and bizarre crime psychopath! |date=2006-03-23 |website=[[Daum.net]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kim Sun-ja (serial killer)|Kim Sun-ja]]: poisoned five people with potassium cyanide between 1986 and 1988 for monetary reasons; executed 1997.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hyunbulnews.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=296863|title=Death penalthy for the elderly Kim is unfair|last=Kim|first=Jiwon|date=November 23, 2011|work=Modern Buddhist Newspaper|access-date=July 16, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Lee Choon-jae]]: responsible for the \"Hwaseong serial murders\"; murdered fifteen women, including his sister-in-law, and raped numerous others; sentenced to life imprisonment for one murder in 1994, and connected to the others decades later.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2019/09/serial-killer-who-terrorized-south-korea-identified-after-30-years/ |title=South Korean serial killer who inspired 'Memories of Murder' identified after 30 years |date=September 18, 2019 |website=[[BNO News]] |accessdate=September 19, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Yoo Young-chul]]: cannibal; killed twenty-one people from September 2003 to July 2004, mainly young women and rich men; sentenced to death in 2004.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2004/08/13/2004081361048.html |title=Serial Killer Claims to Have Eaten Victims' Organs |first=Yong-hyun |last=Ahn |date=13 August 2004 |newspaper=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Spain===\n*[[The \"Frenchman's Garden\" Murders|Andr\u00e9s Aldije Monmej\u00e1 and Jos\u00e9 Mu\u00f1oz Lopera]]: responsible for the \"Frenchman's Garden\" murders; owners of an illegal gambling house who killed six visitors from 1889 to 1904; both garroted in 1906.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://gaceta.es/noticias/huerto-frances-peligroso-casino-andalucia-profunda-26052017-1710/ |title=El huerto del franc\u00e9s, un peligroso casino en la Andaluc\u00eda profunda |trans-title=The French Orchard, a dangerous casino in deepest Andalusia |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=26 May 2017 |newspaper=[[La Gaceta (Spain)|La Gaceta]] |language=es |access-date=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Francisca Ballesteros]]: known as ''La Viuda Negra''<ref name=\"abc.es\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.abc.es/espana/asesinos-serie-201012010000_noticia.html |title=La negra lista de asesinos en serie de Espa\u00f1a |trans-title=The black list of serial killers in Spain |date=December 1, 2010 |newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref> (\"The [[Latrodectus|Black Widow]]\"), poisoned her husband and three children in [[Valencia, Spain|Valencia]] between 1990 and 2004 (one survived), sentenced to 84 years in prison in 2005.\n*[[Manuel Blanco Romasanta]]: travelling salesman who claimed to be a [[werewolf]], confessed to thirteen murders and was convicted of eight in 1853; his initial death sentence commuted in order to make a study in [[clinical lycanthropy]], died in prison ten years later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.typicallyspanish.com/news/publish/article_13582.shtml |title=The Wolfman of Allariz |author=m.p. |date=13 November 2007 |website=Typically Spanish |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111204040513/http://www.typicallyspanish.com/news/publish/article_13582.shtml |archive-date=2011-12-04}}</ref>\n*[[Manuel Delgado Villegas]]: also known as ''El Arropiero''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The [[Arrope]] Trader\"), wandering criminal with [[XYY syndrome]] that confessed to 48 murders in [[Spain]], [[France]] and [[Italy]], including his girlfriend; considered guilty of seven and interned in a mental institution until his death in 1998.\n*[[Joaqu\u00edn Ferr\u00e1ndiz Ventura]]: insurance salesman who murdered five women in [[Castell\u00f3n Province]] between 1995 and 1996.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://elpais.com/diario/1998/09/10/cvalenciana/905455100_850215.html |title=La Guardia Civil detiene al supuesto asesino de Sonia Rubio en Benic\u00e0ssim. El supuesto asesino de Sonia Rubio ya fue condenado por abuso sexual |trans-title=The Civil Guard arrests the presumed killer of Sonia Rubio in Benic\u00e0ssim. The presumed killer of Sonia Rubio had been convicted previously of sexual assault |last=Fabra |first=Mar\u00eda |date=September 10, 1998 |newspaper=El Pa\u00eds |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 5, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Alfredo Gal\u00e1n]]: also known as \"The Playing Card Killer\", Spanish Army corporal who killed six individuals in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elobservadordelmundo.com/reportaje_detalle.asp?cod=1020 |title=La Parte Oscura de la Mente: Alfredo Gal\u00e1n Sotillo - El Asesino de la Baraja |trans-title=The Dark Part of the Mind: Alfredo Gal\u00e1n Sotillo - The Killer of the Baraja |date=August 19, 2011 |website=El Observador del Mundo |language=es |accessdate=March 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110910130600/http://www.elobservadordelmundo.com/reportaje_detalle.asp?cod=1020 |archive-date=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n*[[Juan D\u00edaz de Garayo]]: also known as \"The Sacamantecas\"; killed six people from 1870 to 1879 in [[\u00c1lava]]. Executed by [[garrote]] in 1881.<ref>{{cite book |last=Becerro de Bengoa |first=Ricardo |date=1881 |title=El Sacamantecas. Su Retrato y sus Cr\u00edmenes. Narraci\u00f3n escrita con arreglo a todos los datos aut\u00e9nticos |location=Vitoria |publisher=Viuda e Hijos de Iturbe |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Bernaldo de Quir\u00f3s |first=Constancio |date=1909 |title=Vidas Delincuentes |location=Madrid |publisher=Centro Editorial G\u00f3ngora |language=es}}</ref>\n*[[Francisco Garc\u00eda Escalero]]: also known as ''El Mendigo Asesino''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The Killer Beggar\"); [[schizophrenia|schizophrenic]] beggar convicted of eleven murders, confined to a psychiatric hospital since 1995\n*[[Gila Giraldo]]: also known as \"La Serrana de la Verra\"; alleged 15th-16th century serial killer who beheaded men she slept with.\n*[[Murder of Roc\u00edo Wanninkhof#Tony Alexander King|Tony Alexander King]]: also known as the \"Costa Killer\"; British sex offender who murdered two girls in [[Malaga]] in 1999 and 2003; suspected of possibly committing more murders in his native UK; sentenced to 19 years imprisonment.<ref name=\"El Mundo\">{{cite news |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2003/09/22/sociedad/1064218068.html |title=El asesino de Sonia y Roc\u00edo estrangul\u00f3 a cinco mujeres en Reino Unido |trans-title=The murderer of Sonia and Roc\u00edo who strangled five women in the United Kingdom |date=September 23, 2003 |newspaper=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]] |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 21, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Ram\u00f3n Laso]]: killed his two wives, child and brother in law in order to pursue extra-marital relationships.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elespanol.com/reportajes/grandes-historias/20170113/185732087_0.html |title=El enterrador convertido en asesino cuyas v\u00edctimas jam\u00e1s aparecieron |trans-title=The undertaker turned murderer whose victims were never found |last=Rada |first=Juan |date=January 15, 2017 |newspaper=[[El Espa\u00f1ol]] |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 9, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Enriqueta Mart\u00ed]]: self-proclaimed [[witch]] who kidnapped, prostituted, murdered and made potions with the remains of small children in early 20th century [[Barcelona]] (12 bodies were identified in her home); murdered in prison while awaiting trial in 1913.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://hemeroteca.lavanguardia.com/preview/1912/04/19/pagina-3/33336536/pdf.html |title=Poco despu\u00e9s de las tres y media de la madrugada de ayer, falleci\u00f3 en la c\u00e1rcel de mujeres la tristemente c\u00e9lebre secuestradora Enriqueta Mart\u00ed Ripoli... |trans-title=Shortly after half past three in the morning yesterday, the sadly celebrated kidnapper Enriqueta Mart\u00ed Ripoli died in the women's prison... |date=13 May 1913 |page=3 |newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]] |language=es |access-date=21 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[D\u00e1maso Rodr\u00edguez Mart\u00edn]]: ''El Brujo'' (\"The Warlock\"), serial rapist and [[voyeur]] imprisoned in 1981 after attacking a couple, killing the man and raping the woman. Escaped from prison to the [[Anaga]] mountains in 1991, where he killed two German hikers (one of them was raped). Cornered in an abandoned house, he shot himself unsuccessfully, only to be shot dead in turn by law enforcement.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.laopinion.es/sucesos/2016/02/14/brujo-bestia-moquinal/655875.html |title='El Brujo', la bestia de El Moquinal |trans-title='El Brujo', the beast of El Moquinal |last=Herrero |first=Antonio |date=15 February 2016 |newspaper=[[La Opini\u00f3n]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304005951/http://www.laopinion.es/sucesos/2016/02/14/brujo-bestia-moquinal/655875.html |archive-date=4 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Rodr\u00edguez Vega]]: ''El Mataviejas''<ref name=\"abc.es\"/> (\"The Old Lady Killer\"), raped and killed at least sixteen elderly women, sentenced to 440 years in prison in 1995, murdered by fellow inmates in 2002.\n*[[Abdelkader Salhi (serial killer)|Abdelkader Salhi]]: known as the \"10 Killer\"; German convicted of a robbery-murder in 1988 in Germany, later moving to Spain and allegedly murdering three prostitutes from August to September 2011; currently awaiting sentencing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.euroweeklynews.com/2011/09/29/costa-del-sol-serial-killer-arrested/#.XLCrBDAzbIV |title='Costa del Sol Serial Killer' arrested |date=29 September 2011 |website=[[EuroWeekly News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Gustavo Romero Tercero]]: \"The [[Valdepe\u00f1as]] Killer\", killed three people from 1993 to 1998.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2005/04/21/sociedad/1114074425.html |title=Condenan a 103 a\u00f1os de prisi\u00f3n a Gustavo Romero por el asesinato de tres personas en Valdepe\u00f1as |trans-title=Gustavo Romero sentenced to 103 years in prison for the murder of three people in Valdepe\u00f1as |date=April 22, 2005 |newspaper=El Mundo |location=Madrid, Spain |language=es |access-date=September 14, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Margarita S\u00e1nchez Guti\u00e9rrez]]: known as \"The Black Widow of Barcelona\"; poisoned family members and relatives, killing four of them; acquitted of the murders, but sentenced to 34 years for other crimes.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elpais.com/articulo/opinion/buzon/nicho/abierto/elpepiopi/19960801elpepiopi_1/Tes |title=Un buz\u00f3n como un nicho abierto |trans-title=A mailbox as an open niche |last1=Martin |first1=Andreu |date=1 August 1996 |newspaper=El Pa\u00eds |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Swaziland===\n*[[David Thabo Simelane]]: raped and killed 28 women, suspected of 45; sentenced to death in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.swazilive.com/Swaziland_News/Swaziland_News_Stories.asp?News_id=2722 |title=David Simelane gets death penalty, to be hanged |first=Linda |last=Jele |date=2 April 2011 |website=Swaziland News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Sweden===\n*[[Malm\u00f6 \u00d6stra hospital murders|Anders Hansson]]: hospital [[orderly]] in [[Malm\u00f6]] who poisoned his victims with detergents Gevisol and Ivisol between October 1978 and January 1979; his actions were called the \"[[Malm\u00f6 \u00d6stra hospital murders]]\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article12915042.ab |title=99 dagar \u2013 27 mord |trans-title=99 days - 27 murders |first=Linda |last=Hjert\u00e9n |date=2011-04-24 |newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]] |language=sv |accessdate=2014-01-17}}</ref>\n*[[Anders Lindb\u00e4ck (vicar)|Anders Lindb\u00e4ck]]: [[vicar]] who poisoned poor people with arsenic, three of them who died; committed suicide in custody in 1865.\n*[[John Ingvar L\u00f6vgren]]: confessed to four murders committed between 1958 and 1963 in the Stockholm region.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://stockholm.edublogs.org/2012/12/17/vi-kartlagger-fleminggatan-nummer-for-nummer/ |title=Vi kartl\u00e4gger Fleminggatan nummer f\u00f6r nummer |trans-title=We map Fleminggatan number by number |date=2012-12-17 |website=Stockholm \u2013 en guide till kultur, sev\u00e4rdheter och |language=sv |accessdate=2014-01-17}}</ref>\n*[[Hilda Nilsson]]: known as \"The Angel Maker on Bruks Street\"; [[Helsingborg]] baby farmer who murdered eight children; committed suicide in custody in 1917.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/malmo/atskilliga-spadbarn-dog-hos-anglamakerskorna/ |title=\u00c5tskilliga sp\u00e4dbarn dog hos \u00e4nglamakerskorna |trans-title=Several infants died at the hands of angel makers |last=Andersson |first=Martin |date=2 December 2012 |newspaper=[[Sydsvenskan]] |location=[[Malm\u00f6]] |language=sv |accessdate=6 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Switzerland===\n*[[Roger Andermatt]]: also known as the \"Death-Keeper of [[Lucerne]]\"; nurse who killed twenty-two people from 1995 to 2001; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nzz.ch/aktuell/startseite/articleDL2GQ-1.11845 |title=Es bleibt bei lebensl\u00e4nglich f\u00fcr den \"Todespfleger\" |trans-title=It remains a life sentence for the \"death-keeper\" |date=16 February 2006 |newspaper=[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]] |language=de |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Werner Ferrari]]: child killer who lured his victims from popular festivals, strangling them afterwards; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.blick.ch/news/schweiz/die-eltern-der-ermordeten-fabienne-imhof-klagen-an-warum-bloss-lernen-die-richter-nichts-id1799956.html |title=Die Eltern der ermordeten Fabienne Imhof klagen an: \"Warum bloss lernen die Richter nichts?\" |trans-title=The parents of the murdered Fabienne Imhof complain: \"Why are the judges learning nothing?\" |date=2012-03-08 |newspaper=[[Blick]] |language=de |accessdate=2014-09-25}}</ref>\n*[[Erich Hauert]]: sex offender who committed eleven rapes and three murders from 1982 to 1983; sentenced to life imprisonment; his case impacted treatment of dangerous sexual offenders in Switzerland tremendously.<ref>''Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung'', 20 September 1996, p. 53.</ref>\n\n===Taiwan===\n*[[Zhang Renbao]]: murdered three women from 1993 to 2003, also sexually violating the first victim; sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.appledaily.com.tw/appledaily/article/headline/20040617/1013505/ |title=\u7bb1\u5c4d\u6848\u8b8a\u614b\u6bba\u4eba\u72af\u5224\u6b7b |trans-title=Box corpse case murderer sentenced to death |date=17 June 2004 |newspaper=[[Apple Daily (Taiwan)|Apple Daily]] |language=zh |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Tunisia===\n*[[Naceur Damergi]]: rapist who killed thirteen minors in the [[Nabeul]] region in the 1980s; executed by hanging in 1990.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leaders.com.tn/article/11418-comment-a-ete-pendu-le-tueur-en-serie-de-nabeul |title=Comment a \u00e9t\u00e9 pendu le tueur en s\u00e9rie de Nabeul |trans-title=How was the serial killer of Nabeul hanged |date=17 May 2013 |website=Leaders |language=fr |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/crime_series_show.php?series_number=13&id=857 |title=Worldwide Hangings: Naceur Damergi |date=2014 |website=True Crime Library |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222024758/http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/crime_series_show.php?series_number=13&id=857 |archive-date=February 22, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Turkey===\n*[[S\u00fcleyman Akta\u015f]]: also known as the \"Nailing Killer\"; killed five people and nailed them in the eyes and head; he is kept in a psychiatric hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.haber7.com/guncel/haber/220403-civici-katilden-folklor-gosterisi |title='\u00c7ivici katil'den folklor g\u00f6sterisi |trans-title=Folklore show from 'The Nail Killer' |first=Aziz |last=G\u00fcl |date=2007-02-16 |website=Haber7.com |language=tr |accessdate=2014-03-04}}</ref>\n*[[Adnan \u00c7olak]]: also known as \"The Beast of Artvin\"; killed seventeen elderly women in [[Artvin]], Turkey from 1992 to 1995; in 2000 he was sentenced to death six times, and 40 years in prison. However, since October 1984, Turkey has not executed any prisoners, and {{as of|2004|lc=y}}, Turkey does not have capital punishment.\n*[[Seyit Ahmet Demirci]]: also known as the \"Furniture dealers' killer\"; killed three furniture dealers selected at random and because he was sexually abused by his employer during his youth;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/mobilyaci-seri-katili-39131508 |title=Mobilyac\u0131 seri katili |trans-title=The serial killer |date=6 February 2000 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |language=tr |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref> sentenced to death.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnnturk.com/turkiye/turkiyenin-korkunc-cinayetler-isleyen-14-seri-katili |title=T\u00fcrkiye'nin korkun\u00e7 cinayetler i\u015fleyen 14 seri katili |trans-title=Turkey's 14 serial killers committed terrible murders |date=13 June 2016 |website=[[CNN T\u00fcrk]] |language=tr |accessdate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[\u00d6zg\u00fcr Dengiz]]: serial killer from [[Ankara]], who killed four people and cannibalized at least one.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/09/16/guncel/agun.html |title=Yerli Hannibal'\u0131n anatomisi |trans-title=Anatomy of the native Hannibal |first1=Mansur |last1=\u00c7eli\u0307k |first2=G\u00f6k\u00e7er |last2=Tahi\u0307nci\u0307o\u011flu |date=September 16, 2007 |newspaper=[[Milliyet]] |language=tr |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071105112638/http://www.milliyet.com.tr/2007/09/16/guncel/agun.html |archive-date=5 November 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Atalay Filiz]]: fugitive suspected of four murders from 2012 to 2016.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/son-dakika-haberi-atalay-filiz-yakalandi-40116460 |title=Son dakika haberi: Atalay Filiz yakaland\u0131, \u00fcst\u00fcnden \u00e7\u0131kanlar \u015foke etti! |trans-title=Breaking news: Atalay Filiz caught, shocked by those on top! |first1=Banu |last1=\u015een |first2=Taylan |last2=Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m |date=2016-06-12 |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] |language=tr |accessdate=2016-06-12}}</ref>\n*[[Ali Kaya (serial killer)|Ali Kaya]]: also known as \"The Babyface Killer\"; responsible for ten murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/Yasam/2014/01/06/bebek-yuzlu-katil-firar-etti |title='Bebek y\u00fczl\u00fc katil' firar etti |trans-title='Baby-faced killer' escaped |first=Ads\u0131z |last=G\u00fcnebakan |date=6 January 2014 |newspaper=[[Sabah (newspaper)|Sabah]] |language=tr |accessdate=6 January 2014 }}</ref>\n*[[Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar]]: also known as \"Avc\u0131\" (\"Hunter\"); killed eight people from 1994 to 2018; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.haberturk.com/kayseri-haberleri/62629762-seri-katil-hamdi-kayapinar-adliyeye-sevk-edildikiz-kardesi-dahil-7-kisiyi-olduren-hamdi |title=Seri katil Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar adliyeye sevk edildi |trans-title=Serial killer Hamdi Kayap\u0131nar was sent to court |date=7 August 2018 |newspaper=[[Habert\u00fcrk]] |language=tr |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Yavuz Yap\u0131c\u0131o\u011flu]]: also known as \"The Screwdriver Killer\"; responsible for at least eighteen murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.radikal.com.tr/haber.php?haberno=60681 |title=Tornavidal\u0131 seri cinayet |trans-title=Serial murder with a screwdriver |first=Erdal |last=\u00d6zcan |date=2002-12-25 |newspaper=[[Radikal]] |language=tr |accessdate=2014-03-05 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305170036/http://www.radikal.com.tr/haber.php?haberno=60681 |archive-date=2014-03-05}}</ref>\n\n===Ukraine===\n*[[Zaven Almazyan]]: also known as the \"Voroshilovgrad Maniac\"; Russian soldier who raped and killed three women in [[Voroshilovgrad]]; executed 1973.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.allkriminal.ru/article/17492/671 |title=\u041b\u0443\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a \u0417\u0430\u0432\u0435\u043d \u0410\u043b\u043c\u0430\u0437\u044f\u043d |trans-title=Lugansk maniac Zaven Almazyan |date=3 October 2011 |website=AllKriminal.ru |language=ru |access-date=2013-10-07}}</ref>\n*[[Oleksandr Berlizov]]: also known as the \"Night Demon\"; sexual psychopath who raped numerous women from 1969 to 1972 in [[Dnipropetrovsk]], killing nine of them; executed 1972.\n*[[Sergei Dovzhenko]]: killed between seventeen and nineteen people in his native home of [[Mariupol]] for \"mocking\" him; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://ilich.in.ua/news.php?id=84 |title=\u041e\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043b\u0438 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446\u0430 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043c \u043e\u043d \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0432\u0430\u043b? |trans-title=Is he a lone serial killer and why did he kill? |first=D. |last=Sumtsov |date=1 January 2003 |newspaper=Illichivets |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716002407/http://ilich.in.ua/news.php?id=84 |archive-date=2014-07-16}}</ref>\n*[[Tamara Ivanyutina]]: also known as the \"Kiev Poisoner\"; poisoned people from personal spite 1976 to 1987, killing nine of them; executed 1987.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bulvar.com.ua/arch/2012/4/4f206e104267f/ |title=\u041e\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432\u0435\u043a\u0430 |last=Poddubny |first=Nikolay |date=2012-01-24 |website=\u0411\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0432\u0430\u0440 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0430 |language=ru |access-date=2012-11-05 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6DV9upYYV?url=http://www.bulvar.com.ua/arch/2012/4/4f206e104267f/ |archive-date=7 January 2013 }}</ref>\n*[[Ruslan Khamarov]]: seduced and murdered eleven women in his home from 2000 to 2003; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.segodnya.ua/oldarchive/c2256713004f33f5c2256e7f0035f846.html |title=\"\u0411\u0435\u0440\u0434\u044f\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0430\u043d\u044c\u044f\u043a\" \u0422\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0443\u0435\u0442 \u041f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0414\u0435\u0432\u0443\u0448\u043a\u0443 \u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e \u041a \u041d\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0412 \u041a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0443 |date=24 April 2004 |newspaper=[[Segodnya]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Oleg Kuznetsov (serial killer)|Oleg Kuznetsov]]: also known as \"The [[Balashikha]] Ripper\"; killed a total of ten people in Russia and Ukraine; sentenced to death but commuted to life imprisonment.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tyurma.com/mordovskaya-edinichka-prigovorennye-k-zhizni |title=\u041c\u043e\u0440\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \"\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0430\" - \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043a \u0436\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0438 |trans-title=Mordovian \"one\" - sentenced to life |website=Tyurma.com |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106104333/http://www.tyurma.com/mordovskaya-edinichka-prigovorennye-k-zhizni |archive-date=6 January 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*[[Anatoly Onoprienko]]: also known as \"The Terminator\"; murdered 52 people from 1989 until his capture in 1996; died in prison in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/europe/9811/30/ukraine.serial.killer/index.html |title=Accused Ukrainian serial killer makes surprise request at trial |date=1998-11-30 |website=CNN |accessdate=2008-09-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080519073812/http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/europe/9811/30/ukraine.serial.killer/index.html |archivedate=2008-05-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/from_our_own_correspondent/219734.stm |title=The lives changed by Onoprienko |first=James |last=Commarasamy |date=1998-11-23 |website=BBC News |accessdate=2008-09-10}}</ref>\n*[[Dnepropetrovsk maniacs|Viktor Sayenko and Igor Suprunyuk]]: also known as the \"Dnepropetrovsk Maniacs\"; teenagers in [[Dnipro|Dnipropetrovsk]] who bludgeoned 21 people to death in 2007 with the aid of a third teenager, often filming their murders; sentenced to life in prison in 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.unian.net/eng/news/news-204617.html |title=Three 19\u2011year-old youths committed 19 murders in Dnepropetrovsk during a month|publisher=[[UNIAN]] |access-date=2008-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115153056/http://www.unian.net/eng/news/news-204617.html |archive-date=2012-01-15 |url-status=live }}</ref>   \n*[[Serhiy Tkach]]: convicted of raping and murdering 36 women between 1980-2005; claims the total is 100.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/ukraine/3933579/Man-sentenced-to-life-in-prison-for-murdering-36-women.html |title=Man sentenced to life in prison for murdering 36 women |first=Miriam |last=Elder |date=24 December 2008 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=2008-12-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/7798753.stm |title=BBC News: Serial killer jailed in Ukraine |date=24 December 2008 |website=BBC News |accessdate=24 December 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Nighttime Killers|Vladyslav Volkovich and Volodymyr Kondratenko]]: also known as the \"Nighttime Killers\"; charged with shooting, stabbing and bludgeoning sixteen victims to death in [[Kiev]] between 1991 and 1997; Kondratenko committed suicide in prison during the trial; Volkovich was found guilty and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.podrobnosti.com.ua/projects/vovremya/2003/06/02/62096.html |title=\u0414\u0443\u044d\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0439\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0443\u0431\u0438\u0439\u0446 |trans-title=The Serial Killer Duo |date=June 2, 2003 |website=[[Podrobnosti]] |accessdate=2009-01-04 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090123055610/http://podrobnosti.com.ua/projects/vovremya/2003/06/02/62096.html |archive-date=2009-01-23}}</ref>\n<!-- NOTE: The Dnepropetrovsk maniacs are spree killers. Please do not add them to this article. -->\n\n===United Kingdom===\n\n====England====\n*[[Stephen Akinmurele]]: also known as the \"Cul-de-sac killer\"; committed suicide in [[Manchester Prison|Strangeways]] in 1999 while awaiting trial for the murders of five elderly people in [[Blackpool]] and the [[Isle of Man]] between 1995 and 1998.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/1999/aug/30/jamiewilson1 |title='Serial killer' found hanged |first=Jamie |last=Wilson |date=August 30, 1999 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Beverley Allitt]]: also known as \"Angel of Death\"; [[Lincolnshire]] [[paediatric]] nurse who killed four children in her care and injured at least nine others; sentenced to life imprisonment in 1991.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/child-murderer-confesses-at-last-1510845.html |title=Child murderer confesses at last |last=Foster |first=Jonathan |date=15 October 1993 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Bateman]]: also known as the \"[[Yorkshire]] Witch\"; 19th century thief hanged for the poisoning of a couple (husband survived); suspected in three more deaths; executed 1809.<ref>{{cite book |last=Strevens |first=Summer |date=2017 |title=The Yorkshire Witch: The Life and Trial of Mary Bateman |location=[[Barnsley]] |publisher=[[Pen and Sword Books]] |page=135 |isbn=978-1-47386-387-3}}</ref>\n*[[Levi Bellfield]]: also known as the \"Bus Stop Stalker\"; convicted of the 2002 [[murder of Amanda Dowler]] and two fatal hammer attacks on young women in [[South West (London sub region)|South West London]] in 2003 and 2004.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/he-murdered-two-how-many-more-did-bellfield-target-1.875373 |title=He murdered two... how many more did Bellfield target? |date=26 February 2008 |newspaper=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Herald]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[London Burkers|John Bishop, Thomas Williams, Michael Shields and James May]]: known as \"The London Burkers\"; English copycats of [[Burke and Hare murders|Burke and Hare]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.historybytheyard.co.uk/early_murder_investigations.htm |title=Early Murder Investigations |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=History by the Yard |access-date=24 January 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Geordie Bourne]]: Scottish 16th century bandit who killed seven people around the [[Scottish Marches|East English Marches]]; executed by unknown means.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/stream/memoirsrobertca00orregoog#page/n66/mode/2up |editor-last=Powell |editor-first=G. H. |date=1905 |title=Memoirs of Robert Carey, Earl of Monmouth |location=London, UK |publisher=Alexander Moring Ltd. The De La More Press |pages=42\u201345 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Brady]] and [[Myra Hindley]]: also known as the \"[[Moors murders|Moors Murderers]]\"; murdered five children, aged between 10 and 17 between 1963 and 1965. Buried four of their victims on [[Saddleworth Moor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/661139.stm |title=Hindley: I wish I'd been hanged |date=29 February 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=11 August 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Ann Britland]]: poisoned her daughter, husband, and the wife of her lover in 1886; first woman to be executed by hanging at [[HM Prison Manchester|Strangeways Prison]] in [[Manchester]] in 1886 by executioner [[James Berry (executioner)|James Berry]].<ref>{{cite book |url=https://archive.org/stream/MyExperiencesAsAnExecutioner/Berry#page/n37/mode/1up |last=Berry |first=James |editor-first=H. Snowden |editor-last=Ward |date=1892 |title=My Experiences as an Executioner |location=London, UK |publisher=Percy Lund & Co |pages=74\u201376 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Bryan]]: [[Psychiatric hospital|institutionalized]] for fatal hammer attack on woman in 1993; re-apprehended for [[cannibalism|cannibalizing]] a friend in 2004, but able to batter a fellow patient to death months later.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2009/09/03/2009-09-03_series_of_blunders_frees_cannibal_peter_bryan.html |title=Series of blunders frees schizophrenic cannibal Peter Bryan, who kills two more people |last=Hazlett |first=Alexandra |date=3 September 2009 |newspaper=New York Daily News |accessdate=23 November 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905074132/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/2009/09/03/2009-09-03_series_of_blunders_frees_cannibal_peter_bryan.html |archive-date=5 September 2009}}</ref>\n*[[George Chapman (murderer)|George Chapman]]: Polish-born poisoner who murdered three women between 1897 and 1902; suspected by some authors of being [[Jack the Ripper]]. Executed in 1903.<ref>{{cite book |first=Peter |last=De Loriol |title=Murder and Crime in London |year=2010 |publisher=History Press Limited |isbn=978-0-7524-5657-7 |pages=61\u201362}}</ref>\n*[[John Childs (murderer)|John Childs]]: known as the most prolific [[hit man]] in the United Kingdom, he was convicted in 1979 of six [[contract killing]]s, though none of the bodies have been found.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1946&dat=19791206&id=2DsyAAAAIBAJ&sjid=sqQFAAAAIBAJ&pg=4729,3210267 |title=British hired killer shocks Old Bailey |date=6 December 1979 |agency=UPI |newspaper=[[Montreal Gazette]] |accessdate=23 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[John Christie (murderer)|John Christie]]: gassed, raped and strangled at least five women from 1943 to 1953, hiding the bodies at his house in [[Notting Hill]], London; also strangled his wife Ethel, as well as the wife and baby daughter of neighbour [[Timothy Evans]], who was wrongfully executed for their murders.<ref>{{Cite book |title=John Christie |last=Marston |first=Edward |authorlink=Keith Miles |year=2007 |publisher=[[The National Archives (United Kingdom)|The National Archives]] |location=Kew, Surrey |isbn=978-1-90561-516-2 |page=[https://archive.org/details/johnchristie0000mars/page/108 108] |url=https://archive.org/details/johnchristie0000mars/page/108 }}</ref>\n*[[Robert George Clements]]: doctor who committed suicide when due to be arrested for poisoning his fourth wife; his other three wives all died suspiciously during the interwar period.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=-XvaAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Robert+George+Clements%22&dq=%22Robert+George+Clements%22 |title=The New Murderers' Who's Who |last1=Gaute |first1=J. H. H. |last2=Odell |first2=Robin |page=86 |date=1989 |location=London, UK |publisher=Harrap |isbn=978-0-245-54639-6}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Ann Cotton]]: [[Victorian era|Victorian]] killer; said to have poisoned more than twenty victims; hanged in 1873.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2016/10/31/dark-angel-joanne-froggatt-stars-in-the-gruesome-real-life-story/ |title=Dark Angel: the gruesome true story of Mary Ann Cotton, Britain's first serial killer |last1=Armstrong |first1=Neil |date=2016-10-31 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=31 October 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Neill Cream]]: also known as the \"[[Lambeth]] Poisoner\"; began his killing spree in the [[United States]] then moved to London; hanged in 1892.<ref>{{cite book |last=Edwards |first=Wallace |title=I am Jack The... |year=2013 |publisher=Absolute Crime |isbn=978-1484872215}}</ref>\n*[[Dale Cregan]]: sentenced to a whole life order in prison for four counts of homicide in 2012 involving the use of firearms, including killing two police officers, and three separate counts of attempted murder in [[Greater Manchester]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-22893157 |title=Dale Cregan trial: Police killer sentenced to whole of life in jail |date=13 June 2013 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Sarah Dazley]]: also known as the \"[[Potton]] Poisoner\"; poisoned her husband with arsenic; suspected of killing her first husband and child; hanged 1843.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM9BZB_The_Potton_Poisoner_Wrestlingworth_Beds_UK |title=The Potton Poisoner, Wrestlingworth, Beds, UK - Infamous Crime Scenes |website=Waymarking.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Frederick Bailey Deeming]]: in 1891 killed his wife and four children in Britain; remarried and moved to Australia, and then murdered his new wife.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article196998457 |title=The Windsor Tragedy: Search For the Murderer: Discovery of Clues |date=5 March 1892 |newspaper=[[The Age]] |issue=11553 |location=Melbourne, Victoria |accessdate=11 April 2018 |page=7 |via=National Library of Australia}}</ref>\n*[[Peterborough ditch murders|Joanna Dennehy]]: stabbed three men to death and tried to kill two others selected at random in what would become known as the \"[[Peterborough]] Ditch Murders\" in 2013; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-24987953 |title=Peterborough ditch deaths: Joanna Dennehy pleads guilty |date=18 November 2013 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/serial-killer-joanna-dennehy-stuns-old-bailey-by-pleading-guilty-to-murdering-three-men-and-dumping-their-bodies-in-remote-ditches-8947023.html |title=Joanna Dennehy trial: Serial killer stuns Old Bailey by pleading guilty to murdering three men and dumping bodies in ditches |first=Rob |last=Williams |date=18 November 2013 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=12 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[John Duffy and David Mulcahy]]: also known as the \"Railway Killers\"; killed three women near railway stations in the 1980s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/954909.stm |title=Murder victims' fate 'revealed' |date=3 October 2000 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Amelia Dyer]]: murdered infants in her care; executed by hanging at [[Newgate Prison]] in 1896.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thamesvalley.police.uk/aboutus-museum-baby-farmer |title=The Baby Farmer |website=Thames Valley Police |accessdate=17 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302213715/http://www.thamesvalley.police.uk/aboutus-museum-baby-farmer |archivedate=2 March 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Kenneth Erskine]]: also known as the \"[[Stockwell]] Strangler\"; sentenced to life imprisonment in 1988 for murdering seven pensioners.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/8149050.stm |title='Strangler' wins murders appeal |date=14 July 2009 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Black Widows of Liverpool|Catherine Flannigan and Margaret Higgins]]: two [[Irish people|Irish]] women known as \"The Black Widows of [[Liverpool]]\"; killed at least four people by poisoning in the 1880s in order to obtain insurance money.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/liverpool-news/liverpool-murders/2010/01/07/mersey-murders-black-widows-margaret-higgins-and-catherine-flannagan-100252-25541424/ |title=Liverpool Murder Most Foul: Day 4: Black widows Margaret Higgins and Catherine Flannagan |first=Ben |last=Rossington |date=7 January 2010 |newspaper=[[Liverpool Echo]] |accessdate=7 May 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Steven Grieveson]]: also known as \"The Sunderland Strangler\"; murdered four teenage boys in [[City of Sunderland|Sunderland]], [[Tyne and Wear]] between 1990 and 1994.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/gay-serial-killer-is-given-three-life-sentences-1321584.html |title=Gay serial killer is given three life sentences |date=29 February 1996 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bradford murders|Stephen Griffiths]]: also known as the \"Crossbow Cannibal\"; convicted of murdering three prostitutes in [[Bradford]] in 2009 and 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/may/27/bradford-murders-timeline |title=Bradford murders timeline |date=27 May 2010 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London, UK |accessdate=11 June 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Allan Grimson]]: [[Royal Navy]] petty officer convicted of two murders from 1997 to 1998; suspected of murdering up to twenty people across the UK, [[Gibraltar]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/police-search-gibraltar-for-sailor-missing-since-1986-109945.html |title=Police search Gibraltar for sailor missing since 1986 |last1=Bennetto |first1=Jason |date=23 June 2003 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=22 February 2017}}</ref>\n*[[John Haigh]]: also known as the \"Acid Bath Murderer\" and the \"Vampire of London\"; active in England during the 1940s; convicted of six murders, but claimed to have killed nine; executed in 1949.<ref>{{Cite journal |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_go1613/is_4_15/ai_n29310480/ |last=Ramsland |first=K. |title=John George Haigh: a malingerer's legacy |journal=The Forensic Examiner |volume=15 |issue=4 |year=2006 |via=[[FindArticles]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120629235153/findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_go1613/is_4_15/ai_n29310480/ |archive-date=29 June 2012}}</ref>\n*[[Anthony Hardy]]: also known as the \"[[Camden Town|Camden]] Ripper\"; convicted of three murders; suspected of at least four.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/may/14/camden-ripper-never-released-judge |title=Camden Ripper must never be released, judge rules |date=14 May 2010 |agency=Press Association |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=25 June 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Trevor Hardy]]: also known as \"The Beast of Manchester\"; killed three teenage girls in [[Manchester]] from 1974 to 1976.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/s/1053972_serial_killer_will_die_in_jail |title=Serial killer will die in jail |first=Chris |last=Osuh |date=13 June 2008 |newspaper=[[Manchester Evening News]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Philip Herbert, 7th Earl of Pembroke|Philip Herbert]]: also known as the \"Infamous Earl of Pembroke\"; 17th century nobleman convicted of manslaughter but discharged; later killed the prosecutor and pardoned for a third murder.<ref>{{cite book |chapterurl=http://www.exclassics.com/newgate/ng37.htm |chapter=Philip, Earl of Pembroke and Montgomery, Tried for the Murder of Nathaniel Cony by his Brother Peers in 1678 and found guilty of Manslaughter later |editor1-first=J.L. |editor1-last=Rayner |editor2-first=G.T |editor2-last=Crook |date=1926 |title=The Complete Newgate Calendar |location=London, UK |publisher=Navarre Society |via=Ex-Classics.com |access-date=24 November 2019|title-link=The Newgate Calendar }}</ref>\n*[[Colin Ireland]]: also known as \"The Gay Slayer\"; killed five gay men in London in the early 1990s; died in prison in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.crimeandinvestigation.co.uk/crime-files/colin-ireland |title=Colin Ireland |date=June 30, 2017 |website=Crime + Investigation |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><!-- NOTE: Jack the Ripper is listed in the \"Unidentified serial killers\" section. Please do not add him to this section. -->\n*[[Theodore Johnson (serial killer)|Theodore Johnson]]: [[Jamaica]]n immigrant who murdered his wife and two girlfriends from 1981 to 2016; sentenced to 26 years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/jan/05/man-theodore-johnson-on-conditional-release-who-killed-partner-lied-to-authorities-about-relationship |title=Killer on conditional release who murdered partner given life sentence |first=Jamie |last=Grierson |date=5 January 2018 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Bruce George Peter Lee]]: serial killer and arsonist responsible for 26 deaths in the town of [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]] from 1973 to 1979.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://infotrac.galegroup.com/itw/infomark/531/644/115751697w16/purl=&dyn=11!pdy_3_0FFO-1981-JAN21-003-F?sw_aep=corlonli |title=Special hospital for young man who admitted killing 26 people and ten charges of arson |date=21 January 1984 |newspaper=The Times |page=3 |accessdate=7 July 2010}} ''(Library card access)''</ref>\n*[[Robin Ligus]]: drug addict convicted of robbing and bludgeoning three men to death with an iron bar in [[Shropshire]] in 1994.\n*[[Michael Lupo]]: also known as \"The Wolf Man\"; Italian-born man convicted of the murders of four men and two attempted murders in London in the 1980s; died in prison in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/serial-killer-with-hiv-virus-dies-in-jail-1573604.html |title=Serial killer with HIV virus dies in jail |last=Bennetto |first=Jason |date=18 February 1995 |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=26 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Patrick Mackay]]: charged with the murders of five individuals in London and [[Kent]], convicted of three; confessed to killing eleven people from 1974 to 1975.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/mass/patrick_mackay/2.html |title=Patrick Mackay, psychopathic repeat killer |last=Ramsland |first=Katherine |website=[[Crime Library]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080401002015/http://www.crimelibrary.com/notorious_murders/mass/patrick_mackay/2.html |archive-date=1 April 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Maudsley]]: also known as \"Hannibal The Cannibal\"; killer of four; killed three in prison.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2003/apr/27/ukcrime |title=The caged misery of Britain's real 'Hannibal the Cannibal' |last1=Thompson |first1=Tony |date=27 April 2003 |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=30 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/tragic-life-led-hannibal-killings-3554260 |title=Tragic life that led to Hannibal killings |last=Shennan |first=Paddy |date=7 May 2003 |newspaper=Liverpool Echo |accessdate=8 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Cannock Chase murders|Raymond Morris]]: also known as the \"[[A34 road|A34]] Killer\"; convicted of one murder, considered to have committed at least two more.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://static.expressandstar.com/millennium/1900/1950-1975/1969.html |title=Chase killer jailed for life |date=16 November 1968 |newspaper=[[Express & Star]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Hicks Murray]]: bigamist who murdered his first wife and three children, and then killed himself in a [[murder-suicide]] in 1912; posthumously connected to the killings of at least seven previous wives.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042373/1912-09-11/ed-1/seq-1/#date1=1789&sort=date&rows=20&words=Hicks+Murray+Robert&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=12&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=Robert+Hicks+Murray&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1 |title=Tragedy Reveals Modern Bluebeard Who Had Murdered Seven Wives |date=September 11, 1912 |page=1 |volume=7 |number=216 |newspaper=The Evening Times |location=[[Grand Forks]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Chronicling America}}</ref>\n*[[Robert Napper]]: also known as the \"[[South East London Green Chain|Green Chain]] Rapist\"; killed two women and a child in the 1990s.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/inside-the-mind-of-robert-napper-jlfxmbf7wr7 |title=Inside the mind of Robert Napper |first1=Sean |last1=O'Neill |first2=Adam |last2=Fresco |date=18 December 2008 |newspaper=The Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Donald Neilson]]: also known as the \"Black Panther\"; killed four people, including heiress [[Murder of Lesley Whittle|Lesley Whittle]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/news/midlands-news/black-panther-donald-neilsons-trail-8464470 |title=Black Panther Donald Neilson's trail of Terror and Murder of Lesley Whittle 40 Years ago Remembered by Top Cop |first=Mike |last=Lockley |date=17 January 2015 |newspaper=The Birmingham Mail |access-date=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Dennis Nilsen]]: also known as \"The [[Muswell Hill]] Murderer\"; killer of fifteen (possibly 16) men between 1978 and 1983 in North London.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nilsen given 25-year sentence |first=David |last=Nicholson |newspaper=[[The Times]] |location=London, UK |date=5 November 1983 |page=1 |issue=61682}}</ref>\n*[[Colin Norris]]: nurse convicted of killing four patients in [[Leeds]] hospitals between 2001 and 2002.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-15068743 |title=Colin Norris case: Murder convictions 'unsafe' |date=4 October 2011 |website=BBC News |accessdate=19 October 2011}}</ref>\n*[[William Palmer (murderer)|William Palmer]]: also known as \"Palmer the Poisoner\"; doctor suspected of numerous murders, convicted of one; hanged in 1856.<ref>{{cite book |title=Old Lamps For New Ones, And Other Sketches and Essays Hitherto Uncollected |chapter-url=https://archive.org/stream/oldlampsfornewon00dick#page/268/mode/2up |chapter=The Demeanor of Murderers |first=Charles |last=Dickens |author-link=Charles Dickens |year=1897 |page=269 |location=New York |publisher=New Amsterdam Book Company |accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Stephen Port]]: drugged, raped and murdered four men in [[Barking, London|Barking]], London between 2014 and 2015; convicted in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-38077859 |title=Stephen Port: Serial killer guilty of murdering four men |date=23 November 2016 |website=BBC News |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Elizabeth Ridgeway]]: poisoned her husband in 1684; after arrest, confessed to poisoning three more people starting from 1681; executed 1684.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A52275.0001.001/1:4?rgn=div1;view=fulltext |title=The penitent recognition of Joseph's brethren: a sermon occasion'd by Elizabeth Ridgeway, who for the petit treason of poysoning her husband, was, on March 24, 1683/4, according to the sentence of the Right Honourable Sir Thomas Street ... burnt at Leicester ... : to which is prefixed a full relation of the womans fact, tryal, carriage, and death |last=Newton |first=John |publisher=Printed for Richard Chiswel |year=1684 |location=London, UK |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=University of Michigan University Library}}</ref>\n*[[Amelia Sach and Annie Walters]]: known as \"The [[East Finchley|Finchley]] Baby Farmers\"; baby farmers who used [[chlorodyne]] to poison an unknown number of infants; both hanged at the [[HM Prison Holloway]] in 1903.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1394309/Baby-killer-Amelia-Sach-Penninah-Ashers-family-Researching-background-popular--past-hide-horrific-secrets.html |title=The baby killer in my family: Researching your background has never been so popular... but the past can hide horrific secrets |first=Penninah |last=Asher |date=5 June 2011 |newspaper=Daily Mail |accessdate=14 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Harold Shipman]]: also known as \"Dr. Death\"; doctor convicted of fifteen murders; a later inquiry stated he had killed at least 215 and possibly up to 457 people over a 25-year period; committed suicide in 2004 in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/3391897.stm |title=Harold Shipman: The killer doctor |date=13 January 2004 |website=BBC News |accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>\n*[[George Joseph Smith]]: also known as \"The Brides in the Bath\" killer who murdered three women.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kentlive.news/news/kent-news/george-joseph-smith-notorious-brides-1219108 |title=George Joseph Smith and the notorious 'Brides in the Bath' murders |first=Adam |last=John |date=17 February 2018 |newspaper=[[Kent and Sussex Courier]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Rebecca Smith (infanticide)|Rebecca Smith]]: poisoned her infant son with arsenic in 1849, later confessing to doing the same to seven of her other children; executed 1849.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.academia.edu/9671973 |title=Religion, Community and the Infanticidal Mother: Evidence from 1840s Rural Wiltshire |first1=Katherine D. |last1=Watson |date=November 2008 |journal=Family & Community History |volume=11 |issue=2 |page=119 |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[John Straffen]]: murdered three children between 1951 and 1952; Britain's longest-serving prisoner until his death in 2007.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2007/nov/19/ukcrime.prisonsandprobation |title=Longest-serving UK prisoner dies, aged 77 |first=Allegra |last=Stratton |date=19 November 2007 |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Sutcliffe]]: also known as the \"[[Yorkshire]] Ripper\"; convicted in 1981 of murdering thirteen women and attacking seven more from 1975 to 1980.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/sutcliffe/mask_1.html |title=A Killer's Mask |first=Fiona |last=Steel |website=TruTV.com |accessdate=29 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090321003633/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/serial_killers/predators/sutcliffe/mask_1.html |archivedate=21 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Griffiths Wainewright]]: artist considered to have poisoned four people.<ref>{{cite book |chapter=Wainewright, Thomas Griffiths (1794\u20131847) |chapter-url=http://www.adb.online.anu.edu.au/biogs/A020509b.htm |first=V. W. |last=Hodgman |title=Australian Dictionary of Biography, Volume 2 |publisher=[[Melbourne University Press|MUP]] |year=1967 |pages=558\u2013559 |accessdate=2007-09-28|title-link=Australian Dictionary of Biography }}</ref>\n*[[Margaret Waters]]: baby farmer from [[Brixton]] who drugged and starved the infants in her care; believed to have killed at least nineteen children; executed on 11 October 1870.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DwNVbOcTncwC&pg=PA428 |title=The Encyclopedia of Serial Killers |last=Newton |first=Michael |publisher=Infobase Publishing |year=2006 |page=428 |isbn=978-0-81606-987-3 |accessdate=2012-06-20}}</ref>\n*[[Fred West]] and [[Rosemary West]]: also known as the \"House of Horrors\" murderers; she was convicted of ten murders; both are believed to have tortured and murdered at least twelve young women between 1967 and 1987, many at their home in [[Gloucester]]; he committed suicide in 1995 while awaiting trial.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eveyo.com/stories/world-news/54357-she-cut-heather-up-and-put-her-in-a-dustbin-our-daughter-in-a-dustbin-the-chilling-confession-of-serial-killer-fred-west-about-his-16-year-old-daughter-s-murder-to-be-heard-in-new-television-documenta.html |title=The Chilling Confession of Serial Killer Fred West about His 16-year-old Daughter's Murder to be Heard in New Television Documentary |first=Paul |last=Donnelley |date=2014-04-04 |website=Eveyo.com |accessdate=2018-03-14 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314110331/https://www.eveyo.com/stories/world-news/54357-she-cut-heather-up-and-put-her-in-a-dustbin-our-daughter-in-a-dustbin-the-chilling-confession-of-serial-killer-fred-west-about-his-16-year-old-daughter-s-murder-to-be-heard-in-new-television-documenta.html |archive-date=2018-03-14}}</ref>\n*[[Ada Williams (baby farmer)|Ada Williams]]: 19th-century baby farmer who strangled an infant in September 1899; suspected of more murders; executed 1900.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19000113.2.58.9 |title=Babies Slaughtered |date=13 January 1900 |newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |volume=XXXVII |issue=11270 |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=[[Papers Past]]}}</ref>\n*[[Catherine Wilson]]: nurse considered to have poisoned seven people in the 19th century; executed in 1862.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.sonofthesouth.net/leefoundation/civil-war/1862/november/execution-catharine-wilson.htm |title=The Gallows |magazine=[[Harper's Weekly]] |date=22 November 1862 |page=743 |access-date=24 November 2019 |via=Son of the South.net}}</ref>\n*[[Mary Elizabeth Wilson]]: also known as the \"Merry Widow of [[Windy Nook]]\"; convicted of murdering two husbands by poisoning and considered to have killed two others.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/history/dark-angel-look-another-north-12103801 |title=Dark Angel: We look at another North East woman serial killer - The Merry Widow of Windy Nook Case bears similarities to Dark Angel killer Mary Ann Cotton |first=Ian |last=Robson |date=31 October 2016 |newspaper=[[Evening Chronicle]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Steve Wright (serial killer)|Steve Wright]]: also known as \"The Suffolk Strangler\"; [[Ipswich 2006 serial murders|killed five women]] in six weeks around [[Ipswich]] in late 2006; sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1579403/Steve-Wright-A-real-Jekyll-and-Hyde.html |title=Steve Wright: A real Jekyll and Hyde |last=Allen |first=Nick |date=21 February 2008 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London, UK |accessdate=27 September 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Graham Young]]: also known as \"The Teacup Poisoner\"; killed three people from 1962 to 1971; died in prison in 1990.<ref>{{cite book |last=Lane |first=Brian |date=1993 |title=The Murder Guide: 100 Extraordinary, Bizarre and Gruesome Murders |location=London, UK |publisher=Robinson |page=191 |isbn=1-85487-083-1}}</ref>\n\n====Northern Ireland====\n*[[Shankill Butchers]]: The Shankill Butchers was an Ulster loyalist gang\u2014many of whom were members of the [[Ulster Volunteer Force]] (UVF)\u2014that was active between 1975 and 1982 in Belfast, Northern Ireland. The gang was based in the Shankill area and were responsible for the deaths of at least twenty-three people, most of whom were [[Irish Catholic]]s killed in sectarian attacks.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.politics.ie/history/18916-sectarianism-racism-one-same.html |title=Sectarianism \u2013 Racism \u2013 One and the Same? |author=Conuil |date=July 2007 |website=Politics.ie |access-date=21 December 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609160824/http://www.politics.ie/history/18916-sectarianism-racism-one-same.html |archive-date=2011-06-09}}</ref>\n\n====Scotland====\n*[[Robert Black (serial killer)|Robert Black]]: schoolgirl killer; convicted of four murders in [[Northern Ireland]], [[England]], and [[Scotland]] between 1981 and 1986, suspected of many more; died in prison in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.truecrimelibrary.com/magazinearticle/death-of-a-serial-killer-robert-blacks-timeline-of-terror/ |title=Death of A Serial Killer \u2013 Robert Black's Timeline Of Terror |date=April 2016 |website=True Crime Library |accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-35296135 |title=Robert Black: Convicted child killer dies in prison |date=12 January 2016 |website=BBC News |accessdate=12 January 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Burke and Hare murders|William Burke and William Hare]]: notorious [[body snatcher]]s in [[Edinburgh]] in the 19th century.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofScotland/Burke-Hare-infamous-murderers-graverobbers/ |title=The Story of Burke and Hare |first=Ben |last=Johnson |website=Historic UK |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Archibald Hall]]: also known as the \"Monster Butler\"; killed five in the 1970s, three with accomplice Michael Kitto.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/nostalgia/crimelibrary/archibaldthomsonhall/themurderousbutler/ |title=The Murderous Butler: Archibald Thomson Hall, alias Roy Fontaine |newspaper=[[Watford Observer]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Manuel]]: also known as the \"Beast of [[Birkenshaw, North Lanarkshire|Birkenshaw]]\"; American-born murderer of seven, suspected of killing 15; executed in 1958.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Dv6G7xTW0FUC&pg=PT25&lpg=PT25&dq=capelrig+Anne+Kneilands#v=onepage&q=capelrig%20Anne%20Kneilands |first1=Hector |last1=MacLeod |first2=Malcolm |last2=McLeod |title=Peter Manuel, Serial Killer |date=2010 |edition=ebook |publisher=Mainstream Publishing |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-1-84596-883-0}}</ref>\n*[[Edward William Pritchard]]: English doctor who poisoned his wife and her mother in [[Glasgow]] in 1865; two years earlier their maid had died in a mysterious fire.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://heritage.scotsman.com/notoriouscriminalsfeatureseries/A-deadly-bedside-manner.2680240.jp |title=A deadly beside manner |first=Leighton |last=Bruce |date=21 November 2005 |newspaper=[[The Scotsman]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307062517/http://heritage.scotsman.com/notoriouscriminalsfeatureseries/A-deadly-bedside-manner.2680240.jp |archive-date=7 March 2009}}</ref>\n*[[World's End Murders|Angus Sinclair]]: convicted of the murders of four young women, including the \"World's End Murders\" in [[Edinburgh]], believed to have murdered eight; died in prison in 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1309040/Child-killer-gets-life-for-1978-death-of-teenager.html |title=Child killer gets life for 1978 death of teenager |first=Tara |last=Womersley |date=14 June 2001 |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London, UK |accessdate=5 February 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Tobin]]: rapist and killer of three women in Scotland and England between 1991 and 2006; sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/8132283.stm |title=Piecing together serial killer Peter Tobin's past |first=Mario |last=Cacciottolo |date=16 December 2009 |website=BBC News |access-date=9 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Wales====\n*[[John Cooper (serial killer)|John Cooper]]: also known as \"The Wildman\" and \"The Bullseye Killer\"; [[Pembrokeshire]] burglar responsible for the robbery and shotgun double-murders of a brother and sister in 1985 and a couple in 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/the-moment-bullseye-revealed-killer-6025096 |title='The moment Bullseye revealed the killer': How shotgun killer John Cooper was caught |last=McCarthy |first=James |date=16 September 2013 |website=[[Wales Online]] |accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Moore (serial killer)|Peter Moore]]: also known as \"The Man in Black\"; businessman who killed four men at random in [[North Wales]] in 1995.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.flintshirechronicle.co.uk/flintshire-news/local-flintshire-news//tm_headline=flintshire-murderer-peter-moore-in-european-court-of-human-rights-appeal-over-life-sentence%26method=full%26objectid=28267583%26siteid=51352-name_page.html |title=Flintshire murderer Peter Moore in European Court of Human Rights appeal over life sentence |first=Eleanor |last=Barlow |date=3 March 2011 |newspaper=[[Flintshire Chronicle]] |accessdate=13 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720013139/http://www.flintshirechronicle.co.uk/flintshire-news/local-flintshire-news//tm_headline=flintshire-murderer-peter-moore-in-european-court-of-human-rights-appeal-over-life-sentence%26method=full%26objectid=28267583%26siteid=51352-name_page.html |archive-date=20 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n===United States===\n{{main|List of serial killers in the United States}}\n\n===Uruguay===\n*[[Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez]]: Spanish-born murderer who killed tennis player [[Patricia Miller (tennis)|Patricia Miller]]'s half-sister and two other women; freed in 2016 but was arrested in 2017 in [[Paraguay]] for carrying an unregistered weapon and a quantity of cocaine.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.teledoce.com/telemundo/nacionales/pablo-goncalvez-en-libertad-salio-de-campanero-a-las-2357-del-jueves/ |title=Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez en libertad: sali\u00f3 de Campanero a las 23:57 del jueves 23 de junio |trans-title=Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez released: he left Campanero at 23:57 on Thursday, June 23 |date=24 June 2016 |website=[[Teledoce]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=23 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.elpais.com.uy/informacion/paraguay-analiza-expulsion-goncalvez.html |title=Paraguay analiza la expulsi\u00f3n de Gonc\u00e1lvez |trans-title=Paraguay analyzes the expulsion of Gonc\u00e1lvez |date=27 June 2017 |newspaper=[[El Pa\u00eds (Uruguay)|El Pa\u00eds]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/bonomi-paraguay-pidio-informacion-pablo-goncalvez-n1089872\n|title=Bonomi: \"Paraguay pidi\u00f3 informacion\" sobre Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez |trans-title=Bonomi: \"Paraguay asked for information\" about Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez |date=26 June 2017 |newspaper=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.subrayado.com.uy/noticias/68137/la-historia-de-pablo-goncalvez-ahora-preso-en-paraguay |title=La historia de Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez, ahora preso en Paraguay |trans-title=The story of Pablo Gonc\u00e1lvez, now imprisoned in Paraguay |date=25 June 2017 |website=[[Channel 10 (Uruguay)|Subrayado]] |location=Uruguay |language=es |access-date=27 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Uzbekistan===\n*[[Polatbay Berdaliyev]]: raped, murdered and robbed a total of eleven women in Uzbekistan and neighboring [[Kazakhstan]] with accomplice Abduseit Ormanov between 2011 and 2012; both sentenced to life imprisonment in both countries.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.kazpravda.kz/articles/view/taksi-na-tot-svet |title=\u0422\u0430\u043a\u0441\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u0442 \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0442 |trans-title=Taxi to the next world |first=Irina |last=Orlova |date=19 October 2018 |newspaper=[[Kazakhskaya Pravda]] |language=ru |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Venezuela===\n*[[Dor\u00e1ngel Vargas]]: killed and cannibalized at least ten men between 1997 and 1999 in [[San Crist\u00f3bal, T\u00e1chira]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.absurddiari.com/s/llegir.php?llegir=llegir&ref=5673 |title=El can\u00edbal de los Andes confiesa: \"Comer gente es como comer peras\" |trans-title=The cannibal of the Andes confesses: 'Eating people is like eating pears' |date=19 November 2004 |website=L'absurd Diari |language=es |accessdate=10 September 2008}}</ref>\n\n===Yemen===\n*[[Abdallah al-Hubal]]: killed seven people in 1990 after the Yemeni reunion; fled prison and killed a young couple and three other people in 1998; killed in a shootout with the police.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.tueursenserie.org/article.php?id_article=30 |title=Al-Hubal, Abdallah |first=Emily |last=Tibbatts |website=Tueurs en Serie.org |language=fr |access-date=2007-10-22 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120915095812/http://www.tueursenserie.org/article.php?id_article=30 |archive-date=2012-09-15}}</ref>\n*[[Mohammed Adam Omar]]: known as \"The Sana'a Ripper\"; [[Sudan]]ese morgue assistant who killed between two and 51 women across Yemen and other countries from 1975 to 1999; guilt has been questioned; executed 2001.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/14/world/sana-journal-a-fittingly-gory-finale-to-a-sordid-murder-case.html |title=Sana Journal; A Fittingly Gory Finale To a Sordid Murder Case |first=John F. |last=Burns |date=August 14, 2001 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20191013081509/https://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/14/world/sana-journal-a-fittingly-gory-finale-to-a-sordid-murder-case.html |archive-date=13 October 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Dhu Shanatir]]: 5th-century Yemeni (formerly Himyarite) serial killer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.paperstreetprod.com/compendium/archives/text/5intothe.txt |title=Into the Abyss |last=Horberg |first=Karl |date=8 May 1997 |website=Paper Street Productions |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050426080712/http://www.paperstreetprod.com/compendium/archives/text/5intothe.txt |archivedate=April 26, 2005}}</ref>\n\n===Zambia===\n*[[Mailoni Brothers]]: three brothers who killed at least twelve people from 2007 to 2013 in [[Central Province, Zambia|Central Province]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201306300093.html |title=Zambia: Mailoni Brothers - History of Serial Killers in Zambia |last=Kaluba |first=Austin |date=29 June 2013 |website=[[AllAfrica.com]] |accessdate=2014-04-15 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402135713/http://allafrica.com/stories/201306300093.html |archive-date=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Zimbabwe===\n*[[Richard McGown]]: also known as \"Dr. Death\"; Scottish doctor responsible for administering fatal doses of morphine to at least five patients in [[Harare]] from 1986 to 1992; convicted of two counts of [[culpable homicide]] and sentenced to a year in prison, after which he was released and returned to the UK.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/race-trial-doctor-guilty-of-homicide-1567492.html |title='Race-trial' doctor guilty of homicide |first=Angus |last=Shaw |date=11 January 1995 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Unidentified serial killers==\nThis is a list of unidentified serial killers. It includes circumstances where a suspect has been arrested, but not convicted.\n\n===Australia===\n*[[Bowraville Murders]]: murders of three [[Indigenous Australians|Aboriginal]] children in 1990 and 1991.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Truth be Told (transcript) |url=http://www.abc.net.au/austory/content/2006/s1733527.htm |access-date=24 November 2019 |series=Australian Story |series-link=Australian Story |first=Caroline |last=Jones |network=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |station=[[ABC Television]] |date=4 September 2006 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701073359/http://www.abc.net.au/austory/content/2006/s1733527.htm |archive-date=1 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2004/02/07/1075854109819.html |title=Lone cop to tell inquest name of killer suspect |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=February 8, 2004 |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Ghosts of Bowraville (transcript) |url=http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?http%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Frn%2Ftalks%2Fbbing%2Fstories%2Fs10587.htm |access-date=2019-02-21 |series=Background Briefing |first=Chris |last=Bullock |network=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |station=[[ABC Radio National]] |date=20 July 1997 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101001011/http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?http%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Frn%2Ftalks%2Fbbing%2Fstories%2Fs10587.htm |archive-date=2017-01-01}}</ref>\n*[[Claremont serial killings]]: murders of two young women and the disappearance of a third in 1996 and 1997.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-02-22/bradley-edwards-charged-with-sarah-spiers-murder/9475258 |title=Claremont serial killings: Sarah Spiers murder charge for Bradley Robert Edwards |date=23 February 2018 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=27 February 2018}}</ref>\n*[[The Family Murders]]: murder and mutilation of five young men and boys from 1979 to 1983. [[Bevan Spencer von Einem]] was convicted of one murder.<ref>{{cite episode |title=The Butchered Boys |series=Crime Investigation Australia |series-link=Crime Investigation Australia |network=[[Crime & Investigation Network]] |series-no=1 |number=16}}</ref>\n*[[Tynong North and Frankston Murders]]: murders of six females in [[Tynong North, Victoria|Tynong North]] and Frankston in 1980 and 1981.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theage.com.au/national/retired-detectives-back-in-the-hunt-20051121-ge1a2c.html |title=Retired detectives back in the hunt |last=Silvester |first=John |date=2005-11-21 |newspaper=The Age |access-date=2018-09-14}}</ref>\n\n===Belgium===\n*[[Brabant killers]]: gang of serial killers who operated in the [[Brabant (province)|Brabant]] province from 1982 until 1985; murdered 28 people and injured 40.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.vice.com/article/police-are-running-out-of-time-to-catch-the-crazy-brabant-killers |title=Police Are Running Out of Time to Catch the 'Crazy Brabant Killers' |last=Dall'Armellina |first=Virgile |date=24 October 2014 |website=Vice.com |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*The [[Butcher of Mons]]: unidentified serial killer who committed five murders from January 1996 to July 1997 in [[Mons]]. Montenegrin murderer [[Smail Tulja]] is suspected of being the Butcher.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/01/08/magazine/hunt-for-a-serial-killer.html |title=On the Trail of an Intercontinental Killer |last=Schmidle |first=Nicholas |date=5 January 2012 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Brazil===\n*[[Paturis Park murders]]: also known as the \"Rainbow Maniac\"; series of thirteen gunshot murders of gay men between July 2007 and August 2008 in Paturis Park in [[Carapicuiba]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2008/12/10/2442827.htm |title=Police hunt suspected serial killer in Brazil |last=Olle |first=Nick |authorlink=Nick Olle |date=10 December 2008 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |access-date=5 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Canada===\n*[[Highway of Tears murders|Highway of Tears]]: death and disappearance of around 40 young women in [[British Columbia]] since 1969.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbc.ca/archives/entry/bcs-infamous-highway-of-tears |title=BC's infamous 'Highway of Tears' |last=Lee |first=Miyoung |date=November 17, 2009 |website=CBC Digital Archives |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] |accessdate=10 December 2009}}</ref>\n*[[Toronto hospital baby deaths]]: deaths of at least eight babies at Toronto's Hospital for Sick Children in 1980 and 1981 were initially alleged to be [[digoxin]] poisonings, a theory which was cast into doubt by new evidence in 2010-2011.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2011/03/06/dead-babies-remain-a-mystery |title=Dead babies remain a mystery |agency=[[QMI Agency]] |date=March 6, 2011 |newspaper=[[St. Catharines Standard]] |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225035344/http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2011/03/06/dead-babies-remain-a-mystery |archive-date=2017-12-25}}</ref>\n\n===Costa Rica===\n*[[El Psic\u00f3pata]]: killed nineteen people from 1986 to 1996 in [[Cartago, Costa Rica|Cartago]], [[Curridabat]] and [[Desamparados]]; suspected of other similar crimes.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.diarioextra.com/2001/febrero/13/sucesos03.html |title=De Jack el Destripador de Londres al Destripador de San Jos\u00e9 |trans-title=From Jack the Ripper of London to the Ripper of San Jos\u00e9 |last=Araya |first=Hugo |date=February 13, 2001 |newspaper=[[Diario Extra (Costa Rica)|Diario Extra]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101121031159/http://www.diarioextra.com/2001/febrero/13/sucesos03.html |archive-date=2010-11-21}}</ref>\n\n===Finland===\n*[[Murder of Susanne Lindholm#Serial killer theory|Helsinki cellar killer]]: suspected of raping and strangling three women in Helsinki cellars between 1979 and 1981, including Susanne Lindholm; the validity of this theory has been disputed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.is.fi/kotimaa/art-2000000964453.html|title=Who killed them? 'The old thing can be reopened'|last=|first=|date=July 20, 2015|website=Ilta-Sanomat|language=fi-FI|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=August 25, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Hausj\u00e4rvi Gravel Pit Murders|J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4 Serial Killer]]: responsible for the so-called \"[[Hausj\u00e4rvi]] [[Gravel Pit]] Murders\"; killed a woman in 1991 and suspected in the disappearance of another in 1993; possibly responsible for other abductions and murders in the late 20th century.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://keski-uusimaa.fi/Uutiset/Arkisto/2008/07/15/Jarvenpaan-sarjamurhaaja-yrittanyt-ehka-uusia-tekonsa2 |title=Jarvenpaan sarjamurhaaja yrittanyt ehka uusia tekonsa |trans-title=J\u00e4rvenp\u00e4\u00e4's serial killer perhaps tried new things |first=Malin |last=Jarkko |date=15 July 2008 |newspaper=[[Uusimaa (newspaper)|Uusimaa]] |language=fi |accessdate=22 April 2014}}{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n\n===Germany===\n{{Main|List of German serial killers}}\n\n===India===\n*Beer Man: murdered seven people in south [[Mumbai]] between October 2006 and January 2007.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/beer-man-acquitted-in-second-murder-case-too/story-yG21TyRav3e80e9SlETFlM.html |title='Beer Man' acquitted in second murder case too |last=Iyer |first=Vignesh |date=July 12, 2008 |newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=May 23, 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Stoneman]]: responsible for thirteen murders in [[Kolkata]] in 1989.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/the-elusive-stoneman-of-kolkata/story-BQBcCHfk87WvoLp2LSCKRN.html |title=The elusive stoneman of Kolkata |first=Ritujay |last=Ghosh |date=December 30, 2006 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Italy===\n*[[Monster of Florence]]: committed eight murders of couples in a series of sixteen between 1968 and 1985. Giancarlo Lotti and Mario Vanni were convicted of four of the murders, but this conviction has been widely criticized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/predators/monster_florence/10.html |title=The Monster of Florence |first=David |last=Lohr |authorlink=David Lohr |website=[[Crime Library]] |page=10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403090508/http://www.crimelibrary.com/serial_killers/predators/monster_florence/10.html |archivedate=2014-04-03}}</ref>\n*[[Monster of Udine]]: killed at least four victims in the [[Province of Udine]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://messaggeroveneto.gelocal.it/udine/cronaca/2012/01/27/news/in-un-ventennio-14-omicidi-e-3-arresti-1.3113223 |title=In un ventennio 14 omicidi e 3 arresti |trans-title=In twenty years, 14 murders and 3 arrests |date=27 January 2012 |newspaper=[[Messaggero Veneto \u2013 Giornale del Friuli]] |language=it |accessdate=18 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Japan===\n*[[Paraquat murders]]: series of indiscriminate poisonings carried out in Japan in 1985 where twelve people were killed.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/12/10/world/japanese-puzzle-the-vending-machine-murders.html |title=Japanese Puzzle: The Vending Machine Murders |last1=Haberman |first1=Clyde |date=December 10, 1985 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Wednesday Strangler]]: killed 7 children and women in [[Saga Prefecture]] between 1975 and 1989, most of them on Wednesdays; a suspect was indicted for three of the murders, but later acquitted.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20071011104304/http://www.nishinippon.co.jp/news/wordbox/display/4796/ Kitamachi consecutive female murder case (West Japan Newspaper WORDBOX)]</ref>\n\n===Mexico===\n*[[Female homicides in Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]]: also known as \"The dead women of Ju\u00e1rez\"; the violent deaths of hundreds of women since 1993 in the northern Mexican city of [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Violencia Femicida : Violence Against Women and Mexico's Structural Crisis |last=Olivera |first=Mercedes |journal=[[Latin American Perspectives]] |date=March 1, 2006 |volume=33 |issue=104 |pages=104\u2013114 |doi=10.1177/0094582X05286092|url=https://semanticscholar.org/paper/24615d971dc35c9dd58cfc0884cf7de0ea8f5029 }}</ref>\n\n===Namibia===\n*[[B1 Butcher]]: murdered at least five women between 2005 and 2007, with all murders related to the [[B1 road (Namibia)|National Road B1]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.namibian.com.na/40811/archive-read/B-1-Butcher-DNA-evidence-in-spotlight-REPORTS |title=B-1 Butcher: DNA evidence in spotlight |last=Menges |first=Werner |date=29 April 2008 |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Nicaragua===\n*[[San Juan del Sur Psychopath]]: murdered between two and ten men in the coastal town of [[San Juan del Sur]], from 2000 to 2002; a German [[alien (law)|illegal alien]] residing in [[Managua]] was arrested on suspicion, but later cleared of the murders.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2002/03/10/nacionales/829404-misterio-ronda-crmenes-de-san-juan-del-sur |title=Misterio ronda cr\u00edmenes de San Juan del Sur |trans-title=Mystery around crimes of San Juan del Sur |first=Noelia |last=S\u00e1nchez |date=March 10, 2002 |newspaper=[[La Prensa (Managua)|La Prensa]] |language=es |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Poland===\n*[[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a Gay Murderer]]: murdered seven homosexual men from 1988 to 1993 in \u0141\u00f3d\u017a.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://lodz.wyborcza.pl/lodz/1,35136,7956685,_Zdarzylo_sie_w_Lodzi___Mordowal_gejow_na_Fabrycznym.html |title=\"Zdarzy\u0142o si\u0119 w \u0141odzi\": Mordowa\u0142 gej\u00f3w na Fabrycznym |trans-title=\"It happened in \u0141\u00f3d\u017a\": He murdered gays on Fabryczny |first1=Marcin |last1=Mas\u0142owski |first2=Agnieszka |last2=Urazi\u0144ska |first3=Jerzy |last3=Walczyk |lastauthoramp=yes |date=May 31, 2010 |newspaper=[[Gazeta Wyborcza]] |language=pl |accessdate=15 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Portugal===\n*[[Lisbon Ripper]]: murdered three women in [[Lisbon]] between 1992 and 1993.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/coldcases/lisbon.html |title=Unsolved Serial Killings; Portugal, Lisbon |date=October 27, 2009 |website=Serial Killer A-Z |access-date=24 November 2019 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091027121656/http://geocities.com/verbal_plainfield/coldcases/lisbon.html |archive-date=2009-10-27}}</ref>\n\n===Russia===\n{{Main|List of Russian serial killers}}\n\n===South Africa===\n*[[Sleepy Hollow Killer]]: thought to be responsible for the murders of at least thirteen women in the late 1990s, including three more in 2007, around [[Pietermaritzburg]] and the surrounding area.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/serial-killer-in-pietermaritzburg-report-387211 |title=Serial killer in Pietermaritzburg: report |date=28 January 2008 |website=[[Independent Online (South Africa)|Independent Online]] |access-date=24 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n===United Kingdom===\n*[[Bible John]]: thought to be responsible for the deaths of three women in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], in the late 1960s.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=v-NAAAAAIBAJ&sjid=3KYMAAAAIBAJ&pg=3021%2C2603615 |title=A Kiss Before Dying: 20 years on, the mystery of Bible John still haunts a city |last=Skelton |first=Douglas |date=10 February 1989 |newspaper=[[Evening Times]] |accessdate=22 May 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Jack the Ripper]]: murdered prostitutes in the East End of London in 1888.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.met.police.uk/history/ripper.htm |title=The Enduring Mystery of Jack the Ripper |website=[[Metropolitan Police]] |accessdate=31 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100204014147/http://www.met.police.uk/history/ripper.htm |archivedate=4 February 2010}}</ref>\n*[[Jack the Stripper]]: responsible for the London \"[[Hammersmith]] nude murders\" between 1964 and 1965.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/lifestyle/nostalgia/retro-mystery-jack-stripper-murders-5978691 |title=Retro: The mystery of the Jack the Stripper murders |first=James |last=Gates |date=12 March 2012 |work=[[Trinity Mirror|Get West London]] |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411025947/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/lifestyle/nostalgia/retro-mystery-jack-stripper-murders-5978691 |archive-date=April 11, 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Thames Torso Murders|Thames Torso Murderer]]: thought to be responsible for the murder and dismemberment of four women in London between 1887 and 1889.<ref>{{cite book |first=R. Michael |last=Gordon |title=The Thames Torso Murders of Victorian London |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cbCzCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA1 |date=3 October 2015 |publisher=McFarland |location=London, UK |isbn=978-1-4766-1665-0}}</ref>\n\n===United States===\n{{main|List of serial killers in the United States}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of non-state terrorist incidents]] (includes Unabomber, [[Theodore Kaczynski]])\n*[[List of serial killers before 1900]]\n*[[List of serial killers by number of victims]]\n*[[Mass murder]]\n*[[Spree killer]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Active editnotice}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Serial Killers By Country}}\n[[Category:Death-related lists|serial killers]]\n[[Category:Lists of murderers|serial country]]\n[[Category:Serial killers by nationality]]\n", "name_user": "ExRat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNetherlands", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_serial_killers_by_country"}
{"title_page": "27th United States Congress", "text_new": "{{redirect|27th Congress|the Soviet congress|27th Congress of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union}}\n{{no footnotes|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox United States Congress\n|number = 27th\n|previous = 26th\n|next = 28th\n|image = Capitol1846.jpg\n|imagedate = 1846\n|start = March 4, 1841\n|end = March 4, 1843\n|sessionnumber1 = Special\n|sessionstart1= March 4, 1841\n|sessionend1 = March 15, 1841\n|sessionnumber2 = 1st \n|sessionstart2 = May 31, 1841\n|sessionend2 = September 13, 1841\n|sessionnumber3 = 2nd \n|sessionstart3 = December 6, 1841\n|sessionend3 = August 31, 1842\n|sessionnumber4 = 3rd \n|sessionstart4 = December 5, 1842\n|sessionend4 = March 3, 1843 ([[lame duck (politics)|lame duck]])\n|vp = [[John Tyler]] (W) <br><small>until April 4, 1841</small> <br>Vacant <br><small>from April 4, 1841</small>\n|pro tem = [[William R. King]] (D)<br>[[Samuel L. Southard]] (W)<br>[[Willie Person Mangum|Willie P. Mangum]] (W)\n|speaker = [[John White (Kentucky politician)|John White]] (W)\n|senators = 52\n|reps = 242\n|delegates = 3\n|s-majority = [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]]\n|h-majority = [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]]\n}}\nThe '''Twenty-seventh United States Congress''' was a meeting of the legislative branch of the United States federal government, consisting of the [[United States Senate]] and the [[United States House of Representatives]]. It met in [[Washington, D.C.]] between March 4, 1841, and March 4, 1843, during the one-month [[Presidency of William Henry Harrison|administration]] of [[President of the United States|U.S. President]] [[William Henry Harrison]] and the first two years of the [[Presidency of John Tyler|presidency]] of his successor, [[John Tyler]]. The apportionment of seats in the [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] was based on the [[United States Census, 1830|Fifth Census of the United States in 1830]]. Both chambers had a [[Whig Party (United States)|Whig]] majority.\n{{TOClimit|2}}\n\n==Major events==\n{{main|1841 in the United States|1842 in the United States|1843 in the United States}}\n*March 4, 1841: [[William Henry Harrison]] was inaugurated as [[President of the United States]]\n*April 4, 1841: President Harrison died and Vice President [[John Tyler]] became President\n* August 16, 1841: President Tyler's veto of a bill to re-establish the [[Second Bank of the United States]] led Whig Party members to riot outside the White House in the most violent demonstration on White House grounds in U.S. history.\n* May 19, 1842: [[Dorr Rebellion]]\n\n==Major legislation==\n{{main|List of United States federal legislation, 1789\u20131901#1821 to 1831|l1=Major legislation: 27th United States Congress}}\n* April 19, 1841: [[Bankruptcy Act of 1841]], ch. 9, {{USStat|5|440}}\n* September 4, 1841: [[Preemption Act of 1841]], ch. 16, {{USStat|5|453}}\n* August 4, 1842: [[Armed Occupation Act]], {{USStat|5|502}}\n* August 30, 1842: [[Tariff of 1842]] (\"Black Tariff\"), ch. 270, {{USStat|5|548}}\n\n== Treaties ==\n* August 9, 1842: [[Webster-Ashburton Treaty]] signed, establishing the United States\u2013Canada border east of the Rocky Mountains.\n\n== Party summary ==\n=== Senate ===\n\n{{US Congress party summary\n| congress           = 27\n\n| party1             = Democratic\n| abb1               = D\n| seats1_last        = 30\n| seats1_begin       = 22\n| seats1_end         = 20\n| seats1_next        = 22\n\n| party2             = Whig\n| abb2               = W\n| seats2_last        = 20\n| seats2_begin       = 29\n| seats2_end         = 29\n| seats2_next        = 26\n\n| seats_vacant_last  = 0\n| seats_vacant_begin = 1\n| seats_vacant_end   = 3\n| seats_vacant_next  = 4\n\n}}\n\n===House of Representatives===\n\n{{US Congress party summary\n| congress           = 27\n\n| party1             = Democratic\n| abb1               = D\n| seats1_last        = 124\n| seats1_begin       = 98\n| seats1_end         = 101\n| seats1_next        = 147\n\n| party2             = Independent Democratic\n| abb2               = ID\n| seats2_last        = 0\n| seats2_begin       = 1\n| seats2_end         = 1\n| seats2_next        = 1\n\n| party3             = Whig\n| abb3               = W\n| seats3_last        = 111\n| seats3_begin       = 142\n| seats3_end         = 139\n| seats3_next        = 72\n\n| party4             = Other\n| abb4               = \n| seats4_last        = 2\n| note4_last         = [[Conservative Party (Virginia, 1834)|Conservative]]\n| seats4_begin       = 0\n| seats4_end         = 0\n| seats4_next        = 3\n| note4_next         = [[Law and Order Party of Rhode Island|Law and Order]]<br/>& Independent Whig\n\n| seats_vacant_last  = 0\n| seats_vacant_begin = 1\n| seats_vacant_end   = 1\n| seats_vacant_next  = 0\n\n| delegates1         = \n| delegates2         = \n| delegates3         = \n| delegates4         = \n| delegates5         = \n| delegates_vacant   = \n\n}}\n\n==Leadership==\n[[File:John Tyler.png|thumb|175px|President of the Senate<br>[[John Tyler]]]]\n\n===Senate===\n* [[President of the United States Senate|President]]: [[John Tyler]] (W), until April 4, 1841, thereafter vacant\n* [[President pro tempore of the United States Senate|Presidents pro tempore]]: [[William R. King]] (D), elected March 4, 1841\n** [[Samuel L. Southard]]) (W), elected March 11, 1841\n** [[Willie Person Mangum|Willie P. Mangum]] (W), elected May 31, 1842\n\n===House of Representatives===\n* [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker]]: [[John White (Kentucky politician)|John D. White]] (W)\n\n==Members==\nThis list is arranged by chamber, then by state. Senators are listed in order of seniority, and Representatives are listed by district.\n\n:''[[#House of Representatives_3|Skip to House of Representatives]], below''\n\n===Senate===\nSenators were elected by the state legislatures every two years, with one-third beginning new six-year terms with each Congress. Preceding the names in the list below are [[Classes of United States Senators|Senate class numbers]], which indicate the cycle of their election. In this Congress, Class 1 meant their term began in the last Congress, requiring re-election in 1844; Class 2 meant their term began with this Congress, requiring re-election in 1846; and Class 3 meant their term ended with this Congress, requiring re-election in 1842.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Alabama|Alabama]] ====\n* 2. [[William R. King]] (D)\n* 3. [[Clement Comer Clay|Clement C. Clay]] (D), until November 15, 1841\n** [[Arthur P. Bagby]] (D), from November 24, 1841\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Arkansas|Arkansas]] ====\n* 2. [[William Savin Fulton|William Fulton]] (D)\n* 3. [[Ambrose Hundley Sevier|Ambrose Sevier]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Connecticut|Connecticut]] ====\n* 1. [[Jabez W. Huntington]] (W)\n* 3. [[Perry Smith (U.S. Congressman)|Perry Smith]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Delaware|Delaware]] ====\n* 1. [[Richard H. Bayard]] (W)\n* 2. [[Thomas Clayton]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Georgia|Georgia]] ====\n* 2. [[John M. Berrien|John Berrien]] (W)\n* 3. [[Alfred Cuthbert]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Illinois|Illinois]] ====\n* 2. [[Samuel McRoberts]] (D)\n* 3. [[Richard M. Young]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Indiana|Indiana]] ====\n* 1. [[Albert White (U.S. Senator)|Albert White]] (W)\n* 3. [[Oliver H. Smith]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Kentucky|Kentucky]] ====\n* 2. [[James Turner Morehead (Kentucky)|James T. Morehead]] (W)\n* 3. [[Henry Clay]] (W), until March 31, 1842\n** [[John J. Crittenden]] (W), from March 31, 1842\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Louisiana|Louisiana]] ====\n* 2. [[Alexander Barrow]] (W)\n* 3. [[Alexander Mouton]] (D), until March 1, 1842\n** [[Charles Magill Conrad|Charles Conrad]] (W), from April 14, 1842\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Maine|Maine]] ====\n* 1. [[Reuel Williams]] (D), until February 15, 1843\n* 2. [[George Evans (American politician)|George Evans]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Maryland|Maryland]] ====\n* 1. [[William Duhurst Merrick|William Merrick]] (W)\n* 3. [[John Leeds Kerr|John L. Kerr]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Massachusetts|Massachusetts]] ====\n* 1. [[Rufus Choate]] (W)\n* 2. [[Isaac C. Bates]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Michigan|Michigan]] ====\n* 1. [[Augustus Seymour Porter|Augustus S. Porter]] (W)\n* 2. [[William Woodbridge]] (W)\n{{col-break}}\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Mississippi|Mississippi]] ====\n* 1. [[John Henderson (Mississippi politician)|John Henderson]] (W)\n* 2. [[Robert J. Walker]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Missouri|Missouri]] ====\n* 1. [[Thomas Hart Benton (senator)|Thomas Benton]] (D)\n* 3. [[Lewis F. Linn]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from New Hampshire|New Hampshire]] ====\n* 2. [[Levi Woodbury]] (D)\n* 3. [[Franklin Pierce]] (D), until February 28, 1842\n** [[Leonard Wilcox]] (D), from March 1, 1842\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from New Jersey|New Jersey]] ====\n* 1. [[Samuel L. Southard]] (W), until June 26, 1842\n** [[William L. Dayton]] (W), from July 2, 1842\n* 2. [[Jacob W. Miller]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from New York|New York]] ====\n* 1. [[Nathaniel P. Tallmadge]] (W)\n* 3. [[Silas Wright]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from North Carolina|North Carolina]] ====\n* 2. [[Willie Person Mangum|Willie Mangum]] (W)\n* 3. [[William Alexander Graham|William Graham]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Ohio|Ohio]] ====\n* 1. [[Benjamin Tappan]] (D)\n* 3. [[William Allen (governor)|William Allen]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Senators from Pennsylvania|Pennsylvania]] ====\