d Bronson]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated May 31, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|New York|26|New York 26th}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Francis Granger]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned March 5, 1841, after being appointed [[United States Postmaster General]]\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[John Greig (representative)|John Greig]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated May 21, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|Massachusetts|5|Massachusetts 5th}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Levi Lincoln, Jr.]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned March 16, 1841, after being appointed Collector of the port of Boston\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Charles Hudson (Massachusetts)|Charles Hudson]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated May 3, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|Pennsylvania|20|Pennsylvania 20th}}\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Enos Hook]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned April 18, 1841\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Henry White Beeson|Henry W. Beeson]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| Seated May 31, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|Pennsylvania|18|Pennsylvania 18th}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Charles Ogle (politician)|Charles Ogle]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Died May 10, 1841\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Henry Black (Representative)|Henry Black]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated June 28, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|Pennsylvania|2|Pennsylvania 2nd}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[John Sergeant (politician)|John Sergeant]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned September 15, 1841\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Joseph Reed Ingersoll|Joseph R. Ingersoll]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated October 12, 1841\n|-\n| {{ushr|New York|26|New York 26th}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[John Greig (representative)|John Greig]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\