usetts|3|3}}. [[Caleb Cushing]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|4|4}}. [[William Parmenter]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|5|5}}. [[Levi Lincoln, Jr.]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|6|6}}. [[James C. Alvord]] (W), until September 27, 1839\n** [[Osmyn Baker]] (W), from January 14, 1840\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|7|7}}. [[George N. Briggs]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|8|8}}. [[William B. Calhoun]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|9|9}}. [[William Soden Hastings|William S. Hastings]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|10|10}}. [[Henry Williams (Massachusetts)|Henry Williams]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|11|11}}. [[John Reed, Jr.]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Massachusetts|12|12}}. [[John Quincy Adams]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Michigan|Michigan]] ====\n*{{ushr|Michigan|AL|At-large}}. [[Isaac E. Crary]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Mississippi|Mississippi]] ====\nBoth representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n*{{ushr|Mississippi|AL|At-large}}. [[Albert G. Brown]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Mississippi|AL|At-large}}. [[Jacob Thompson]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Missouri|Missouri]] ====\nBoth representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n*{{ushr|Missouri|AL|At-large}}. [[Albert G. Harrison]] (D), until September 7, 1839\n** [[John Jameson (politician)|John Jameson]] (D), from December 12, 1839\n*{{ushr|Missouri|AL|At-large}}. [[John Miller (Missouri)|John Miller]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from New Hampshire|New Hampshire]] ====\nAll representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n*{{ushr|New Hampshire|AL|At-large}}. [[Charles G. Atherton]] (D)\n*{{ushr|New Hampshire|AL|At-large}}. [[Edmund Burke (congressman)|Edmund Burke]] (D)\n*{{ushr|New Hampshire|AL|At-large}}. [[Ira A. Eastman]] (D)\n*{{ushr|New Hampshire|AL|At-large}}. [[Tristram Shaw]] (D)\n*{{ushr|New Hampshire|AL|At-large}}. [[Jared W. Williams]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives 