ry W. Connor]] (D)\n*{{ushr|North Carolina|12|12}}. [[James Graham (NC politician)|James Graham]] (W)\n*{{ushr|North Carolina|13|13}}. [[Lewis Williams]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Ohio|Ohio]] ====\n*{{ushr|Ohio|1|1}}. [[Alexander Duncan (politician)|Alexander Duncan]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|2|2}}. [[John B. Weller]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|3|3}}. [[Patrick Gaines Goode|Patrick G. Goode]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|4|4}}. [[Thomas Corwin]] (W), until May 30, 1840\n** [[Jeremiah Morrow]] (W), from October 13, 1840\n*{{ushr|Ohio|5|5}}. [[William Doan]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|6|6}}. [[Calvary Morris]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|7|7}}. [[William K. Bond]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|8|8}}. [[Joseph Ridgway]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|9|9}}. [[William Medill]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|10|10}}. [[Samson Mason]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|11|11}}. [[Isaac Parrish]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|12|12}}. [[Jonathan Taylor (representative)|Jonathan Taylor]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|13|13}}. [[Daniel Parkhurst Leadbetter|Daniel P. Leadbetter]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|14|14}}. [[George Sweeny]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|15|15}}. [[John W. Allen]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|16|16}}. [[Joshua Reed Giddings|Joshua R. Giddings]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|17|17}}. [[John Hastings (representative)|John Hastings]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|18|18}}. [[David A. Starkweather]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Ohio|19|19}}. [[Henry Swearingen]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Pennsylvania|Pennsylvania]] ====\nThere were two plural districts, the 2nd had two representatives, the 4th had three representatives.\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|1|1}}. [[Lemuel Paynter]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|2|2}}. [[John Sergeant (politician)|John Sergeant]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|2|2}}. [[George Washington Toland|George W. Toland]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|3|3}}. [[Charles Naylor]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|4|4}}. [[Edward Davies (Pennsylvania)|Edward Davies]] (AM)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|4|4}}. [[John Edwards (Pennsylvania)|John Edwards]] (AM)\n*{{ushr|Pennsylvania|4|4}}. [[Francis James (congressma