. Anderson]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Died August 11, 1840\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[John Burton Thompson|John B. Thompson]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated December 7, 1840\n|-\n| {{ushr|Massachusetts|1|Massachusetts 1st}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Abbott Lawrence]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned September 18, 1840\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Robert Charles Winthrop|Robert C. Winthrop]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated November 9, 1840\n|-\n| {{ushr|Pennsylvania|13|Pennsylvania 13th}}\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[William Sterrett Ramsey|William S. Ramsey]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Died October 17, 1840\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Charles McClure (Pennsylvania)|Charles McClure]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| Seated December 7, 1840\n|-\n| {{ushr|Iowa Territory|AL|Iowa Territory At-large}}\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[William W. Chapman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Term expired by law October 27, 1840\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Augustus C. Dodge]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| Seated October 28, 1840\n|-\n| {{ushr|Virginia|1|Virginia 1st}}\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} | [[Joel Holleman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned in December 1840\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[Francis Mallory]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| Seated December 28, 1840\n|-\n| {{ushr|Maine|4|Maine 4th}}\n| {{party shading/Whig}} | [[George Evans (Maine)|George Evans]] ([[Whig Party (United States)|W]])\n| style=\"font-size:80%\" | Resigned March 3, 1841, after being elected to the [[US Senate]]\n| Vacant\n| Not filled this term\n|}\n\n==Committees==\nLists of committees and their party leaders.\n\n===Senate===\n\n* [[United States Senate Committee on Agriculture|Agriculture]] (Chairman